P_HTM[689]="*pāpikā icchā na hoti, tathāhimaṃ āyasmantaṃ pāpikā icchā nābhibhuyya iriyatī’”ti.**and corrupt wishes, so corrupt wishes don’t master them and keep going.’”*";
P_HTM[690]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[691]="*4. Mahācundasuttaṃ**By Mahācunda*";
P_HTM[692]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā mahācundo cetīsu viharati sahajātiyaṃ.**At one time Venerable Mahācunda was staying in the land of the Cetis at Sahajāti.*";
P_HTM[693]="*Tatra kho āyasmā mahācundo bhikkhū āmantesi:**There he addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[694]="*“āvuso bhikkhave”ti.**“Reverends, mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[695]="*“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahācundassa paccassosuṃ.**“Reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[696]="*Āyasmā mahācundo etadavoca:**Venerable Mahācunda said this:*";
P_HTM[697]="*“Ñāṇavādaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu vadamāno:**“Reverends, a mendicant who makes a declaration of knowledge says:*";
P_HTM[698]="*‘jānāmimaṃ dhammaṃ, passāmimaṃ dhamman’ti.**‘I know this teaching, I see this teaching.’*";
P_HTM[699]="*Tañce, āvuso, bhikkhuṃ lobho abhibhuyya tiṭṭhati,**Suppose that greed masters that mendicant and keeps going.*";
P_HTM[700]="*doso …**Or that hate …*";
