P_HTM[741]="*Ñāṇavādañca, āvuso, bhikkhu vadamāno bhāvanāvādañca:**A mendicant who makes a declaration of both knowledge and development says:*";
P_HTM[742]="*‘jānāmimaṃ dhammaṃ, passāmimaṃ dhammaṃ, bhāvitakāyomhi bhāvitasīlo bhāvitacitto bhāvitapañño’ti.**‘I know this teaching, I see this teaching. And I am developed in physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom.’*";
P_HTM[743]="*Tañce, āvuso, bhikkhuṃ lobho abhibhuyya tiṭṭhati,**Suppose that greed masters that mendicant and keeps going.*";
