P_HTM[762]="*pāpikā icchā na hoti, tathāhimaṃ āyasmantaṃ pāpikā icchā abhibhuyya tiṭṭhatī’ti.**or corrupt wishes, so corrupt wishes master them and keep going.’*";
P_HTM[763]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso, puriso daliddova samāno aḍḍhavādaṃ vadeyya, adhanova samāno dhanavāvādaṃ vadeyya, abhogova samāno bhogavāvādaṃ vadeyya.**Suppose a poor, needy, and penniless person was to declare themselves to be rich, affluent, and wealthy.*";
P_HTM[764]="*So kismiñcideva dhanakaraṇīye samuppanne na sakkuṇeyya upanīhātuṃ dhanaṃ vā dhaññaṃ vā rajataṃ vā jātarūpaṃ vā.**But when it came time to make a payment they weren’t able to come up with any money, grain, silver, or gold.*";
P_HTM[765]="*Tamenaṃ evaṃ jāneyyuṃ:**Then they would know of them:*";
P_HTM[766]="*‘daliddova ayamāyasmā samāno aḍḍhavādaṃ vadeti, adhanova ayamāyasmā samāno dhanavāvādaṃ vadeti, abhogavāva ayamāyasmā samāno bhogavāvādaṃ vadeti.**‘This person declares themselves to be rich, affluent, and wealthy, but they are in fact poor, penniless, and needy.’*";
P_HTM[767]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[768]="*Tathā hi ayamāyasmā kismiñcideva dhanakaraṇīye samuppanne na sakkoti upanīhātuṃ dhanaṃ vā dhaññaṃ vā rajataṃ vā jātarūpaṃ vā’ti.**Because when it came time to make a payment they weren’t able to come up with any money, grain, silver, or gold.*";
P_HTM[769]="*Evamevaṃ kho, āvuso, ñāṇavādañca bhikkhu vadamāno bhāvanāvādañca:**In the same way, a mendicant who makes a declaration of knowledge and development says:*";
P_HTM[770]="*‘jānāmimaṃ dhammaṃ, passāmimaṃ dhammaṃ, bhāvitakāyomhi bhāvitasīlo bhāvitacitto bhāvitapañño’ti.**‘I know this teaching, I see this teaching. And I am developed in physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom.’*";
P_HTM[771]="*Tañce, āvuso, bhikkhuṃ lobho abhibhuyya tiṭṭhati,**Suppose that greed masters that mendicant and keeps going.*";
