P_HTM[2370]="*atthūpaparikkhā natthi …* **";
P_HTM[2371]="*dhammānudhammappaṭipatti natthi …* **";
P_HTM[2372]="*appamādo natthi kusalesu dhammesu tassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, hāniyeva pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu no vuddhi.**can expect decline, not growth, in skillful qualities, whether by day or by night.*";
P_HTM[2373]="*Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, kāḷapakkhe candassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, hāyateva vaṇṇena hāyati maṇḍalena hāyati ābhāya hāyati ārohapariṇāhena;**It’s like the moon in the waning fortnight. Whether by day or by night, its beauty, roundness, light, and diameter and circumference only decline.*";
