P_HTM[2383]="*dhammānudhammappaṭipatti atthi …* **";
P_HTM[2384]="*appamādo atthi kusalesu dhammesu, tassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, vuddhiyeva pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu no parihāni.**can expect growth, not decline, in skillful qualities, whether by day or by night.*";
P_HTM[2385]="*Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, juṇhapakkhe candassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, vaḍḍhateva vaṇṇena vaḍḍhati maṇḍalena vaḍḍhati ābhāya vaḍḍhati ārohapariṇāhena;**It’s like the moon in the waxing fortnight. Whether by day or by night, its beauty, roundness, light, and diameter and circumference only grow.*";
P_HTM[2386]="*evamevaṃ kho, sāriputta, yassa kassaci saddhā atthi kusalesu dhammesu … pe …**In the same way, whoever has faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom; who wants to listen, memorizes the teachings, examines their meaning, and practices accordingly, and is diligent when it comes to skillful qualities*";
P_HTM[2387]="*appamādo atthi kusalesu dhammesu, tassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, vuddhiyeva pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu no parihānī”ti.**can expect growth, not decline, in skillful qualities, whether by day or by night.”*";
P_HTM[2388]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2389]="*9. Paṭhamakathāvatthusuttaṃ**Topics of Discussion (1st)*";
P_HTM[2390]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[2391]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantā upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ sannisinnā sannipatitā anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, seyyathidaṃ—**Now at that time, after the meal, on return from alms-round, several mendicants sat together in the meeting hall. They engaged in all kinds of unworthy talk, such as*";
P_HTM[2392]="*rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ mahāmattakathaṃ senākathaṃ bhayakathaṃ yuddhakathaṃ annakathaṃ pānakathaṃ vatthakathaṃ sayanakathaṃ mālākathaṃ gandhakathaṃ ñātikathaṃ yānakathaṃ gāmakathaṃ nigamakathaṃ nagarakathaṃ janapadakathaṃ itthikathaṃ sūrakathaṃ visikhākathaṃ kumbhaṭṭhānakathaṃ pubbapetakathaṃ nānattakathaṃ lokakkhāyikaṃ samuddakkhāyikaṃ itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vāti.**talk about kings, bandits, and ministers; talk about armies, threats, and wars; talk about food, drink, clothes, and beds; talk about garlands and fragrances; talk about family, vehicles, villages, towns, cities, and countries; talk about women and heroes; street talk and well talk; talk about the departed; motley talk; tales of land and sea; and talk about being reborn in this or that state of existence.*";
P_HTM[2393]="*Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena upaṭṭhānasālā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to the assembly hall, where he sat on the seat spread out*";
P_HTM[2394]="*Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**and addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[2395]="*“kāya nuttha, bhikkhave, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā sannipatitā, kā ca pana vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti?**“Mendicants, what were you sitting talking about just now? What conversation was left unfinished?”*";
P_HTM[2396]="*“Idha mayaṃ, bhante, pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantā upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ sannisinnā sannipatitā anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ anuyuttā viharāma, seyyathidaṃ—**And they told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[2397]="*rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ … pe … itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2398]="*“Na kho panetaṃ, bhikkhave, tumhākaṃ patirūpaṃ kulaputtānaṃ saddhāya agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitānaṃ, yaṃ tumhe anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ anuyuttā vihareyyātha, seyyathidaṃ—**“Mendicants, it is not appropriate for you gentlemen who have gone forth in faith from the lay life to homelessness to engage in these kinds of unworthy talk.*";
P_HTM[2399]="*rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ mahāmattakathaṃ senākathaṃ bhayakathaṃ yuddhakathaṃ annakathaṃ pānakathaṃ vatthakathaṃ sayanakathaṃ mālākathaṃ gandhakathaṃ ñātikathaṃ yānakathaṃ gāmakathaṃ nigamakathaṃ nagarakathaṃ janapadakathaṃ itthikathaṃ sūrakathaṃ visikhākathaṃ kumbhaṭṭhānakathaṃ pubbapetakathaṃ nānattakathaṃ lokakkhāyikaṃ samuddakkhāyikaṃ itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vāti.* **";
P_HTM[2400]="*Dasayimāni, bhikkhave, kathāvatthūni.**There are, mendicants, these ten topics of discussion.*";
P_HTM[2401]="*Katamāni dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[2402]="*Appicchakathā, santuṭṭhikathā, pavivekakathā, asaṃsaggakathā, vīriyārambhakathā, sīlakathā, samādhikathā, paññākathā, vimuttikathā, vimuttiñāṇadassanakathāti—**Talk about fewness of wishes, contentment, seclusion, aloofness, arousing energy, ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and the knowledge and vision of freedom.*";
P_HTM[2403]="*imāni kho, bhikkhave, dasa kathāvatthūni.**These are the ten topics of discussion.*";
P_HTM[2404]="*Imesañce tumhe, bhikkhave, dasannaṃ kathāvatthūnaṃ upādāyupādāya kathaṃ katheyyātha, imesampi candimasūriyānaṃ evaṃmahiddhikānaṃ evaṃmahānubhāvānaṃ tejasā tejaṃ pariyādiyeyyātha, ko pana vādo aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānan”ti.**Mendicants, if you bring up these topics of conversation again and again then your glory could surpass even the sun and moon, so mighty and powerful, let alone the wanderers who follow other paths.”*";
P_HTM[2405]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2406]="*10. Dutiyakathāvatthusuttaṃ**Topics of Discussion (2nd)*";
P_HTM[2407]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[2408]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantā upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ sannisinnā sannipatitā anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, seyyathidaṃ—**Now at that time, after the meal, on return from alms-round, several mendicants sat together in the meeting hall.*";
P_HTM[2409]="*rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ mahāmattakathaṃ … pe … itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vāti.**They engaged in all kinds of unworthy talk, such as talk about kings, bandits, and ministers; talk about armies, threats, and wars; talk about food, drink, clothes, and beds; talk about garlands and fragrances; talk about family, vehicles, villages, towns, cities, and nations; talk about women and heroes; street talk and well talk; talk about the departed; miscellaneous talk; tales of land and sea; and talk about being reborn in this or that state of existence.*";
P_HTM[2410]="*“Dasayimāni, bhikkhave, pāsaṃsāni ṭhānāni.**“Mendicants, there are ten grounds for praise.*";
P_HTM[2411]="*Katamāni dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[2412]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu attanā ca appiccho hoti, appicchakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā hoti.**It’s when a mendicant personally has few wishes, and speaks to the mendicants on having few wishes.*";
P_HTM[2413]="*‘Appiccho bhikkhu appicchakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā’ti pāsaṃsametaṃ ṭhānaṃ. (1)**This is a ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[2414]="*Attanā ca santuṭṭho hoti, santuṭṭhikathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā hoti.**A mendicant personally is content, and speaks to the mendicants on contentment.*";
P_HTM[2415]="*‘Santuṭṭho bhikkhu santuṭṭhikathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā’ti pāsaṃsametaṃ ṭhānaṃ. (2)**This is a ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[2416]="*Attanā ca pavivitto hoti, pavivekakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā hoti.**A mendicant personally is secluded, and speaks to the mendicants on seclusion.*";
P_HTM[2417]="*‘Pavivitto bhikkhu pavivekakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā’ti pāsaṃsametaṃ ṭhānaṃ. (3)**This is a ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[2418]="*Attanā ca asaṃsaṭṭho hoti, asaṃsaṭṭhakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā hoti.**A mendicant personally doesn’t mix closely with others, and speaks to the mendicants on not mixing closely with others.*";
P_HTM[2419]="*‘Asaṃsaṭṭho bhikkhu asaṃsaṭṭhakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā’ti pāsaṃsametaṃ ṭhānaṃ. (4)**This is a ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[2420]="*Attanā ca āraddhavīriyo hoti, vīriyārambhakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā hoti.**A mendicant personally is energetic, and speaks to the mendicants on being energetic.*";
P_HTM[2421]="*‘Āraddhavīriyo bhikkhu vīriyārambhakathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā’ti pāsaṃsametaṃ ṭhānaṃ. (5)**This is a ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[2422]="*Attanā ca sīlasampanno hoti, sīlasampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā hoti.**A mendicant personally is accomplished in ethics, and speaks to the mendicants on being accomplished in ethics.*";
P_HTM[2423]="*‘Sīlasampanno bhikkhu sīlasampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā’ti pāsaṃsametaṃ ṭhānaṃ. (6)**This is a ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[2424]="*Attanā ca samādhisampanno hoti, samādhisampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā hoti.**A mendicant personally is accomplished in immersion, and speaks to the mendicants on being accomplished in immersion.*";
P_HTM[2425]="*‘Samādhisampanno bhikkhu samādhisampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā’ti pāsaṃsametaṃ ṭhānaṃ. (7)**This is a ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[2426]="*Attanā ca paññāsampanno hoti, paññāsampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā hoti.**A mendicant personally is accomplished in wisdom, and speaks to the mendicants on being accomplished in wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2427]="*‘Paññāsampanno bhikkhu paññāsampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā’ti pāsaṃsametaṃ ṭhānaṃ. (8)**This is a ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[2428]="*Attanā ca vimuttisampanno hoti, vimuttisampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā hoti.**A mendicant personally is accomplished in freedom, and speaks to the mendicants on being accomplished in freedom.*";
P_HTM[2429]="*‘Vimuttisampanno bhikkhu vimuttisampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā’ti pāsaṃsametaṃ ṭhānaṃ. (9)**This is a ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[2430]="*Attanā ca vimuttiñāṇadassanasampanno hoti, vimuttiñāṇadassanasampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā hoti.**A mendicant personally is accomplished in the knowledge and vision of freedom, and speaks to the mendicants on being accomplished in the knowledge and vision of freedom.*";
P_HTM[2431]="*‘Vimuttiñāṇadassanasampanno bhikkhu vimuttiñāṇadassanasampadākathañca bhikkhūnaṃ kattā’ti pāsaṃsametaṃ ṭhānaṃ. (10)**This is a ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[2432]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, dasa pāsaṃsāni ṭhānānī”ti.**These are the ten grounds for praise.”*";
P_HTM[2433]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2434]="*Yamakavaggo dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[2435]="*Avijjā taṇhā niṭṭhā ca,* **";
P_HTM[2436]="*avecca dve sukhāni ca;* **";
P_HTM[2437]="*Naḷakapāne dve vuttā,* **";
P_HTM[2438]="*kathāvatthūpare duveti.* **";
P_HTM[2439]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**If You Want*";
P_HTM[2440]="*1. Ākaṅkhasuttaṃ**One Might Wish*";
P_HTM[2441]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[2442]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[2443]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[2444]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[2445]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[2446]="*“Sampannasīlā, bhikkhave, viharatha sampannapātimokkhā, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvutā viharatha ācāragocarasampannā aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvino, samādāya sikkhatha sikkhāpadesu.**“Mendicants, live by the ethical precepts and the monastic code. Live restrained in the code of conduct, conducting yourselves well and seeking alms in suitable places. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, keep the rules you’ve undertaken.*";
P_HTM[2447]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo cassaṃ manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo cā’ti, sīlesvevassa paripūrakārī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathamanuyutto anirākatajjhāno vipassanāya samannāgato brūhetā suññāgārānaṃ. (1)**A mendicant might wish: ‘May I be liked and approved by my spiritual companions, respected and admired.’ So let them fulfill their precepts, be committed to inner serenity of the heart, not neglect absorption, be endowed with discernment, and frequent empty huts.*";
P_HTM[2448]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘lābhī assaṃ cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānapaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānan’ti, sīlesvevassa paripūrakārī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathamanuyutto anirākatajjhāno vipassanāya samannāgato brūhetā suññāgārānaṃ. (2)**A mendicant might wish: ‘May I receive robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.’ So let them fulfill their precepts, be committed to inner serenity of the heart, not neglect absorption, be endowed with discernment, and frequent empty huts.*";
P_HTM[2449]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘yesāhaṃ paribhuñjāmi cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānapaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ tesaṃ te kārā mahapphalā assu mahānisaṃsā’ti, sīlesvevassa … pe … brūhetā suññāgārānaṃ. (3)**A mendicant might wish: ‘May the services of those whose robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick I enjoy be very fruitful and beneficial for them.’ So let them fulfill their precepts …*";
P_HTM[2450]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘ye me petā ñātī sālohitā kālaṅkatā pasannacittā anussaranti tesaṃ taṃ mahapphalaṃ assa mahānisaṃsan’ti, sīlesvevassa … pe … brūhetā suññāgārānaṃ. (4)**A mendicant might wish: ‘When deceased family and relatives who have passed away recollect me with a confident mind, may this be very fruitful and beneficial for them.’ So let them fulfill their precepts …*";
P_HTM[2451]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘santuṭṭho assaṃ itarītaracīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānapaccayabhesajjaparikkhārenā’ti, sīlesvevassa … pe … brūhetā suññāgārānaṃ. (5)**A mendicant might wish: ‘May I be content with any kind of robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.’ So let them fulfill their precepts …*";
P_HTM[2452]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘khamo assaṃ sītassa uṇhassa jighacchāya pipāsāya ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ, duruttānaṃ durāgatānaṃ vacanapathānaṃ uppannānaṃ sārīrikānaṃ vedanānaṃ dukkhānaṃ tibbānaṃ kharānaṃ kaṭukānaṃ asātānaṃ amanāpānaṃ pāṇaharānaṃ adhivāsakajātiko assan’ti, sīlesvevassa … pe … brūhetā suññāgārānaṃ. (6)**A mendicant might wish: ‘May I endure cold, heat, hunger, and thirst. May I endure the touch of flies, mosquitoes, wind, sun, and reptiles. May I endure rude and unwelcome criticism. And may I put up with physical pain—sharp, severe, acute, unpleasant, disagreeable, and life-threatening.’ So let them fulfill their precepts …*";
P_HTM[2453]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘aratiratisaho assaṃ, na ca maṃ aratirati saheyya, uppannaṃ aratiratiṃ abhibhuyya abhibhuyya vihareyyan’ti, sīlesvevassa … pe … brūhetā suññāgārānaṃ. (7)**A mendicant might wish: ‘May I prevail over desire and discontent, and may desire and discontent not prevail over me. May I live having mastered desire and discontent whenever they have arisen.’ So let them fulfill their precepts …*";
P_HTM[2454]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘bhayabheravasaho assaṃ, na ca maṃ bhayabheravo saheyya, uppannaṃ bhayabheravaṃ abhibhuyya abhibhuyya vihareyyan’ti, sīlesvevassa … pe … brūhetā suññāgārānaṃ. (8)**A mendicant might wish: ‘May I prevail over fear and dread, and may fear and dread not prevail over me. May I live having mastered fear and dread whenever they arise.’ So let them fulfill their precepts …*";
P_HTM[2455]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī assaṃ akicchalābhī akasiralābhī’ti, sīlesvevassa … pe … brūhetā suññāgārānaṃ. (9)**A mendicant might wish: ‘May I get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when I want, without trouble or difficulty.’ So let them fulfill their precepts …*";
P_HTM[2456]="*Ākaṅkheyya ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyan’ti, sīlesvevassa paripūrakārī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathamanuyutto anirākatajjhāno vipassanāya samannāgato brūhetā suññāgārānaṃ. (10)**A mendicant might wish: ‘May I realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having realized it with my own insight due to the ending of defilements.’ So let them fulfill their precepts, be committed to inner serenity of the heart, not neglect absorption, be endowed with discernment, and frequent empty huts.*";
P_HTM[2457]="*‘Sampannasīlā, bhikkhave, viharatha sampannapātimokkhā, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvutā viharatha ācāragocarasampannā aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvino, samādāya sikkhatha sikkhāpadesū’ti,**‘Live by the ethical precepts and the monastic code. Live restrained in the code of conduct, conducting yourselves well and seeking alms in suitable places. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, keep the rules you’ve undertaken.’*";
P_HTM[2458]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttan”ti.**That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.”*";
P_HTM[2459]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2460]="*2. Kaṇṭakasuttaṃ**Thorns*";
P_HTM[2461]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ sambahulehi abhiññātehi abhiññātehi therehi sāvakehi saddhiṃ—**At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof, together with several well-known senior disciples.*";
P_HTM[2462]="*āyasmatā ca cālena, āyasmatā ca upacālena, āyasmatā ca kukkuṭena, āyasmatā ca kaḷimbhena, āyasmatā ca nikaṭena, āyasmatā ca kaṭissahena;**They included Venerables Cāla, Upacāla, Kakkaṭa, Kaṭimbha, Kaṭa, Kaṭissaṅga,*";
P_HTM[2463]="*aññehi ca abhiññātehi abhiññātehi therehi sāvakehi saddhiṃ.**and other well-known senior disciples.*";
P_HTM[2464]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā licchavī bhadrehi bhadrehi yānehi parapurāya uccāsaddā mahāsaddā mahāvanaṃ ajjhogāhanti bhagavantaṃ dassanāya.**Now at that time several well-known Licchavis plunged deep into the Great Wood to see the Buddha. Driving a succession of fine carriages, they made a dreadful racket.*";
P_HTM[2465]="*Atha kho tesaṃ āyasmantānaṃ etadahosi:**Then those venerables thought:*";
P_HTM[2466]="*“ime kho sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā licchavī bhadrehi bhadrehi yānehi parapurāya uccāsaddā mahāsaddā mahāvanaṃ ajjhogāhanti bhagavantaṃ dassanāya.**“These several well-known Licchavis have plunged deep into the Great Wood to see the Buddha. Driving a succession of fine carriages, they’re making a dreadful racket.*";
P_HTM[2467]="*Saddakaṇṭakā kho pana jhānā vuttā bhagavatā.**But the Buddha has said that sound is a thorn to absorption.*";
P_HTM[2468]="*Yannūna mayaṃ yena gosiṅgasālavanadāyo tenupasaṅkameyyāma.**Let’s go to the Gosiṅga Sal Wood.*";
P_HTM[2469]="*Tattha mayaṃ appasaddā appākiṇṇā phāsuṃ vihareyyāmā”ti.**There we can meditate comfortably, free of noise and crowds.”*";
P_HTM[2470]="*Atha kho te āyasmanto yena gosiṅgasālavanadāyo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;**Then those venerables went to the Gosiṅga Sal Wood,*";
P_HTM[2471]="*tattha te āyasmanto appasaddā appākiṇṇā phāsuṃ viharanti.**where they meditated comfortably, free of noise and crowds.*";
P_HTM[2472]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[2473]="*“kahaṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, cālo, kahaṃ upacālo, kahaṃ kukkuṭo, kahaṃ kaḷimbho, kahaṃ nikaṭo, kahaṃ kaṭissaho;**“Mendicants, where are Cāla, Upacāla, Kakkaṭa, Kaṭimbha, Kaṭa, and Kaṭissaṅga?*";
P_HTM[2474]="*kahaṃ nu kho te, bhikkhave, therā sāvakā gatā”ti?**Where have these senior disciples gone?”*";
P_HTM[2475]="*“Idha, bhante, tesaṃ āyasmantānaṃ etadahosi:**And the mendicants told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[2476]="*‘ime kho sambahulā abhiññātā abhiññātā licchavī bhadrehi bhadrehi yānehi parapurāya uccāsaddā mahāsaddā mahāvanaṃ ajjhogāhanti bhagavantaṃ dassanāya saddakaṇṭakā kho pana jhānā vuttā bhagavatā yannūna mayaṃ yena gosiṅgasālavanadāyo tenupasaṅkameyyāma tattha mayaṃ appasaddā appākiṇṇā phāsuṃ vihareyyāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2477]="*Atha kho te, bhante, āyasmanto yena gosiṅgasālavanadāyo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[2478]="*Tattha te āyasmanto appasaddā appākiṇṇā phāsuṃ viharantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2479]="*“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhave, yathā te mahāsāvakā sammā byākaramānā byākareyyuṃ, saddakaṇṭakā hi, bhikkhave, jhānā vuttā mayā.**“Good, good, mendicants! It’s just as those great disciples have so rightly explained. I have said that sound is a thorn to absorption.*";
P_HTM[2480]="*Dasayime, bhikkhave, kaṇṭakā.**Mendicants, there are these ten thorns.*";
P_HTM[2481]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[2482]="*Pavivekārāmassa saṅgaṇikārāmatā kaṇṭako, asubhanimittānuyogaṃ anuyuttassa subhanimittānuyogo kaṇṭako, indriyesu guttadvārassa visūkadassanaṃ kaṇṭako, brahmacariyassa mātugāmūpacāro kaṇṭako, paṭhamassa jhānassa saddo kaṇṭako, dutiyassa jhānassa vitakkavicārā kaṇṭakā, tatiyassa jhānassa pīti kaṇṭako, catutthassa jhānassa assāsapassāso kaṇṭako, saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā saññā ca vedanā ca kaṇṭako rāgo kaṇṭako doso kaṇṭako moho kaṇṭako.**Relishing company is a thorn for someone who loves seclusion. Focusing on the beautiful feature of things is a thorn for someone pursuing the meditation on ugliness. Seeing shows is a thorn to someone restraining the senses. Lingering in the neighborhood of females is a thorn to celibacy. Sound is a thorn to the first absorption. Placing the mind and keeping it connected are a thorn to the second absorption. Rapture is a thorn to the third absorption. Breathing is a thorn to the fourth absorption. Perception and feeling are a thorn to the attainment of the cessation of perception and feeling. Greed, hate, and delusion are thorns.*";
P_HTM[2483]="*Akaṇṭakā, bhikkhave, viharatha.**Mendicants, live free of thorns!*";
P_HTM[2484]="*Nikkaṇṭakā, bhikkhave, viharatha.**Live rid of thorns!*";
P_HTM[2485]="*Akaṇṭakanikkaṇṭakā, bhikkhave, viharatha.**Mendicants, live free of thorns and rid of thorns!*";
P_HTM[2486]="*Akaṇṭakā, bhikkhave, arahanto;**The perfected ones live free of thorns,*";
P_HTM[2487]="*nikkaṇṭakā, bhikkhave, arahanto;**rid of thorns,*";
P_HTM[2488]="*akaṇṭakanikkaṇṭakā, bhikkhave, arahanto”ti.**free and rid of thorns.”*";
P_HTM[2489]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2490]="*3. Iṭṭhadhammasuttaṃ**Likable*";
P_HTM[2491]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dullabhā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these ten likable, desirable, and agreeable things are rare in the world.*";
P_HTM[2492]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[2493]="*Bhogā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dullabhā lokasmiṃ;**Wealth,*";
P_HTM[2494]="*vaṇṇo iṭṭho kanto manāpo dullabho lokasmiṃ;**beauty,*";
P_HTM[2495]="*ārogyaṃ iṭṭhaṃ kantaṃ manāpaṃ dullabhaṃ lokasmiṃ;**health,*";
P_HTM[2496]="*sīlaṃ iṭṭhaṃ kantaṃ manāpaṃ dullabhaṃ lokasmiṃ;**ethical conduct,*";
P_HTM[2497]="*brahmacariyaṃ iṭṭhaṃ kantaṃ manāpaṃ dullabhaṃ lokasmiṃ;**the spiritual life,*";
P_HTM[2498]="*mittā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dullabhā lokasmiṃ;**friends,*";
P_HTM[2499]="*bāhusaccaṃ iṭṭhaṃ kantaṃ manāpaṃ dullabhaṃ lokasmiṃ;**learning,*";
P_HTM[2500]="*paññā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dullabhā lokasmiṃ;**wisdom,*";
P_HTM[2501]="*dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dullabhā lokasmiṃ;**good qualities,*";
P_HTM[2502]="*saggā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā dullabhā lokasmiṃ.**and heaven are likable, desirable, and agreeable things that are rare in the world.*";
P_HTM[2503]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dasannaṃ dhammānaṃ iṭṭhānaṃ kantānaṃ manāpānaṃ dullabhānaṃ lokasmiṃ dasa dhammā paripanthā—**Ten things hinder the ten likable, desirable, and agreeable things that are rare in the world.*";
P_HTM[2504]="*ālasyaṃ anuṭṭhānaṃ bhogānaṃ paripantho, amaṇḍanā avibhūsanā vaṇṇassa paripantho, asappāyakiriyā ārogyassa paripantho, pāpamittatā sīlānaṃ paripantho, indriyaasaṃvaro brahmacariyassa paripantho, visaṃvādanā mittānaṃ paripantho, asajjhāyakiriyā bāhusaccassa paripantho, asussūsā aparipucchā paññāya paripantho, ananuyogo apaccavekkhaṇā dhammānaṃ paripantho, micchāpaṭipatti saggānaṃ paripantho.**Sloth and lack of initiative hinder wealth. Lack of adornment and decoration hinder beauty. Unsuitable activity hinders health. Bad friendship hinders ethical conduct. Lack of sense restraint hinders the spiritual life. Dishonesty hinders friends. Not reciting hinders learning. Not wanting to listen and ask questions hinders wisdom. Lack of commitment and reviewing hinder good qualities. Wrong practice hinders heaven.*";
P_HTM[2505]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dasannaṃ iṭṭhānaṃ kantānaṃ manāpānaṃ dullabhānaṃ lokasmiṃ ime dasa dhammā paripanthā.**These ten things hinder the ten likable, desirable, and agreeable things that are rare in the world.*";
P_HTM[2506]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dasannaṃ dhammānaṃ iṭṭhānaṃ kantānaṃ manāpānaṃ dullabhānaṃ lokasmiṃ dasa dhammā āhārā—**Ten things nourish the ten likable, desirable, and agreeable things that are rare in the world.*";
P_HTM[2507]="*uṭṭhānaṃ anālasyaṃ bhogānaṃ āhāro, maṇḍanā vibhūsanā vaṇṇassa āhāro, sappāyakiriyā ārogyassa āhāro, kalyāṇamittatā sīlānaṃ āhāro, indriyasaṃvaro brahmacariyassa āhāro, avisaṃvādanā mittānaṃ āhāro, sajjhāyakiriyā bāhusaccassa āhāro, sussūsā paripucchā paññāya āhāro, anuyogo paccavekkhaṇā dhammānaṃ āhāro, sammāpaṭipatti saggānaṃ āhāro.**Application and initiative nourish wealth. Adornment and decoration nourish beauty. Suitable activity nourishes health. Good friendship nourishes ethical conduct. Sense restraint nourishes the spiritual life. Honesty nourishes friends. Reciting nourishes learning. Wanting to listen and ask questions nourishes wisdom. Commitment and reviewing nourish good qualities. Right practice nourishes heaven.*";
P_HTM[2508]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dasannaṃ dhammānaṃ iṭṭhānaṃ kantānaṃ manāpānaṃ dullabhānaṃ lokasmiṃ ime dasa dhammā āhārā”ti.**These ten things nourish the ten likable, desirable, and agreeable things that are rare in the world.”*";
P_HTM[2509]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2510]="*4. Vaḍḍhisuttaṃ**Growth*";
P_HTM[2511]="*“Dasahi, bhikkhave, vaḍḍhīhi vaḍḍhamāno ariyasāvako ariyāya vaḍḍhiyā vaḍḍhati, sārādāyī ca hoti varādāyī kāyassa.**“Mendicants, a noble disciple who grows in ten ways grows nobly, taking on what is essential and excellent in this life.*";
P_HTM[2512]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[2513]="*Khettavatthūhi vaḍḍhati, dhanadhaññena vaḍḍhati, puttadārehi vaḍḍhati, dāsakammakaraporisehi vaḍḍhati, catuppadehi vaḍḍhati, saddhāya vaḍḍhati, sīlena vaḍḍhati, sutena vaḍḍhati, cāgena vaḍḍhati, paññāya vaḍḍhati—**He grows in fields and lands, money and grain, wives and children, in bondservants, workers, and staff, and in livestock. And he grows in faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2514]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi vaḍḍhīhi vaḍḍhamāno ariyasāvako ariyāya vaḍḍhiyā vaḍḍhati, sārādāyī ca hoti varādāyī kāyassāti.**A noble disciple who grows in ten ways grows nobly, taking on what is essential and excellent in this life.*";
P_HTM[2515]="*Dhanena dhaññena ca yodha vaḍḍhati,**Someone who grows in money and grain,*";
P_HTM[2516]="*Puttehi dārehi catuppadehi ca;**in wives, children, and livestock,*";
P_HTM[2517]="*Sa bhogavā hoti yasassi pūjito,**is wealthy, famous, and respected*";
P_HTM[2518]="*Ñātīhi mittehi athopi rājubhi.**by relatives and friends, and even by royals.*";
P_HTM[2519]="*Saddhāya sīlena ca yodha vaḍḍhati,**When someone grows in faith and ethics,*";
P_HTM[2520]="*Paññāya cāgena sutena cūbhayaṃ;**wisdom, and both generosity and learning—*";
P_HTM[2521]="*So tādiso sappuriso vicakkhaṇo,**a good man such as he sees clearly,*";
P_HTM[2522]="*Diṭṭheva dhamme ubhayena vaḍḍhatī”ti.**and in the present life he grows in both ways.”*";
P_HTM[2523]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2524]="*5. Migasālāsuttaṃ**With Migasālā*";
P_HTM[2525]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[2526]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena migasālāya upāsikāya nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**Then Venerable Ānanda robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to the home of the laywoman Migasālā, where he sat on the seat spread out.*";
P_HTM[2527]="*Atha kho migasālā upāsikā yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho migasālā upāsikā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**Then the laywoman Migasālā went up to Ānanda, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[2528]="*“Kathaṃ kathaṃ nāmāyaṃ, bhante ānanda, bhagavatā dhammo desito aññeyyo, yatra hi nāma brahmacārī ca abrahmacārī ca ubho samasamagatikā bhavissanti abhisamparāyaṃ.**“Sir, Ānanda, how on earth are we supposed to understand the teaching taught by the Buddha, when the chaste and the unchaste are both reborn in exactly the same place in the next life?*";
P_HTM[2529]="*Pitā me, bhante, purāṇo brahmacārī hoti ārācārī virato methunā gāmadhammā.**My father Purāṇa was celibate, set apart, avoiding the common practice of sex.*";
P_HTM[2530]="*So kālaṅkato bhagavatā byākato: ‘sakadāgāmī satto tusitaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno’ti.**When he passed away the Buddha declared that he was a once-returner, who was reborn in the company of the Joyful Gods.*";
P_HTM[2531]="*Pitāmaho me, bhante, isidatto abrahmacārī ahosi sadārasantuṭṭho.**But my uncle Isidatta was not celibate; he lived content with his wife.*";
P_HTM[2532]="*Sopi kālaṅkato bhagavatā byākato: ‘sakadāgāmī satto tusitaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno’ti.**When he passed away the Buddha declared that he was also a once-returner, who was reborn in the company of the Joyful Gods.*";
P_HTM[2533]="*Kathaṃ kathaṃ nāmāyaṃ, bhante ānanda, bhagavatā dhammo desito aññeyyo, yatra hi nāma brahmacārī ca abrahmacārī ca ubho samasamagatikā bhavissanti abhisamparāyan”ti?**How on earth are we supposed to understand the teaching taught by the Buddha, when the chaste and the unchaste are both reborn in exactly the same place in the next life?”*";
P_HTM[2534]="*“Evaṃ kho panetaṃ, bhagini, bhagavatā byākatan”ti.**“You’re right, sister, but that’s how the Buddha declared it.”*";
P_HTM[2535]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando migasālāya upāsikāya nivesane piṇḍapātaṃ gahetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi.**Then Ānanda, after receiving almsfood at Migasālā’s house, rose from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[2536]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then after the meal, on his return from alms-round, Ānanda went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[2537]="*“Idhāhaṃ, bhante, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena migasālāya upāsikāya nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2538]="*Atha kho, bhante, migasālā upāsikā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho, bhante, migasālā upāsikā maṃ etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[2539]="*‘Kathaṃ kathaṃ nāmāyaṃ, bhante ānanda, bhagavatā dhammo desito aññeyyo, yatra hi nāma brahmacārī ca abrahmacārī ca ubho samasamagatikā bhavissanti abhisamparāyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2540]="*Pitā me, bhante, purāṇo brahmacārī ahosi ārācārī virato methunā gāmadhammā.* **";
P_HTM[2541]="*So kālaṅkato bhagavatā byākato sakadāgāmī satto tusitaṃ kāyaṃ upapannoti.* **";
P_HTM[2542]="*Pitāmaho me, bhante, isidatto abrahmacārī ahosi sadārasantuṭṭho.* **";
P_HTM[2543]="*Sopi kālaṅkato bhagavatā byākato—sakadāgāmī satto tusitaṃ kāyaṃ upapannoti.* **";
P_HTM[2544]="*Kathaṃ kathaṃ nāmāyaṃ, bhante ānanda, bhagavatā dhammo desito aññeyyo, yatra hi nāma brahmacārī ca abrahmacārī ca ubho samasamagatikā bhavissanti abhisamparāyan’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2545]="*Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhante, migasālaṃ upāsikaṃ etadavocaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2546]="*‘evaṃ kho panetaṃ, bhagini, bhagavatā byākatan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2547]="*“Kā cānanda, migasālā upāsikā bālā abyattā ammakā ammakapaññā, ke ca purisapuggalaparopariye ñāṇe?**“Ānanda, who is this laywoman Migasālā, a foolish incompetent matron, with a matron’s wit? And who is it that knows how to assess individuals?*";
P_HTM[2548]="*Dasayime, ānanda, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**These ten people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2549]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[2550]="*Idhānanda, ekacco puggalo dussīlo hoti.**Take a certain person who is unethical.*";
P_HTM[2551]="*Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, yatthassa taṃ dussilyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati.**And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where that unethical conduct ceases without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[2552]="*Tassa savanenapi akataṃ hoti, bāhusaccenapi akataṃ hoti, diṭṭhiyāpi appaṭividdhaṃ hoti, sāmāyikampi vimuttiṃ na labhati.**And they’ve not listened or learned or comprehended theoretically or found even temporary freedom.*";
P_HTM[2553]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā hānāya pareti, no visesāya;**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re headed for a lower place, not a higher.*";
P_HTM[2554]="*hānagāmīyeva hoti, no visesagāmī. (1)**They’re going to a lower place, not a higher.*";
P_HTM[2555]="*Idha panānanda, ekacco puggalo dussīlo hoti.**Take a certain person who is unethical.*";
P_HTM[2556]="*Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa taṃ dussilyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati.**But they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where that unethical conduct ceases without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[2557]="*Tassa savanenapi kataṃ hoti, bāhusaccenapi kataṃ hoti, diṭṭhiyāpi paṭividdhaṃ hoti, sāmāyikampi vimuttiṃ labhati.**And they have listened and learned and comprehended theoretically and found at least temporary freedom.*";
P_HTM[2558]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā visesāya pareti, no hānāya;**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re headed for a higher place, not a lower.*";
P_HTM[2559]="*visesagāmīyeva hoti, no hānagāmī. (2)**They’re going to a higher place, not a lower.*";
P_HTM[2560]="*Tatrānanda, pamāṇikā pamiṇanti:**Judgmental people compare them, saying:*";
P_HTM[2561]="*‘imassapi teva dhammā, aparassapi teva dhammā. Kasmā nesaṃ eko hīno eko paṇīto’ti?**‘This one has just the same qualities as the other, so why is one worse and one better?’*";
P_HTM[2562]="*Tañhi tesaṃ, ānanda, hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya.**This will be for their lasting harm and suffering.*";
P_HTM[2563]="*Tatrānanda, yvāyaṃ puggalo dussīlo hoti.**In this case, the person who is unethical,*";
P_HTM[2564]="*Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa taṃ dussilyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati.**but truly understands the freedom of heart …*";
P_HTM[2565]="*Tassa savanenapi kataṃ hoti, bāhusaccenapi kataṃ hoti, diṭṭhiyāpi paṭividdhaṃ hoti, sāmāyikampi vimuttiṃ labhati.**and has listened and learned and comprehended theoretically and found at least temporary freedom*";
P_HTM[2566]="*Ayaṃ, ānanda, puggalo amunā purimena puggalena abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro ca.**is better and finer than the other person.*";
P_HTM[2567]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2568]="*Imaṃ hānanda, puggalaṃ dhammasoto nibbahati.**Because the stream of the teaching carries them along.*";
P_HTM[2569]="*Tadantaraṃ ko jāneyya, aññatra tathāgatena.**But who knows the difference between them except a Realized One?*";
P_HTM[2570]="*Tasmātihānanda, mā puggalesu pamāṇikā ahuvattha,**So, Ānanda, don’t be judgmental about people.*";
P_HTM[2571]="*mā puggalesu pamāṇaṃ gaṇhittha.**Don’t pass judgment on people.*";
P_HTM[2572]="*Khaññati hānanda, puggalesu pamāṇaṃ gaṇhanto.**Those who pass judgment on people harm themselves.*";
P_HTM[2573]="*Ahaṃ vā, ānanda, puggalesu pamāṇaṃ gaṇheyyaṃ yo vā panassa mādiso.**I, or someone like me, may pass judgment on people.*";
P_HTM[2574]="*Idha panānanda, ekacco puggalo sīlavā hoti.**Take a certain person who is ethical.*";
P_HTM[2575]="*Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa taṃ sīlaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati.**But they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where that ethical conduct ceases without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[2576]="*Tassa savanenapi akataṃ hoti, bāhusaccenapi akataṃ hoti, diṭṭhiyāpi appaṭividdhaṃ hoti, sāmāyikampi vimuttiṃ na labhati.**And they’ve not listened or learned or comprehended theoretically or found even temporary freedom.*";
P_HTM[2577]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā hānāya pareti, no visesāya;**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re headed for a lower place, not a higher.*";
P_HTM[2578]="*hānagāmīyeva hoti, no visesagāmī. (3)**They’re going to a lower place, not a higher.*";
P_HTM[2579]="*Idha panānanda, ekacco puggalo sīlavā hoti.**Take a certain person who is ethical.*";
P_HTM[2580]="*Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa taṃ sīlaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati.**And they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where that ethical conduct ceases without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[2581]="*Tassa savanenapi kataṃ hoti, bāhusaccenapi kataṃ hoti, diṭṭhiyāpi paṭividdhaṃ hoti, sāmāyikampi vimuttiṃ labhati.**And they’ve listened and learned and comprehended theoretically and found at least temporary freedom.*";
P_HTM[2582]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā visesāya pareti, no hānāya;**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re headed for a higher place, not a lower.*";
P_HTM[2583]="*visesagāmīyeva hoti, no hānagāmī. (4)**They’re going to a higher place, not a lower.*";
P_HTM[2584]="*Tatrānanda, pamāṇikā pamiṇanti … pe …**Judgmental people compare them …*";
P_HTM[2585]="*ahaṃ vā, ānanda, puggalesu pamāṇaṃ gaṇheyyaṃ yo vā panassa mādiso.**I, or someone like me, may pass judgment on people.*";
P_HTM[2586]="*Idha panānanda, ekacco puggalo tibbarāgo hoti.**Take a certain person who is very lustful.*";
P_HTM[2587]="*Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa so rāgo apariseso nirujjhati.**And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where that lust ceases without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[2588]="*Tassa savanenapi akataṃ hoti, bāhusaccenapi akataṃ hoti, diṭṭhiyāpi appaṭividdhaṃ hoti, sāmāyikampi vimuttiṃ na labhati.**And they’ve not listened or learned or comprehended theoretically or found even temporary freedom.*";
P_HTM[2589]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā hānāya pareti, no visesāya;**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re headed for a lower place, not a higher.*";
P_HTM[2590]="*hānagāmīyeva hoti, no visesagāmī. (5)**They’re going to a lower place, not a higher.*";
P_HTM[2591]="*Idha panānanda, ekacco puggalo tibbarāgo hoti.**Take a certain person who is very lustful.*";
P_HTM[2592]="*Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa so rāgo apariseso nirujjhati.**But they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where that lust ceases without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[2593]="*Tassa savanenapi kataṃ hoti, bāhusaccenapi kataṃ hoti, diṭṭhiyāpi paṭividdhaṃ hoti, sāmāyikampi vimuttiṃ labhati.**And they’ve listened and learned and comprehended theoretically and found at least temporary freedom.*";
P_HTM[2594]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā visesāya pareti, no hānāya;**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re headed for a higher place, not a lower.*";
P_HTM[2595]="*visesagāmīyeva hoti, no hānagāmī. (6)**They’re going to a higher place, not a lower.*";
P_HTM[2596]="*Tatrānanda, pamāṇikā pamiṇanti … pe …**Judgmental people compare them …*";
P_HTM[2597]="*ahaṃ vā, ānanda, puggalesu pamāṇaṃ gaṇheyyaṃ yo vā panassa mādiso.**I, or someone like me, may pass judgment on people.*";
P_HTM[2598]="*Idha panānanda, ekacco puggalo kodhano hoti.**Take a certain person who is irritable.*";
P_HTM[2599]="*Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa so kodho apariseso nirujjhati.**And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where that anger ceases without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[2600]="*Tassa savanenapi akataṃ hoti, bāhusaccenapi akataṃ hoti, diṭṭhiyāpi appaṭividdhaṃ hoti, sāmāyikampi vimuttiṃ na labhati.**And they’ve not listened or learned or comprehended theoretically or found even temporary freedom.*";
P_HTM[2601]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā hānāya pareti, no visesāya;**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re headed for a lower place, not a higher.*";
P_HTM[2602]="*hānagāmīyeva hoti, no visesagāmī. (7)**They’re going to a lower place, not a higher.*";
P_HTM[2603]="*Idha panānanda, ekacco puggalo kodhano hoti.**Take a certain person who is irritable.*";
P_HTM[2604]="*Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa so kodho apariseso nirujjhati.**But they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where that anger ceases without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[2605]="*Tassa savanenapi kataṃ hoti, bāhusaccenapi kataṃ hoti, diṭṭhiyāpi paṭividdhaṃ hoti, sāmāyikampi vimuttiṃ labhati.**And they’ve listened and learned and comprehended theoretically and found at least temporary freedom.*";
P_HTM[2606]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā visesāya pareti, no hānāya;**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re headed for a higher place, not a lower.*";
P_HTM[2607]="*visesagāmīyeva hoti, no hānagāmī. (8)**They’re going to a higher place, not a lower.*";
P_HTM[2608]="*Tatrānanda, pamāṇikā pamiṇanti … pe …**Judgmental people compare them …*";
P_HTM[2609]="*ahaṃ vā, ānanda, puggalesu pamāṇaṃ gaṇheyyaṃ yo vā panassa mādiso.**I, or someone like me, may pass judgment on people.*";
P_HTM[2610]="*Idha panānanda, ekacco puggalo uddhato hoti.**Take a certain person who is restless.*";
P_HTM[2611]="*Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa taṃ uddhaccaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati.**And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where that restlessness ceases without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[2612]="*Tassa savanenapi akataṃ hoti, bāhusaccenapi akataṃ hoti, diṭṭhiyāpi appaṭividdhaṃ hoti, sāmāyikampi vimuttiṃ na labhati.**And they’ve not listened or learned or comprehended theoretically or found even temporary freedom.*";
P_HTM[2613]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā hānāya pareti, no visesāya;**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re headed for a lower place, not a higher.*";
P_HTM[2614]="*hānagāmīyeva hoti, no visesagāmī. (9)**They’re going to a lower place, not a higher.*";
P_HTM[2615]="*Idha panānanda, ekacco puggalo uddhato hoti.**Take a certain person who is restless.*";
P_HTM[2616]="*Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa taṃ uddhaccaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati.**But they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where that restlessness ceases without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[2617]="*Tassa savanenapi kataṃ hoti, bāhusaccenapi kataṃ hoti, diṭṭhiyāpi paṭividdhaṃ hoti, sāmāyikampi vimuttiṃ labhati.**And they’ve listened and learned and comprehended theoretically and found at least temporary freedom.*";
P_HTM[2618]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā visesāya pareti, no hānāya;**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re headed for a higher place, not a lower.*";
P_HTM[2619]="*visesagāmīyeva hoti, no hānagāmī. (10)**They’re going to a higher place, not a lower.*";
P_HTM[2620]="*Tatrānanda, pamāṇikā pamiṇanti:**Judgmental people compare them, saying:*";
P_HTM[2621]="*‘imassapi teva dhammā, aparassapi teva dhammā. Kasmā nesaṃ eko hīno eko paṇīto’ti?**‘This one has just the same qualities as the other, so why is one worse and one better?’*";
P_HTM[2622]="*Tañhi tesaṃ, ānanda, hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya.**This will be for their lasting harm and suffering.*";
P_HTM[2623]="*Tatrānanda, yvāyaṃ puggalo uddhato hoti tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa taṃ uddhaccaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati,**In this case the person who is restless, but truly understands the freedom of heart …*";
P_HTM[2624]="*tassa savanenapi kataṃ hoti, bāhusaccenapi kataṃ hoti, diṭṭhiyāpi paṭividdhaṃ hoti, sāmāyikampi vimuttiṃ labhati.**and has listened and learned and comprehended theoretically and found at least temporary freedom*";
P_HTM[2625]="*Ayaṃ, ānanda, puggalo amunā purimena puggalena abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro ca.**is better and finer than the other person.*";
P_HTM[2626]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2627]="*Imaṃ hānanda, puggalaṃ dhammasoto nibbahati.**Because the stream of the teaching carries them along.*";
P_HTM[2628]="*Tadantaraṃ ko jāneyya aññatra tathāgatena.**But who knows the difference between them except a Realized One?*";
P_HTM[2629]="*Tasmātihānanda, mā puggalesu pamāṇikā ahuvattha;**So, Ānanda, don’t be judgmental about people.*";
P_HTM[2630]="*mā puggalesu pamāṇaṃ gaṇhittha.**Don’t pass judgment on people.*";
P_HTM[2631]="*Khaññati hānanda, puggalesu pamāṇaṃ gaṇhanto.**Those who pass judgment on people harm themselves.*";
P_HTM[2632]="*Ahaṃ vā, ānanda, puggalesu pamāṇaṃ gaṇheyyaṃ yo vā panassa mādiso.**I, or someone like me, may pass judgment on people.*";
P_HTM[2633]="*Kā cānanda, migasālā upāsikā bālā abyattā ammakā ammakapaññā, ke ca purisapuggalaparopariye ñāṇe.**Who is this laywoman Migasālā, a foolish incompetent matron, with a matron’s wit? And who is it that knows how to assess individuals?*";
P_HTM[2634]="*Ime kho, ānanda, dasa puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**These ten people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2635]="*Yathārūpena, ānanda, sīlena purāṇo samannāgato ahosi tathārūpena sīlena isidatto samannāgato abhavissa, nayidha purāṇo isidattassa gatimpi aññassa.**If Isidatta had achieved Purāṇa’s level of ethical conduct, Purāṇa could not have even known Isidatta’s destination.*";
P_HTM[2636]="*Yathārūpāya cānanda, paññāya isidatto samannāgato ahosi tathārūpāya paññāya purāṇo samannāgato abhavissa, nayidha isidatto purāṇassa gatimpi aññassa.**And if Purāṇa had achieved Isidatta’s level of wisdom, Isidatta could not have even known Purāṇa’s destination.*";
P_HTM[2637]="*Iti kho, ānanda, ime puggalā ubho ekaṅgahīnā”ti.**So both individuals were lacking in one respect.”*";
P_HTM[2638]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2639]="*6. Tayodhammasuttaṃ**Three Things*";
P_HTM[2640]="*“Tayome, bhikkhave, dhammā loke na saṃvijjeyyuṃ, na tathāgato loke uppajjeyya arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, na tathāgatappavedito dhammavinayo loke dibbeyya.**“Mendicants, if three things were not found, the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha would not arise in the world, and the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One would not shine in the world.*";
P_HTM[2641]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2642]="*Jāti ca, jarā ca, maraṇañca—**Rebirth, old age, and death.*";
P_HTM[2643]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhammā loke na saṃvijjeyyuṃ, na tathāgato loke uppajjeyya arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, na tathāgatappavedito dhammavinayo loke dibbeyya.**If these three things were not found, the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha would not arise in the world, and the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One would not shine in the world.*";
P_HTM[2644]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, ime tayo dhammā loke saṃvijjanti tasmā tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, tasmā tathāgatappavedito dhammavinayo loke dibbati.**But since these three things are found, the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha arises in the world, and the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One shines in the world.*";
P_HTM[2645]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme appahāya abhabbo jātiṃ pahātuṃ jaraṃ pahātuṃ maraṇaṃ pahātuṃ.**Without giving up three things you can’t give up rebirth, old age, and death.*";
P_HTM[2646]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2647]="*Rāgaṃ appahāya, dosaṃ appahāya, mohaṃ appahāya—**Greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[2648]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme appahāya abhabbo jātiṃ pahātuṃ jaraṃ pahātuṃ maraṇaṃ pahātuṃ. (1)**Without giving up these three things you can’t give up rebirth, old age, and death.*";
P_HTM[2649]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme appahāya abhabbo rāgaṃ pahātuṃ dosaṃ pahātuṃ mohaṃ pahātuṃ.**Without giving up three things you can’t give up greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[2650]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2651]="*Sakkāyadiṭṭhiṃ appahāya, vicikicchaṃ appahāya, sīlabbataparāmāsaṃ appahāya—**Identity view, doubt, and misapprehension of precepts and observances.*";
P_HTM[2652]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme appahāya abhabbo rāgaṃ pahātuṃ dosaṃ pahātuṃ mohaṃ pahātuṃ. (2)**Without giving up these three things you can’t give up greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[2653]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme appahāya abhabbo sakkāyadiṭṭhiṃ pahātuṃ vicikicchaṃ pahātuṃ sīlabbataparāmāsaṃ pahātuṃ.**Without giving up three things you can’t give up identity view, doubt, and misapprehension of precepts and observances.*";
P_HTM[2654]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2655]="*Ayonisomanasikāraṃ appahāya, kummaggasevanaṃ appahāya, cetaso līnattaṃ appahāya—**Improper attention, following a wrong path, and mental sluggishness.*";
P_HTM[2656]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme appahāya abhabbo sakkāyadiṭṭhiṃ pahātuṃ vicikicchaṃ pahātuṃ sīlabbataparāmāsaṃ pahātuṃ. (3)**Without giving up these three things you can’t give up identity view, doubt, and misapprehension of precepts and observances.*";
P_HTM[2657]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme appahāya abhabbo ayoniso manasikāraṃ pahātuṃ kummaggasevanaṃ pahātuṃ cetaso līnattaṃ pahātuṃ.**Without giving up three things you can’t give up improper attention, following a wrong path, and mental sluggishness.*";
P_HTM[2658]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2659]="*Muṭṭhassaccaṃ appahāya, asampajaññaṃ appahāya, cetaso vikkhepaṃ appahāya—**Unmindfulness, lack of situational awareness, and distracted mind.*";
P_HTM[2660]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme appahāya abhabbo ayonisomanasikāraṃ pahātuṃ kummaggasevanaṃ pahātuṃ cetaso līnattaṃ pahātuṃ. (4)**Without giving up these three things you can’t give up improper attention, following a wrong path, and mental sluggishness.*";
P_HTM[2661]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme appahāya abhabbo muṭṭhassaccaṃ pahātuṃ asampajaññaṃ pahātuṃ cetaso vikkhepaṃ pahātuṃ.**Without giving up three things you can’t give up unmindfulness, lack of situational awareness, and distracted mind.*";
P_HTM[2662]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2663]="*Ariyānaṃ adassanakamyataṃ appahāya, ariyadhammassa asotukamyataṃ appahāya, upārambhacittataṃ appahāya—**Not wanting to see the noble ones, not wanting to hear the teaching of the noble ones, and a fault-finding mind.*";
P_HTM[2664]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme appahāya abhabbo muṭṭhassaccaṃ pahātuṃ asampajaññaṃ pahātuṃ cetaso vikkhepaṃ pahātuṃ. (5)**Without giving up these three things you can’t give up unmindfulness, lack of situational awareness, and distracted mind.*";
P_HTM[2665]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme appahāya abhabbo ariyānaṃ adassanakamyataṃ pahātuṃ ariyadhammassa asotukamyataṃ pahātuṃ upārambhacittataṃ pahātuṃ.**Without giving up three things you can’t give up not wanting to see the noble ones, not wanting to hear the teaching of the noble ones, and a fault-finding mind.*";
P_HTM[2666]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2667]="*Uddhaccaṃ appahāya, asaṃvaraṃ appahāya, dussilyaṃ appahāya—**Restlessness, lack of restraint, and unethical conduct.*";
P_HTM[2668]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme appahāya abhabbo ariyānaṃ adassanakamyataṃ pahātuṃ ariyadhammassa asotukamyataṃ pahātuṃ upārambhacittataṃ pahātuṃ. (6)**Without giving up these three things you can’t give up not wanting to see the noble ones, not wanting to hear the teaching of the noble ones, and a fault-finding mind.*";
P_HTM[2669]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme appahāya abhabbo uddhaccaṃ pahātuṃ asaṃvaraṃ pahātuṃ dussilyaṃ pahātuṃ.**Without giving up three things you can’t give up restlessness, lack of restraint, and unethical conduct.*";
P_HTM[2670]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2671]="*Assaddhiyaṃ appahāya, avadaññutaṃ appahāya, kosajjaṃ appahāya—**Faithlessness, uncharitableness, and laziness.*";
P_HTM[2672]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme appahāya abhabbo uddhaccaṃ pahātuṃ asaṃvaraṃ pahātuṃ dussilyaṃ pahātuṃ. (7)**Without giving up these three things you can’t give up restlessness, lack of restraint, and unethical conduct.*";
P_HTM[2673]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme appahāya abhabbo assaddhiyaṃ pahātuṃ avadaññutaṃ pahātuṃ kosajjaṃ pahātuṃ.**Without giving up three things you can’t give up faithlessness, uncharitableness, and laziness.*";
P_HTM[2674]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2675]="*Anādariyaṃ appahāya, dovacassataṃ appahāya, pāpamittataṃ appahāya—**Disregard, being hard to admonish, and having bad friends.*";
P_HTM[2676]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme appahāya abhabbo assaddhiyaṃ pahātuṃ avadaññutaṃ pahātuṃ kosajjaṃ pahātuṃ. (8)**Without giving up these three things you can’t give up faithlessness, uncharitableness, and laziness.*";
P_HTM[2677]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme appahāya abhabbo anādariyaṃ pahātuṃ dovacassataṃ pahātuṃ pāpamittataṃ pahātuṃ.**Without giving up three things you can’t give up disregard, being hard to admonish, and having bad friends.*";
P_HTM[2678]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2679]="*Ahirikaṃ appahāya, anottappaṃ appahāya, pamādaṃ appahāya—**Lack of conscience, imprudence, and negligence.*";
P_HTM[2680]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme appahāya abhabbo anādariyaṃ pahātuṃ dovacassataṃ pahātuṃ pāpamittataṃ pahātuṃ. (9)**Without giving up these three things you can’t give up disregard, being hard to admonish, and having bad friends.*";
P_HTM[2681]="*Ahirikoyaṃ, bhikkhave, anottāpī pamatto hoti.**Mendicants, someone who lacks conscience and prudence is negligent.*";
P_HTM[2682]="*So pamatto samāno abhabbo anādariyaṃ pahātuṃ dovacassataṃ pahātuṃ pāpamittataṃ pahātuṃ.**When you’re negligent you can’t give up disregard, being hard to admonish, and having bad friends.*";
P_HTM[2683]="*So pāpamitto samāno abhabbo assaddhiyaṃ pahātuṃ avadaññutaṃ pahātuṃ kosajjaṃ pahātuṃ.**When you’ve got bad friends you can’t give up faithlessness, uncharitableness, and laziness.*";
P_HTM[2684]="*So kusīto samāno abhabbo uddhaccaṃ pahātuṃ asaṃvaraṃ pahātuṃ dussilyaṃ pahātuṃ.**When you’re lazy you can’t give up restlessness, lack of restraint, and unethical conduct.*";
P_HTM[2685]="*So dussīlo samāno abhabbo ariyānaṃ adassanakamyataṃ pahātuṃ ariyadhammassa asotukamyataṃ pahātuṃ upārambhacittataṃ pahātuṃ.**When you’re unethical you can’t give up not wanting to see the noble ones, not wanting to hear the teaching of the noble ones, and a fault-finding mind.*";
P_HTM[2686]="*So upārambhacitto samāno abhabbo muṭṭhassaccaṃ pahātuṃ asampajaññaṃ pahātuṃ cetaso vikkhepaṃ pahātuṃ.**When you’ve got a fault-finding mind you can’t give up unmindfulness, lack of situational awareness, and a distracted mind.*";
P_HTM[2687]="*So vikkhittacitto samāno abhabbo ayonisomanasikāraṃ pahātuṃ kummaggasevanaṃ pahātuṃ cetaso līnattaṃ pahātuṃ.**When your mind is scattered you can’t give up improper attention, following a wrong path, and mental sluggishness.*";
P_HTM[2688]="*So līnacitto samāno abhabbo sakkāyadiṭṭhiṃ pahātuṃ vicikicchaṃ pahātuṃ sīlabbataparāmāsaṃ pahātuṃ.**When your mind is sluggish you can’t give up identity view, doubt, and misapprehension of precepts and observances.*";
P_HTM[2689]="*So vicikiccho samāno abhabbo rāgaṃ pahātuṃ dosaṃ pahātuṃ mohaṃ pahātuṃ.**When you have doubts you can’t give up greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[2690]="*So rāgaṃ appahāya dosaṃ appahāya mohaṃ appahāya abhabbo jātiṃ pahātuṃ jaraṃ pahātuṃ maraṇaṃ pahātuṃ. (10)**Without giving up greed, hate, and delusion you can’t give up rebirth, old age, and death.*";
P_HTM[2691]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme pahāya bhabbo jātiṃ pahātuṃ jaraṃ pahātuṃ maraṇaṃ pahātuṃ.**After giving up three things you can give up rebirth, old age, and death.*";
P_HTM[2692]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2693]="*Rāgaṃ pahāya, dosaṃ pahāya, mohaṃ pahāya—**Greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[2694]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme pahāya bhabbo jātiṃ pahātuṃ jaraṃ pahātuṃ maraṇaṃ pahātuṃ. (1)**After giving up these three things you can give up rebirth, old age, and death.*";
P_HTM[2695]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme pahāya bhabbo rāgaṃ pahātuṃ dosaṃ pahātuṃ mohaṃ pahātuṃ.**After giving up three things you can give up greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[2696]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2697]="*Sakkāyadiṭṭhiṃ pahāya, vicikicchaṃ pahāya, sīlabbataparāmāsaṃ pahāya—**Identity view, doubt, and misapprehension of precepts and observances.*";
P_HTM[2698]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme pahāya bhabbo rāgaṃ pahātuṃ dosaṃ pahātuṃ mohaṃ pahātuṃ. (2)**After giving up these three things you can give up greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[2699]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme pahāya bhabbo sakkāyadiṭṭhiṃ pahātuṃ vicikicchaṃ pahātuṃ sīlabbataparāmāsaṃ pahātuṃ.**After giving up three things you can give up identity view, doubt, and misapprehension of precepts and observances.*";
P_HTM[2700]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2701]="*Ayonisomanasikāraṃ pahāya, kummaggasevanaṃ pahāya, cetaso līnattaṃ pahāya—**Improper attention, following a wrong path, and mental sluggishness.*";
P_HTM[2702]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme pahāya bhabbo sakkāyadiṭṭhiṃ pahātuṃ vicikicchaṃ pahātuṃ sīlabbataparāmāsaṃ pahātuṃ. (3)**After giving up these three things you can give up identity view, doubt, and misapprehension of precepts and observances.*";
P_HTM[2703]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme pahāya bhabbo ayonisomanasikāraṃ pahātuṃ kummaggasevanaṃ pahātuṃ cetaso līnattaṃ pahātuṃ.**After giving up three things you can give up improper attention, following a wrong path, and mental sluggishness.*";
P_HTM[2704]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2705]="*Muṭṭhassaccaṃ pahāya, asampajaññaṃ pahāya, cetaso vikkhepaṃ pahāya—**Unmindfulness, lack of situational awareness, and a distracted mind.*";
P_HTM[2706]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme pahāya bhabbo ayonisomanasikāraṃ pahātuṃ kummaggasevanaṃ pahātuṃ cetaso līnattaṃ pahātuṃ. (4)**After giving up these three things you can give up improper attention, following a wrong path, and mental sluggishness.*";
P_HTM[2707]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme pahāya bhabbo muṭṭhassaccaṃ pahātuṃ asampajaññaṃ pahātuṃ cetaso vikkhepaṃ pahātuṃ.**After giving up three things you can give up unmindfulness, lack of situational awareness, and distracted mind.*";
P_HTM[2708]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2709]="*Ariyānaṃ adassanakamyataṃ pahāya, ariyadhammassa asotukamyataṃ pahāya, upārambhacittataṃ pahāya—**Not wanting to see the noble ones, not wanting to hear the teaching of the noble ones, and a fault-finding mind.*";
P_HTM[2710]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme pahāya bhabbo muṭṭhassaccaṃ pahātuṃ asampajaññaṃ pahātuṃ cetaso vikkhepaṃ pahātuṃ. (5)**After giving up these three things you can give up unmindfulness, lack of situational awareness, and distracted mind.*";
P_HTM[2711]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme pahāya bhabbo ariyānaṃ adassanakamyataṃ pahātuṃ ariyadhammassa asotukamyataṃ pahātuṃ upārambhacittataṃ pahātuṃ.**After giving up three things you can give up not wanting to see the noble ones, not wanting to hear the teaching of the noble ones, and a fault-finding mind.*";
P_HTM[2712]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2713]="*Uddhaccaṃ pahāya, asaṃvaraṃ pahāya, dussilyaṃ pahāya—**Restlessness, lack of restraint, and unethical conduct.*";
P_HTM[2714]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme pahāya bhabbo ariyānaṃ adassanakamyataṃ pahātuṃ ariyadhammassa asotukamyataṃ pahātuṃ upārambhacittataṃ pahātuṃ. (6)**After giving up these three things you can give up not wanting to see the noble ones, not wanting to hear the teaching of the noble ones, and a fault-finding mind.*";
P_HTM[2715]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme pahāya bhabbo uddhaccaṃ pahātuṃ asaṃvaraṃ pahātuṃ dussilyaṃ pahātuṃ.**After giving up three things you can give up restlessness, lack of restraint, and unethical conduct.*";
P_HTM[2716]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2717]="*Assaddhiyaṃ pahāya, avadaññutaṃ pahāya, kosajjaṃ pahāya—**Faithlessness, uncharitableness, and laziness.*";
P_HTM[2718]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme pahāya bhabbo uddhaccaṃ pahātuṃ asaṃvaraṃ pahātuṃ dussilyaṃ pahātuṃ. (7)**After giving up these three things you can give up restlessness, lack of restraint, and unethical conduct.*";
P_HTM[2719]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme pahāya bhabbo assaddhiyaṃ pahātuṃ avadaññutaṃ pahātuṃ kosajjaṃ pahātuṃ.**After giving up three things you can give up faithlessness, uncharitableness, and laziness.*";
P_HTM[2720]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2721]="*Anādariyaṃ pahāya, dovacassataṃ pahāya, pāpamittataṃ pahāya—**Disregard, being hard to admonish, and having bad friends.*";
P_HTM[2722]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme pahāya bhabbo assaddhiyaṃ pahātuṃ avadaññutaṃ pahātuṃ kosajjaṃ pahātuṃ. (8)**After giving up these three things you can give up faithlessness, uncharitableness, and laziness.*";
P_HTM[2723]="*Tayome, bhikkhave, dhamme pahāya bhabbo anādariyaṃ pahātuṃ dovacassataṃ pahātuṃ pāpamittataṃ pahātuṃ.**After giving up three things you can give up disregard, being hard to admonish, and having bad friends.*";
P_HTM[2724]="*Katame tayo?**What three?*";
P_HTM[2725]="*Ahirikaṃ pahāya, anottappaṃ pahāya, pamādaṃ pahāya—**Lack of conscience, imprudence, and negligence.*";
P_HTM[2726]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo dhamme pahāya bhabbo anādariyaṃ pahātuṃ dovacassataṃ pahātuṃ pāpamittataṃ pahātuṃ. (9)**After giving up these three things you can give up disregard, being hard to admonish, and having bad friends.*";
P_HTM[2727]="*Hirīmāyaṃ, bhikkhave, ottāpī appamatto hoti.**Mendicants, someone who has conscience and prudence is diligent.*";
P_HTM[2728]="*So appamatto samāno bhabbo anādariyaṃ pahātuṃ dovacassataṃ pahātuṃ pāpamittataṃ pahātuṃ.**When you’re diligent you can give up disregard, being hard to admonish, and having bad friends.*";
P_HTM[2729]="*So kalyāṇamitto samāno bhabbo assaddhiyaṃ pahātuṃ avadaññutaṃ pahātuṃ kosajjaṃ pahātuṃ.**When you’ve got good friends you can give up faithlessness, uncharitableness, and laziness.*";
P_HTM[2730]="*So āraddhavīriyo samāno bhabbo uddhaccaṃ pahātuṃ asaṃvaraṃ pahātuṃ dussilyaṃ pahātuṃ.**When you’re energetic you can give up restlessness, lack of restraint, and unethical conduct.*";
P_HTM[2731]="*So sīlavā samāno bhabbo ariyānaṃ adassanakamyataṃ pahātuṃ ariyadhammassa asotukamyataṃ pahātuṃ upārambhacittataṃ pahātuṃ.**When you’re ethical you can give up not wanting to see the noble ones, not wanting to hear the teaching of the noble ones, and a fault-finding mind.*";
P_HTM[2732]="*So anupārambhacitto samāno bhabbo muṭṭhassaccaṃ pahātuṃ asampajaññaṃ pahātuṃ cetaso vikkhepaṃ pahātuṃ.**When you don’t have a fault-finding mind you can give up unmindfulness, lack of situational awareness, and a distracted mind.*";
P_HTM[2733]="*So avikkhittacitto samāno bhabbo ayonisomanasikāraṃ pahātuṃ kummaggasevanaṃ pahātuṃ cetaso līnattaṃ pahātuṃ.**When your mind isn’t scattered you can give up improper attention, following a wrong path, and mental sluggishness.*";
P_HTM[2734]="*So alīnacitto samāno bhabbo sakkāyadiṭṭhiṃ pahātuṃ vicikicchaṃ pahātuṃ sīlabbataparāmāsaṃ pahātuṃ.**When your mind isn’t sluggish you can give up identity view, doubt, and misapprehension of precepts and observances.*";
P_HTM[2735]="*So avicikiccho samāno bhabbo rāgaṃ pahātuṃ dosaṃ pahātuṃ mohaṃ pahātuṃ.**When you have no doubts you can give up greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[2736]="*So rāgaṃ pahāya dosaṃ pahāya mohaṃ pahāya bhabbo jātiṃ pahātuṃ jaraṃ pahātuṃ maraṇaṃ pahātun”ti. (10)**After giving up greed, hate, and delusion you can give up rebirth, old age, and death.”*";
P_HTM[2737]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2738]="*7. Kākasuttaṃ**A Crow*";
P_HTM[2739]="*“Dasahi, bhikkhave, asaddhammehi samannāgato kāko.**“Mendicants, a crow has ten bad qualities.*";
P_HTM[2740]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[2741]="*Dhaṃsī ca, pagabbho ca, tintiṇo ca, mahagghaso ca, luddo ca, akāruṇiko ca, dubbalo ca, oravitā ca, muṭṭhassati ca, necayiko ca—**They’re rude and impudent, gluttonous and voracious, cruel and pitiless, weak and raucous, unmindful and acquisitive.*";
P_HTM[2742]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi asaddhammehi samannāgato kāko.**A crow has these ten bad qualities.*";
P_HTM[2743]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dasahi asaddhammehi samannāgato pāpabhikkhu.**In the same way, a bad mendicant has these ten bad qualities.*";
P_HTM[2744]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[2745]="*Dhaṃsī ca, pagabbho ca, tintiṇo ca, mahagghaso ca, luddo ca, akāruṇiko ca, dubbalo ca, oravitā ca, muṭṭhassati ca, necayiko ca—**They’re rude and impudent, gluttonous and voracious, cruel and pitiless, weak and raucous, unmindful and acquisitive.*";
P_HTM[2746]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi asaddhammehi samannāgato pāpabhikkhū”ti.**A bad mendicant has these ten bad qualities.”*";
P_HTM[2747]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2748]="*8. Nigaṇṭhasuttaṃ**Jains*";
P_HTM[2749]="*“Dasahi, bhikkhave, asaddhammehi samannāgatā nigaṇṭhā.**“Mendicants, Jain ascetics have ten bad qualities.*";
P_HTM[2750]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[2751]="*Assaddhā, bhikkhave, nigaṇṭhā;**They’re faithless and*";
P_HTM[2752]="*dussīlā, bhikkhave, nigaṇṭhā;**unethical,*";
P_HTM[2753]="*ahirikā, bhikkhave, nigaṇṭhā;**without conscience*";
P_HTM[2754]="*anottappino, bhikkhave, nigaṇṭhā;**or prudence,*";
P_HTM[2755]="*asappurisasambhattino, bhikkhave, nigaṇṭhā;**and devoted to bad persons.*";
P_HTM[2756]="*attukkaṃsakaparavambhakā, bhikkhave, nigaṇṭhā;**They glorify themselves and put others down.*";
P_HTM[2757]="*sandiṭṭhiparāmāsā ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggino, bhikkhave, nigaṇṭhā;**They’re attached to their own views, holding them tight, and refusing to let go.*";
P_HTM[2758]="*kuhakā, bhikkhave, nigaṇṭhā;**They’re deceptive,*";
P_HTM[2759]="*pāpicchā, bhikkhave, nigaṇṭhā;**with bad desires*";
P_HTM[2760]="*pāpamittā, bhikkhave, nigaṇṭhā—**and bad friends.*";
P_HTM[2761]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi asaddhammehi samannāgatā nigaṇṭhā”ti.**Jain ascetics have these ten bad qualities.”*";
P_HTM[2762]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2763]="*9. Āghātavatthusuttaṃ**Grounds for Resentment*";
P_HTM[2764]="*“Dasayimāni, bhikkhave, āghātavatthūni.**“Mendicants, there are ten grounds for resentment.*";
P_HTM[2765]="*Katamāni dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[2766]="*‘Anatthaṃ me acarī’ti āghātaṃ bandhati;**Thinking: ‘They did wrong to me,’ you harbor resentment.*";
P_HTM[2767]="*‘anatthaṃ me caratī’ti āghātaṃ bandhati;**Thinking: ‘They are doing wrong to me’ …*";
P_HTM[2768]="*‘anatthaṃ me carissatī’ti āghātaṃ bandhati;**‘They will do wrong to me’ …*";
P_HTM[2769]="*‘piyassa me manāpassa anatthaṃ acarī’ti … pe …**‘They did wrong by someone I love’ …*";
P_HTM[2770]="*‘anatthaṃ caratī’ti … pe …**‘They are doing wrong by someone I love’ …*";
P_HTM[2771]="*‘anatthaṃ carissatī’ti āghātaṃ bandhati,**‘They will do wrong by someone I love’ …*";
P_HTM[2772]="*‘appiyassa me amanāpassa atthaṃ acarī’ti … pe …**‘They helped someone I dislike’ …*";
P_HTM[2773]="*‘atthaṃ caratī’ti … pe …**‘They are helping someone I dislike’ …*";
P_HTM[2774]="*‘atthaṃ carissatī’ti āghātaṃ bandhati;**Thinking: ‘They will help someone I dislike,’ you harbor resentment.*";
P_HTM[2775]="*aṭṭhāne ca kuppati—**You get angry for no reason.*";
P_HTM[2776]="*imāni kho, bhikkhave, dasa āghātavatthūnī”ti.**These are the ten grounds for resentment.”*";
P_HTM[2777]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2778]="*10. Āghātapaṭivinayasuttaṃ**Getting Rid of Resentment*";
P_HTM[2779]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, āghātapaṭivinayā.**“Mendicants, there are these ten methods to get rid of resentment.*";
P_HTM[2780]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[2781]="*‘Anatthaṃ me acari, taṃ kutettha labbhā’ti āghātaṃ paṭivineti,**Thinking: ‘They harmed me, but what can I possibly do?’ you get rid of resentment.*";
P_HTM[2782]="*‘anatthaṃ me carati, taṃ kutettha labbhā’ti āghātaṃ paṭivineti,**Thinking: ‘They are harming me …’ …*";
P_HTM[2783]="*‘anatthaṃ me carissati, taṃ kutettha labbhā’ti āghātaṃ paṭivineti,**‘They will harm me …’ …*";
P_HTM[2784]="*piyassa me manāpassa anatthaṃ acari … pe …**‘They harmed someone I love …’ …*";
P_HTM[2785]="*carati … pe …**‘They are harming someone I love …’*";
P_HTM[2786]="*carissati, taṃ kutettha labbhāti āghātaṃ paṭivineti, appiyassa me amanāpassa atthaṃ acari … pe …**‘They will harm someone I love …’ … They helped someone I dislike …’ …*";
P_HTM[2787]="*atthaṃ carati … pe …**‘They are helping someone I dislike …’ …*";
P_HTM[2788]="*atthaṃ carissati, taṃ kutettha labbhāti āghātaṃ paṭivineti,**Thinking: ‘They will help someone I dislike, but what can I possibly do?’ you get rid of resentment.*";
P_HTM[2789]="*aṭṭhāne ca na kuppati—**And you don’t get angry for no reason.*";
P_HTM[2790]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa āghātapaṭivinayā”ti.**These are the ten ways of getting rid of resentment.”*";
P_HTM[2791]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2792]="*Ākaṅkhavaggo tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[2793]="*Ākaṅkho kaṇṭako iṭṭhā,* **";
P_HTM[2794]="*vaḍḍhi ca migasālāya;* **";
P_HTM[2795]="*Tayo dhammā ca kāko ca,* **";
P_HTM[2796]="*nigaṇṭhā dve ca āghātāti.* **";
P_HTM[2797]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Senior Mendicants*";
P_HTM[2798]="*1. Vāhanasuttaṃ**With Bāhuna*";
P_HTM[2799]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā campāyaṃ viharati gaggarāya pokkharaṇiyā tīre.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Campā on the banks of the Gaggarā Lotus Pond.*";
P_HTM[2800]="*Atha kho āyasmā vāhano yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā vāhano bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Bāhuna went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[2801]="*“katihi nu kho, bhante, dhammehi tathāgato nissaṭo visaṃyutto vippamutto vimariyādīkatena cetasā viharatī”ti?**“Sir, how many things has the Realized One escaped from, so that he lives unattached, liberated, his mind free of limits?”*";
P_HTM[2802]="*“Dasahi kho, vāhana, dhammehi tathāgato nissaṭo visaṃyutto vippamutto vimariyādīkatena cetasā viharati.**“Bāhuna, the Realized One has escaped from ten things, so that he lives unattached, liberated, his mind free of limits.*";
P_HTM[2803]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[2804]="*Rūpena kho, vāhana, tathāgato nissaṭo visaṃyutto vippamutto vimariyādīkatena cetasā viharati,**Form …*";
P_HTM[2805]="*vedanāya kho, vāhana … pe …**feeling …*";
P_HTM[2806]="*saññāya kho, vāhana …**perception …*";
P_HTM[2807]="*saṅkhārehi kho, vāhana …**choices …*";
P_HTM[2808]="*viññāṇena kho, vāhana …**consciousness …*";
P_HTM[2809]="*jātiyā kho, vāhana …**rebirth …*";
P_HTM[2810]="*jarāya kho, vāhana …**old age …*";
P_HTM[2811]="*maraṇena kho, vāhana …**death …*";
P_HTM[2812]="*dukkhehi kho, vāhana …**suffering …*";
P_HTM[2813]="*kilesehi kho, vāhana, tathāgato nissaṭo visaṃyutto vippamutto vimariyādīkatena cetasā viharati.**defilements …*";
P_HTM[2814]="*Seyyathāpi, vāhana, uppalaṃ vā padumaṃ vā puṇḍarīkaṃ vā udake jātaṃ udake saṃvaḍḍhaṃ udakā paccuggamma ṭhitaṃ anupalittaṃ udakena;**Suppose there was a blue water lily, or a pink or white lotus. Though it sprouted and grew in the water, it would rise up above the water and stand with no water clinging to it.*";
P_HTM[2815]="*evamevaṃ kho, vāhana, imehi dasahi dhammehi tathāgato nissaṭo visaṃyutto vippamutto vimariyādīkatena cetasā viharatī”ti.**In the same way, the Realized One has escaped from ten things, so that he lives unattached, liberated, his mind free of limits.”*";
P_HTM[2816]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2817]="*2. Ānandasuttaṃ**With Ānanda*";
P_HTM[2818]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[2819]="*“So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘assaddho samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. (1)**“Ānanda, it’s not possible for a faithless mendicant to achieve growth, improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[2820]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘dussīlo samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. (2)**It’s not possible for a mendicant who is unethical …*";
P_HTM[2821]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘appassuto samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. (3)**uneducated …*";
P_HTM[2822]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘dubbaco samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. (4)**hard to admonish …*";
P_HTM[2823]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘pāpamitto samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. (5)**with bad friends …*";
P_HTM[2824]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘kusīto samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. (6)**lazy …*";
P_HTM[2825]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘muṭṭhassati samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. (7)**unmindful …*";
P_HTM[2826]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘asantuṭṭho samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. (8)**lacking contentment …*";
P_HTM[2827]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘pāpiccho samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. (9)**of bad desires …*";
P_HTM[2828]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘micchādiṭṭhiko samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. (10)**of wrong view to achieve growth, improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[2829]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘imehi dasahi dhammehi samannāgato imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**It’s not possible for a mendicant with these ten qualities to achieve growth, improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[2830]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘saddho samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. (1)**It is possible for a faithful mendicant to achieve growth, improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[2831]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘sīlavā samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. (2)**It is possible for a mendicant who is ethical …*";
P_HTM[2832]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘bahussuto sutadharo samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. (3)**a learned memorizer …*";
P_HTM[2833]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘suvaco samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. (4)**easy to admonish …*";
P_HTM[2834]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘kalyāṇamitto samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. (5)**with good friends …*";
P_HTM[2835]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘āraddhavīriyo samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. (6)**energetic …*";
P_HTM[2836]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘upaṭṭhitassati samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. (7)**mindful …*";
P_HTM[2837]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘santuṭṭho samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. (8)**contented …*";
P_HTM[2838]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘appiccho samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. (9)**of few desires …*";
P_HTM[2839]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘sammādiṭṭhiko samāno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. (10)**of right view to achieve growth, improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[2840]="*So vatānanda, bhikkhu ‘imehi dasahi dhammehi samannāgato imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti ṭhānametaṃ vijjatī”ti.**It is possible for a mendicant with these ten qualities to achieve growth, improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training.”*";
P_HTM[2841]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2842]="*3. Puṇṇiyasuttaṃ**With Puṇṇiya*";
P_HTM[2843]="*Atha kho āyasmā puṇṇiyo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā puṇṇiyo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Puṇṇiya went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[2844]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo yena appekadā tathāgataṃ dhammadesanā paṭibhāti appekadā nappaṭibhātī”ti?**“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why sometimes the Realized One feels inspired to teach, and other times not?”*";
P_HTM[2845]="*“Saddho ca, puṇṇiya, bhikkhu hoti, no ca upasaṅkamitā; neva tāva tathāgataṃ dhammadesanā paṭibhāti.**“Puṇṇiya, when a mendicant has faith but doesn’t approach, the Realized One doesn’t feel inspired to teach.*";
P_HTM[2846]="*Yato ca kho, puṇṇiya, bhikkhu saddho ca hoti upasaṅkamitā ca, evaṃ tathāgataṃ dhammadesanā paṭibhāti.**But when a mendicant has faith and approaches, the Realized One feels inspired to teach.*";
P_HTM[2847]="*Saddho ca, puṇṇiya, bhikkhu hoti upasaṅkamitā ca, no ca payirupāsitā … pe …**When a mendicant has faith and approaches, but doesn’t pay homage …*";
P_HTM[2848]="*payirupāsitā ca, no ca paripucchitā …**they pay homage, but don’t ask questions …*";
P_HTM[2849]="*paripucchitā ca, no ca ohitasoto dhammaṃ suṇāti …**they ask questions, but don’t lend an ear …*";
P_HTM[2850]="*ohitasoto ca dhammaṃ suṇāti, no ca sutvā dhammaṃ dhāreti …**they lend an ear, but don’t remember the teaching they’ve heard …*";
P_HTM[2851]="*sutvā ca dhammaṃ dhāreti, no ca dhātānaṃ dhammānaṃ atthaṃ upaparikkhati …**they remember the teaching they’ve heard, but don’t reflect on the meaning of the teachings they’ve remembered …*";
P_HTM[2852]="*dhātānañca dhammānaṃ atthaṃ upaparikkhati no ca atthamaññāya dhammamaññāya dhammānudhammappaṭipanno hoti …**they reflect on the meaning of the teachings they’ve remembered, but, having understood the meaning and the teaching, they don’t practice accordingly …*";
P_HTM[2853]="*atthamaññāya dhammamaññāya dhammānudhammappaṭipanno ca hoti, no ca kalyāṇavāco hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagaḷāya atthassa viññāpaniyā …**they practice accordingly, but they’re not a good speaker. Their voice is not polished, clear, articulate, and doesn’t express the meaning …*";
P_HTM[2854]="*kalyāṇavāco ca hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagaḷāya atthassa viññāpaniyā, no ca sandassako hoti samādapako samuttejako sampahaṃsako sabrahmacārīnaṃ, neva tāva tathāgataṃ dhammadesanā paṭibhāti.**They’re a good speaker, but they don’t educate, encourage, fire up, and inspire their spiritual companions. The Realized One doesn’t feel inspired to teach.*";
P_HTM[2855]="*Yato ca kho, puṇṇiya, bhikkhu saddho ca hoti, upasaṅkamitā ca, payirupāsitā ca, paripucchitā ca, ohitasoto ca dhammaṃ suṇāti, sutvā ca dhammaṃ dhāreti, dhātānañca dhammānaṃ atthaṃ upaparikkhati, atthamaññāya dhammamaññāya dhammānudhammappaṭipanno ca hoti, kalyāṇavāco ca hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagaḷāya atthassa viññāpaniyā, sandassako ca hoti samādapako samuttejako sampahaṃsako sabrahmacārīnaṃ—**But when a mendicant has faith, approaches, pays homage, asks questions, lends an ear, remembers the teachings, reflects on the meaning, practices accordingly, has a good voice, and encourages their spiritual companions,*";
P_HTM[2856]="*evaṃ tathāgataṃ dhammadesanā paṭibhāti.**the Realized One feels inspired to teach.*";
P_HTM[2857]="*Imehi kho, puṇṇiya, dasahi dhammehi samannāgatā ekantapaṭibhānā tathāgataṃ dhammadesanā hotī”ti.**When someone has these ten qualities, the Realized One feels totally inspired to teach.”*";
P_HTM[2858]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2859]="*4. Byākaraṇasuttaṃ**Declaration*";
P_HTM[2860]="*Tatra kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhikkhū āmantesi:**There Venerable Mahāmoggallāna addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[2861]="*“āvuso bhikkhave”ti.**“Reverends, mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[2862]="*“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa paccassosuṃ.**“Reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[2863]="*Āyasmā mahāmoggallāno etadavoca:**Venerable Mahāmoggallāna said this:*";
P_HTM[2864]="*“Idhāvuso, bhikkhu aññaṃ byākaroti:**“Take a mendicant who declares enlightenment:*";
P_HTM[2865]="*‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāmī’ti.**‘I understand: “Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.”’*";
P_HTM[2866]="*Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo paracittakusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo samanuyuñjati samanuggāhati samanubhāsati.**They’re pursued, pressed, and grilled by the Realized One, or by one of his disciples who has the absorptions, and is skilled in attainments, in the minds of others, and in the ways of another’s mind.*";
P_HTM[2867]="*So tathāgatena vā tathāgatasāvakena vā jhāyinā samāpattikusalena paracittakusalena paracittapariyāyakusalena samanuyuñjiyamāno samanuggāhiyamāno samanubhāsiyamāno irīṇaṃ āpajjati vicinaṃ āpajjati anayaṃ āpajjati byasanaṃ āpajjati anayabyasanaṃ āpajjati.**Grilled in this way they get stuck or lose their way. They fall to ruin and disaster.*";
P_HTM[2868]="*Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo paracittakusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca manasi karoti:**The Realized One or one of his disciples comprehends their mind and investigates:*";
P_HTM[2869]="*‘kiṃ nu kho ayamāyasmā aññaṃ byākaroti—**‘Why does this venerable declare enlightenment, saying:*";
P_HTM[2870]="*khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāmī’ti?**“I understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’?”’*";
P_HTM[2871]="*Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo paracittakusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāti:**They understand:*";
P_HTM[2872]="*‘Kodhano kho ayamāyasmā;**‘This venerable gets irritable,*";
P_HTM[2873]="*kodhapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati.**and often lives with a heart full of anger.*";
P_HTM[2874]="*Kodhapariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (1)**But being full of anger means decline in the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[2875]="*Upanāhī kho pana ayamāyasmā;**This venerable is hostile …*";
P_HTM[2876]="*upanāhapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati.* **";
P_HTM[2877]="*Upanāhapariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (2)* **";
P_HTM[2878]="*Makkhī kho pana ayamāyasmā;**prone to offensiveness …*";
P_HTM[2879]="*makkhapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati.* **";
P_HTM[2880]="*Makkhapariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (3)* **";
P_HTM[2881]="*Paḷāsī kho pana ayamāyasmā;**contemptuous …*";
P_HTM[2882]="*paḷāsapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati.* **";
P_HTM[2883]="*Paḷāsapariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (4)* **";
P_HTM[2884]="*Issukī kho pana ayamāyasmā;**jealous …*";
P_HTM[2885]="*issāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati.* **";
P_HTM[2886]="*Issāpariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (5)* **";
P_HTM[2887]="*Maccharī kho pana ayamāyasmā;**stingy …*";
P_HTM[2888]="*maccherapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati.* **";
P_HTM[2889]="*Maccherapariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (6)* **";
P_HTM[2890]="*Saṭho kho pana ayamāyasmā;**devious …*";
P_HTM[2891]="*sāṭheyyapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati.* **";
P_HTM[2892]="*Sāṭheyyapariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (7)* **";
P_HTM[2893]="*Māyāvī kho pana ayamāyasmā;**deceitful …*";
P_HTM[2894]="*māyāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati.* **";
P_HTM[2895]="*Māyāpariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (8)* **";
P_HTM[2896]="*Pāpiccho kho pana ayamāyasmā;**This venerable has bad desires,*";
P_HTM[2897]="*icchāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati.**and often lives with a heart full of desire.*";
P_HTM[2898]="*Icchāpariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (9)**But being full of desire means decline in the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[2899]="*Sati kho pana ayamāyasmā uttari karaṇīye oramattakena visesādhigamena antarā vosānaṃ āpanno.**When there is still more to be done, this venerable stopped half-way after achieving some insignificant distinction.*";
P_HTM[2900]="*Antarā vosānagamanaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ’. (10)**But stopping half-way means decline in the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One.’*";
P_HTM[2901]="*So vatāvuso, bhikkhu ‘ime dasa dhamme appahāya imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**It’s not possible for a mendicant to achieve growth, improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training without giving up these ten qualities.*";
P_HTM[2902]="*So vatāvuso, bhikkhu ‘ime dasa dhamme pahāya imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti ṭhānametaṃ vijjatī”ti.**It is possible for a mendicant to achieve growth, improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training after giving up these ten qualities.”*";
P_HTM[2903]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2904]="*5. Katthīsuttaṃ**A Boaster*";
P_HTM[2905]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā mahācundo cetīsu viharati sahajātiyaṃ.**At one time Venerable Mahācunda was staying in the land of the Cetis at Sahajāti.*";
P_HTM[2906]="*Tatra kho āyasmā mahācundo bhikkhū āmantesi:**There he addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[2907]="*“āvuso bhikkhave”ti.**“Reverends, mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[2908]="*“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahācundassa paccassosuṃ.**“Reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[2909]="*Āyasmā mahācundo etadavoca:**Venerable Mahācunda said this:*";
P_HTM[2910]="*“Idhāvuso, bhikkhu katthī hoti vikatthī adhigamesu:**“Take a mendicant who boasts and brags about their achievements:*";
P_HTM[2911]="*‘ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipi, ahaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipi, ahaṃ tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipi, ahaṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipi, ahaṃ ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipi, ahaṃ viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipi, ahaṃ ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipi, ahaṃ nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipi, ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipī’ti.**‘I enter and emerge from the first absorption, the second absorption, the third absorption, and the fourth absorption. And I enter and emerge from the dimensions of infinite space, infinite consciousness, nothingness, and neither perception nor non-perception. And I enter and emerge from the cessation of perception and feeling.’*";
P_HTM[2912]="*Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo paracittakusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo samanuyuñjati samanuggāhati samanubhāsati.**They’re pursued, pressed, and grilled by the Realized One, or by one of his disciples who has the absorptions, and is skilled in attainments, in the minds of others, and in the ways of another’s mind.*";
P_HTM[2913]="*So tathāgatena vā tathāgatasāvakena vā jhāyinā samāpattikusalena paracittakusalena paracittapariyāyakusalena samanuyuñjiyamāno samanuggāhiyamāno samanubhāsiyamāno irīṇaṃ āpajjati vicinaṃ āpajjati anayaṃ āpajjati byasanaṃ āpajjati anayabyasanaṃ āpajjati.**Grilled in this way they get stuck or lose their way. They fall to ruin and disaster.*";
P_HTM[2914]="*Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo paracittakusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca manasi karoti:**The Realized One or one of his disciples comprehends their mind and investigates:*";
P_HTM[2915]="*‘kiṃ nu kho ayamāyasmā katthī hoti vikatthī adhigamesu—**‘Why does this venerable boast and brag about their achievements, saying,*";
P_HTM[2916]="*ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipi … pe …**“I enter and emerge from the first absorption …*";
P_HTM[2917]="*ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipī’ti.**and the cessation of perception and feeling.”’*";
P_HTM[2918]="*Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo paracittakusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāti:**They understand,*";
P_HTM[2919]="*‘Dīgharattaṃ kho ayamāyasmā khaṇḍakārī chiddakārī sabalakārī kammāsakārī na santatakārī na santatavutti sīlesu.**‘For a long time this venerable’s deeds have been broken, tainted, spotty, and marred. Their deeds and behavior are inconsistent.*";
P_HTM[2920]="*Dussīlo kho ayamāyasmā.**This venerable is unethical,*";
P_HTM[2921]="*Dussilyaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (1)**and unethical conduct means decline in the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[2922]="*Assaddho kho pana ayamāyasmā;**This venerable is unfaithful,*";
P_HTM[2923]="*assaddhiyaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (2)**and lack of faith means decline …*";
P_HTM[2924]="*Appassuto kho pana ayamāyasmā anācāro;**This venerable is uneducated and unpracticed,*";
P_HTM[2925]="*appasaccaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (3)**and lack of learning means decline …*";
P_HTM[2926]="*Dubbaco kho pana ayamāyasmā;**This venerable is hard to admonish,*";
P_HTM[2927]="*dovacassatā kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (4)**and being hard to admonish means decline …*";
P_HTM[2928]="*Pāpamitto kho pana ayamāyasmā;**This venerable has bad friends,*";
P_HTM[2929]="*pāpamittatā kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (5)**and bad friends mean decline …*";
P_HTM[2930]="*Kusīto kho pana ayamāyasmā;**This venerable is lazy,*";
P_HTM[2931]="*kosajjaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (6)**and laziness means decline …*";
P_HTM[2932]="*Muṭṭhassati kho pana ayamāyasmā;**This venerable is unmindful,*";
P_HTM[2933]="*muṭṭhassaccaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (7)**and unmindfulness means decline …*";
P_HTM[2934]="*Kuhako kho pana ayamāyasmā;**This venerable is deceptive,*";
P_HTM[2935]="*kohaññaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (8)**and deceitfulness means decline …*";
P_HTM[2936]="*Dubbharo kho pana ayamāyasmā;**This venerable is hard to look after,*";
P_HTM[2937]="*dubbharatā kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (9)**and being hard to look after means decline …*";
P_HTM[2938]="*Duppañño kho pana ayamāyasmā;**This venerable is witless,*";
P_HTM[2939]="*duppaññatā kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ’. (10)**and lack of wisdom means decline in the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One.’*";
P_HTM[2940]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso, sahāyako sahāyakaṃ evaṃ vadeyya:**Suppose one friend was to say to another:*";
P_HTM[2941]="*‘yadā te, samma, dhanena dhanakaraṇīyaṃ assa, yāceyyāsi maṃ dhanaṃ. Dassāmi te dhanan’ti.**‘My dear friend, when you need money for some payment, just ask me and I’ll give it.’*";
P_HTM[2942]="*So kiñcideva dhanakaraṇīye samuppanne sahāyako sahāyakaṃ evaṃ vadeyya: ‘attho me, samma, dhanena. Dehi me dhanan’ti.**Then when some payment falls due, that friend says to their friend: ‘I need some money, my dear friend. Give me some.’*";
P_HTM[2943]="*So evaṃ vadeyya:**They’d say:*";
P_HTM[2944]="*‘tena hi, samma, idha khanāhī’ti. So tatra khananto nādhigaccheyya.**‘Well then, my dear friend, dig here.’ So they dig there, but don’t find anything.*";
P_HTM[2945]="*So evaṃ vadeyya:**They’d say:*";
P_HTM[2946]="*‘alikaṃ maṃ, samma, avaca; tucchakaṃ maṃ, samma, avaca—idha khanāhī’ti.**‘You lied to me, my dear friend, you spoke hollow words when you told me to dig here.’*";
P_HTM[2947]="*So evaṃ vadeyya:**They’d say:*";
P_HTM[2948]="*‘nāhaṃ taṃ, samma, alikaṃ avacaṃ, tucchakaṃ avacaṃ. Tena hi, samma, idha khanāhī’ti.**‘My dear friend, I didn’t lie or speak hollow words. Well then, dig here.’*";
P_HTM[2949]="*So tatrapi khananto nādhigaccheyya.**So they dig there as well, but don’t find anything.*";
P_HTM[2950]="*So evaṃ vadeyya:**They’d say:*";
P_HTM[2951]="*‘alikaṃ maṃ, samma, avaca, tucchakaṃ maṃ, samma, avaca—idha khanāhī’ti.**‘You lied to me, my dear friend, you spoke hollow words when you said dig here.’*";
P_HTM[2952]="*So evaṃ vadeyya:**They’d say:*";
P_HTM[2953]="*‘nāhaṃ taṃ, samma, alikaṃ avacaṃ, tucchakaṃ avacaṃ. Tena hi, samma, idha khanāhī’ti.**‘My dear friend, I didn’t lie or speak hollow words. Well then, dig here.’*";
P_HTM[2954]="*So tatrapi khananto nādhigaccheyya.**So they dig there as well, but don’t find anything.*";
P_HTM[2955]="*So evaṃ vadeyya:**They’d say:*";
P_HTM[2956]="*‘alikaṃ maṃ, samma, avaca, tucchakaṃ maṃ, samma, avaca—idha khanāhī’ti.**‘You lied to me, my dear friend, you spoke hollow words when you said dig here.’*";
P_HTM[2957]="*So evaṃ vadeyya:**They’d say:*";
P_HTM[2958]="*‘nāhaṃ taṃ, samma, alikaṃ avacaṃ, tucchakaṃ avacaṃ. Api ca ahameva ummādaṃ pāpuṇiṃ cetaso vipariyāyan’ti.**‘My dear friend, I didn’t lie or speak hollow words. But I had gone mad, I was out of my mind.’*";
P_HTM[2959]="*Evamevaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu katthī hoti vikatthī adhigamesu:**In the same way, take a mendicant who boasts and brags about their achievements:*";
P_HTM[2960]="*‘ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipi, ahaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipi, ahaṃ tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipi, ahaṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipi, ahaṃ ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipi, ahaṃ viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipi, ahaṃ ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipi, ahaṃ nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipi, ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipī’ti.**‘I enter and emerge from the first absorption … and the cessation of perception and feeling.’*";
P_HTM[2961]="*Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo paracittakusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo samanuyuñjati samanuggāhati samanubhāsati.**They’re pursued, pressed, and grilled by the Realized One, or by one of his disciples …*";
P_HTM[2962]="*So tathāgatena vā tathāgatasāvakena vā jhāyinā samāpattikusalena paracittakusalena paracittapariyāyakusalena samanuyuñjiyamāno samanuggāhiyamāno samanubhāsiyamāno irīṇaṃ āpajjati vicinaṃ āpajjati anayaṃ āpajjati byasanaṃ āpajjati anayabyasanaṃ āpajjati.**Grilled in this way they get stuck or lose their way. They fall to ruin and disaster.*";
P_HTM[2963]="*Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo paracittakusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca manasi karoti:**The Realized One or one of his disciples comprehends their mind and investigates:*";
P_HTM[2964]="*‘kiṃ nu kho ayamāyasmā katthī hoti vikatthī adhigamesu—**‘Why does this venerable boast and brag about their achievements, saying,*";
P_HTM[2965]="*ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmipi … pe …**“I enter and emerge from the first absorption …*";
P_HTM[2966]="*ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjāmipi vuṭṭhahāmipī’ti.**and the cessation of perception and feeling.”’*";
P_HTM[2967]="*Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo cetasā ceto paricca pajānāti:**They understand,*";
P_HTM[2968]="*‘Dīgharattaṃ kho ayamāyasmā khaṇḍakārī chiddakārī sabalakārī kammāsakārī, na santatakārī na santatavutti sīlesu.**‘For a long time this venerable’s deeds have been broken, tainted, spotty, and marred. Their deeds and behavior are inconsistent.*";
P_HTM[2969]="*Dussīlo kho ayamāyasmā;**This venerable is unethical,*";
P_HTM[2970]="*dussilyaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (1)**and unethical conduct means decline in the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[2971]="*Assaddho kho pana ayamāyasmā;**This venerable is unfaithful …*";
P_HTM[2972]="*assaddhiyaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (2)* **";
P_HTM[2973]="*Appassuto kho pana ayamāyasmā anācāro;**uneducated and unpracticed …*";
P_HTM[2974]="*appasaccaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (3)* **";
P_HTM[2975]="*Dubbaco kho pana ayamāyasmā;**hard to admonish …*";
P_HTM[2976]="*dovacassatā kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (4)* **";
P_HTM[2977]="*Pāpamitto kho pana ayamāyasmā;**with bad friends …*";
P_HTM[2978]="*pāpamittatā kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (5)* **";
P_HTM[2979]="*Kusīto kho pana ayamāyasmā;**lazy …*";
P_HTM[2980]="*kosajjaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (6)* **";
P_HTM[2981]="*Muṭṭhassati kho pana ayamāyasmā;**unmindful …*";
P_HTM[2982]="*muṭṭhassaccaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (7)* **";
P_HTM[2983]="*Kuhako kho pana ayamāyasmā;**deceptive …*";
P_HTM[2984]="*kohaññaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (8)* **";
P_HTM[2985]="*Dubbharo kho pana ayamāyasmā;**hard to look after …*";
P_HTM[2986]="*dubbharatā kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (9)* **";
P_HTM[2987]="*Duppañño kho pana ayamāyasmā;**This venerable is witless,*";
P_HTM[2988]="*duppaññatā kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ’. (10)**and lack of wisdom means decline in the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One.’*";
P_HTM[2989]="*So vatāvuso, bhikkhu ‘ime dasa dhamme appahāya imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**It’s not possible for a mendicant to achieve growth, improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training without giving up these ten qualities.*";
P_HTM[2990]="*So vatāvuso, bhikkhu ‘ime dasa dhamme pahāya imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti ṭhānametaṃ vijjatī”ti.**It is possible for a mendicant to achieve growth, improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training after giving up these ten qualities.”*";
P_HTM[2991]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2992]="*6. Adhimānasuttaṃ**Overestimation*";
P_HTM[2993]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā mahākassapo rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time Venerable Mahākassapa was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[2994]="*Tatra kho āyasmā mahākassapo bhikkhū āmantesi:**There he addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[2995]="*“āvuso bhikkhave”ti.**“Reverends, mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[2996]="*“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahākassapassa paccassosuṃ.**“Reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[2997]="*Āyasmā mahākassapo etadavoca:**Venerable Mahākassapa said this:*";
P_HTM[2998]="*“Idhāvuso, bhikkhu aññaṃ byākaroti:**“Take a mendicant who declares enlightenment:*";
P_HTM[2999]="*‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāmī’ti.**‘I understand: “Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.”’*";
P_HTM[3000]="*Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo paracittakusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo samanuyuñjati samanuggāhati samanubhāsati.**They’re pursued, pressed, and grilled by the Realized One, or by one of his disciples who has the absorptions, and is skilled in attainments, in the minds of others, and in the ways of another’s mind.*";
P_HTM[3001]="*So tathāgatena vā tathāgatasāvakena vā jhāyinā samāpattikusalena paracittakusalena paracittapariyāyakusalena samanuyuñjiyamāno samanuggāhiyamāno samanubhāsiyamāno irīṇaṃ āpajjati vicinaṃ āpajjati anayaṃ āpajjati byasanaṃ āpajjati anayabyasanaṃ āpajjati.**Grilled in this way they get stuck or lose their way. They fall to ruin and disaster.*";
P_HTM[3002]="*Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo paracittakusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca manasi karoti:**The Realized One or one of his disciples comprehends their mind and investigates:*";
P_HTM[3003]="*‘kiṃ nu kho ayamāyasmā aññaṃ byākaroti—**‘Why does this venerable declare enlightenment, saying,*";
P_HTM[3004]="*khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāmī’ti.**“I understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’?”’*";
P_HTM[3005]="*Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo paracittakusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāti:**They understand,*";
P_HTM[3006]="*‘Adhimāniko kho ayamāyasmā adhimānasacco, appatte pattasaññī, akate katasaññī, anadhigate adhigatasaññī.**‘This venerable overestimates themselves and takes that to be the truth. They perceive that they’ve attained what they haven’t attained, done what they haven’t done, and achieved what they haven’t achieved.*";
P_HTM[3007]="*Adhimānena aññaṃ byākaroti—**And they declare enlightenment out of overestimation:*";
P_HTM[3008]="*khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāmī’ti.**“I understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”’*";
P_HTM[3009]="*Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo paracittakusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca manasi karoti:**The Realized One or one of his disciples comprehends their mind and investigates:*";
P_HTM[3010]="*‘kiṃ nu kho ayamāyasmā nissāya adhimāniko adhimānasacco, appatte pattasaññī, akate katasaññī, anadhigate adhigatasaññī.**‘Why does this venerable overestimate themselves and take that to be the truth? Why do they perceive that they’ve attained what they haven’t attained, done what they haven’t done, and achieved what they haven’t achieved?*";
P_HTM[3011]="*Adhimānena aññaṃ byākaroti—**And why do they declare enlightenment out of overestimation:*";
P_HTM[3012]="*khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāmī’ti.**“I understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”’*";
P_HTM[3013]="*Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo paracittakusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāti:**They understand,*";
P_HTM[3014]="*‘Bahussuto kho pana ayamāyasmā sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā.**‘This venerable is very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and comprehending them theoretically.*";
P_HTM[3015]="*Tasmā ayamāyasmā adhimāniko adhimānasacco, appatte pattasaññī, akate katasaññī, anadhigate adhigatasaññī.**Therefore this venerable overestimates themselves and takes that to be the truth. …’*";
P_HTM[3016]="*Adhimānena aññaṃ byākaroti—* **";
P_HTM[3017]="*khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāmī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3018]="*Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo paracittakusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāti:**They understand,*";
P_HTM[3019]="*‘Abhijjhālu kho pana ayamāyasmā;**‘This venerable is covetous,*";
P_HTM[3020]="*abhijjhāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati.**and often lives with a heart full covetousness.*";
P_HTM[3021]="*Abhijjhāpariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (1)**Being full of covetousness means decline in the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[3022]="*Byāpanno kho pana ayamāyasmā;**This venerable has ill will …*";
P_HTM[3023]="*byāpādapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati.* **";
P_HTM[3024]="*Byāpādapariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (2)* **";
P_HTM[3025]="*Thinamiddho kho pana ayamāyasmā;**dullness and drowsiness …*";
P_HTM[3026]="*thinamiddhapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati.* **";
P_HTM[3027]="*Thinamiddhapariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (3)* **";
P_HTM[3028]="*Uddhato kho pana ayamāyasmā;**restlessness …*";
P_HTM[3029]="*uddhaccapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati.* **";
P_HTM[3030]="*Uddhaccapariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (4)* **";
P_HTM[3031]="*Vicikiccho kho pana ayamāyasmā;**doubt …*";
P_HTM[3032]="*vicikicchāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati.* **";
P_HTM[3033]="*Vicikicchāpariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (5)* **";
P_HTM[3034]="*Kammārāmo kho pana ayamāyasmā kammarato kammārāmataṃ anuyutto.**This venerable relishes work. They love it and like to relish it …*";
P_HTM[3035]="*Kammārāmatā kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (6)* **";
P_HTM[3036]="*Bhassārāmo kho pana ayamāyasmā bhassarato bhassārāmataṃ anuyutto.**This venerable relishes talk …*";
P_HTM[3037]="*Bhassārāmatā kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (7)* **";
P_HTM[3038]="*Niddārāmo kho pana ayamāyasmā niddārato niddārāmataṃ anuyutto.**sleep …*";
P_HTM[3039]="*Niddārāmatā kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (8)* **";
P_HTM[3040]="*Saṅgaṇikārāmo kho pana ayamāyasmā saṅgaṇikarato saṅgaṇikārāmataṃ anuyutto.**company …*";
P_HTM[3041]="*Saṅgaṇikārāmatā kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (9)* **";
P_HTM[3042]="*Sati kho pana ayamāyasmā uttari karaṇīye oramattakena visesādhigamena antarā vosānaṃ āpanno.**When there is still more to be done, this venerable stopped half-way after achieving some insignificant distinction.*";
P_HTM[3043]="*Antarā vosānagamanaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ’. (10)**Stopping half-way means decline in the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One.’*";
P_HTM[3044]="*So vatāvuso, bhikkhu ‘ime dasa dhamme appahāya imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**It’s not possible for a mendicant to achieve growth, improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training without giving up these ten qualities.*";
P_HTM[3045]="*So vatāvuso, bhikkhu ‘ime dasa dhamme pahāya imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti ṭhānametaṃ vijjatī”ti.**It is possible for a mendicant to achieve growth, improvement, or maturity in this teaching and training after giving up these ten qualities.”*";
P_HTM[3046]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3047]="*7. Nappiyasuttaṃ**Disciplinary Issues*";
P_HTM[3048]="*Tatra kho bhagavā kālaṅkataṃ bhikkhuṃ ārabbha bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants concerning the mendicant Kalandaka:*";
P_HTM[3049]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[3050]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[3051]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[3052]="*“Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu adhikaraṇiko hoti, adhikaraṇasamathassa na vaṇṇavādī.**“Firstly, a mendicant raises disciplinary issues and doesn’t praise the settlement of disciplinary issues.*";
P_HTM[3053]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu adhikaraṇiko hoti adhikaraṇasamathassa na vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo na piyatāya na garutāya na bhāvanāya na sāmaññāya na ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (1)**This quality doesn’t conduce to warmth, respect, esteem, harmony, and unity.*";
P_HTM[3054]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na sikkhākāmo hoti, sikkhāsamādānassa na vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant doesn’t want to train, and doesn’t praise taking up the training. …*";
P_HTM[3055]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na sikkhākāmo hoti sikkhāsamādānassa na vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo na piyatāya na garutāya na bhāvanāya na sāmaññāya na ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (2)* **";
P_HTM[3056]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pāpiccho hoti, icchāvinayassa na vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant has bad desires, and doesn’t praise getting rid of desires. …*";
P_HTM[3057]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pāpiccho hoti icchāvinayassa na vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo na piyatāya na garutāya na bhāvanāya na sāmaññāya na ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (3)* **";
P_HTM[3058]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kodhano hoti, kodhavinayassa na vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant is irritable, and doesn’t praise getting rid of anger. …*";
P_HTM[3059]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kodhano hoti kodhavinayassa na vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo na piyatāya na garutāya na bhāvanāya na sāmaññāya na ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (4)* **";
P_HTM[3060]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu makkhī hoti, makkhavinayassa na vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant denigrates others, and doesn’t praise getting rid of denigration. …*";
P_HTM[3061]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu makkhī hoti makkhavinayassa na vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo na piyatāya na garutāya na bhāvanāya na sāmaññāya na ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (5)* **";
P_HTM[3062]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saṭho hoti, sāṭheyyavinayassa na vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant is devious, and doesn’t praise getting rid of deviousness. …*";
P_HTM[3063]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saṭho hoti sāṭheyyavinayassa na vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo na piyatāya na garutāya na bhāvanāya na sāmaññāya na ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (6)* **";
P_HTM[3064]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu māyāvī hoti, māyāvinayassa na vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant is deceitful, and doesn’t praise getting rid of deceitfulness. …*";
P_HTM[3065]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu māyāvī hoti māyāvinayassa na vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo na piyatāya na garutāya na bhāvanāya na sāmaññāya na ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (7)* **";
P_HTM[3066]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammānaṃ na nisāmakajātiko hoti, dhammanisantiyā na vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant doesn’t pay attention to the teachings, and doesn’t praise attending to the teachings. …*";
P_HTM[3067]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammānaṃ na nisāmakajātiko hoti dhammanisantiyā na vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo na piyatāya na garutāya na bhāvanāya na sāmaññāya na ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (8)* **";
P_HTM[3068]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na paṭisallīno hoti, paṭisallānassa na vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant is not in retreat, and doesn’t praise retreat. …*";
P_HTM[3069]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na paṭisallīno hoti paṭisallānassa na vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo na piyatāya na garutāya na bhāvanāya na sāmaññāya na ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (9)* **";
P_HTM[3070]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ na paṭisanthārako hoti, paṭisanthārakassa na vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant is inhospitable to their spiritual companions, and doesn’t praise hospitality.*";
P_HTM[3071]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ na paṭisanthārako hoti paṭisanthārakassa na vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo na piyatāya na garutāya na bhāvanāya na sāmaññāya na ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (10)**This quality doesn’t conduce to warmth, respect, esteem, harmony, and unity.*";
P_HTM[3072]="*Evarūpassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno kiñcāpi evaṃ icchā uppajjeyya:**Even though a mendicant such as this might wish:*";
P_HTM[3073]="*‘aho vata maṃ sabrahmacārī sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyun’ti, atha kho naṃ sabrahmacārī na ceva sakkaronti na garuṃ karonti na mānenti na pūjenti.**‘If only my spiritual companions would honor, respect, esteem, and venerate me!’ Still they don’t honor, respect, esteem, and venerate them.*";
P_HTM[3074]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3075]="*Tathāhissa, bhikkhave, viññū sabrahmacārī te pāpake akusale dhamme appahīne samanupassanti.**Because their sensible spiritual companions see that they haven’t given up those bad unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[3076]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, assakhaḷuṅkassa kiñcāpi evaṃ icchā uppajjeyya:**Suppose a wild colt was to wish:*";
P_HTM[3077]="*‘aho vata maṃ manussā ājānīyaṭṭhāne ṭhapeyyuṃ, ājānīyabhojanañca bhojeyyuṃ, ājānīyaparimajjanañca parimajjeyyun’ti, atha kho naṃ manussā na ceva ājānīyaṭṭhāne ṭhapenti na ca ājānīyabhojanaṃ bhojenti na ca ājānīyaparimajjanaṃ parimajjanti.**‘If only the humans would put me in a thoroughbred’s place, feed me a thoroughbred’s food, and give me a thoroughbred’s grooming.’ Still the humans wouldn’t put them in a thoroughbred’s place, feed them a thoroughbred’s food, or give them a thoroughbred’s grooming.*";
P_HTM[3078]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3079]="*Tathāhissa, bhikkhave, viññū manussā tāni sāṭheyyāni kūṭeyyāni jimheyyāni vaṅkeyyāni appahīnāni samanupassanti.**Because sensible humans see that they haven’t given up their tricks, bluffs, ruses, and feints.*";
P_HTM[3080]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, evarūpassa bhikkhuno kiñcāpi evaṃ icchā uppajjeyya:**In the same way, even though a mendicant such as this might wish:*";
P_HTM[3081]="*‘aho vata maṃ sabrahmacārī sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyun’ti, atha kho naṃ sabrahmacārī na ceva sakkaronti na garuṃ karonti na mānenti na pūjenti.**‘If only my spiritual companions would honor, respect, esteem, and venerate me!’ Still they don’t honor, respect, esteem, and venerate them.*";
P_HTM[3082]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3083]="*Tathāhissa, bhikkhave, viññū sabrahmacārī te pāpake akusale dhamme appahīne samanupassanti.**Because their sensible spiritual companions see that they haven’t given up those bad unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[3084]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na adhikaraṇiko hoti, adhikaraṇasamathassa vaṇṇavādī.**Next, a mendicant doesn’t raise disciplinary issues and praises the settlement of disciplinary issues.*";
P_HTM[3085]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na adhikaraṇiko hoti adhikaraṇasamathassa vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo piyatāya garutāya bhāvanāya sāmaññāya ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (1)**This quality conduces to warmth, respect, esteem, harmony, and unity.*";
P_HTM[3086]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sikkhākāmo hoti, sikkhāsamādānassa vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant wants to train, and praises taking up the training. …*";
P_HTM[3087]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sikkhākāmo hoti sikkhāsamādānassa vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo piyatāya garutāya bhāvanāya sāmaññāya ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (2)* **";
P_HTM[3088]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu appiccho hoti, icchāvinayassa vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant has few desires, and praises getting rid of desires. …*";
P_HTM[3089]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu appiccho hoti icchāvinayassa vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo … pe … ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (3)* **";
P_HTM[3090]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkodhano hoti, kodhavinayassa vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant is not irritable, and praises getting rid of anger. …*";
P_HTM[3091]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkodhano hoti kodhavinayassa vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo … pe … ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (4)* **";
P_HTM[3092]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu amakkhī hoti, makkhavinayassa vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant doesn’t denigrate others, and praises getting rid of denigration. …*";
P_HTM[3093]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu amakkhī hoti makkhavinayassa vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo … pe … ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (5)* **";
P_HTM[3094]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu asaṭho hoti, sāṭheyyavinayassa vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant isn’t devious, and praises getting rid of deviousness. …*";
P_HTM[3095]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu asaṭho hoti sāṭheyyavinayassa vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo … pe … ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (6)* **";
P_HTM[3096]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu amāyāvī hoti, māyāvinayassa vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant isn’t deceitful, and praises getting rid of deceitfulness. …*";
P_HTM[3097]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu amāyāvī hoti māyāvinayassa vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo … pe … ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (7)* **";
P_HTM[3098]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammānaṃ nisāmakajātiko hoti, dhammanisantiyā vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant pays attention to the teachings, and praises attending to the teachings. …*";
P_HTM[3099]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammānaṃ nisāmakajātiko hoti dhammanisantiyā vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo … pe … ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (8)* **";
P_HTM[3100]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paṭisallīno hoti, paṭisallānassa vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant is in retreat, and praises retreat. …*";
P_HTM[3101]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paṭisallīno hoti paṭisallānassa vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo … pe … ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (9)* **";
P_HTM[3102]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ paṭisanthārako hoti, paṭisanthārakassa vaṇṇavādī.**Furthermore, a mendicant is hospitable to their spiritual companions, and praises hospitality.*";
P_HTM[3103]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ paṭisanthārako hoti paṭisanthārakassa vaṇṇavādī, ayampi dhammo piyatāya garutāya bhāvanāya sāmaññāya ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (10)**This quality conduces to warmth, respect, esteem, harmony, and unity.*";
P_HTM[3104]="*Evarūpassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno kiñcāpi na evaṃ icchā uppajjeyya:**Even though a mendicant such as this might never wish:*";
P_HTM[3105]="*‘aho vata maṃ sabrahmacārī sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyun’ti, atha kho naṃ sabrahmacārī sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti.**‘If only my spiritual companions would honor, respect, esteem, and venerate me!’ Still they honor, respect, esteem, and venerate them.*";
P_HTM[3106]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3107]="*Tathāhissa, bhikkhave, viññū sabrahmacārī te pāpake akusale dhamme pahīne samanupassanti.**Because their sensible spiritual companions see that they’ve given up those bad unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[3108]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, bhaddassa assājānīyassa kiñcāpi na evaṃ icchā uppajjeyya:**Suppose a fine thoroughbred never wished:*";
P_HTM[3109]="*‘aho vata maṃ manussā ājānīyaṭṭhāne ṭhapeyyuṃ, ājānīyabhojanañca bhojeyyuṃ, ājānīyaparimajjanañca parimajjeyyun’ti, atha kho naṃ manussā ājānīyaṭṭhāne ca ṭhapenti ājānīyabhojanañca bhojenti ājānīyaparimajjanañca parimajjanti.**‘If only the humans would put me in a thoroughbred’s place, feed me a thoroughbred’s food, and give me a thoroughbred’s grooming.’ Still the humans would put them in a thoroughbred’s place, feed them a thoroughbred’s food, and give them a thoroughbred’s grooming.*";
P_HTM[3110]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3111]="*Tathāhissa, bhikkhave, viññū manussā tāni sāṭheyyāni kūṭeyyāni jimheyyāni vaṅkeyyāni pahīnāni samanupassanti.**Because sensible humans see that they’ve given up their tricks, bluffs, ruses, and feints.*";
P_HTM[3112]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, evarūpassa bhikkhuno kiñcāpi na evaṃ icchā uppajjeyya:**In the same way, even though a mendicant such as this might never wish:*";
P_HTM[3113]="*‘aho vata maṃ sabrahmacārī sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyun’ti, atha kho naṃ sabrahmacārī sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti.**‘If only my spiritual companions would honor, respect, esteem, and venerate me!’ Still they honor, respect, esteem, and venerate them.*";
P_HTM[3114]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3115]="*Tathāhissa, bhikkhave, viññū sabrahmacārī te pāpake akusale dhamme pahīne samanupassantī”ti.**Because their sensible spiritual companions see that they’ve given up those bad unskillful qualities.”*";
P_HTM[3116]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3117]="*8. Akkosakasuttaṃ**An Abuser*";
P_HTM[3118]="*“Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkosakaparibhāsako ariyūpavādī sabrahmacārīnaṃ ṭhānametaṃ avakāso yaṃ so dasannaṃ byasanānaṃ aññataraṃ byasanaṃ nigaccheyya.**“Mendicants, any mendicant who abuses and insults their spiritual companions, speaking ill of the noble ones, will, without a doubt, fall into one or other of these ten disasters.*";
P_HTM[3119]="*Katamesaṃ dasannaṃ?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[3120]="*Anadhigataṃ nādhigacchati, adhigatā parihāyati, saddhammassa na vodāyanti, saddhammesu vā adhimāniko hoti anabhirato vā brahmacariyaṃ carati, aññataraṃ vā saṃkiliṭṭhaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, gāḷhaṃ vā rogātaṅkaṃ phusati, ummādaṃ vā pāpuṇāti cittakkhepaṃ, sammūḷho kālaṃ karoti, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati.**They don’t achieve the unachieved. What they have achieved falls away. They don’t refine their good qualities. They overestimate their good qualities, or live the spiritual life dissatisfied, or commit a corrupt offense, or contract a severe illness, or go mad and lose their mind. They feel lost when they die. And when their body breaks up, after death, they are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[3121]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkosakaparibhāsako ariyūpavādī sabrahmacārīnaṃ, ṭhānametaṃ avakāso yaṃ so imesaṃ dasannaṃ byasanānaṃ aññataraṃ byasanaṃ nigaccheyyā”ti.**Any mendicant who abuses and insults their spiritual companions, speaking ill of the noble ones, will, without a doubt, fall into one or other of these ten disasters.”*";
P_HTM[3122]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3123]="*9. Kokālikasuttaṃ**With Kokālika*";
P_HTM[3124]="*Atha kho kokāliko bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho kokāliko bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then the mendicant Kokālika went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[3125]="*“pāpicchā, bhante, sāriputtamoggallānā, pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gatā”ti.**“Sir, Sāriputta and Moggallāna have wicked desires. They’ve fallen under the sway of wicked desires.”*";
P_HTM[3126]="*“Mā hevaṃ, kokālika, mā hevaṃ, kokālika.**“Don’t say that, Kokālika! Don’t say that, Kokālika!*";
P_HTM[3127]="*Pasādehi, kokālika, sāriputtamoggallānesu cittaṃ.**Have confidence in Sāriputta and Moggallāna,*";
P_HTM[3128]="*Pesalā sāriputtamoggallānā”ti.**they’re good monks.”*";
P_HTM[3129]="*Dutiyampi kho kokāliko bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**For a second time Kokālika said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[3130]="*“kiñcāpi me, bhante, bhagavā saddhāyiko paccayiko, atha kho pāpicchāva sāriputtamoggallānā, pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gatā”ti.**“Despite my faith and trust in the Buddha, Sāriputta and Moggallāna have wicked desires. They’ve fallen under the sway of wicked desires.”*";
P_HTM[3131]="*“Mā hevaṃ, kokālika, mā hevaṃ, kokālika.**“Don’t say that, Kokālika! Don’t say that, Kokālika!*";
P_HTM[3132]="*Pasādehi, kokālika, sāriputtamoggallānesu cittaṃ.**Have confidence in Sāriputta and Moggallāna,*";
P_HTM[3133]="*Pesalā sāriputtamoggallānā”ti.**they’re good monks.”*";
P_HTM[3134]="*Tatiyampi kho kokāliko bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**For a third time Kokālika said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[3135]="*“kiñcāpi me, bhante, bhagavā saddhāyiko paccayiko, atha kho pāpicchāva sāriputtamoggallānā, pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gatā”ti.**“Despite my faith and trust in the Buddha, Sāriputta and Moggallāna have wicked desires. They’ve fallen under the sway of wicked desires.”*";
P_HTM[3136]="*“Mā hevaṃ, kokālika, mā hevaṃ, kokālika.**“Don’t say that, Kokālika! Don’t say that, Kokālika!*";
P_HTM[3137]="*Pasādehi, kokālika, sāriputtamoggallānesu cittaṃ.**Have confidence in Sāriputta and Moggallāna,*";
P_HTM[3138]="*Pesalā sāriputtamoggallānā”ti.**they’re good monks.”*";
P_HTM[3139]="*Atha kho kokāliko bhikkhu uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**Then Kokālika got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving.*";
P_HTM[3140]="*Acirapakkantassa ca kokālikassa bhikkhuno sāsapamattīhi pīḷakāhi sabbo kāyo phuṭo ahosi.**Not long after he left his body erupted with boils the size of mustard seeds.*";
P_HTM[3141]="*Sāsapamattiyo hutvā muggamattiyo ahesuṃ, muggamattiyo hutvā kalāyamattiyo ahesuṃ, kalāyamattiyo hutvā kolaṭṭhimattiyo ahesuṃ, kolaṭṭhimattiyo hutvā kolamattiyo ahesuṃ, kolamattiyo hutvā āmalakamattiyo ahesuṃ, āmalakamattiyo hutvā tiṇḍukamattiyo ahesuṃ, tiṇḍukamattiyo hutvā, beḷuvasalāṭukamattiyo ahesuṃ, beḷuvasalāṭukamattiyo hutvā billamattiyo ahesuṃ, billamattiyo hutvā pabhijjiṃsu, pubbañca lohitañca pagghariṃsu.**The boils grew to the size of mung beans, then chickpeas, then jujube seeds, then jujubes, then myrobalans, then unripe wood apples, then ripe wood apples. Finally they burst open, and pus and blood oozed out.*";
P_HTM[3142]="*So sudaṃ kadalipattesu seti macchova visagilito.**He just laid down on banana leaves like a poisoned fish.*";
P_HTM[3143]="*Atha kho turū paccekabrahmā yena kokāliko bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā vehāse ṭhatvā kokālikaṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca:**Then Tudu the independent brahmā went to Kokālika, and standing in the sky he said to him,*";
P_HTM[3144]="*“pasādehi, kokālika, sāriputtamoggallānesu cittaṃ.**“Kokālika, have confidence in Sāriputta and Moggallāna,*";
P_HTM[3145]="*Pesalā sāriputtamoggallānā”ti.**they’re good monks.”*";
P_HTM[3146]="*“Kosi tvaṃ, āvuso”ti?**“Who are you, reverend?”*";
P_HTM[3147]="*“Ahaṃ turū paccekabrahmā”ti.**“I am Tudu the independent brahmā.”*";
P_HTM[3148]="*“Nanu tvaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā anāgāmī byākato, atha kiñcarahi idhāgato?**“Didn’t the Buddha declare you a non-returner? So what are you doing back here?*";
P_HTM[3149]="*Passa yāvañca te idaṃ aparaddhan”ti.**See how far you have strayed!”*";
P_HTM[3150]="*Atha kho turū paccekabrahmā kokālikaṃ bhikkhuṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi:**Then Tudu addressed Kokālika in verse:*";
P_HTM[3151]="*“Purisassa hi jātassa,**“A person is born*";
P_HTM[3152]="*kuṭhārī jāyate mukhe;**with an axe in their mouth.*";
P_HTM[3153]="*Yāya chindati attānaṃ,**A fool cuts themselves with it*";
P_HTM[3154]="*bālo dubbhāsitaṃ bhaṇaṃ.**when they say bad words.*";
P_HTM[3155]="*Yo nindiyaṃ pasaṃsati,**When you praise someone worthy of criticism,*";
P_HTM[3156]="*Taṃ vā nindati yo pasaṃsiyo;**or criticize someone worthy of praise,*";
P_HTM[3157]="*Vicināti mukhena so kaliṃ,**you choose bad luck with your own mouth:*";
P_HTM[3158]="*Kalinā tena sukhaṃ na vindati.**you’ll never find happiness that way.*";
P_HTM[3159]="*Appamattako ayaṃ kali,**Bad luck at dice is a trivial thing,*";
P_HTM[3160]="*Yo akkhesu dhanaparājayo;**if all you lose is your money*";
P_HTM[3161]="*Sabbassāpi sahāpi attanā,**and all you own, even yourself.*";
P_HTM[3162]="*Ayameva mahattaro kali;**What’s really terrible luck*";
P_HTM[3163]="*Yo sugatesu manaṃ padūsaye.**is to hate the holy ones.*";
P_HTM[3164]="*Sataṃ sahassānaṃ nirabbudānaṃ,**For more than two quinquadecillion years,*";
P_HTM[3165]="*Chattiṃsati pañca ca abbudāni;**and another five quattuordecillion years,*";
P_HTM[3166]="*Yamariyagarahī nirayaṃ upeti,**a slanderer of noble ones goes to hell,*";
P_HTM[3167]="*Vācaṃ manañca paṇidhāya pāpakan”ti.**having aimed bad words and thoughts at them.”*";
P_HTM[3168]="*Atha kho kokāliko bhikkhu teneva ābādhena kālamakāsi.**Then the mendicant Kokālika died of that illness.*";
P_HTM[3169]="*Kālaṅkato ca kokāliko bhikkhu padumaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati sāriputtamoggallānesu cittaṃ āghātetvā.**He was reborn in the Pink Lotus hell because of his resentment for Sāriputta and Moggallāna.*";
P_HTM[3170]="*Atha kho brahmā sahampati abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho brahmā sahampati bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then, late at night, the beautiful Brahmā Sahampati, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[3171]="*“kokāliko, bhante, bhikkhu kālaṅkato.**“Sir, the mendicant Kokālika has passed away.*";
P_HTM[3172]="*Kālaṅkato ca, bhante, kokāliko bhikkhu padumaṃ nirayaṃ upapanno sāriputtamoggallānesu cittaṃ āghātetvā”ti.**He was reborn in the pink lotus hell because of his resentment for Sāriputta and Moggallāna.”*";
P_HTM[3173]="*Idamavoca brahmā sahampati.**That’s what Brahmā Sahampati said.*";
P_HTM[3174]="*Idaṃ vatvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyi.**Then he bowed and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right side, before vanishing right there.*";
P_HTM[3175]="*Atha kho bhagavā tassā rattiyā accayena bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then, when the night had passed, the Buddha told the mendicants all that had happened.*";
P_HTM[3176]="*“imaṃ, bhikkhave, rattiṃ brahmā sahampati abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho, bhikkhave, brahmā sahampati maṃ etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[3177]="*‘kokāliko, bhante, bhikkhu kālaṅkato;* **";
P_HTM[3178]="*kālaṅkato ca, bhante, kokāliko bhikkhu padumaṃ nirayaṃ upapanno sāriputtamoggallānesu cittaṃ āghātetvā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3179]="*Idamavoca, bhikkhave, brahmā sahampati.* **";
P_HTM[3180]="*Idaṃ vatvā maṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3181]="*Evaṃ vutte, aññataro bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, one of the mendicants asked the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[3182]="*“kīva dīghaṃ nu kho, bhante, padume niraye āyuppamāṇan”ti?**“Sir, how long is the life span in the Pink Lotus hell?”*";
P_HTM[3183]="*“Dīghaṃ kho, bhikkhu, padume niraye āyuppamāṇaṃ.**“It’s long, mendicant.*";
P_HTM[3184]="*Na taṃ sukaraṃ saṅkhātuṃ:**It’s not easy to calculate*";
P_HTM[3185]="*‘ettakāni vassānīti vā ettakāni vassasatānīti vā ettakāni vassasahassānīti vā ettakāni vassasatasahassānīti vā’”ti.**how many years, how many hundreds or thousands or hundreds of thousands of years it lasts.”*";
P_HTM[3186]="*“Sakkā pana, bhante, upamaṃ kātun”ti?**“But sir, is it possible to give a simile?”*";
P_HTM[3187]="*“Sakkā, bhikkhū”ti bhagavā avoca:**“It’s possible,” said the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3188]="*“seyyathāpi, bhikkhu, vīsatikhāriko kosalako tilavāho tato puriso vassasatassa vassasatassa accayena ekamekaṃ tilaṃ uddhareyya.**“Suppose there was a Kosalan cartload of twenty bushels of sesame seed. And at the end of every hundred years someone would remove a single seed from it.*";
P_HTM[3189]="*Khippataraṃ kho so, bhikkhu, vīsatikhāriko kosalako tilavāho iminā upakkamena parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya, na tveva eko abbudo nirayo.**By this means the Kosalan cartload of twenty bushels of sesame seed would run out faster than a single lifetime in the Abbuda hell.*";
P_HTM[3190]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhu, vīsati abbudā nirayā; evameko nirabbudo nirayo.**Now, twenty lifetimes in the Abbuda hell equal one lifetime in the Nirabbuda hell.*";
P_HTM[3191]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhu, vīsati nirabbudā nirayā; evameko ababo nirayo.**Twenty lifetimes in the Nirabbuda hell equal one lifetime in the Ababa hell.*";
P_HTM[3192]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhu, vīsati ababā nirayā; evameko aṭaṭo nirayo.**Twenty lifetimes in the Ababa hell equal one lifetime in the Aṭaṭa hell.*";
P_HTM[3193]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhu, vīsati aṭaṭā nirayā; evameko ahaho nirayo.**Twenty lifetimes in the Aṭaṭa hell equal one lifetime in the Ahaha hell.*";
P_HTM[3194]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhu, vīsati ahahā nirayā; evameko kumudo nirayo.**Twenty lifetimes in the Ahaha hell equal one lifetime in the Yellow Lotus hell.*";
P_HTM[3195]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhu, vīsati kumudā nirayā; evameko sogandhiko nirayo.**Twenty lifetimes in the Yellow Lotus hell equal one lifetime in the Sweet-Smelling hell.*";
P_HTM[3196]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhu, vīsati sogandhikā nirayā; evameko uppalako nirayo.**Twenty lifetimes in the Sweet-Smelling hell equal one lifetime in the Blue Water Lily hell.*";
P_HTM[3197]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhu, vīsati uppalakā nirayā; evameko puṇḍarīko nirayo.**Twenty lifetimes in the Blue Water Lily hell equal one lifetime in the White Lotus hell.*";
P_HTM[3198]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhu, vīsati puṇḍarīkā nirayā; evameko padumo nirayo.**Twenty lifetimes in the White Lotus hell equal one lifetime in the Pink Lotus hell.*";
P_HTM[3199]="*Padumaṃ kho pana, bhikkhu, nirayaṃ kokāliko bhikkhu upapanno sāriputtamoggallānesu cittaṃ āghātetvā”ti.**The mendicant Kokālika has been reborn in the Pink Lotus hell because of his resentment for Sāriputta and Moggallāna.”*";
P_HTM[3200]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3201]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[3202]="*“Purisassa hi jātassa,**“A person is born*";
P_HTM[3203]="*kuṭhārī jāyate mukhe;**with an axe in their mouth.*";
P_HTM[3204]="*Yāya chindati attānaṃ,**A fool cuts themselves with it*";
P_HTM[3205]="*bālo dubbhāsitaṃ bhaṇaṃ.**when they say bad words.*";
P_HTM[3206]="*Yo nindiyaṃ pasaṃsati,**When you praise someone worthy of criticism,*";
P_HTM[3207]="*Taṃ vā nindati yo pasaṃsiyo;**or criticize someone worthy of praise,*";
P_HTM[3208]="*Vicināti mukhena so kaliṃ,**you choose bad luck with your own mouth:*";
P_HTM[3209]="*Kalinā tena sukhaṃ na vindati.**you’ll never find happiness that way.*";
P_HTM[3210]="*Appamattako ayaṃ kali,**Bad luck at dice is a trivial thing,*";
P_HTM[3211]="*Yo akkhesu dhanaparājayo;**if all you lose is your money*";
P_HTM[3212]="*Sabbassāpi sahāpi attanā,**and all you own, even yourself.*";
P_HTM[3213]="*Ayameva mahattaro kali;**What’s really terrible luck*";
P_HTM[3214]="*Yo sugatesu manaṃ padūsaye.**is to hate the holy ones.*";
P_HTM[3215]="*Sataṃ sahassānaṃ nirabbudānaṃ,**For more than two quinquadecillion years,*";
P_HTM[3216]="*Chattiṃsati pañca ca abbudāni;**and another five quattuordecillion years,*";
P_HTM[3217]="*Yamariyagarahī nirayaṃ upeti,**a slanderer of noble ones goes to hell,*";
P_HTM[3218]="*Vācaṃ manañca paṇidhāya pāpakan”ti.**having aimed bad words and thoughts at them.”*";
P_HTM[3219]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3220]="*10. Khīṇāsavabalasuttaṃ**The Powers of One Who has Ended Defilements*";
P_HTM[3221]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then Venerable Sāriputta went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[3222]="*“kati nu kho, sāriputta, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno balāni, yehi balehi samannāgato khīṇāsavo bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayaṃ paṭijānāti:**“Sāriputta, how many powers does a mendicant who has ended the defilements have that qualify them to claim:*";
P_HTM[3223]="*‘khīṇā me āsavā’”ti?**‘My defilements have ended.’”*";
P_HTM[3224]="*“Dasa, bhante, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno balāni, yehi balehi samannāgato khīṇāsavo bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayaṃ paṭijānāti:**“Sir, a mendicant who has ended the defilements has ten powers that qualify them to claim:*";
P_HTM[3225]="*‘khīṇā me āsavā’ti.**‘My defilements have ended.’*";
P_HTM[3226]="*Katamāni dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[3227]="*Idha, bhante, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno aniccato sabbe saṅkhārā yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhā honti.**Firstly, a mendicant with defilements ended has clearly seen with right wisdom all conditions as truly impermanent.*";
P_HTM[3228]="*Yampi, bhante, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno aniccato sabbe saṅkhārā yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhā honti, idampi, bhante, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno balaṃ hoti, yaṃ balaṃ āgamma khīṇāsavo bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayaṃ paṭijānāti:**This is a power that a mendicant who has ended the defilements relies on to claim:*";
P_HTM[3229]="*‘khīṇā me āsavā’ti. (1)**‘My defilements have ended.’*";
P_HTM[3230]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhante, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno aṅgārakāsūpamā kāmā yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhā honti.**Furthermore, a mendicant with defilements ended has clearly seen with right wisdom that sensual pleasures are truly like a pit of glowing coals.*";
P_HTM[3231]="*Yampi, bhante, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno aṅgārakāsūpamā kāmā yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhā honti, idampi, bhante, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno balaṃ hoti, yaṃ balaṃ āgamma khīṇāsavo bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayaṃ paṭijānāti:**This is a power that a mendicant who has ended the defilements relies on to claim:*";
P_HTM[3232]="*‘khīṇā me āsavā’ti. (2)**‘My defilements have ended.’*";
P_HTM[3233]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhante, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno vivekaninnaṃ cittaṃ hoti vivekapoṇaṃ vivekapabbhāraṃ vivekaṭṭhaṃ nekkhammābhirataṃ byantībhūtaṃ sabbaso āsavaṭṭhāniyehi dhammehi.**Furthermore, the mind of a mendicant with defilements ended slants, slopes, and inclines to seclusion. They’re withdrawn, loving renunciation, and they’ve totally done with defiling influences.*";
P_HTM[3234]="*Yampi, bhante, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno vivekaninnaṃ cittaṃ hoti vivekapoṇaṃ vivekapabbhāraṃ vivekaṭṭhaṃ nekkhammābhirataṃ byantībhūtaṃ sabbaso āsavaṭṭhāniyehi dhammehi, idampi, bhante, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno balaṃ hoti, yaṃ balaṃ āgamma khīṇāsavo bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayaṃ paṭijānāti:**This is a power that a mendicant who has ended the defilements relies on to claim:*";
P_HTM[3235]="*‘khīṇā me āsavā’ti. (3)**‘My defilements have ended.’*";
P_HTM[3236]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhante, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā honti subhāvitā.**Furthermore, a mendicant with defilements ended has well developed the four kinds of mindfulness meditation.*";
P_HTM[3237]="*Yampi, bhante, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā honti subhāvitā, idampi, bhante, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno balaṃ hoti, yaṃ balaṃ āgamma khīṇāsavo bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayaṃ paṭijānāti:**This is a power that a mendicant who has ended the defilements relies on to claim:*";
P_HTM[3238]="*‘khīṇā me āsavā’ti. (4)**‘My defilements have ended.’*";
P_HTM[3239]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhante, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno cattāro sammappadhānā bhāvitā honti subhāvitā … pe …**Furthermore, a mendicant with defilements ended has well developed the four right efforts. …*";
P_HTM[3240]="*cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā honti subhāvitā … pe …**the four bases of psychic power …*";
P_HTM[3241]="*pañcindriyāni …**the five faculties …*";
P_HTM[3242]="*pañca balāni bhāvitāni honti subhāvitāni …**the five powers …*";
P_HTM[3243]="*satta bojjhaṅgā bhāvitā honti subhāvitā …**the seven awakening factors …*";
P_HTM[3244]="*ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo bhāvito hoti subhāvito.**the noble eightfold path.*";
P_HTM[3245]="*Yampi, bhante, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo bhāvito hoti subhāvito, idampi, bhante, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno balaṃ hoti, yaṃ balaṃ āgamma khīṇāsavo bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayaṃ paṭijānāti:**This is a power that a mendicant who has ended the defilements relies on to claim:*";
P_HTM[3246]="*‘khīṇā me āsavā’ti. (5–10.)**‘My defilements have ended.’*";
P_HTM[3247]="*Imāni kho, bhante, dasa khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno balāni, yehi balehi samannāgato khīṇāsavo bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayaṃ paṭijānāti:**A mendicant who has ended the defilements has these ten powers that qualify them to claim:*";
P_HTM[3248]="*‘khīṇā me āsavā’”ti.**‘My defilements have ended.’”*";
P_HTM[3249]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3250]="*Theravaggo catuttho.* **";
P_HTM[3251]="*Vāhanānando puṇṇiyo,* **";
P_HTM[3252]="*byākaraṃ katthimāniko;* **";
P_HTM[3253]="*Napiyakkosakokāli,* **";
P_HTM[3254]="*khīṇāsavabalena cāti.* **";
P_HTM[3255]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**With Upāli*";
P_HTM[3256]="*1. Kāmabhogīsuttaṃ**Pleasure Seekers*";
P_HTM[3257]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[3258]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then the householder Anāthapiṇḍika went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. Seated to one side, the Buddha said to the householder Anāthapiṇḍika:*";
P_HTM[3259]="*“Dasayime, gahapati, kāmabhogī santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“These ten pleasure seekers are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3260]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[3261]="*Idha, gahapati, ekacco kāmabhogī adhammena bhoge pariyesati sāhasena;**First, a pleasure seeker seeks wealth using illegitimate, coercive means.*";
P_HTM[3262]="*adhammena bhoge pariyesitvā sāhasena na attānaṃ sukheti na pīṇeti na saṃvibhajati na puññāni karoti. (1)**They don’t make themselves happy and pleased, nor share it and make merit.*";
P_HTM[3263]="*Idha pana, gahapati, ekacco kāmabhogī adhammena bhoge pariyesati sāhasena;**Next, a pleasure seeker seeks wealth using illegitimate, coercive means.*";
P_HTM[3264]="*adhammena bhoge pariyesitvā sāhasena attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti, na saṃvibhajati na puññāni karoti. (2)**They make themselves happy and pleased, but don’t share it and make merit.*";
P_HTM[3265]="*Idha pana, gahapati, ekacco kāmabhogī adhammena bhoge pariyesati sāhasena;**Next, a pleasure seeker seeks wealth using illegitimate, coercive means.*";
P_HTM[3266]="*adhammena bhoge pariyesitvā sāhasena attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti saṃvibhajati puññāni karoti. (3)**They make themselves happy and pleased, and they share it and make merit.*";
P_HTM[3267]="*Idha pana, gahapati, ekacco kāmabhogī dhammādhammena bhoge pariyesati sāhasenapi asāhasenapi;**Next, a pleasure seeker seeks wealth using means both legitimate and illegitimate, and coercive and non-coercive.*";
P_HTM[3268]="*dhammādhammena bhoge pariyesitvā sāhasenapi asāhasenapi na attānaṃ sukheti na pīṇeti na saṃvibhajati na puññāni karoti. (4)**They don’t make themselves happy and pleased, nor share it and make merit.*";
P_HTM[3269]="*Idha pana, gahapati, ekacco kāmabhogī dhammādhammena bhoge pariyesati sāhasenapi asāhasenapi;**Next, a pleasure seeker seeks wealth using means both legitimate and illegitimate, and coercive and non-coercive.*";
P_HTM[3270]="*dhammādhammena bhoge pariyesitvā sāhasenapi asāhasenapi attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti, na saṃvibhajati na puññāni karoti. (5)**They make themselves happy and pleased, but don't share it and make merit.*";
P_HTM[3271]="*Idha pana, gahapati, ekacco kāmabhogī dhammādhammena bhoge pariyesati sāhasenapi asāhasenapi;**Next, a pleasure seeker seeks wealth using means both legitimate and illegitimate, and coercive and non-coercive.*";
P_HTM[3272]="*dhammādhammena bhoge pariyesitvā sāhasenapi asāhasenapi attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti saṃvibhajati puññāni karoti. (6)**They make themselves happy and pleased, and they share it and make merit.*";
P_HTM[3273]="*Idha pana, gahapati, ekacco kāmabhogī dhammena bhoge pariyesati asāhasena;**Next, a pleasure seeker seeks wealth using legitimate, non-coercive means.*";
P_HTM[3274]="*dhammena bhoge pariyesitvā asāhasena na attānaṃ sukheti na pīṇeti na saṃvibhajati na puññāni karoti. (7)**They don’t make themselves happy and pleased, nor share it and make merit.*";
P_HTM[3275]="*Idha pana, gahapati, ekacco kāmabhogī dhammena bhoge pariyesati asāhasena;**Next, a pleasure seeker seeks wealth using legitimate, non-coercive means.*";
P_HTM[3276]="*dhammena bhoge pariyesitvā asāhasena attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti, na saṃvibhajati na puññāni karoti. (8)**They make themselves happy and pleased, but don’t share it and make merit.*";
P_HTM[3277]="*Idha pana, gahapati, ekacco kāmabhogī dhammena bhoge pariyesati asāhasena;**Next, a pleasure seeker seeks wealth using legitimate, non-coercive means.*";
P_HTM[3278]="*dhammena bhoge pariyesitvā asāhasena attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti saṃvibhajati puññāni karoti.**They make themselves happy and pleased, and they share it and make merit.*";
P_HTM[3279]="*Te ca bhoge gathito mucchito ajjhosanno anādīnavadassāvī anissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati. (9)**But they enjoy that wealth tied, infatuated, attached, blind to the drawbacks, and not understanding the escape.*";
P_HTM[3280]="*Idha pana, gahapati, ekacco kāmabhogī dhammena bhoge pariyesati asāhasena;**Next, a pleasure seeker seeks wealth using legitimate, non-coercive means.*";
P_HTM[3281]="*dhammena bhoge pariyesitvā asāhasena attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti saṃvibhajati puññāni karoti.**They make themselves happy and pleased, and they share it and make merit.*";
P_HTM[3282]="*Te ca bhoge agathito amucchito anajjhosanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati. (10)**And they enjoy that wealth untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawbacks, and understanding the escape.*";
P_HTM[3283]="*Tatra, gahapati, yvāyaṃ kāmabhogī adhammena bhoge pariyesati sāhasena, adhammena bhoge pariyesitvā sāhasena na attānaṃ sukheti na pīṇeti na saṃvibhajati na puññāni karoti, ayaṃ, gahapati, kāmabhogī tīhi ṭhānehi gārayho.**Now, consider the pleasure seeker who seeks wealth using illegitimate, coercive means, and who doesn’t make themselves happy and pleased, nor share it and make merit. They may be criticized on three grounds.*";
P_HTM[3284]="*‘Adhammena bhoge pariyesati sāhasenā’ti, iminā paṭhamena ṭhānena gārayho.**They seek for wealth using illegitimate, coercive means. This is the first ground for criticism.*";
P_HTM[3285]="*‘Na attānaṃ sukheti na pīṇetī’ti, iminā dutiyena ṭhānena gārayho.**They don’t make themselves happy and pleased. This is the second ground for criticism.*";
P_HTM[3286]="*‘Na saṃvibhajati na puññāni karotī’ti, iminā tatiyena ṭhānena gārayho.**They don’t share it and make merit. This is the third ground for criticism.*";
P_HTM[3287]="*Ayaṃ, gahapati, kāmabhogī imehi tīhi ṭhānehi gārayho. (1)**This pleasure seeker may be criticized on these three grounds.*";
P_HTM[3288]="*Tatra, gahapati, yvāyaṃ kāmabhogī adhammena bhoge pariyesati sāhasena, adhammena bhoge pariyesitvā sāhasena attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti na saṃvibhajati na puññāni karoti, ayaṃ, gahapati, kāmabhogī dvīhi ṭhānehi gārayho ekena ṭhānena pāsaṃso.**Now, consider the pleasure seeker who seeks wealth using illegitimate, coercive means, and who makes themselves happy and pleased, but doesn’t share it and make merit. They may be criticized on two grounds, and praised on one.*";
P_HTM[3289]="*‘Adhammena bhoge pariyesati sāhasenā’ti, iminā paṭhamena ṭhānena gārayho.**They seek for wealth using illegitimate, coercive means. This is the first ground for criticism.*";
P_HTM[3290]="*‘Attānaṃ sukheti pīṇetī’ti, iminā ekena ṭhānena pāsaṃso.**They make themselves happy and pleased. This is the one ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[3291]="*‘Na saṃvibhajati na puññāni karotī’ti iminā dutiyena ṭhānena gārayho.**They don’t share it and make merit. This is the second ground for criticism.*";
P_HTM[3292]="*Ayaṃ, gahapati, kāmabhogī imehi dvīhi ṭhānehi gārayho iminā ekena ṭhānena pāsaṃso. (2)**This pleasure seeker may be criticized on these two grounds, and praised on this one.*";
P_HTM[3293]="*Tatra, gahapati, yvāyaṃ kāmabhogī adhammena bhoge pariyesati sāhasena, adhammena bhoge pariyesitvā sāhasena attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti saṃvibhajati puññāni karoti, ayaṃ, gahapati, kāmabhogī ekena ṭhānena gārayho dvīhi ṭhānehi pāsaṃso.**Now, consider the pleasure seeker who seeks wealth using illegitimate, coercive means, and who makes themselves happy and pleased, and shares it and makes merit. They may be criticized on one ground, and praised on two.*";
P_HTM[3294]="*‘Adhammena bhoge pariyesati sāhasenā’ti, iminā ekena ṭhānena gārayho.**They seek for wealth using illegitimate, coercive means. This is the one ground for criticism.*";
P_HTM[3295]="*‘Attānaṃ sukheti pīṇetī’ti, iminā paṭhamena ṭhānena pāsaṃso.**They make themselves happy and pleased. This is the first ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[3296]="*‘Saṃvibhajati puññāni karotī’ti, iminā dutiyena ṭhānena pāsaṃso.**They share it and make merit. This is the second ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[3297]="*Ayaṃ, gahapati, kāmabhogī iminā ekena ṭhānena gārayho, imehi dvīhi ṭhānehi pāsaṃso. (3)**This pleasure seeker may be criticized on this one ground, and praised on these two.*";
P_HTM[3298]="*Tatra, gahapati, yvāyaṃ kāmabhogī dhammādhammena bhoge pariyesati sāhasenapi asāhasenapi, dhammādhammena bhoge pariyesitvā sāhasenapi asāhasenapi na attānaṃ sukheti na pīṇeti na saṃvibhajati na puññāni karoti, ayaṃ, gahapati, kāmabhogī ekena ṭhānena pāsaṃso tīhi ṭhānehi gārayho.**Now, consider the pleasure seeker who seeks wealth using means both legitimate and illegitimate, and coercive and non-coercive, and who doesn’t make themselves happy and pleased, nor share it and make merit. They may be praised on one ground, and criticized on three.*";
P_HTM[3299]="*‘Dhammena bhoge pariyesati asāhasenā’ti, iminā ekena ṭhānena pāsaṃso.**They seek for wealth using legitimate, non-coercive means. This is the one ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[3300]="*‘Adhammena bhoge pariyesati sāhasenā’ti, iminā paṭhamena ṭhānena gārayho.**They seek for wealth using illegitimate, coercive means. This is the first ground for criticism.*";
