P_HTM[3320]="*Ayaṃ, gahapati, kāmabhogī iminā ekena ṭhānena pāsaṃso imehi dvīhi ṭhānehi gārayho. (7)**This pleasure seeker may be praised on this one ground, and criticized on these two.*";
P_HTM[3321]="*Tatra, gahapati, yvāyaṃ kāmabhogī dhammena bhoge pariyesati asāhasena, dhammena bhoge pariyesitvā asāhasena attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti na saṃvibhajati na puññāni karoti, ayaṃ, gahapati, kāmabhogī dvīhi ṭhānehi pāsaṃso ekena ṭhānena gārayho.**Now, consider the pleasure seeker who seeks wealth using legitimate, non-coercive means, and who makes themselves happy and pleased, but doesn’t share it and make merit. They may be praised on two grounds and criticized on one.*";
P_HTM[3322]="*‘Dhammena bhoge pariyesati asāhasenā’ti, iminā paṭhamena ṭhānena pāsaṃso.**They seek for wealth using legitimate, non-coercive means. This is the first ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[3323]="*‘Attānaṃ sukheti pīṇetī’ti, iminā dutiyena ṭhānena pāsaṃso.**They make themselves happy and pleased. This is the second ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[3324]="*‘Na saṃvibhajati na puññāni karotī’ti iminā ekena ṭhānena gārayho.**They don’t share it and make merit. This is the one ground for criticism.*";
