P_HTM[3326]="*Tatra, gahapati yvāyaṃ kāmabhogī dhammena bhoge pariyesati asāhasena, dhammena bhoge pariyesitvā asāhasena attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti saṃvibhajati puññāni karoti, te ca bhoge gathito mucchito ajjhosanno anādīnavadassāvī anissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati, ayaṃ, gahapati, kāmabhogī tīhi ṭhānehi pāsaṃso ekena ṭhānena gārayho.**Now, consider the pleasure seeker who seeks wealth using legitimate, non-coercive means, and who makes themselves happy and pleased, and shares it and makes merit. But they enjoy that wealth tied, infatuated, attached, blind to the drawbacks, and not understanding the escape. They may be praised on three grounds and criticized on one.*";
P_HTM[3327]="*‘Dhammena bhoge pariyesati asāhasenā’ti, iminā paṭhamena ṭhānena pāsaṃso.**They seek for wealth using legitimate, non-coercive means. This is the first ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[3328]="*‘Attānaṃ sukheti pīṇetī’ti, iminā dutiyena ṭhānena pāsaṃso.**They make themselves happy and pleased. This is the second ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[3329]="*‘Saṃvibhajati puññāni karotī’ti, iminā tatiyena ṭhānena pāsaṃso.**They share it and make merit. This is the third ground for praise.*";
