P_HTM[3331]="*Ayaṃ, gahapati, kāmabhogī imehi tīhi ṭhānehi pāsaṃso iminā ekena ṭhānena gārayho. (9)**This pleasure seeker may be praised on these three grounds, and criticized on this one.*";
P_HTM[3332]="*Tatra, gahapati, yvāyaṃ kāmabhogī dhammena bhoge pariyesati asāhasena, dhammena bhoge pariyesitvā asāhasena attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti saṃvibhajati puññāni karoti, te ca bhoge agathito amucchito anajjhosanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati, ayaṃ, gahapati, kāmabhogī catūhi ṭhānehi pāsaṃso.**Now, consider the pleasure seeker who seeks wealth using legitimate, non-coercive means, and who makes themselves happy and pleased, and shares it and makes merit. And they enjoy that wealth untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawbacks, and understanding the escape. They may be praised on four grounds.*";
P_HTM[3333]="*‘Dhammena bhoge pariyesati asāhasenā’ti, iminā paṭhamena ṭhānena pāsaṃso.**They seek for wealth using legitimate, non-coercive means. This is the first ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[3334]="*‘Attānaṃ sukheti pīṇetī’ti, iminā dutiyena ṭhānena pāsaṃso.**They make themselves happy and pleased. This is the second ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[3335]="*‘Saṃvibhajati puññāni karotī’ti, iminā tatiyena ṭhānena pāsaṃso.**They share it and make merit. This is the third ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[3336]="*‘Te ca bhoge agathito amucchito anajjhosanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjatī’ti, iminā catutthena ṭhānena pāsaṃso.**They enjoy that wealth untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawbacks, and understanding the escape. This is the fourth ground for praise.*";
P_HTM[3337]="*Ayaṃ, gahapati, kāmabhogī imehi catūhi ṭhānehi pāsaṃso. (10)**This pleasure seeker may be praised on these four grounds.*";
P_HTM[3338]="*Ime kho, gahapati, dasa kāmabhogī santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**These are the ten pleasure seekers found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3339]="*Imesaṃ kho, gahapati, dasannaṃ kāmabhogīnaṃ yvāyaṃ kāmabhogī dhammena bhoge pariyesati asāhasena, dhammena bhoge pariyesitvā asāhasena attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti saṃvibhajati puññāni karoti, te ca bhoge agathito amucchito anajjhosanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati, ayaṃ imesaṃ dasannaṃ kāmabhogīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca pāmokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro ca.**The pleasure seeker who seeks wealth using legitimate, non-coercive means, who makes themselves happy and pleased, and shares it and makes merit, and who uses that wealth untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawbacks, and understanding the escape is the foremost, best, chief, highest, and finest of the ten.*";
P_HTM[3340]="*Seyyathāpi, gahapati, gavā khīraṃ, khīramhā dadhi, dadhimhā navanītaṃ, navanītamhā sappi, sappimhā sappimaṇḍo. Sappimaṇḍo tattha aggamakkhāyati.**From a cow comes milk, from milk comes curds, from curds come butter, from butter comes ghee, and from ghee comes cream of ghee. And the cream of ghee is said to be the best of these.*";
P_HTM[3341]="*Evamevaṃ kho, gahapati, imesaṃ dasannaṃ kāmabhogīnaṃ yvāyaṃ kāmabhogī dhammena bhoge pariyesati asāhasena, dhammena bhoge pariyesitvā asāhasena attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti saṃvibhajati puññāni karoti, te ca bhoge agathito amucchito anajjhosanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati, ayaṃ imesaṃ dasannaṃ kāmabhogīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca pāmokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro cā”ti.**In the same way, the pleasure seeker who seeks wealth using legitimate, non-coercive means, who makes themselves happy and pleased, and shares it and makes merit, and who uses that wealth untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawbacks, and understanding the escape is the foremost, best, chief, highest, and finest of the ten.”*";
P_HTM[3342]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3343]="*2. Bhayasuttaṃ**Dangers*";
P_HTM[3344]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then the householder Anāthapiṇḍika went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[3345]="*“Yato, kho, gahapati, ariyasāvakassa pañca bhayāni verāni vūpasantāni honti, catūhi ca sotāpattiyaṅgehi samannāgato hoti, ariyo cassa ñāyo paññāya sudiṭṭho hoti suppaṭividdho, so ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya:**“Householder, when a noble disciple has quelled five dangers and threats, has the four factors of stream-entry, and has clearly seen and comprehended the noble cycle with wisdom, they may, if they wish, declare of themselves:*";
P_HTM[3346]="*‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto. Sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’ti.**‘I’ve finished with rebirth in hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. I’ve finished with all places of loss, bad places, the underworld. I am a stream-enterer! I’m not liable to be reborn in the underworld, and am bound for awakening.’*";
P_HTM[3347]="*Katamāni pañca bhayāni verāni vūpasantāni honti?**What are the five dangers and threats they have quelled?*";
P_HTM[3348]="*Yaṃ, gahapati, pāṇātipātī pāṇātipātapaccayā diṭṭhadhammikampi bhayaṃ veraṃ pasavati samparāyikampi bhayaṃ veraṃ pasavati cetasikampi dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti, pāṇātipātā paṭivirato neva diṭṭhadhammikampi bhayaṃ veraṃ pasavati na samparāyikampi bhayaṃ veraṃ pasavati na cetasikampi dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**Anyone who kills living creatures creates dangers and threats both in the present life and in lives to come, and experiences mental pain and sadness. Anyone who refrains from killing living creatures creates no dangers and threats either in the present life or in lives to come, and doesn’t experience mental pain and sadness.*";
P_HTM[3349]="*Pāṇātipātā paṭiviratassa evaṃ taṃ bhayaṃ veraṃ vūpasantaṃ hoti.**So that danger and threat is quelled for anyone who refrains from killing living creatures.*";
P_HTM[3350]="*Yaṃ, gahapati, adinnādāyī … pe …**Anyone who steals …*";
P_HTM[3351]="*kāmesumicchācārī …**Anyone who commits sexual misconduct …*";
P_HTM[3352]="*musāvādī …**Anyone who lies …*";
P_HTM[3353]="*surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhāyī surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānapaccayā diṭṭhadhammikampi bhayaṃ veraṃ pasavati samparāyikampi bhayaṃ veraṃ pasavati cetasikampi dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato neva diṭṭhadhammikampi bhayaṃ veraṃ pasavati na samparāyikampi bhayaṃ veraṃ pasavati na cetasikampi dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**Anyone who uses alcoholic drinks that cause negligence creates dangers and threats both in the present life and in lives to come, and experiences mental pain and sadness. Anyone who refrains from using alcoholic drinks that cause negligence creates no dangers and threats either in the present life or in lives to come, and doesn’t experience mental pain and sadness.*";
P_HTM[3354]="*Surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭiviratassa evaṃ taṃ bhayaṃ veraṃ vūpasantaṃ hoti.**So that danger and threat is quelled for anyone who refrains from using alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[3355]="*Imāni pañca bhayāni verāni vūpasantāni honti.**These are the five dangers and threats they have quelled.*";
P_HTM[3356]="*Katamehi catūhi sotāpattiyaṅgehi samannāgato hoti?**What are the four factors of stream-entry that they have?*";
P_HTM[3357]="*Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:**It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[3358]="*‘itipi so bhagavā … pe … buddho bhagavā’ti;**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[3359]="*dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:**They have experiential confidence in the teaching:*";
P_HTM[3360]="*‘svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo sandiṭṭhiko akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī’ti;**‘The teaching is well explained by the Buddha—visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves.’*";
P_HTM[3361]="*saṅghe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:**They have experiential confidence in the Saṅgha:*";
P_HTM[3362]="*‘suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, ujuppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, ñāyappaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, sāmīcippaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, yadidaṃ cattāri purisayugāni aṭṭha purisapuggalā, esa bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho āhuneyyo pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā’ti;**‘The Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is practicing the way that’s good, straightforward, methodical, and proper. It consists of the four pairs, the eight individuals. This is the Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples that is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of greeting with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.’*";
P_HTM[3363]="*ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti ‘akhaṇḍehi acchiddehi asabalehi akammāsehi bhujissehi viññuppasatthehi aparāmaṭṭhehi samādhisaṃvattanikehi’.**And a noble disciple’s ethical conduct is loved by the noble ones, unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred, liberating, praised by sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[3364]="*Imehi catūhi sotāpattiyaṅgehi samannāgato hoti.**These are the four factors of stream-entry that they have.*";
P_HTM[3365]="*Katamo cassa ariyo ñāyo paññāya sudiṭṭho hoti suppaṭividdho?**And what is the noble cycle that they have clearly seen and comprehended with wisdom?*";
P_HTM[3366]="*Idha, gahapati, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**It’s when a noble disciple reflects:*";
P_HTM[3367]="*‘iti imasmiṃ sati idaṃ hoti; imassuppādā idaṃ uppajjati;**‘When this exists, that is; due to the arising of this, that arises.*";
P_HTM[3368]="*imasmiṃ asati idaṃ na hoti; imassa nirodhā idaṃ nirujjhati, yadidaṃ—**When this doesn’t exist, that is not; due to the cessation of this, that ceases. That is:*";
P_HTM[3369]="*avijjāpaccayā saṅkhārā,**Ignorance is a condition for choices.*";
P_HTM[3370]="*saṅkhārapaccayā viññāṇaṃ,**Choices are a condition for consciousness.*";
P_HTM[3371]="*viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpaṃ,**Consciousness is a condition for name and form.*";
P_HTM[3372]="*nāmarūpapaccayā saḷāyatanaṃ,**Name and form are conditions for the six sense fields.*";
P_HTM[3373]="*saḷāyatanapaccayā phasso,**The six sense fields are conditions for contact.*";
P_HTM[3374]="*phassapaccayā vedanā,**Contact is a condition for feeling.*";
P_HTM[3375]="*vedanāpaccayā taṇhā,**Feeling is a condition for craving.*";
P_HTM[3376]="*taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ,**Craving is a condition for grasping.*";
P_HTM[3377]="*upādānapaccayā bhavo,**Grasping is a condition for continued existence.*";
P_HTM[3378]="*bhavapaccayā jāti,**Continued existence is a condition for rebirth.*";
P_HTM[3379]="*jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti,**Rebirth is a condition for old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress to come to be.*";
P_HTM[3380]="*evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti;**That is how this entire mass of suffering originates.*";
P_HTM[3381]="*avijjāya tveva asesavirāganirodhā saṅkhāranirodho … pe …**When ignorance fades away and ceases with nothing left over, choices cease. When choices cease, consciousness ceases. When consciousness ceases, name and form cease. When name and form cease, the six sense fields cease. When the six sense fields cease, contact ceases. When contact ceases, feeling ceases. When feeling ceases, craving ceases. When craving ceases, grasping ceases. When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases. When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases. When rebirth ceases, old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress cease.*";
P_HTM[3382]="*evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hotī’ti.**That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.’*";
P_HTM[3383]="*Ayañcassa ariyo ñāyo paññāya sudiṭṭho hoti suppaṭividdho.**This is the noble cycle that they have clearly seen and comprehended with wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3384]="*Yato kho, gahapati, ariyasāvakassa imāni pañca bhayāni verāni vūpasantāni honti, imehi ca catūhi sotāpattiyaṅgehi samannāgato hoti, ayañcassa ariyo ñāyo paññāya sudiṭṭho hoti suppaṭividdho, so ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya:**When a noble disciple has quelled five dangers and threats, has the four factors of stream-entry, and has clearly seen and comprehended the noble cycle with wisdom, they may, if they wish, declare of themselves:*";
P_HTM[3385]="*‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto; sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’”ti.**‘I’ve finished with rebirth in hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. I’ve finished with all places of loss, bad places, the underworld. I am a stream-enterer! I’m not liable to be reborn in the underworld, and am bound for awakening.’”*";
P_HTM[3386]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3387]="*3. Kiṃdiṭṭhikasuttaṃ**What Is Your View?*";
P_HTM[3388]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[3389]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati divā divassa sāvatthiyā nikkhami bhagavantaṃ dassanāya.**Then the householder Anāthapiṇḍika left Sāvatthī in the middle of the day to see the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3390]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa etadahosi:**Then it occurred to him,*";
P_HTM[3391]="*“akālo kho tāva bhagavantaṃ dassanāya.**“It’s the wrong time to see the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[3392]="*Paṭisallīno bhagavā.**as he’s in retreat.*";
P_HTM[3393]="*Manobhāvanīyānampi bhikkhūnaṃ akālo dassanāya.**And it’s the wrong time to see the esteemed mendicants,*";
P_HTM[3394]="*Paṭisallīnā manobhāvanīyā bhikkhū.**as they’re in retreat.*";
P_HTM[3395]="*Yannūnāhaṃ yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti.**Why don’t I go to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths?”*";
P_HTM[3396]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkami.**Then he went to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths.*";
P_HTM[3397]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatitthiyā paribbājakā saṅgamma samāgamma unnādino uccāsaddamahāsaddā anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ kathentā nisinnā honti.**Now at that time, the wanderers who follow other paths had come together, making an uproar, a dreadful racket as they sat and talked about all kinds of unworthy topics.*";
P_HTM[3398]="*Addasaṃsu kho te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**They saw Anāthapiṇḍika coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[3399]="*Disvāna aññamaññaṃ saṇṭhāpesuṃ:**and stopped each other, saying,*";
P_HTM[3400]="*“appasaddā bhonto hontu, mā bhonto saddamakattha.**“Be quiet, good sirs, don’t make a sound.*";
P_HTM[3401]="*Ayaṃ anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati ārāmaṃ āgacchati samaṇassa gotamassa sāvako.**The householder Anāthapiṇḍika, a disciple of the ascetic Gotama, is coming into our monastery.*";
P_HTM[3402]="*Yāvatā kho pana samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakā gihī odātavasanā sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasanti, ayaṃ tesaṃ aññataro anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati.**He is included among the white-clothed lay disciples of the ascetic Gotama, who is residing in Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3403]="*Appasaddakāmā kho pana te āyasmanto appasaddavinītā appasaddassa vaṇṇavādino.**Such venerables like the quiet, are educated to be quiet, and praise the quiet.*";
P_HTM[3404]="*Appeva nāma appasaddaṃ parisaṃ viditvā upasaṅkamitabbaṃ maññeyyā”ti.**Hopefully if he sees that our assembly is quiet he’ll see fit to approach.”*";
P_HTM[3405]="*Atha kho te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā tuṇhī ahesuṃ.**Then those wanderers who follow other paths fell silent.*";
P_HTM[3406]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā tehi aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Anāthapiṇḍika went up to them, and exchanged greetings with those wanderers.*";
P_HTM[3407]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā etadavocuṃ:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side. The wanderers said to him,*";
P_HTM[3408]="*“vadehi, gahapati, kiṃdiṭṭhiko samaṇo gotamo”ti?**“Tell us, householder, what is the view of the ascetic Gotama?”*";
P_HTM[3409]="*“Na kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavato sabbaṃ diṭṭhiṃ jānāmī”ti.**“Sirs, I don’t know all his views.”*";
P_HTM[3410]="*“Iti kira tvaṃ, gahapati, na samaṇassa gotamassa sabbaṃ diṭṭhiṃ jānāsi;**“Well then, since it seems you don’t know all the views of the ascetic Gotama,*";
P_HTM[3411]="*vadehi, gahapati, kiṃdiṭṭhikā bhikkhū”ti?**tell us, what are the views of the mendicants?”*";
P_HTM[3412]="*“Bhikkhūnampi kho ahaṃ, bhante, na sabbaṃ diṭṭhiṃ jānāmī”ti.**“Sirs, I don’t know all the mendicants’ views.”*";
P_HTM[3413]="*“Iti kira tvaṃ, gahapati, na samaṇassa gotamassa sabbaṃ diṭṭhiṃ jānāsi napi bhikkhūnaṃ sabbaṃ diṭṭhiṃ jānāsi;**“Well then, since it seems you don’t know all the views of the ascetic Gotama or of the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[3414]="*vadehi, gahapati, kiṃdiṭṭhikosi tuvan”ti?**tell us, householder, what is your view?”*";
P_HTM[3415]="*“Etaṃ kho, bhante, amhehi na dukkaraṃ byākātuṃ yaṃdiṭṭhikā mayaṃ.**“Sirs, it’s not hard for me to explain what my views are.*";
P_HTM[3416]="*Iṅgha tāva āyasmanto yathāsakāni diṭṭhigatāni byākarontu, pacchāpetaṃ amhehi na dukkaraṃ bhavissati byākātuṃ yaṃdiṭṭhikā mayan”ti.**But please, let the venerables explain their own convictions first. Afterwards it won’t be hard for me to explain my views.”*";
P_HTM[3417]="*Evaṃ vutte, aññataro paribbājako anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, one of the wanderers said to him,*";
P_HTM[3418]="*“sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—**“The world is eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.*";
P_HTM[3419]="*evaṃdiṭṭhiko ahaṃ, gahapatī”ti.**That’s my view, householder.”*";
P_HTM[3420]="*Aññataropi kho paribbājako anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca:**Another wanderer said,*";
P_HTM[3421]="*“asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—**“The world is not eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.*";
P_HTM[3422]="*evaṃdiṭṭhiko ahaṃ, gahapatī”ti.**That’s my view, householder.”*";
P_HTM[3423]="*Aññataropi kho paribbājako anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca:**Another wanderer said,*";
P_HTM[3424]="*“antavā loko … pe …**“The world is finite …” …*";
P_HTM[3425]="*anantavā loko …**“The world is infinite …” …*";
P_HTM[3426]="*taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ …**“The soul and the body are the same thing …” …*";
P_HTM[3427]="*aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīraṃ …**“The soul and the body are different things …” …*";
P_HTM[3428]="*hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …**“A Realized One exists after death …” …*";
P_HTM[3429]="*na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …**“A Realized One doesn’t exist after death …” …*";
P_HTM[3430]="*hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …**“A Realized One both exists and doesn’t exist after death …” …*";
P_HTM[3431]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—**“A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.*";
P_HTM[3432]="*evaṃdiṭṭhiko ahaṃ, gahapatī”ti.**That’s my view, householder.”*";
P_HTM[3433]="*Evaṃ vutte, anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati te paribbājake etadavoca:**When this was said, Anāthapiṇḍika said this,*";
P_HTM[3434]="*“yvāyaṃ, bhante, āyasmā evamāha:**“Sirs, regarding the venerable who said this:*";
P_HTM[3435]="*‘sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—**‘The world is eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.*";
P_HTM[3436]="*evaṃdiṭṭhiko ahaṃ, gahapatī’ti,**That’s my view, householder.’*";
P_HTM[3437]="*imassa ayamāyasmato diṭṭhi attano vā ayonisomanasikārahetu uppannā paratoghosapaccayā vā.**This view of his has either arisen from his own improper attention, or is conditioned by what someone else says.*";
P_HTM[3438]="*Sā kho panesā diṭṭhi bhūtā saṅkhatā cetayitā paṭiccasamuppannā.**But that view is created, conditioned, chosen, dependently originated.*";
P_HTM[3439]="*Yaṃ kho pana kiñci bhūtaṃ saṅkhataṃ cetayitaṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ tadaniccaṃ.**Anything that is created, conditioned, chosen, and dependently originated is impermanent.*";
P_HTM[3440]="*Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ.**And what’s impermanent is suffering.*";
P_HTM[3441]="*Yaṃ dukkhaṃ tadeveso āyasmā allīno, tadeveso āyasmā ajjhupagato.**What he clings to and holds to is just suffering.*";
P_HTM[3442]="*Yopāyaṃ, bhante, āyasmā evamāha:**Regarding the venerable who said this:*";
P_HTM[3443]="*‘asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—**‘The world is not eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.*";
P_HTM[3444]="*evaṃdiṭṭhiko ahaṃ, gahapatī’ti,**That’s my view, householder.’*";
P_HTM[3445]="*imassāpi ayamāyasmato diṭṭhi attano vā ayonisomanasikārahetu uppannā paratoghosapaccayā vā.**This view of his has either arisen from his own improper attention, or is conditioned by what someone else says.*";
P_HTM[3446]="*Sā kho panesā diṭṭhi bhūtā saṅkhatā cetayitā paṭiccasamuppannā.**But that view is created, conditioned, chosen, dependently originated.*";
P_HTM[3447]="*Yaṃ kho pana kiñci bhūtaṃ saṅkhataṃ cetayitaṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ tadaniccaṃ.**Anything that is created, conditioned, chosen, and dependently originated is impermanent.*";
P_HTM[3448]="*Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ.**And what’s impermanent is suffering.*";
P_HTM[3449]="*Yaṃ dukkhaṃ tadeveso āyasmā allīno, tadeveso āyasmā ajjhupagato.**What he clings to and holds to is just suffering.*";
P_HTM[3450]="*Yopāyaṃ, bhante, āyasmā evamāha:**Regarding the venerable who said this:*";
P_HTM[3451]="*‘antavā loko … pe …**‘The world is finite …’ …*";
P_HTM[3452]="*anantavā loko …**‘The world is infinite …’ …*";
P_HTM[3453]="*taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ …**‘The soul and the body are the same thing …’ …*";
P_HTM[3454]="*aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīraṃ …**‘The soul and the body are different things …’ …*";
P_HTM[3455]="*hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …**‘A Realized One exists after death …’ …*";
P_HTM[3456]="*na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …**‘A Realized One doesn’t exist after death …’ …*";
P_HTM[3457]="*hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …**‘A Realized One both exists and doesn’t exist after death …’ …*";
P_HTM[3458]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—**‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly.*";
P_HTM[3459]="*evaṃdiṭṭhiko ahaṃ, gahapatī’ti,**That’s my view, householder.’*";
P_HTM[3460]="*imassāpi ayamāyasmato diṭṭhi attano vā ayonisomanasikārahetu uppannā paratoghosapaccayā vā.**This view of his has either arisen from his own improper attention, or is conditioned by what someone else says.*";
P_HTM[3461]="*Sā kho panesā diṭṭhi bhūtā saṅkhatā cetayitā paṭiccasamuppannā.**But that view is created, conditioned, chosen, dependently originated.*";
P_HTM[3462]="*Yaṃ kho pana kiñci bhūtaṃ saṅkhataṃ cetayitaṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ tadaniccaṃ.**Anything that is created, conditioned, chosen, and dependently originated is impermanent.*";
P_HTM[3463]="*Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ.**And what’s impermanent is suffering.*";
P_HTM[3464]="*Yaṃ dukkhaṃ tadeveso āyasmā allīno, tadeveso āyasmā ajjhupagato”ti.**What he clings to and holds to is just suffering.”*";
P_HTM[3465]="*Evaṃ vutte te paribbājakā anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavocuṃ:**When he said this the wanderers said to him,*";
P_HTM[3466]="*“byākatāni kho, gahapati, amhehi sabbeheva yathāsakāni diṭṭhigatāni.**“Householder, we’ve each explained our own convictions.*";
P_HTM[3467]="*Vadehi, gahapati, kiṃdiṭṭhikosi tuvan”ti?**Tell us, householder, what is your view?”*";
P_HTM[3468]="*“Yaṃ kho, bhante, kiñci bhūtaṃ saṅkhataṃ cetayitaṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ tadaniccaṃ.**“Sirs, anything that is created, conditioned, chosen, and dependently originated is impermanent.*";
P_HTM[3469]="*Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ.**And what’s impermanent is suffering.*";
P_HTM[3470]="*‘Yaṃ dukkhaṃ taṃ netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti—**And what’s suffering is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.*";
P_HTM[3471]="*evaṃdiṭṭhiko ahaṃ, bhante”ti.**That’s my view, sirs.”*";
P_HTM[3472]="*“Yaṃ kho, gahapati, kiñci bhūtaṃ saṅkhataṃ cetayitaṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ tadaniccaṃ.**“Householder, anything that is created, conditioned, chosen, and dependently originated is impermanent.*";
P_HTM[3473]="*Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ.**And what’s impermanent is suffering.*";
P_HTM[3474]="*Yaṃ dukkhaṃ tadeva tvaṃ, gahapati, allīno, tadeva tvaṃ, gahapati, ajjhupagato”ti.**What you cling to and hold to is just suffering.”*";
P_HTM[3475]="*“Yaṃ kho, bhante, kiñci bhūtaṃ saṅkhataṃ cetayitaṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ tadaniccaṃ.**“Sirs, anything that is created, conditioned, chosen, and dependently originated is impermanent.*";
P_HTM[3476]="*Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ.**And what’s impermanent is suffering.*";
P_HTM[3477]="*‘Yaṃ dukkhaṃ taṃ netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, nameso attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhaṃ.**And I’ve truly seen clearly with right wisdom that what’s suffering is not mine, I am not this, it’s not my self.*";
P_HTM[3478]="*Tassa ca uttari nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāmī”ti.**And I truly understand the escape beyond that.”*";
P_HTM[3479]="*Evaṃ vutte te paribbājakā tuṇhībhūtā maṅkubhūtā pattakkhandhā adhomukhā pajjhāyantā appaṭibhānā nisīdiṃsu.**When this was said, those wanderers sat silent, dismayed, shoulders drooping, downcast, depressed, with nothing to say.*";
P_HTM[3480]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati te paribbājake tuṇhībhūte maṅkubhūte pattakkhandhe adhomukhe pajjhāyante appaṭibhāne viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yāvatako ahosi tehi aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi.**Seeing this, Anāthapiṇḍika got up from his seat. He went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and informed the Buddha of all they had discussed.*";
P_HTM[3481]="*“Sādhu sādhu, gahapati.**“Good, good, householder!*";
P_HTM[3482]="*Evaṃ kho te, gahapati, moghapurisā kālena kālaṃ sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggahetabbā”ti.**That’s how you should legitimately and completely refute those foolish men from time to time.”*";
P_HTM[3483]="*Atha kho bhagavā anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**Then the Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired the householder Anāthapiṇḍika with a Dhamma talk,*";
P_HTM[3484]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**after which Anāthapiṇḍika got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha before leaving.*";
P_HTM[3485]="*Atha kho bhagavā acirapakkante anāthapiṇḍike gahapatimhi bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then, not long after Anāthapiṇḍika had left, the Buddha addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[3486]="*“yopi so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vassasatupasampanno imasmiṃ dhammavinaye, sopi evamevaṃ aññatitthiye paribbājake sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggaṇheyya yathā taṃ anāthapiṇḍikena gahapatinā niggahitā”ti.**“Mendicants, even a mendicant who has ordained for a hundred years in this teaching and training would legitimately and completely refute those wanderers who follow other paths just as the householder Anāthapiṇḍika did.”*";
P_HTM[3487]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3488]="*4. Vajjiyamāhitasuttaṃ**With Vajjiyamāhita*";
P_HTM[3489]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā campāyaṃ viharati gaggarāya pokkharaṇiyā tīre.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Campā on the banks of the Gaggarā Lotus Pond.*";
P_HTM[3490]="*Atha kho vajjiyamāhito gahapati divā divassa campāya nikkhami bhagavantaṃ dassanāya.**Then the householder Vajjiyamāhita left Sāvatthī in the middle of the day to see the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3491]="*Atha kho vajjiyamāhitassa gahapatissa etadahosi:**Then it occurred to him,*";
P_HTM[3492]="*“akālo kho tāva bhagavantaṃ dassanāya.**“It’s the wrong time to see the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[3493]="*Paṭisallīno bhagavā.**as he’s in retreat.*";
P_HTM[3494]="*Manobhāvanīyānampi bhikkhūnaṃ akālo dassanāya.**And it’s the wrong time to see the esteemed mendicants,*";
P_HTM[3495]="*Paṭisallīnā manobhāvanīyāpi bhikkhū.**as they’re in retreat.*";
P_HTM[3496]="*Yannūnāhaṃ yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti.**Why don’t I go to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths?”*";
P_HTM[3497]="*Atha kho vajjiyamāhito gahapati yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkami.**Then he went to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths.*";
P_HTM[3498]="*Tena kho pana samayena te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā saṅgamma samāgamma unnādino uccāsaddamahāsaddā anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ kathentā nisinnā honti.**Now at that time, the wanderers who follow other paths had come together, making an uproar, a dreadful racket as they sat and talked about all kinds of unworthy topics.*";
P_HTM[3499]="*Addasaṃsu kho te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā vajjiyamāhitaṃ gahapatiṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ. Disvāna aññamaññaṃ saṇṭhāpesuṃ:**They saw Vajjiyamāhita coming off in the distance, and stopped each other, saying,*";
P_HTM[3500]="*“appasaddā bhonto hontu. Mā bhonto saddamakattha.**“Be quiet, good sirs, don’t make a sound.*";
P_HTM[3501]="*Ayaṃ vajjiyamāhito gahapati āgacchati samaṇassa gotamassa sāvako.**The householder Vajjiyamāhita, a disciple of the ascetic Gotama, is coming into our monastery.*";
P_HTM[3502]="*Yāvatā kho pana samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakā gihī odātavasanā campāyaṃ paṭivasanti, ayaṃ tesaṃ aññataro vajjiyamāhito gahapati.**He is included among the white-clothed lay disciples of the ascetic Gotama, who is residing near Campā.*";
P_HTM[3503]="*Appasaddakāmā kho pana te āyasmanto appasaddavinītā appasaddassa vaṇṇavādino.**Such venerables like the quiet, are educated to be quiet, and praise the quiet.*";
P_HTM[3504]="*Appeva nāma appasaddaṃ parisaṃ viditvā upasaṅkamitabbaṃ maññeyyā”ti.**Hopefully if he sees that our assembly is quiet he’ll see fit to approach.”*";
P_HTM[3505]="*Atha kho te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā tuṇhī ahesuṃ.**Then those wanderers who follow other paths fell silent.*";
P_HTM[3506]="*Atha kho vajjiyamāhito gahapati yena te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā tehi aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Vajjiyamāhita went up to them, and exchanged greetings with the wanderers there.*";
P_HTM[3507]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho vajjiyamāhitaṃ gahapatiṃ te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā etadavocuṃ:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side. The wanderers said to him:*";
P_HTM[3508]="*“saccaṃ kira, gahapati, samaṇo gotamo sabbaṃ tapaṃ garahati, sabbaṃ tapassiṃ lūkhājīviṃ ekaṃsena upakkosati upavadatī”ti?**“Is it really true, householder? Does the ascetic Gotama criticize all forms of mortification? Does he categorically condemn and denounce those self-mortifiers who live rough?”*";
P_HTM[3509]="*“Na kho, bhante, bhagavā sabbaṃ tapaṃ garahati napi sabbaṃ tapassiṃ lūkhājīviṃ ekaṃsena upakkosati upavadati.**“No, sirs, the ascetic Gotama does not criticize all forms of mortification. Nor does he categorically condemn and denounce those self-mortifiers who live rough.*";
P_HTM[3510]="*Gārayhaṃ kho, bhante, bhagavā garahati, pasaṃsitabbaṃ pasaṃsati.**The Buddha criticizes where it is due, and praises where it is due.*";
P_HTM[3511]="*Gārayhaṃ kho pana, bhante, bhagavā garahanto pasaṃsitabbaṃ pasaṃsanto vibhajjavādo bhagavā.**In doing so he is one who speaks after analyzing the question,*";
P_HTM[3512]="*Na so bhagavā ettha ekaṃsavādo”ti.**without making generalizations on this point.”*";
P_HTM[3513]="*Evaṃ vutte, aññataro paribbājako vajjiyamāhitaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, one of the wanderers said to him,*";
P_HTM[3514]="*“āgamehi tvaṃ, gahapati, yassa tvaṃ samaṇassa gotamassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, samaṇo gotamo venayiko appaññattiko”ti?**“Hold on, householder! That ascetic Gotama who you praise is an exterminator who refrains from making statements.”*";
P_HTM[3515]="*“Etthapāhaṃ, bhante, āyasmante vakkhāmi sahadhammena:**“On this point, also, I reasonably respond to the venerables.*";
P_HTM[3516]="*‘idaṃ kusalan’ti, bhante, bhagavatā paññattaṃ;**The Buddha has stated ‘This is skillful’ and*";
P_HTM[3517]="*‘idaṃ akusalan’ti, bhante, bhagavatā paññattaṃ.**‘This is unskillful’.*";
P_HTM[3518]="*Iti kusalākusalaṃ bhagavā paññāpayamāno sapaññattiko bhagavā;**So when it comes to what is skillful and unskillful the Buddha makes a statement.*";
P_HTM[3519]="*na so bhagavā venayiko appaññattiko”ti.**He is not an exterminator who refrains from making statements.”*";
P_HTM[3520]="*Evaṃ vutte te paribbājakā tuṇhībhūtā maṅkubhūtā pattakkhandhā adhomukhā pajjhāyantā appaṭibhānā nisīdiṃsu.**When this was said, those wanderers sat silent, dismayed, shoulders drooping, downcast, depressed, with nothing to say.*";
P_HTM[3521]="*Atha kho vajjiyamāhito gahapati te paribbājake tuṇhībhūte maṅkubhūte pattakkhandhe adhomukhe pajjhāyante appaṭibhāne viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Seeing this, Vajjiyamāhita got up from his seat. He went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side,*";
P_HTM[3522]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vajjiyamāhito gahapati yāvatako ahosi tehi aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi.**and informed the Buddha of all they had discussed.*";
P_HTM[3523]="*“Sādhu sādhu, gahapati.**“Good, good, householder!*";
P_HTM[3524]="*Evaṃ kho te, gahapati, moghapurisā kālena kālaṃ sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggahetabbā.**That’s how you should legitimately and completely refute those foolish men from time to time.*";
P_HTM[3525]="*Nāhaṃ, gahapati, sabbaṃ tapaṃ tapitabbanti vadāmi;**Householder, I don’t say that all mortifications should be undergone.*";
P_HTM[3526]="*na ca panāhaṃ, gahapati, sabbaṃ tapaṃ na tapitabbanti vadāmi;**But I don’t say that no mortifications should be undergone.*";
P_HTM[3527]="*nāhaṃ, gahapati, sabbaṃ samādānaṃ samāditabbanti vadāmi;**I don’t say that all observances should be undertaken.*";
P_HTM[3528]="*na panāhaṃ, gahapati, sabbaṃ samādānaṃ na samāditabbanti vadāmi;**But I don’t say that no observances should be undertaken.*";
P_HTM[3529]="*nāhaṃ, gahapati, sabbaṃ padhānaṃ padahitabbanti vadāmi;**I don’t say that all efforts should be tried.*";
P_HTM[3530]="*na panāhaṃ, gahapati, sabbaṃ padhānaṃ na padahitabbanti vadāmi;**But I don’t say that no efforts should be tried.*";
P_HTM[3531]="*nāhaṃ, gahapati, sabbo paṭinissaggo paṭinissajjitabboti vadāmi.**I don’t say that everything should be given up.*";
P_HTM[3532]="*Na panāhaṃ, gahapati, sabbo paṭinissaggo na paṭinissajjitabboti vadāmi;**But I don’t say that nothing should be given up.*";
P_HTM[3533]="*nāhaṃ, gahapati, sabbā vimutti vimuccitabbāti vadāmi;**I don’t say that you should be liberated with all kinds of freedom.*";
P_HTM[3534]="*na panāhaṃ, gahapati, sabbā vimutti na vimuccitabbāti vadāmi.**But I don’t say that you should not be liberated with any kind of freedom.*";
P_HTM[3535]="*Yañhi, gahapati, tapaṃ tapato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti, evarūpaṃ tapaṃ na tapitabbanti vadāmi.**When undergoing certain mortifications, unskillful qualities grow while skillful qualities decline. I say that you shouldn’t undergo those mortifications.*";
P_HTM[3536]="*Yañca khvassa, gahapati, tapaṃ tapato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, evarūpaṃ tapaṃ tapitabbanti vadāmi.**When undergoing certain mortifications, unskillful qualities decline while skillful qualities grow. I say that you should undergo those mortifications.*";
P_HTM[3537]="*Yañhi, gahapati, samādānaṃ samādiyato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti, evarūpaṃ samādānaṃ na samāditabbanti vadāmi.**When undertaking certain observances, unskillful qualities grow while skillful qualities decline. I say that you shouldn’t undertake those observances.*";
P_HTM[3538]="*Yañca khvassa, gahapati, samādānaṃ samādiyato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, evarūpaṃ samādānaṃ samāditabbanti vadāmi.**When undertaking certain observances, unskillful qualities decline while skillful qualities grow. I say that you should undertake those observances.*";
P_HTM[3539]="*Yañhi, gahapati, padhānaṃ padahato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti, evarūpaṃ padhānaṃ na padahitabbanti vadāmi.**When trying certain efforts, unskillful qualities grow while skillful qualities decline. I say that you shouldn’t try those efforts.*";
P_HTM[3540]="*Yañca khvassa, gahapati, padhānaṃ padahato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, evarūpaṃ padhānaṃ padahitabbanti vadāmi.**When trying certain efforts, unskillful qualities decline while skillful qualities grow. I say that you should try those efforts.*";
P_HTM[3541]="*Yañhi, gahapati, paṭinissaggaṃ paṭinissajjato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti, evarūpo paṭinissaggo na paṭinissajjitabboti vadāmi.**When giving up certain things, unskillful qualities grow while skillful qualities decline. I say that you shouldn’t give up those things.*";
P_HTM[3542]="*Yañca khvassa, gahapati, paṭinissaggaṃ paṭinissajjato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, evarūpo paṭinissaggo paṭinissajjitabboti vadāmi.**When giving up certain things, unskillful qualities decline while skillful qualities grow. I say that you should give up those things.*";
P_HTM[3543]="*Yañhi, gahapati, vimuttiṃ vimuccato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti, evarūpā vimutti na vimuccitabbāti vadāmi.**When being liberated with certain kinds of freedom, unskillful qualities grow while skillful qualities decline. I say that you shouldn’t be liberated with those kinds of freedom.*";
P_HTM[3544]="*Yañca khvassa, gahapati, vimuttiṃ vimuccato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, evarūpā vimutti vimuccitabbāti vadāmī”ti.**When being liberated with certain kinds of freedom, unskillful qualities decline while skillful qualities grow. I say that you should be liberated with those kinds of freedom.”*";
P_HTM[3545]="*Atha kho vajjiyamāhito gahapati bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**After Vajjiyamāhita had been educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired with a Dhamma talk by the Buddha, he got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha before leaving.*";
P_HTM[3546]="*Atha kho bhagavā acirapakkante vajjiyamāhite gahapatimhi bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then, not long after Vajjiyamāhita had left, the Buddha addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[3547]="*“yopi so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dīgharattaṃ apparajakkho imasmiṃ dhammavinaye, sopi evamevaṃ aññatitthiye paribbājake sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggaṇheyya yathā taṃ vajjiyamāhitena gahapatinā niggahitā”ti.**“Mendicants, even a mendicant who for a long time has had little dust in their eye in this teaching and training would legitimately and completely refute those wanderers who follow other paths just as the householder Vajjiyamāhita did.”*";
P_HTM[3548]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3549]="*5. Uttiyasuttaṃ**With Uttiya*";
P_HTM[3550]="*Atha kho uttiyo paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the wanderer Uttiya went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[3551]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho uttiyo paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[3552]="*“kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan”ti?**“Master Gotama, is this right: ‘The world is eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[3553]="*“Abyākataṃ kho etaṃ, uttiya, mayā:**“This has not been declared by me, Uttiya.”*";
P_HTM[3554]="*‘sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3555]="*“Kiṃ pana, bho gotama, asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan”ti?**“Then is this right: ‘The world is not eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[3556]="*“Etampi kho, uttiya, abyākataṃ mayā:**“This has not been declared by me, Uttiya.”*";
P_HTM[3557]="*‘asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3558]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, antavā loko … pe …**“Then is this right: ‘The world is finite …’ …*";
P_HTM[3559]="*anantavā loko …**‘The world is infinite …’ …*";
P_HTM[3560]="*taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ …**‘The soul and the body are the same thing …’ …*";
P_HTM[3561]="*aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīraṃ …**‘The soul and the body are different things …’ …*";
P_HTM[3562]="*hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …**‘A Realized One exists after death …’ …*";
P_HTM[3563]="*na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …**‘A Realized One doesn’t exist after death …’ …*";
P_HTM[3564]="*hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …**‘A Realized One both exists and doesn’t exist after death …’ …*";
P_HTM[3565]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan”ti?**‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[3566]="*“Etampi kho, uttiya, abyākataṃ mayā:**“This has not been declared by me, Uttiya.”*";
P_HTM[3567]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3568]="*“‘Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno ‘abyākataṃ kho etaṃ, uttiya, mayā—**“When asked about all these points, Master Gotama says that they have not been declared by him.*";
P_HTM[3569]="*sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3570]="*‘Kiṃ pana, bho gotama, asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno:* **";
P_HTM[3571]="*‘etampi kho, uttiya, abyākataṃ mayā asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3572]="*‘Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, antavā loko … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3573]="*anantavā loko …* **";
P_HTM[3574]="*taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ …* **";
P_HTM[3575]="*aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīraṃ …* **";
P_HTM[3576]="*hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …* **";
P_HTM[3577]="*na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …* **";
P_HTM[3578]="*hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …* **";
P_HTM[3579]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno:* **";
P_HTM[3580]="*‘etampi kho, uttiya, abyākataṃ mayā—* **";
P_HTM[3581]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3582]="*Atha kiñcarahi bhotā gotamena byākatan”ti?**So what exactly has been declared by Master Gotama?”*";
P_HTM[3583]="*“Abhiññāya kho ahaṃ, uttiya, sāvakānaṃ dhammaṃ desemi sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa sacchikiriyāyā”ti.**“Uttiya, I teach my disciples from my own insight in order to purify sentient beings, to get past sorrow and crying, to make an end of pain and sadness, to end the cycle of suffering, and to realize extinguishment.”*";
P_HTM[3584]="*“Yaṃ panetaṃ bhavaṃ gotamo abhiññāya sāvakānaṃ dhammaṃ desesi sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa sacchikiriyāya, sabbo vā tena loko nīyati upaḍḍho vā tibhāgo vā”ti?**“But when Master Gotama teaches in this way, is the whole world saved, or half, or a third?”*";
P_HTM[3585]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā tuṇhī ahosi.**But when he said this, the Buddha kept silent.*";
P_HTM[3586]="*Atha kho āyasmato ānandassa etadahosi:**Then Venerable Ānanda thought,*";
P_HTM[3587]="*“mā hevaṃ kho uttiyo paribbājako pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ paṭilabhi:**“The wanderer Uttiya must not get the harmful misconception:*";
P_HTM[3588]="*‘sabbasāmukkaṃsikaṃ vata me samaṇo gotamo pañhaṃ puṭṭho saṃsādeti, no vissajjeti, na nūna visahatī’ti.**‘When the ascetic Gotama was asked this all-important question he falters without answering. He just can’t do it!’*";
P_HTM[3589]="*Tadassa uttiyassa paribbājakassa dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti.**That would be for his lasting harm and suffering.”*";
P_HTM[3590]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando uttiyaṃ paribbājakaṃ etadavoca:**Then Ānanda said to the wanderer Uttiya,*";
P_HTM[3591]="*“tenahāvuso uttiya, upamaṃ te karissāmi.**“Well then, Reverend Uttiya, I shall give you a simile.*";
P_HTM[3592]="*Upamāya m’idhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti.**For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what is said.*";
P_HTM[3593]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso uttiya, rañño paccantimaṃ nagaraṃ daḷhuddhāpaṃ daḷhapākāratoraṇaṃ ekadvāraṃ.**Suppose there was a king’s frontier citadel with fortified embankments, ramparts, and arches, and a single gate.*";
P_HTM[3594]="*Tatrassa dovāriko paṇḍito byatto medhāvī aññātānaṃ nivāretā ñātānaṃ pavesetā.**And it has a gatekeeper who is astute, competent, and clever. He keeps strangers out and lets known people in.*";
P_HTM[3595]="*So tassa nagarassa samantā anupariyāyapathaṃ anukkamati. Anupariyāyapathaṃ anukkamamāno na passeyya pākārasandhiṃ vā pākāravivaraṃ vā, antamaso biḷāranikkhamanamattampi.**As he walks around the patrol path, he doesn’t see a hole or cleft in the wall, not even one big enough for a cat to slip out.*";
P_HTM[3596]="*No ca khvassa evaṃ ñāṇaṃ hoti: ‘ettakā pāṇā imaṃ nagaraṃ pavisanti vā nikkhamanti vā’ti.**He doesn’t know how many creatures enter or leave the citadel.*";
P_HTM[3597]="*Atha khvassa evamettha hoti: ‘ye kho keci oḷārikā pāṇā imaṃ nagaraṃ pavisanti vā nikkhamanti vā, sabbe te iminā dvārena pavisanti vā nikkhamanti vā’ti.**But he does know that whatever sizable creatures enter or leave the citadel, all of them do so via this gate.*";
P_HTM[3598]="*Evamevaṃ kho, āvuso uttiya, na tathāgatassa evaṃ ussukkaṃ hoti: ‘sabbo vā tena loko nīyati, upaḍḍho vā, tibhāgo vā’ti.**In the same way, it’s not the Realized One’s concern whether the whole world is saved by this, or half, or a third.*";
P_HTM[3599]="*Atha kho evamettha tathāgatassa hoti: ‘ye kho keci lokamhā nīyiṃsu vā nīyanti vā nīyissanti vā, sabbe te pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe, catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacittā, satta bojjhaṅge yathābhūtaṃ bhāvetvā.**But the Realized One knows that whoever is saved from the world—whether in the past, the future, or the present—all have given up the five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken wisdom. They have firmly established their mind in the four kinds of mindfulness meditation. And they have truly developed the seven awakening factors.*";
P_HTM[3600]="*Evamete lokamhā nīyiṃsu vā nīyanti vā nīyissanti vā’ti.**That’s how they’re saved from the world, in the past, future, or present.*";
P_HTM[3601]="*Yadeva kho tvaṃ, āvuso uttiya, bhagavantaṃ pañhaṃ apucchi tadevetaṃ pañhaṃ bhagavantaṃ aññena pariyāyena apucchi.**Uttiya, you were just asking the Buddha the same question as before in a different way.*";
P_HTM[3602]="*Tasmā te taṃ bhagavā na byākāsī”ti.**That’s why he didn’t answer.”*";
P_HTM[3603]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3604]="*6. Kokanudasuttaṃ**With Kokanada*";
P_HTM[3605]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ānando rājagahe viharati tapodārāme.**At one time Venerable Ānanda was staying near Rājagaha in the Hot Springs Monastery.*";
P_HTM[3606]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya yena tapodā tenupasaṅkami gattāni parisiñcituṃ.**Then Ānanda rose at the crack of dawn and went to the hot springs to bathe.*";
P_HTM[3607]="*Tapodāya gattāni parisiñcitvā paccuttaritvā ekacīvaro aṭṭhāsi gattāni pubbāpayamāno.**When he had bathed and emerged from the water he stood in one robe drying himself.*";
P_HTM[3608]="*Kokanudopi kho paribbājako rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya yena tapodā tenupasaṅkami gattāni parisiñcituṃ.**The wanderer Kokanada also rose at the crack of dawn and went to the hot springs to bathe.*";
P_HTM[3609]="*Addasā kho kokanudo paribbājako āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**He saw Ānanda coming off in the distance*";
P_HTM[3610]="*Disvāna āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**and said to him,*";
P_HTM[3611]="*“kvettha, āvuso”ti?**“Who’s here, reverend?”*";
P_HTM[3612]="*“Ahamāvuso, bhikkhū”ti.**“I’m a mendicant, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[3613]="*“Katamesaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhūnan”ti?**“Of which mendicants?”*";
P_HTM[3614]="*“Samaṇānaṃ, āvuso, sakyaputtiyānan”ti.**“Of the ascetics who follow the Sakyan.”*";
P_HTM[3615]="*“Puccheyyāma mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ kiñcideva desaṃ, sace āyasmā okāsaṃ karoti pañhassa veyyākaraṇāyā”ti.**“I’d like to ask the venerable about a certain point, if you’d take the time to answer.”*";
P_HTM[3616]="*“Pucchāvuso, sutvā vedissāmā”ti.**“Ask, reverend. When I’ve heard it I’ll know.”*";
P_HTM[3617]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, bho, ‘sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti—evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavan”ti?**“Is this your view: ‘The world is eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[3618]="*“Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“That’s not my view, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[3619]="*‘sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3620]="*“Kiṃ pana, bho, ‘asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti—evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavan”ti?**“Then is this your view: ‘The world is not eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[3621]="*“Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“That’s not my view, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[3622]="*‘asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3623]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, bho, antavā loko … pe …**“Then is this your view: ‘The world is finite …’ …*";
P_HTM[3624]="*anantavā loko …**‘The world is infinite …’ …*";
P_HTM[3625]="*taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ …**‘The soul and the body are the same thing …’ …*";
P_HTM[3626]="*aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīraṃ …**‘The soul and the body are different things …’ …*";
P_HTM[3627]="*hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …**‘A Realized One exists after death …’ …*";
P_HTM[3628]="*na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …**‘A Realized One doesn’t exist after death …’ …*";
P_HTM[3629]="*hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …**‘A Realized One both exists and doesn’t exist after death …’ …*";
P_HTM[3630]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavan”ti?**‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly’?”*";
P_HTM[3631]="*“Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, evaṃdiṭṭhi:**“That’s not my view, reverend.”*";
P_HTM[3632]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3633]="*“Tena hi bhavaṃ na jānāti, na passatī”ti?**“Then, sir, do you neither know nor see?”*";
P_HTM[3634]="*“Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, na jānāmi na passāmi.**“That’s not so, reverend.*";
P_HTM[3635]="*Jānāmahaṃ, āvuso, passāmī”ti.**I do know and see.”*";
P_HTM[3636]="*“‘Kiṃ nu kho, bho, sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—**“When asked about all these points, you say that’s not your view.*";
P_HTM[3637]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavan’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno:* **";
P_HTM[3638]="*‘na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, evaṃdiṭṭhi—* **";
P_HTM[3639]="*sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3640]="*‘Kiṃ pana, bho, asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—* **";
P_HTM[3641]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavan’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno:* **";
P_HTM[3642]="*‘na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, evaṃdiṭṭhi—* **";
P_HTM[3643]="*asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3644]="*Kiṃ nu kho, bho, antavā loko … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3645]="*anantavā loko …* **";
P_HTM[3646]="*taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ …* **";
P_HTM[3647]="*aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīraṃ …* **";
P_HTM[3648]="*hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …* **";
P_HTM[3649]="*na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …* **";
P_HTM[3650]="*hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …* **";
P_HTM[3651]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti—* **";
P_HTM[3652]="*evaṃdiṭṭhi bhavanti, iti puṭṭho samāno:* **";
P_HTM[3653]="*‘na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, evaṃdiṭṭhi—* **";
P_HTM[3654]="*neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti vadesi.* **";
P_HTM[3655]="*‘Tena hi bhavaṃ na jānāti na passatī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno:**Yet when asked whether you neither know nor see,*";
P_HTM[3656]="*‘na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, na jānāmi na passāmi.**you say, ‘That’s not so, reverend.*";
P_HTM[3657]="*Jānāmahaṃ, āvuso, passāmī’ti vadesi.**I do know and see.’*";
P_HTM[3658]="*Yathā kathaṃ panāvuso, imassa bhāsitassa attho daṭṭhabbo”ti?**How then should we see the meaning of this statement?”*";
P_HTM[3659]="*“‘Sassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti kho, āvuso, diṭṭhigatametaṃ.**“‘The world is eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly:’ that’s a misconception.*";
P_HTM[3660]="*‘Asassato loko, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti kho, āvuso, diṭṭhigatametaṃ.**‘The world is not eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly:’ that’s a misconception.*";
P_HTM[3661]="*Antavā loko … pe …**‘The world is finite …’ …*";
P_HTM[3662]="*anantavā loko …**‘The world is infinite …’ …*";
P_HTM[3663]="*taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīraṃ …**‘The soul and the body are the same thing …’ …*";
P_HTM[3664]="*aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīraṃ …**‘The soul and the body are different things …’ …*";
P_HTM[3665]="*hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …**‘A Realized One exists after death …’ …*";
P_HTM[3666]="*na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …**‘A Realized One doesn’t exist after death …’ …*";
P_HTM[3667]="*hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …**‘A Realized One both exists and doesn’t exist after death …’ …*";
P_HTM[3668]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti kho, āvuso, diṭṭhigatametaṃ.**‘A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly:’ that’s a misconception.*";
P_HTM[3669]="*Yāvatā, āvuso, diṭṭhi yāvatā diṭṭhiṭṭhānaṃ diṭṭhiadhiṭṭhānaṃ diṭṭhipariyuṭṭhānaṃ diṭṭhisamuṭṭhānaṃ diṭṭhisamugghāto, tamahaṃ jānāmi tamahaṃ passāmi.**I know and see the scope of convictions, the scope of grounds for views, fixation on views, obsession with views, the origin of views, and the uprooting of views.*";
P_HTM[3670]="*Tamahaṃ jānanto tamahaṃ passanto kyāhaṃ vakkhāmi:**Knowing and seeing thus, why should I say:*";
P_HTM[3671]="*‘na jānāmi na passāmī’ti?**‘I neither know nor see?’*";
P_HTM[3672]="*Jānāmahaṃ, āvuso, passāmī”ti.**I do know and see.”*";
P_HTM[3673]="*“Ko nāmo āyasmā, kathañca panāyasmantaṃ sabrahmacārī jānantī”ti?**“What is the venerable’s name? And how are you known among your spiritual companions?”*";
P_HTM[3674]="*“‘Ānando’ti kho me, āvuso, nāmaṃ.**“Reverend, my name is Ānanda.*";
P_HTM[3675]="*‘Ānando’ti ca pana maṃ sabrahmacārī jānantī”ti.**And that’s how I’m known among my spiritual companions.”*";
P_HTM[3676]="*“Mahācariyena vata kira, bho, saddhiṃ mantayamānā na jānimha:**“Goodness! I had no idea I was consulting such a great teacher as*";
P_HTM[3677]="*‘āyasmā ānando’ti.**Venerable Ānanda!*";
P_HTM[3678]="*Sace hi mayaṃ jāneyyāma:**If I had known who*";
P_HTM[3679]="*‘ayaṃ āyasmā ānando’ti, ettakampi no nappaṭibhāyeyya.**you were, I wouldn’t have said so much.*";
P_HTM[3680]="*Khamatu ca me āyasmā ānando”ti.**May Venerable Ānanda please forgive me.”*";
P_HTM[3681]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3682]="*7. Āhuneyyasuttaṃ**Worthy of Offerings Dedicated to the Gods*";
P_HTM[3683]="*“Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa.**“Mendicants, a mendicant with ten factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.*";
P_HTM[3684]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[3685]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu.**It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the monastic code, conducting themselves well and seeking alms in suitable places. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken.*";
P_HTM[3686]="*Bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo. Ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā.**They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and comprehending them theoretically.*";
P_HTM[3687]="*Kalyāṇamitto hoti kalyāṇasahāyo kalyāṇasampavaṅko.**They have good friends, companions, and associates.*";
P_HTM[3688]="*Sammādiṭṭhiko hoti sammādassanena samannāgato.**They have right view, possessing right perspective.*";
P_HTM[3689]="*Anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhoti—ekopi hutvā bahudhā hoti; bahudhāpi hutvā eko hoti; āvibhāvaṃ, tirobhāvaṃ; tirokuṭṭaṃ tiropākāraṃ tiropabbataṃ asajjamāno gacchati, seyyathāpi ākāse; pathaviyāpi ummujjanimujjaṃ karoti, seyyathāpi udake; udakepi abhijjamāne gacchati, seyyathāpi pathaviyaṃ; ākāsepi pallaṅkena kamati, seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo; imepi candimasūriye evaṃmahiddhike evaṃmahānubhāve pāṇinā parāmasati parimajjati, yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteti.**They wield the many kinds of psychic power: multiplying themselves and becoming one again; appearing and disappearing; going unimpeded through a wall, a rampart, or a mountain as if through space; diving in and out of the earth as if it were water; walking on water as if it were earth; flying cross-legged through the sky like a bird; touching and stroking with the hand the sun and moon, so mighty and powerful. They control the body as far as the Brahmā realm.*";
P_HTM[3690]="*Dibbāya sotadhātuyā visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya ubho sadde suṇāti dibbe ca mānuse ca ye dūre santike ca.**With clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, they hear both kinds of sounds, human and divine, whether near or far.*";
P_HTM[3691]="*Parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāti. Sarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘sarāgaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti; vītarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘vītarāgaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti; sadosaṃ vā cittaṃ … vītadosaṃ vā cittaṃ … samohaṃ vā cittaṃ … vītamohaṃ vā cittaṃ … saṅkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ … vikkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ … mahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ … amahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ … sauttaraṃ vā cittaṃ … anuttaraṃ vā cittaṃ … samāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ … asamāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ … vimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ … avimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘avimuttaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti.**They understand the minds of other beings and individuals, having comprehended them with their own mind. They understand mind with greed as ‘mind with greed’, and mind without greed as ‘mind without greed’. They understand mind with hate … mind without hate … mind with delusion … mind without delusion … constricted mind … scattered mind … expansive mind … unexpansive mind … mind that is not supreme … mind that is supreme … mind immersed in samādhi … mind not immersed in samādhi … freed mind … They understand unfreed mind as ‘unfreed mind’.*";
P_HTM[3692]="*Anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo tissopi jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo dasapi jātiyo vīsampi jātiyo tiṃsampi jātiyo cattālīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi jātiyo jātisatampi jātisahassampi jātisatasahassampi anekepi saṃvaṭṭakappe anekepi vivaṭṭakappe anekepi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭakappe: ‘amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhapaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ; tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhapaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapanno’ti, iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati.**They recollect many kinds of past lives, that is, one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. They remember: ‘There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn somewhere else. There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn here.’ Thus they recollect their many past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[3693]="*Dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe, sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāti: ‘ime vata kho bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā vacīduccaritena samannāgatā manoduccaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ upavādakā micchādiṭṭhikā micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannā; ime vā pana bhonto sattā kāyasucaritena samannāgatā vacīsucaritena samannāgatā manosucaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ anupavādakā sammādiṭṭhikā sammādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannā’ti. Iti dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe, sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāti.**With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. They understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds. ‘These dear beings did bad things by way of body, speech, and mind. They spoke ill of the noble ones; they had wrong view; and they acted out of that wrong view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. These dear beings, however, did good things by way of body, speech, and mind. They never spoke ill of the noble ones; they had right view; and they acted out of that right view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.’ And so, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. They understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[3694]="*Āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[3695]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti.**A mendicant with these ten factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.”*";
P_HTM[3696]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3697]="*8. Therasuttaṃ**A Senior Mendicant*";
P_HTM[3698]="*“Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu yassaṃ yassaṃ disāyaṃ viharati, phāsuyeva viharati.**“Mendicants, a senior mendicant with ten qualities lives comfortably in whatever region they live.*";
P_HTM[3699]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[3700]="*Thero hoti rattaññū cirapabbajito,**They are senior and have long gone forth.*";
P_HTM[3701]="*sīlavā hoti … pe …**They’re ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, with good behavior and supporters. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken.*";
P_HTM[3702]="*samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu, bahussuto hoti … pe …**They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and comprehending them theoretically.*";
P_HTM[3703]="*diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdho, ubhayāni kho panassa pātimokkhāni vitthārena svāgatāni honti suvibhattāni suppavattīni suvinicchitāni suttaso anubyañjanaso,**Both monastic codes have been passed down to them in detail, well analyzed, well mastered, well judged in both the rules and accompanying material.*";
P_HTM[3704]="*adhikaraṇasamuppādavūpasamakusalo hoti,**They’re skilled in raising and settling disciplinary issues.*";
P_HTM[3705]="*dhammakāmo hoti piyasamudāhāro abhidhamme abhivinaye uḷārapāmojjo,**They love the teachings and are a delight to converse with, being full of joy in the teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[3706]="*santuṭṭho hoti itarītaracīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena,**They’re content with any kind of robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[3707]="*pāsādiko hoti abhikkantapaṭikkante susaṃvuto antaraghare nisajjāya,**They look impressive when going out and coming back, and are well restrained when sitting in an inhabited area.*";
P_HTM[3708]="*catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī,**They get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[3709]="*āsavānañca khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[3710]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu yassaṃ yassaṃ disāyaṃ viharati, phāsuyeva viharatī”ti.**A senior mendicant with these ten qualities lives comfortably in whatever region they live.”*";
P_HTM[3711]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3712]="*9. Upālisuttaṃ**With Upāli*";
P_HTM[3713]="*Atha kho āyasmā upāli yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā upāli bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Upāli went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[3714]="*“icchāmahaṃ, bhante, araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevitun”ti.**“Sir, I wish to frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.”*";
P_HTM[3715]="*“Durabhisambhavāni hi kho, upāli, araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni.**“Upāli, remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest are challenging.*";
P_HTM[3716]="*Dukkaraṃ pavivekaṃ durabhiramaṃ.**It’s hard to maintain seclusion and hard to find joy in it.*";
P_HTM[3717]="*Ekatte haranti maññe mano vanāni samādhiṃ alabhamānassa bhikkhuno.**Staying alone, the forests seem to rob the mind of a mendicant who isn’t immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[3718]="*Yo kho, upāli, evaṃ vadeyya:**If someone should say this,*";
P_HTM[3719]="*‘ahaṃ samādhiṃ alabhamāno araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevissāmī’ti, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ:**‘Though I don’t have immersion, I’m going to frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.’ You can expect that*";
P_HTM[3720]="*‘saṃsīdissati vā uplavissati vā’ti.**they’ll sink down or float away.*";
P_HTM[3721]="*Seyyathāpi, upāli, mahāudakarahado.**Suppose there was a large lake,*";
P_HTM[3722]="*Atha āgaccheyya hatthināgo sattaratano vā aḍḍhaṭṭharatano vā.**and along comes a bull elephant with a height of seven or eight cubits.*";
P_HTM[3723]="*Tassa evamassa:**He’d think,*";
P_HTM[3724]="*‘yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ udakarahadaṃ ogāhetvā kaṇṇasandhovikampi khiḍḍaṃ kīḷeyyaṃ piṭṭhisandhovikampi khiḍḍaṃ kīḷeyyaṃ.**‘Why don’t I plunge into this lake and play around while washing my ears and back?*";
P_HTM[3725]="*Kaṇṇasandhovikampi khiḍḍaṃ kīḷitvā piṭṭhisandhovikampi khiḍḍaṃ kīḷitvā nhatvā ca pivitvā ca paccuttaritvā yena kāmaṃ pakkameyyan’ti.**When I’ve bathed and emerged from the water, I’ll come out and go wherever I want.’*";
P_HTM[3726]="*So taṃ udakarahadaṃ ogāhetvā kaṇṇasandhovikampi khiḍḍaṃ kīḷeyya piṭṭhisandhovikampi khiḍḍaṃ kīḷeyya;**And that’s just what he does.*";
P_HTM[3727]="*kaṇṇasandhovikampi khiḍḍaṃ kīḷitvā piṭṭhisandhovikampi khiḍḍaṃ kīḷitvā nhatvā ca pivitvā ca paccuttaritvā yena kāmaṃ pakkameyya.* **";
P_HTM[3728]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3729]="*Mahā, upāli, attabhāvo gambhīre gādhaṃ vindati.**Because his large life-form finds a footing in the depths.*";
P_HTM[3730]="*Atha āgaccheyya saso vā biḷāro vā.**Then along comes a rabbit or a cat.*";
P_HTM[3731]="*Tassa evamassa:**They’d think,*";
P_HTM[3732]="*‘ko cāhaṃ, ko ca hatthināgo.**‘What difference is there between me and a bull elephant?*";
P_HTM[3733]="*Yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ udakarahadaṃ ogāhetvā kaṇṇasandhovikampi khiḍḍaṃ kīḷeyyaṃ piṭṭhisandhovikampi khiḍḍaṃ kīḷeyyaṃ;**Why don’t I plunge into this lake and play around while washing my ears and back?*";
P_HTM[3734]="*kaṇṇasandhovikampi khiḍḍaṃ kīḷitvā piṭṭhisandhovikampi khiḍḍaṃ kīḷitvā nhatvā ca pivitvā ca paccuttaritvā yena kāmaṃ pakkameyyan’ti.**When I’ve bathed and drunk, I’ll emerge from the water and go wherever I want.’*";
P_HTM[3735]="*So taṃ udakarahadaṃ sahasā appaṭisaṅkhā pakkhandeyya.**They jump into the lake rashly, without thinking.*";
P_HTM[3736]="*Tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ:**You can expect that*";
P_HTM[3737]="*‘saṃsīdissati vā uplavissati vā’ti.**they’ll sink down or float away.*";
P_HTM[3738]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3739]="*Paritto, upāli, attabhāvo gambhīre gādhaṃ na vindati.**Because their little life-form finds no footing in the depths.*";
P_HTM[3740]="*Evamevaṃ kho, upāli, yo evaṃ vadeyya:**If someone should say this,*";
P_HTM[3741]="*‘ahaṃ samādhiṃ alabhamāno araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevissāmī’ti, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ:**‘Though I don’t have immersion, I’m going to frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.’ You can expect that*";
P_HTM[3742]="*‘saṃsīdissati vā uplavissati vā’ti.**they’ll sink down or float away.*";
P_HTM[3743]="*Seyyathāpi, upāli, daharo kumāro mando uttānaseyyako sakena muttakarīsena kīḷati.**Suppose there was a little baby boy playing in his own urine and feces.*";
P_HTM[3744]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, upāli,**What do you think, Upāli?*";
P_HTM[3745]="*nanvāyaṃ kevalā paripūrā bālakhiḍḍā”ti?**Isn’t that a totally foolish game?”*";
P_HTM[3746]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3747]="*“Sa kho so, upāli, kumāro aparena samayena vuddhimanvāya indriyānaṃ paripākamanvāya**“After some time that boy grows up and his faculties mature.*";
P_HTM[3748]="*yāni kānici kumārakānaṃ kīḷāpanakāni bhavanti, seyyathidaṃ—vaṅkakaṃ ghaṭikaṃ mokkhacikaṃ ciṅgulakaṃ pattāḷhakaṃ rathakaṃ dhanukaṃ, tehi kīḷati.**He accordingly plays childish games such as toy plows, tip-cat, somersaults, pinwheels, toy measures, toy carts, and toy bows.*";
P_HTM[3749]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, upāli,**What do you think, Upāli?*";
P_HTM[3750]="*nanvāyaṃ khiḍḍā purimāya khiḍḍāya abhikkantatarā ca paṇītatarā cā”ti?**Aren’t such games better than what he did before?”*";
P_HTM[3751]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3752]="*“Sa kho so, upāli, kumāro aparena samayena vuddhimanvāya indriyānaṃ paripākamanvāya**“After some time that boy grows up and his faculties mature further.*";
P_HTM[3753]="*pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgibhūto paricāreti**He accordingly amuses himself, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[3754]="*cakkhuviññeyyehi rūpehi iṭṭhehi kantehi manāpehi piyarūpehi kāmūpasaṃhitehi rajanīyehi,**Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[3755]="*sotaviññeyyehi saddehi …**Sounds known by the ear …*";
P_HTM[3756]="*ghānaviññeyyehi gandhehi …**Smells known by the nose …*";
P_HTM[3757]="*jivhāviññeyyehi rasehi …**Tastes known by the tongue …*";
P_HTM[3758]="*kāyaviññeyyehi phoṭṭhabbehi iṭṭhehi kantehi manāpehi piyarūpehi kāmūpasaṃhitehi rajanīyehi.**Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[3759]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, upāli,**What do you think, Upāli?*";
P_HTM[3760]="*nanvāyaṃ khiḍḍā purimāhi khiḍḍāhi abhikkantatarā ca paṇītatarā cā”ti?**Aren’t such games better than what he did before?”*";
P_HTM[3761]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3762]="*“Idha kho pana vo, upāli, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā.**“But then a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.*";
P_HTM[3763]="*So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti.**He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others.*";
P_HTM[3764]="*So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti.**He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure.*";
P_HTM[3765]="*Taṃ dhammaṃ suṇāti gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā aññatarasmiṃ vā kule paccājāto.**A householder hears that teaching, or a householder’s child, or someone reborn in some good family.*";
P_HTM[3766]="*So taṃ dhammaṃ sutvā tathāgate saddhaṃ paṭilabhati.**They gain faith in the Realized One,*";
P_HTM[3767]="*So tena saddhāpaṭilābhena samannāgato iti paṭisañcikkhati:**and reflect,*";
P_HTM[3768]="*‘sambādho gharāvāso rajāpatho, abbhokāso pabbajjā.**‘Living in a house is cramped and dirty, but the life of one gone forth is wide open.*";
P_HTM[3769]="*Nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekantaparipuṇṇaṃ ekantaparisuddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ.**It’s not easy for someone living at home to lead the spiritual life utterly full and pure, like a polished shell.*";
P_HTM[3770]="*Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti.**Why don’t I shave off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness?’*";
P_HTM[3771]="*So aparena samayena appaṃ vā bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya mahantaṃ vā bhogakkhandhaṃ pahāya appaṃ vā ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya mahantaṃ vā ñātiparivaṭṭaṃ pahāya kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati.**After some time they give up a large or small fortune, and a large or small family circle. They shave off hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[3772]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāsājīvasamāpanno pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho lajjī dayāpanno sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati.**Once they’ve gone forth, they take up the training and livelihood of the mendicants. They give up killing living creatures, renouncing the rod and the sword. They’re scrupulous and kind, living full of compassion for all living beings.*";
P_HTM[3773]="*Adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti dinnādāyī dinnapāṭikaṅkhī; athenena sucibhūtena attanā viharati.**They give up stealing. They take only what’s given, and expect only what’s given. They keep themselves clean by not thieving.*";
P_HTM[3774]="*Abrahmacariyaṃ pahāya brahmacārī hoti ārācārī virato methunā gāmadhammā.**They give up unchastity. They are celibate, set apart, avoiding the common practice of sex.*";
P_HTM[3775]="*Musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti saccavādī saccasandho theto paccayiko avisaṃvādako lokassa.**They give up lying. They speak the truth and stick to the truth. They’re honest and trustworthy, and don’t trick the world with their words.*";
P_HTM[3776]="*Pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, ito sutvā na amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, amutra vā sutvā na imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya. Iti bhinnānaṃ vā sandhātā sahitānaṃ vā anuppadātā, samaggārāmo samaggarato samagganandī; samaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**They give up divisive speech. They don’t repeat in one place what they heard in another so as to divide people against each other. Instead, they reconcile those who are divided, supporting unity, delighting in harmony, loving harmony, speaking words that promote harmony.*";
P_HTM[3777]="*Pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti. Yā sā vācā nelā kaṇṇasukhā pemanīyā hadayaṅgamā porī bahujanakantā bahujanamanāpā, tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti.**They give up harsh speech. They speak in a way that’s mellow, pleasing to the ear, lovely, going to the heart, polite, likable and agreeable to the people.*";
P_HTM[3778]="*Samphappalāpaṃ pahāya samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī, nidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti kālena sāpadesaṃ pariyantavatiṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ.**They give up talking nonsense. Their words are timely, true, and meaningful, in line with the teaching and training. They say things at the right time which are valuable, reasonable, succinct, and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[3779]="*So bījagāmabhūtagāmasamārambhā paṭivirato hoti.**They avoid injuring plants and seeds.*";
P_HTM[3780]="*Ekabhattiko hoti rattūparato, virato vikālabhojanā.**They eat in one part of the day, abstaining from eating at night and food at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[3781]="*Naccagītavāditavisūkadassanā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid dancing, singing, music, and seeing shows.*";
P_HTM[3782]="*mālāgandhavilepanadhāraṇamaṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid beautifying and adorning themselves with garlands, perfumes, and makeup.*";
P_HTM[3783]="*uccāsayanamahāsayanā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid high and luxurious beds.*";
P_HTM[3784]="*jātarūparajatapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid receiving gold and money,*";
P_HTM[3785]="*āmakadhaññapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**raw grains,*";
P_HTM[3786]="*āmakamaṃsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**raw meat,*";
P_HTM[3787]="*itthikumārikapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**women and girls,*";
P_HTM[3788]="*dāsidāsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**male and female bondservants,*";
P_HTM[3789]="*ajeḷakapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**goats and sheep,*";
P_HTM[3790]="*kukkuṭasūkarapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**chickens and pigs,*";
P_HTM[3791]="*hatthigavassavaḷavapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**elephants, cows, horses, and mares,*";
P_HTM[3792]="*khettavatthupaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato hoti,**and fields and land.*";
P_HTM[3793]="*dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogā paṭivirato hoti,**They avoid running errands and messages;*";
P_HTM[3794]="*kayavikkayā paṭivirato hoti,**buying and selling;*";
P_HTM[3795]="*tulākūṭakaṃsakūṭamānakūṭā paṭivirato hoti,**falsifying weights, metals, or measures;*";
P_HTM[3796]="*ukkoṭanavañcananikatisāciyogā paṭivirato hoti,**bribery, fraud, cheating, and duplicity;*";
P_HTM[3797]="*chedanavadhabandhanaviparāmosaālopasahasākārā paṭivirato hoti.**mutilation, murder, abduction, banditry, plunder, and violence.*";
P_HTM[3798]="*So santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena.**They’re content with robes to look after the body and alms-food to look after the belly.*";
P_HTM[3799]="*Yena yeneva pakkamati samādāyeva pakkamati,**Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things.*";
P_HTM[3800]="*seyyathāpi nāma pakkhī sakuṇo yena yeneva ḍeti sapattabhārova ḍeti.**They’re like a bird: wherever it flies, wings are its only burden.*";
P_HTM[3801]="*Evamevaṃ bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti kāyaparihārikena cīvarena kucchiparihārikena piṇḍapātena. Yena yeneva pakkamati samādāyeva pakkamati.**In the same way, a mendicant is content with robes to look after the body and alms-food to look after the belly. Wherever they go, they set out taking only these things.*";
P_HTM[3802]="*So iminā ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ anavajjasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**When they have this entire spectrum of noble ethics, they experience a blameless happiness inside themselves.*";
P_HTM[3803]="*So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When they see a sight with their eyes, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[3804]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving restraint over it.*";
P_HTM[3805]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā …**When they hear a sound with their ears …*";
P_HTM[3806]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …**When they smell an odor with their nose …*";
P_HTM[3807]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …**When they taste a flavor with their tongue …*";
P_HTM[3808]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …**When they feel a touch with their body …*";
P_HTM[3809]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When they know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[3810]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati manindriyaṃ, manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving its restraint.*";
P_HTM[3811]="*So iminā ariyena indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato ajjhattaṃ abyāsekasukhaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**When they have this noble sense restraint, they experience an unsullied bliss inside themselves.*";
P_HTM[3812]="*So abhikkante paṭikkante sampajānakārī hoti, ālokite vilokite sampajānakārī hoti, samiñjite pasārite sampajānakārī hoti, saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇe sampajānakārī hoti, asite pīte khāyite sāyite sampajānakārī hoti, uccārapassāvakamme sampajānakārī hoti, gate ṭhite nisinne sutte jāgarite bhāsite tuṇhībhāve sampajānakārī hoti.**They act with situational awareness when going out and coming back; when looking ahead and aside; when bending and extending the limbs; when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes; when eating, drinking, chewing, and tasting; when urinating and defecating; when walking, standing, sitting, sleeping, waking, speaking, and keeping silent.*";
P_HTM[3813]="*So iminā ca ariyena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato, iminā ca ariyena indriyasaṃvarena samannāgato, iminā ca ariyena satisampajaññena samannāgato**When they have this noble spectrum of ethics, this noble sense restraint, and this noble mindfulness and situational awareness,*";
P_HTM[3814]="*vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajati araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ.**they frequent a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a tree, a hill, a ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the open air, a heap of straw.*";
P_HTM[3815]="*So araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**Gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut, they sit down cross-legged, with their body straight, and establish mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[3816]="*So abhijjhaṃ loke pahāya vigatābhijjhena cetasā viharati, abhijjhāya cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up desire for the world, they meditate with a heart rid of desire, cleansing the mind of desire.*";
P_HTM[3817]="*Byāpādapadosaṃ pahāya abyāpannacitto viharati sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī, byāpādapadosā cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up ill will and malevolence, they meditate with a mind rid of ill will, full of compassion for all living beings, cleansing the mind of ill will.*";
P_HTM[3818]="*Thinamiddhaṃ pahāya vigatathinamiddho viharati ālokasaññī sato sampajāno, thinamiddhā cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up dullness and drowsiness, they meditate with a mind rid of dullness and drowsiness, perceiving light, mindful and aware, cleansing the mind of dullness and drowsiness.*";
P_HTM[3819]="*Uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahāya anuddhato viharati ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto, uddhaccakukkuccā cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up restlessness and remorse, they meditate without restlessness, their mind peaceful inside, cleansing the mind of restlessness and remorse.*";
P_HTM[3820]="*Vicikicchaṃ pahāya tiṇṇavicikiccho viharati akathaṅkathī kusalesu dhammesu, vicikicchāya cittaṃ parisodheti.**Giving up doubt, they meditate having gone beyond doubt, not undecided about skillful qualities, cleansing the mind of doubt.*";
P_HTM[3821]="*So ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe,**They give up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3822]="*vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Then, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, they enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[3823]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, upāli,**What do you think, Upāli?*";
P_HTM[3824]="*‘nanvāyaṃ vihāro purimehi vihārehi abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā’”ti?**Isn’t this state better than what they had before?”*";
P_HTM[3825]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3826]="*“Imampi kho, upāli, mama sāvakā attani dhammaṃ sampassamānā araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevanti, no ca kho tāva anuppattasadatthā viharanti.**“When my disciples see this quality inside themselves they frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest. But so far they haven’t achieved their own goal.*";
P_HTM[3827]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[3828]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, upāli,**What do you think, Upāli?*";
P_HTM[3829]="*‘nanvāyaṃ vihāro purimehi vihārehi abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā’”ti?**Isn’t this state better than what they had before?”*";
P_HTM[3830]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3831]="*“Imampi kho, upāli, mama sāvakā attani dhammaṃ sampassamānā araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevanti, no ca kho tāva anuppattasadatthā viharanti.**“When my disciples see this quality inside themselves they frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest. But so far they haven’t achieved their own goal.*";
P_HTM[3832]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains in the third absorption. They meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[3833]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, upāli,**What do you think, Upāli?*";
P_HTM[3834]="*‘nanvāyaṃ vihāro purimehi vihārehi abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā’”ti?**Isn’t this state better than what they had before?”*";
P_HTM[3835]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3836]="*“Imampi kho, upāli, mama sāvakā attani dhammaṃ sampassamānā araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevanti, no ca kho tāva anuppattasadatthā viharanti.**“When my disciples see this quality inside themselves they frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest. But so far they haven’t achieved their own goal.*";
P_HTM[3837]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ … pe ….**Furthermore, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness. …” …*";
P_HTM[3838]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**“Furthermore, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, a mendicant enters and remains in the dimension of infinite space.*";
P_HTM[3839]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, upāli,**What do you think, Upāli?*";
P_HTM[3840]="*‘nanvāyaṃ vihāro purimehi vihārehi abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā’”ti?**Isn’t this state better than what they had before?”*";
P_HTM[3841]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3842]="*“Imampi kho, upāli, mama sāvakā attani dhammaṃ sampassamānā araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevanti, no ca kho tāva anuppattasadatthā viharanti.**“When my disciples see this quality inside themselves they frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest. But so far they haven’t achieved their own goal.*";
P_HTM[3843]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, bhikkhu sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati … pe ….**Furthermore, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, a mendicant enters and remains in the dimension of infinite consciousness. …” …*";
P_HTM[3844]="*Sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati … pe ….**“Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, they enter and remain in the dimension of nothingness. …” …*";
P_HTM[3845]="*Sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘santametaṃ paṇītametan’ti nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**“Going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, they enter and remain in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[3846]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, upāli,**What do you think, Upāli?*";
P_HTM[3847]="*‘nanvāyaṃ vihāro purimehi vihārehi abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā’”ti?**Isn’t this state better than what they had before?”*";
P_HTM[3848]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3849]="*“Imampi kho, upāli, mama sāvakā attani dhammaṃ sampassamānā araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevanti, no ca kho tāva anuppattasadatthā viharanti.**“When my disciples see this quality inside themselves they frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest. But so far they haven’t achieved their own goal.*";
P_HTM[3850]="*Puna caparaṃ, upāli, bhikkhu sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharati; paññāya cassa disvā āsavā parikkhīṇā honti.**Furthermore, going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, they enter and remain in the cessation of perception and feeling. And, having seen with wisdom, their defilements come to an end.*";
P_HTM[3851]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, upāli,**What do you think, Upāli?*";
P_HTM[3852]="*‘nanvāyaṃ vihāro purimehi vihārehi abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā’”ti?**Isn’t this state better than what they had before?”*";
P_HTM[3853]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3854]="*“Imampi kho, upāli, mama sāvakā attani dhammaṃ sampassamānā araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevanti, anuppattasadatthā ca viharanti.**“When my disciples see this quality inside themselves they frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest. And they have achieved their own goal.*";
P_HTM[3855]="*Iṅgha tvaṃ, upāli, saṅghe viharāhi.**Come on, Upāli, stay with the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[3856]="*Saṅghe te viharato phāsu bhavissatī”ti.**If you stay with the Saṅgha you’ll be comfortable.”*";
P_HTM[3857]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3858]="*10. Abhabbasuttaṃ**Cannot*";
P_HTM[3859]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, dhamme appahāya abhabbo arahattaṃ sacchikātuṃ.**“Mendicants, without giving up ten things you can’t realize perfection.*";
P_HTM[3860]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[3861]="*Rāgaṃ, dosaṃ, mohaṃ, kodhaṃ, upanāhaṃ, makkhaṃ, paḷāsaṃ, issaṃ, macchariyaṃ, mānaṃ—**Greed, hate, delusion, anger, hostility, offensiveness, contempt, jealousy, stinginess, and conceit.*";
P_HTM[3862]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa dhamme appahāya abhabbo arahattaṃ sacchikātuṃ.**Without giving up these ten things you can’t realize perfection.*";
P_HTM[3863]="*Dasayime, bhikkhave, dhamme pahāya bhabbo arahattaṃ sacchikātuṃ.**After giving up ten things you can realize perfection.*";
P_HTM[3864]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[3865]="*Rāgaṃ, dosaṃ, mohaṃ, kodhaṃ, upanāhaṃ, makkhaṃ, paḷāsaṃ, issaṃ, macchariyaṃ, mānaṃ—**Greed, hate, delusion, anger, hostility, offensiveness, contempt, jealousy, stinginess, and conceit.*";
P_HTM[3866]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa dhamme pahāya bhabbo arahattaṃ sacchikātun”ti.**After giving up these ten things you can realize perfection.”*";
P_HTM[3867]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3868]="*Upālivaggo pañcamo.* **";
P_HTM[3869]="*Kāmabhogī bhayaṃ diṭṭhi,* **";
P_HTM[3870]="*vajjiyamāhituttiyā;* **";
P_HTM[3871]="*Kokanudo āhuneyyo,* **";
P_HTM[3872]="*thero upāli abhabboti.* **";
P_HTM[3873]="*Dutiyo paṇṇāsako samatto.* **";
P_HTM[3874]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Perceptions for Ascetics*";
P_HTM[3875]="*1. Samaṇasaññāsuttaṃ**Perceptions for Ascetics*";
P_HTM[3876]="*“Tisso imā, bhikkhave, samaṇasaññā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta dhamme paripūrenti.**“Mendicants, when these three perceptions for ascetics are developed and cultivated they fulfill seven things.*";
P_HTM[3877]="*Katamā tisso?**What three?*";
P_HTM[3878]="*Vevaṇṇiyamhi ajjhupagato, parapaṭibaddhā me jīvikā, añño me ākappo karaṇīyoti—**‘I have secured freedom from class.’ ‘My livelihood is tied up with others.’ ‘My behavior should be different.’*";
P_HTM[3879]="*imā kho, bhikkhave, tisso samaṇasaññā bhāvitā bahulīkatā satta dhamme paripūrenti.**When these three perceptions for ascetics are developed and cultivated they fulfill seven things.*";
P_HTM[3880]="*Katame satta?**What seven?*";
P_HTM[3881]="*Santatakārī hoti santatavutti sīlesu, anabhijjhālu hoti, abyāpajjo hoti, anatimānī hoti, sikkhākāmo hoti, “idamatthan”tissa hoti jīvitaparikkhāresu, āraddhavīriyo ca viharati.**Their deeds and behavior are always consistent with the precepts. They’re content, kind-hearted, and humble. They want to train. They use the necessities of life after reflecting on their purpose. They’re energetic.*";
P_HTM[3882]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, tisso samaṇasaññā bhāvitā bahulīkatā ime satta dhamme paripūrentī”ti.**When those three perceptions for ascetics are developed and cultivated they fulfill these seven things.”*";
P_HTM[3883]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3884]="*2. Bojjhaṅgasuttaṃ**Awakening Factors*";
P_HTM[3885]="*“Sattime, bhikkhave, bojjhaṅgā bhāvitā bahulīkatā tisso vijjā paripūrenti.**“Mendicants, when the seven awakening factors are developed and cultivated they fulfill three knowledges.*";
P_HTM[3886]="*Katame satta?**What seven?*";
P_HTM[3887]="*Satisambojjhaṅgo, dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgo, vīriyasambojjhaṅgo, pītisambojjhaṅgo, passaddhisambojjhaṅgo, samādhisambojjhaṅgo, upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo—**The awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity.*";
P_HTM[3888]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, satta bojjhaṅgā bhāvitā bahulīkatā tisso vijjā paripūrenti.**When these seven awakening factors are developed and cultivated they fulfill three knowledges.*";
P_HTM[3889]="*Katamā tisso?**What three?*";
P_HTM[3890]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati,**It’s when a mendicant recollects their many kinds of past lives.*";
P_HTM[3891]="*seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo tissopi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati.**That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. They recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[3892]="*Dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena … pe … yathākammūpage satte pajānāti.**With clairvoyance that is purified and surpasses the human, they understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[3893]="*Āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[3894]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, satta bojjhaṅgā bhāvitā bahulīkatā imā tisso vijjā paripūrentī”ti.**When those seven awakening factors are developed and cultivated they fulfill these three knowledges.”*";
P_HTM[3895]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3896]="*3. Micchattasuttaṃ**The Wrong Way*";
P_HTM[3897]="*“Micchattaṃ, bhikkhave, āgamma virādhanā hoti, no ārādhanā.**“Mendicants, relying on the wrong way leads to failure, not success.*";
P_HTM[3898]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, micchattaṃ āgamma virādhanā hoti, no ārādhanā?**And how does relying on the wrong way lead to failure, not success?*";
P_HTM[3899]="*Micchādiṭṭhikassa, bhikkhave, micchāsaṅkappo pahoti, micchāsaṅkappassa micchāvācā pahoti, micchāvācassa micchākammanto pahoti, micchākammantassa micchāājīvo pahoti, micchāājīvassa micchāvāyāmo pahoti, micchāvāyāmassa micchāsati pahoti, micchāsatissa micchāsamādhi pahoti, micchāsamādhissa micchāñāṇaṃ pahoti, micchāñāṇissa micchāvimutti pahoti.**Wrong view gives rise to wrong thought. Wrong thought gives rise to wrong speech. Wrong speech gives rise to wrong action. Wrong action gives rise to wrong livelihood. Wrong livelihood gives rise to wrong effort. Wrong effort gives rise to wrong mindfulness. Wrong mindfulness gives rise to wrong immersion. Wrong immersion gives rise to wrong knowledge. Wrong knowledge gives rise to wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[3900]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, micchattaṃ āgamma virādhanā hoti, no ārādhanā.**That’s how relying on the wrong way leads to failure, not success.*";
P_HTM[3901]="*Sammattaṃ, bhikkhave, āgamma ārādhanā hoti, no virādhanā.**Relying on the right way leads to success, not failure.*";
P_HTM[3902]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, sammattaṃ āgamma ārādhanā hoti, no virādhanā?**And how does relying on the right way lead to success, not failure?*";
P_HTM[3903]="*Sammādiṭṭhikassa, bhikkhave, sammāsaṅkappo pahoti, sammāsaṅkappassa sammāvācā pahoti, sammāvācassa sammākammanto pahoti, sammākammantassa sammāājīvo pahoti, sammāājīvassa sammāvāyāmo pahoti, sammāvāyāmassa sammāsati pahoti, sammāsatissa sammāsamādhi pahoti, sammāsamādhissa sammāñāṇaṃ pahoti, sammāñāṇissa sammāvimutti pahoti.**Right view gives rise to right thought. Right thought gives rise to right speech. Right speech gives rise to right action. Right action gives rise to right livelihood. Right livelihood gives rise to right effort. Right effort gives rise to right mindfulness. Right mindfulness gives rise to right immersion. Right immersion gives rise to right knowledge. Right knowledge gives rise to right freedom.*";
P_HTM[3904]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sammattaṃ āgamma ārādhanā hoti, no virādhanā”ti.**That’s how relying on the right way leads to success, not failure.”*";
P_HTM[3905]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3906]="*4. Bījasuttaṃ**A Seed*";
P_HTM[3907]="*“Micchādiṭṭhikassa, bhikkhave, purisapuggalassa micchāsaṅkappassa micchāvācassa micchākammantassa micchāājīvassa micchāvāyāmassa micchāsatissa micchāsamādhissa micchāñāṇissa micchāvimuttissa**“Mendicants, consider a person who has wrong view, thought, speech, action, livelihood, effort, mindfulness, immersion, knowledge, and freedom.*";
P_HTM[3908]="*yañca kāyakammaṃ yathādiṭṭhi samattaṃ samādinnaṃ yañca vacīkammaṃ yañca manokammaṃ yathādiṭṭhi samattaṃ samādinnaṃ yā ca cetanā yā ca patthanā yo ca paṇidhi ye ca saṅkhārā, sabbe te dhammā aniṭṭhāya akantāya amanāpāya ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattanti.**Whatever bodily, verbal, or mental deeds they undertake in line with that view, their intentions, aims, wishes, and choices all lead to what is unlikable, undesirable, disagreeable, harmful, and suffering.*";
P_HTM[3909]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3910]="*Diṭṭhi hissa, bhikkhave, pāpikā.**Because their view is bad.*";
P_HTM[3911]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, nimbabījaṃ vā kosātakibījaṃ vā tittakālābubījaṃ vā allāya pathaviyā nikkhittaṃ yañceva pathavirasaṃ upādiyati yañca āporasaṃ upādiyati, sabbaṃ taṃ tittakattāya kaṭukattāya asātattāya saṃvattati.**Suppose a seed of neem, angled gourd, or bitter gourd was planted in moist earth. Whatever nutrients it takes up from the earth and water would lead to its bitter, acerbic, and unpleasant taste.*";
P_HTM[3912]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3913]="*Bījañhi, bhikkhave, pāpakaṃ.**Because the seed is bad.*";
P_HTM[3914]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, micchādiṭṭhikassa purisapuggalassa micchāsaṅkappassa micchāvācassa micchākammantassa micchāājīvassa micchāvāyāmassa micchāsatissa micchāsamādhissa micchāñāṇissa micchāvimuttissa yañceva kāyakammaṃ yathādiṭṭhi samattaṃ samādinnaṃ yañca vacīkammaṃ …**In the same way, consider a person who has wrong view, thought, speech, action, livelihood, effort, mindfulness, immersion, knowledge, and freedom.*";
P_HTM[3915]="*yañca manokammaṃ yathādiṭṭhi samattaṃ samādinnaṃ yā ca cetanā yā ca patthanā yo ca paṇidhi ye ca saṅkhārā, sabbe te dhammā aniṭṭhāya akantāya amanāpāya ahitāya dukkhāya saṃvattanti.**Whatever bodily, verbal, or mental deeds they undertake in line with that view, their intentions, aims, wishes, and choices all lead to what is unlikable, undesirable, disagreeable, harmful, and suffering.*";
P_HTM[3916]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3917]="*Diṭṭhi hissa, bhikkhave, pāpikā.**Because their view is bad.*";
P_HTM[3918]="*Sammādiṭṭhikassa, bhikkhave, purisapuggalassa sammāsaṅkappassa sammāvācassa sammākammantassa sammāājīvassa sammāvāyāmassa sammāsatissa sammāsamādhissa sammāñāṇissa sammāvimuttissa yañceva kāyakammaṃ yathādiṭṭhi samattaṃ samādinnaṃ yañca vacīkammaṃ yathādiṭṭhi samattaṃ samādinnaṃ yañca manokammaṃ yathādiṭṭhi samattaṃ samādinnaṃ yā ca cetanā yā ca patthanā yo ca paṇidhi ye ca saṅkhārā, sabbe te dhammā iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya sukhāya saṃvattanti.**Consider a person who has right view, thought, speech, action, livelihood, effort, mindfulness, immersion, knowledge, and freedom. Whatever bodily, verbal, or mental deeds they undertake in line with that view, their intentions, aims, wishes, and choices all lead to what is likable, desirable, agreeable, beneficial, and pleasant.*";
P_HTM[3919]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3920]="*Diṭṭhi hissa, bhikkhave, bhaddikā.**Because their view is good.*";
P_HTM[3921]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ucchubījaṃ vā sālibījaṃ vā muddikābījaṃ vā allāya pathaviyā nikkhittaṃ yañca pathavirasaṃ upādiyati yañca āporasaṃ upādiyati sabbaṃ taṃ sātattāya madhurattāya asecanakattāya saṃvattati.**Suppose a seed of sugar cane, fine rice, or grape was planted in moist earth. Whatever nutrients it takes up from the earth and water would lead to its sweet, pleasant, and delicious taste.*";
P_HTM[3922]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3923]="*Bījañhi, bhikkhave, bhaddakaṃ.**Because the seed is good.*";
P_HTM[3924]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sammādiṭṭhikassa … pe … sammāvimuttissa yañceva kāyakammaṃ yathādiṭṭhi samattaṃ samādinnaṃ yañca vacīkammaṃ …**In the same way, consider a person who has right view, thought, speech, action, livelihood, effort, mindfulness, immersion, knowledge, and freedom.*";
P_HTM[3925]="*yañca manokammaṃ yathādiṭṭhi samattaṃ samādinnaṃ yā ca cetanā yā ca patthanā yo ca paṇidhi ye ca saṅkhārā, sabbe te dhammā iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya sukhāya saṃvattanti.**Whatever bodily, verbal, or mental deeds they undertake in line with that view, their intentions, aims, wishes, and choices all lead to what is likable, desirable, agreeable, beneficial, and pleasant.*";
P_HTM[3926]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3927]="*Diṭṭhi hissa, bhikkhave, bhaddikā”ti.**Because their view is good.”*";
P_HTM[3928]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3929]="*5. Vijjāsuttaṃ**Knowledge*";
P_HTM[3930]="*“Avijjā, bhikkhave, pubbaṅgamā akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ samāpattiyā, anvadeva ahirikaṃ anottappaṃ.**“Mendicants, ignorance precedes the attainment of unskillful qualities, with lack of conscience and prudence following along.*";
P_HTM[3931]="*Avijjāgatassa, bhikkhave, aviddasuno micchādiṭṭhi pahoti, micchādiṭṭhikassa micchāsaṅkappo pahoti, micchāsaṅkappassa micchāvācā pahoti, micchāvācassa micchākammanto pahoti, micchākammantassa micchāājīvo pahoti, micchāājīvassa micchāvāyāmo pahoti, micchāvāyāmassa micchāsati pahoti, micchāsatissa micchāsamādhi pahoti, micchāsamādhissa micchāñāṇaṃ pahoti, micchāñāṇissa micchāvimutti pahoti.**An ignoramus, sunk in ignorance, gives rise to wrong view. Wrong view gives rise to wrong thought. Wrong thought gives rise to wrong speech. Wrong speech gives rise to wrong action. Wrong action gives rise to wrong livelihood. Wrong livelihood gives rise to wrong effort. Wrong effort gives rise to wrong mindfulness. Wrong mindfulness gives rise to wrong immersion. Wrong immersion gives rise to wrong knowledge. Wrong knowledge gives rise to wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[3932]="*Vijjā, bhikkhave, pubbaṅgamā kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ samāpattiyā, anvadeva hirottappaṃ.**Knowledge precedes the attainment of skillful qualities, with conscience and prudence following along.*";
P_HTM[3933]="*Vijjāgatassa, bhikkhave, viddasuno sammādiṭṭhi pahoti, sammādiṭṭhikassa sammāsaṅkappo pahoti, sammāsaṅkappassa sammāvācā pahoti, sammāvācassa sammākammanto pahoti, sammākammantassa sammāājīvo pahoti, sammāājīvassa sammāvāyāmo pahoti, sammāvāyāmassa sammāsati pahoti, sammāsatissa sammāsamādhi pahoti, sammāsamādhissa sammāñāṇaṃ pahoti, sammāñāṇissa sammāvimutti pahotī”ti.**A sage, firm in knowledge, gives rise to right view. Right view gives rise to right thought. Right thought gives rise to right speech. Right speech gives rise to right action. Right action gives rise to right livelihood. Right livelihood gives rise to right effort. Right effort gives rise to right mindfulness. Right mindfulness gives rise to right immersion. Right immersion gives rise to right knowledge. Right knowledge gives rise to right freedom.”*";
P_HTM[3934]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3935]="*6. Nijjarasuttaṃ**Wearing Away*";
P_HTM[3936]="*“Dasayimāni, bhikkhave, nijjaravatthūni.**“Mendicants, there are these ten grounds for wearing away.*";
P_HTM[3937]="*Katamāni dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[3938]="*Sammādiṭṭhikassa, bhikkhave, micchādiṭṭhi nijjiṇṇā hoti;**For one of right view, wrong view is worn away.*";
P_HTM[3939]="*ye ca micchādiṭṭhipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa nijjiṇṇā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities that arise because of wrong view are worn away.*";
P_HTM[3940]="*sammādiṭṭhipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti. (1)**And because of right view, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[3941]="*Sammāsaṅkappassa, bhikkhave, micchāsaṅkappo nijjiṇṇo hoti;**For one of right thought, wrong thought is worn away.*";
P_HTM[3942]="*ye ca micchāsaṅkappapaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa nijjiṇṇā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities that arise because of wrong thought are worn away.*";
P_HTM[3943]="*sammāsaṅkappapaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti. (2)**And because of right thought, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[3944]="*Sammāvācassa, bhikkhave, micchāvācā nijjiṇṇā hoti;**For one of right speech, wrong speech is worn away.*";
P_HTM[3945]="*ye ca micchāvācāpaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa nijjiṇṇā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities that arise because of wrong speech are worn away.*";
P_HTM[3946]="*sammāvācāpaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti. (3)**And because of right speech, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[3947]="*Sammākammantassa, bhikkhave, micchākammanto nijjiṇṇo hoti;**For one of right action, wrong action is worn away.*";
P_HTM[3948]="*ye ca micchākammantapaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa nijjiṇṇā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities that arise because of wrong action are worn away.*";
P_HTM[3949]="*sammākammantapaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti. (4)**And because of right action, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[3950]="*Sammāājīvassa, bhikkhave, micchāājīvo nijjiṇṇo hoti;**For one of right livelihood, wrong livelihood is worn away.*";
P_HTM[3951]="*ye ca micchāājīvapaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa nijjiṇṇā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities that arise because of wrong livelihood are worn away.*";
P_HTM[3952]="*sammāājīvapaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti. (5)**And because of right livelihood, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[3953]="*Sammāvāyāmassa, bhikkhave, micchāvāyāmo nijjiṇṇo hoti;**For one of right effort, wrong effort is worn away.*";
P_HTM[3954]="*ye ca micchāvāyāmapaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa nijjiṇṇā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities that arise because of wrong effort are worn away.*";
P_HTM[3955]="*sammāvāyāmapaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti. (6)**And because of right effort, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[3956]="*Sammāsatissa, bhikkhave, micchāsati nijjiṇṇā hoti;**For one of right mindfulness, wrong mindfulness is worn away.*";
P_HTM[3957]="*ye ca micchāsatipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa nijjiṇṇā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities that arise because of wrong mindfulness are worn away.*";
P_HTM[3958]="*sammāsatipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti. (7)**And because of right mindfulness, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[3959]="*Sammāsamādhissa, bhikkhave, micchāsamādhi nijjiṇṇo hoti;**For one of right immersion, wrong immersion is worn away.*";
P_HTM[3960]="*ye ca micchāsamādhipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa nijjiṇṇā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities that arise because of wrong immersion are worn away.*";
P_HTM[3961]="*sammāsamādhipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti. (8)**And because of right immersion, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[3962]="*Sammāñāṇissa, bhikkhave, micchāñāṇaṃ nijjiṇṇaṃ hoti;**For one of right knowledge, wrong knowledge is worn away.*";
P_HTM[3963]="*ye ca micchāñāṇapaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa nijjiṇṇā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities that arise because of wrong knowledge are worn away.*";
P_HTM[3964]="*sammāñāṇapaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti. (9)**And because of right knowledge, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[3965]="*Sammāvimuttissa, bhikkhave, micchāvimutti nijjiṇṇā hoti;**For one of right freedom, wrong freedom is worn away.*";
P_HTM[3966]="*ye ca micchāvimuttipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa nijjiṇṇā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities that arise because of wrong freedom are worn away.*";
P_HTM[3967]="*sammāvimuttipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti. (10)**And because of right freedom, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[3968]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, dasa nijjaravatthūnī”ti.**These are the ten grounds for wearing away.”*";
P_HTM[3969]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3970]="*7. Dhovanasuttaṃ**Washing*";
P_HTM[3971]="*“Atthi, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇesu janapadesu dhovanaṃ nāma.**“Mendicants, there is a country in the south called ‘Washing’.*";
P_HTM[3972]="*Tattha hoti annampi pānampi khajjampi bhojjampi leyyampi peyyampi naccampi gītampi vāditampi.**They have food, drink, snacks, meals, refreshments, and beverages, as well as dancing, singing, and music.*";
P_HTM[3973]="*Atthetaṃ, bhikkhave, dhovanaṃ; ‘netaṃ natthī’ti vadāmi.**There is such a ‘Washing’, I don’t deny it.*";
P_HTM[3974]="*Tañca kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, dhovanaṃ hīnaṃ gammaṃ pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ na nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati.**But that washing is low, crude, ordinary, ignoble, and pointless. It doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[3975]="*Ahañca kho, bhikkhave, ariyaṃ dhovanaṃ desessāmi, yaṃ dhovanaṃ ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati, yaṃ dhovanaṃ āgamma jātidhammā sattā jātiyā parimuccanti, jarādhammā sattā jarāya parimuccanti, maraṇadhammā sattā maraṇena parimuccanti, sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsadhammā sattā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsehi parimuccanti.**I will teach a noble washing that leads solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. Relying on that washing, sentient beings who are liable to rebirth, old age, and death, to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress are freed from all these things.*";
P_HTM[3976]="*Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[3977]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[3978]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[3979]="*“Katamañca taṃ, bhikkhave, ariyaṃ dhovanaṃ, yaṃ dhovanaṃ ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati, yaṃ dhovanaṃ āgamma jātidhammā sattā jātiyā parimuccanti, jarādhammā sattā jarāya parimuccanti, maraṇadhammā sattā maraṇena parimuccanti, sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsadhammā sattā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsehi parimuccanti?**“And what is that noble washing?*";
P_HTM[3980]="*Sammādiṭṭhikassa, bhikkhave, micchādiṭṭhi niddhotā hoti;**For one of right view, wrong view is washed away.*";
P_HTM[3981]="*ye ca micchādiṭṭhipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa niddhotā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities that arise because of wrong view are washed away.*";
P_HTM[3982]="*sammādiṭṭhipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti.**And because of right view, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[3983]="*Sammāsaṅkappassa, bhikkhave, micchāsaṅkappo niddhoto hoti … pe …**For one of right thought, wrong thought is washed away. …*";
P_HTM[3984]="*sammāvācassa, bhikkhave, micchāvācā niddhotā hoti …**For one of right speech, wrong speech is washed away. …*";
P_HTM[3985]="*sammākammantassa, bhikkhave, micchākammanto niddhoto hoti …**For one of right action, wrong action is washed away. …*";
P_HTM[3986]="*sammāājīvassa, bhikkhave, micchāājīvo niddhoto hoti …**For one of right livelihood, wrong livelihood is washed away. …*";
P_HTM[3987]="*sammāvāyāmassa, bhikkhave, micchāvāyāmo niddhoto hoti …**For one of right effort, wrong effort is washed away. …*";
P_HTM[3988]="*sammāsatissa, bhikkhave, micchāsati niddhotā hoti …**For one of right mindfulness, wrong mindfulness is washed away. …*";
P_HTM[3989]="*sammāsamādhissa, bhikkhave, micchāsamādhi niddhoto hoti …**For one of right immersion, wrong immersion is washed away. …*";
P_HTM[3990]="*sammāñāṇissa, bhikkhave, micchāñāṇaṃ niddhotaṃ hoti … pe ….**For one of right knowledge, wrong knowledge is washed away. …*";
P_HTM[3991]="*Sammāvimuttissa, bhikkhave, micchāvimutti niddhotā hoti;**For one of right freedom, wrong freedom is washed away.*";
P_HTM[3992]="*ye ca micchāvimuttipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa niddhotā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities that arise because of wrong freedom are washed away.*";
P_HTM[3993]="*sammāvimuttipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti.**And because of right freedom, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[3994]="*Idaṃ kho taṃ, bhikkhave, ariyaṃ dhovanaṃ ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati, yaṃ dhovanaṃ āgamma jātidhammā sattā jātiyā parimuccanti, jarādhammā sattā jarāya parimuccanti, maraṇadhammā sattā maraṇena parimuccanti, sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsadhammā sattā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsehi parimuccantī”ti.**This is the noble washing that leads solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. Relying on this washing, sentient beings who are liable to rebirth, old age, and death, to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress are freed from all these things.”*";
P_HTM[3995]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3996]="*8. Tikicchakasuttaṃ**Doctors*";
P_HTM[3997]="*“Tikicchakā, bhikkhave, virecanaṃ denti pittasamuṭṭhānānampi ābādhānaṃ paṭighātāya, semhasamuṭṭhānānampi ābādhānaṃ paṭighātāya, vātasamuṭṭhānānampi ābādhānaṃ paṭighātāya.**“Mendicants, doctors prescribe a purgative for eliminating illnesses stemming from disorders of bile, phlegm, and wind.*";
P_HTM[3998]="*Atthetaṃ, bhikkhave, virecanaṃ; ‘netaṃ natthī’ti vadāmi.**There is such a purgative, I don’t deny it.*";
P_HTM[3999]="*Tañca kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, virecanaṃ sampajjatipi vipajjatipi.**But this kind of purgative sometimes works and sometimes fails.*";
P_HTM[4000]="*Ahañca kho, bhikkhave, ariyaṃ virecanaṃ desessāmi, yaṃ virecanaṃ sampajjatiyeva no vipajjati, yaṃ virecanaṃ āgamma jātidhammā sattā jātiyā parimuccanti, jarādhammā sattā jarāya parimuccanti, maraṇadhammā sattā maraṇena parimuccanti, sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsadhammā sattā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsehi parimuccanti.**I will teach a noble purgative that works without fail. Relying on that purgative, sentient beings who are liable to rebirth, old age, and death, to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress are freed from all these things.*";
P_HTM[4001]="*Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[4002]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4003]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4004]="*“Katamañca taṃ, bhikkhave, ariyaṃ virecanaṃ, yaṃ virecanaṃ sampajjatiyeva no vipajjati, yaṃ virecanaṃ āgamma jātidhammā sattā jātiyā parimuccanti, jarādhammā sattā jarāya parimuccanti, maraṇadhammā sattā maraṇena parimuccanti, sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsadhammā sattā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsehi parimuccanti?**“And what is the noble purgative that works without fail?*";
P_HTM[4005]="*Sammādiṭṭhikassa, bhikkhave, micchādiṭṭhi virittā hoti;**For one of right view, wrong view is purged.*";
P_HTM[4006]="*ye ca micchādiṭṭhipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa virittā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong view are purged.*";
P_HTM[4007]="*sammādiṭṭhipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti.**And because of right view, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[4008]="*Sammāsaṅkappassa, bhikkhave, micchāsaṅkappo viritto hoti … pe …**For one of right thought, wrong thought is purged. …*";
P_HTM[4009]="*sammāvācassa, bhikkhave, micchāvācā virittā hoti …**For one of right speech, wrong speech is purged. …*";
P_HTM[4010]="*sammākammantassa, bhikkhave, micchākammanto viritto hoti …**For one of right action, wrong action is purged. …*";
P_HTM[4011]="*sammāājīvassa, bhikkhave, micchāājīvo viritto hoti …**For one of right livelihood, wrong livelihood is purged. …*";
P_HTM[4012]="*sammāvāyāmassa, bhikkhave, micchāvāyāmo viritto hoti …**For one of right effort, wrong effort is purged.*";
P_HTM[4013]="*sammāsatissa, bhikkhave, micchāsati virittā hoti …**For one of right mindfulness, wrong mindfulness is purged. …*";
P_HTM[4014]="*sammāsamādhissa, bhikkhave, micchāsamādhi viritto hoti …**For one of right immersion, wrong immersion is purged. …*";
P_HTM[4015]="*sammāñāṇissa, bhikkhave, micchāñāṇaṃ virittaṃ hoti … pe ….**For one of right knowledge, wrong knowledge is purged. …*";
P_HTM[4016]="*Sammāvimuttissa, bhikkhave, micchāvimutti virittā hoti;**For one of right freedom, wrong freedom is purged.*";
P_HTM[4017]="*ye ca micchāvimuttipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa virittā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong freedom are purged.*";
P_HTM[4018]="*sammāvimuttipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti.**And because of right freedom, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[4019]="*Idaṃ kho taṃ, bhikkhave, ariyaṃ virecanaṃ yaṃ virecanaṃ sampajjatiyeva no vipajjati, yaṃ virecanaṃ āgamma jātidhammā sattā jātiyā parimuccanti … pe … sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsehi parimuccantī”ti.**This is the noble purgative that works without fail. Relying on this purgative, sentient beings who are liable to rebirth, old age, and death, to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress are freed from all these things.”*";
P_HTM[4020]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4021]="*9. Vamanasuttaṃ**Emetic*";
P_HTM[4022]="*“Tikicchakā, bhikkhave, vamanaṃ denti pittasamuṭṭhānānampi ābādhānaṃ paṭighātāya, semhasamuṭṭhānānampi ābādhānaṃ paṭighātāya, vātasamuṭṭhānānampi ābādhānaṃ paṭighātāya.**“Mendicants, doctors prescribe an emetic for eliminating illnesses stemming from disorders of bile, phlegm, and wind.*";
P_HTM[4023]="*Atthetaṃ, bhikkhave, vamanaṃ; ‘netaṃ natthī’ti vadāmi.**There is such an emetic, I don’t deny it.*";
P_HTM[4024]="*Tañca kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, vamanaṃ sampajjatipi vipajjatipi.**But this kind of emetic sometimes works and sometimes fails.*";
P_HTM[4025]="*Ahañca kho, bhikkhave, ariyaṃ vamanaṃ desessāmi, yaṃ vamanaṃ sampajjatiyeva no vipajjati, yaṃ vamanaṃ āgamma jātidhammā sattā jātiyā parimuccanti, jarādhammā sattā jarāya parimuccanti, maraṇadhammā sattā maraṇena parimuccanti, sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsadhammā sattā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsehi parimuccanti.**I will teach a noble emetic that works without fail. Relying on that emetic, sentient beings who are liable to rebirth, old age, and death, to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress are freed from all these things.*";
P_HTM[4026]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe ….**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak. …*";
P_HTM[4027]="*Katamañca taṃ, bhikkhave, ariyaṃ vamanaṃ, yaṃ vamanaṃ sampajjatiyeva no vipajjati, yaṃ vamanaṃ āgamma jātidhammā sattā jātiyā parimuccanti … pe … sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsadhammā sattā sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsehi parimuccanti?**And what is that noble emetic that works without fail?*";
P_HTM[4028]="*Sammādiṭṭhikassa, bhikkhave, micchādiṭṭhi vantā hoti;**For one of right view, wrong view is vomited up.*";
P_HTM[4029]="*ye ca micchādiṭṭhipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa vantā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong view are vomited up.*";
P_HTM[4030]="*sammādiṭṭhipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti.**And because of right view, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[4031]="*Sammāsaṅkappassa, bhikkhave, micchāsaṅkappo vanto hoti … pe …**For one of right thought, wrong thought is vomited up. …*";
P_HTM[4032]="*sammāvācassa, bhikkhave, micchāvācā vantā hoti …**For one of right speech, wrong speech is vomited up. …*";
P_HTM[4033]="*sammākammantassa, bhikkhave, micchākammanto vanto hoti …**For one of right action, wrong action is vomited up. …*";
P_HTM[4034]="*sammāājīvassa, bhikkhave, micchāājīvo vanto hoti …**For one of right livelihood, wrong livelihood is vomited up. …*";
P_HTM[4035]="*sammāvāyāmassa, bhikkhave, micchāvāyāmo vanto hoti …**For one of right effort, wrong effort is vomited up. …*";
P_HTM[4036]="*sammāsatissa, bhikkhave, micchāsati vantā hoti …**For one of right mindfulness, wrong mindfulness is vomited up. …*";
P_HTM[4037]="*sammāsamādhissa, bhikkhave, micchāsamādhi vanto hoti …**For one of right immersion, wrong immersion is vomited up. …*";
P_HTM[4038]="*sammāñāṇissa, bhikkhave, micchāñāṇaṃ vantaṃ hoti … pe ….**For one of right knowledge, wrong knowledge is vomited up. …*";
P_HTM[4039]="*Sammāvimuttissa, bhikkhave, micchāvimutti vantā hoti;**For one of right freedom, wrong freedom is vomited up.*";
P_HTM[4040]="*ye ca micchāvimuttipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa vantā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong freedom are vomited up.*";
P_HTM[4041]="*sammāvimuttipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti.**And because of right freedom, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[4042]="*Idaṃ kho taṃ, bhikkhave, ariyaṃ vamanaṃ yaṃ vamanaṃ sampajjatiyeva no vipajjati, yaṃ vamanaṃ āgamma jātidhammā sattā jātiyā parimuccanti … pe … sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsehi parimuccantī”ti.**This is the noble emetic that works without fail. Relying on this emetic, sentient beings who are liable to rebirth, old age, and death, to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress are freed from all these things.”*";
P_HTM[4043]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4044]="*10. Niddhamanīyasuttaṃ**Blown Away*";
P_HTM[4045]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, niddhamanīyā dhammā.**“Mendicants, these ten qualities should be blown away.*";
P_HTM[4046]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[4047]="*Sammādiṭṭhikassa, bhikkhave, micchādiṭṭhi niddhantā hoti;**For one of right view, wrong view is blown away.*";
P_HTM[4048]="*ye ca micchādiṭṭhipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa niddhantā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong view are blown away.*";
P_HTM[4049]="*sammādiṭṭhipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti.**And because of right view, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[4050]="*Sammāsaṅkappassa, bhikkhave, micchāsaṅkappo niddhanto hoti … pe …**For one of right thought, wrong thought is blown away. …*";
P_HTM[4051]="*sammāvācassa bhikkhave, micchāvācā niddhantā hoti …**For one of right speech, wrong speech is blown away. …*";
P_HTM[4052]="*sammākammantassa, bhikkhave, micchākammanto niddhanto hoti …**For one of right action, wrong action is blown away. …*";
P_HTM[4053]="*sammāājīvassa, bhikkhave, micchāājīvo niddhanto hoti …**For one of right livelihood, wrong livelihood is blown away. …*";
P_HTM[4054]="*sammāvāyāmassa, bhikkhave, micchāvāyāmo niddhanto hoti …**For one of right effort, wrong effort is blown away. …*";
P_HTM[4055]="*sammāsatissa, bhikkhave, micchāsati niddhantā hoti …**For one of right mindfulness, wrong mindfulness is blown away. …*";
P_HTM[4056]="*sammāsamādhissa, bhikkhave, micchāsamādhi niddhanto hoti …**For one of right immersion, wrong immersion is blown away. …*";
P_HTM[4057]="*sammāñāṇissa, bhikkhave, micchāñāṇaṃ niddhantaṃ hoti ….**For one of right knowledge, wrong knowledge is blown away. …*";
P_HTM[4058]="*Sammāvimuttissa, bhikkhave, micchāvimutti niddhantā hoti;**For one of right freedom, wrong freedom is blown away.*";
P_HTM[4059]="*ye ca micchāvimuttipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti te cassa niddhantā honti;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong freedom are blown away.*";
P_HTM[4060]="*sammāvimuttipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti.**And because of right freedom, many skillful qualities are fully developed.*";
P_HTM[4061]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa niddhamanīyā dhammā”ti.**These are the ten qualities that should be blown away.”*";
P_HTM[4062]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4063]="*11. Paṭhamaasekhasuttaṃ**An Adept (1st)*";
P_HTM[4064]="*Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[4065]="*“‘Asekho asekho’ti, bhante, vuccati.**“Sir, they speak of this person called ‘an adept’.*";
P_HTM[4066]="*Kittāvatā bhante, bhikkhu asekho hotī”ti?**How is an adept mendicant defined?”*";
P_HTM[4067]="*“Idha, bhikkhu, bhikkhu asekhāya sammādiṭṭhiyā samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammāsaṅkappena samannāgato hoti, asekhāya sammāvācāya samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammākammantena samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammāājīvena samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammāvāyāmena samannāgato hoti, asekhāya sammāsatiyā samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammāsamādhinā samannāgato hoti, asekhena sammāñāṇena samannāgato hoti, asekhāya sammāvimuttiyā samannāgato hoti.**“Mendicant, it’s when a mendicant has an adept’s right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4068]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, bhikkhu asekho hotī”ti.**That’s how a mendicant is an adept.”*";
P_HTM[4069]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4070]="*12. Dutiyaasekhasuttaṃ**An Adept (2nd)*";
P_HTM[4071]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, asekhiyā dhammā.**“Mendicants, there are ten qualities of an adept.*";
P_HTM[4072]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[4073]="*Asekhā sammādiṭṭhi, asekho sammāsaṅkappo, asekhā sammāvācā, asekho sammākammanto, asekho sammāājīvo, asekho sammāvāyāmo, asekhā sammāsati, asekho sammāsamādhi, asekhaṃ sammāñāṇaṃ, asekhā sammāvimutti—**An adept's right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4074]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa asekhiyā dhammā”ti.**These are the ten qualities of an adept.”*";
P_HTM[4075]="*Dvādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4076]="*Samaṇasaññāvaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[4077]="*Saññā bojjhaṅgā micchattaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[4078]="*bījaṃ vijjāya nijjaraṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4079]="*Dhovanaṃ tikicchā vamanaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[4080]="*niddhamanaṃ dve asekhāti.* **";
P_HTM[4081]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**The Ceremony of Descent*";
P_HTM[4082]="*1. Paṭhamaadhammasuttaṃ**Bad Principles (1st)*";
P_HTM[4083]="*“Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo anattho ca;**“Mendicants, you should know bad principles with bad results.*";
P_HTM[4084]="*dhammo ca veditabbo attho ca.**And you should know good principles with good results.*";
P_HTM[4085]="*Adhammañca viditvā anatthañca, dhammañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabbaṃ.**Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results.*";
P_HTM[4086]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, adhammo ca anattho ca?**And what are bad principles with bad results?*";
P_HTM[4087]="*Micchādiṭṭhi, micchāsaṅkappo, micchāvācā, micchākammanto, micchāājīvo, micchāvāyāmo, micchāsati, micchāsamādhi, micchāñāṇaṃ, micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4088]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhammo ca anattho ca.**These are called bad principles with bad results.*";
P_HTM[4089]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, dhammo ca attho ca?**And what are good principles with good results?*";
P_HTM[4090]="*Sammādiṭṭhi, sammāsaṅkappo, sammāvācā, sammākammanto, sammāājīvo, sammāvāyāmo, sammāsati, sammāsamādhi, sammāñāṇaṃ, sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4091]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhammo ca attho ca.**These are called good principles with good results.*";
P_HTM[4092]="*‘Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo anattho ca;**‘You should know bad principles with bad results.*";
P_HTM[4093]="*dhammo ca veditabbo attho ca.**And you should know good principles with good results.*";
P_HTM[4094]="*Adhammañca viditvā anatthañca, dhammañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti,**Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results.’*";
P_HTM[4095]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttan”ti.**That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.”*";
P_HTM[4096]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4097]="*2. Dutiyaadhammasuttaṃ**Bad Principles (2nd)*";
P_HTM[4098]="*“Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo dhammo ca;**“Mendicants, you should know bad principles and good principles.*";
P_HTM[4099]="*anattho ca veditabbo attho ca.**And you should know bad results and good results.*";
P_HTM[4100]="*Adhammañca viditvā dhammañca, anatthañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabbaṃ.**Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results.*";
P_HTM[4101]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, adhammo, katamo ca dhammo, katamo ca anattho, katamo ca attho?**So what are bad principles? What are good principles? What are bad results? And what are good results?*";
P_HTM[4102]="*Micchādiṭṭhi, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong view is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4103]="*sammādiṭṭhi dhammo;**Right view is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[4104]="*ye ca micchādiṭṭhipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong view are bad results.*";
P_HTM[4105]="*sammādiṭṭhipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho. (1)**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of right view are good results.*";
P_HTM[4106]="*Micchāsaṅkappo, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong thought is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4107]="*sammāsaṅkappo dhammo;**Right thought is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[4108]="*ye ca micchāsaṅkappapaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong thought are bad results.*";
P_HTM[4109]="*sammāsaṅkappapaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho. (2)**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of right thought are good results.*";
P_HTM[4110]="*Micchāvācā, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong speech is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4111]="*sammāvācā dhammo;**Right speech is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[4112]="*ye ca micchāvācāpaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong speech are bad results.*";
P_HTM[4113]="*sammāvācāpaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho. (3)**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of right speech are good results.*";
P_HTM[4114]="*Micchākammanto, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong action is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4115]="*sammākammanto dhammo;**Right action is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[4116]="*ye ca micchākammantapaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong action are bad results.*";
P_HTM[4117]="*sammākammantapaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho. (4)**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of right action are good results.*";
P_HTM[4118]="*Micchāājīvo, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong livelihood is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4119]="*sammāājīvo dhammo;**Right livelihood is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[4120]="*ye ca micchāājīvapaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong livelihood are bad results.*";
P_HTM[4121]="*sammāājīvapaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho. (5)**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of right livelihood are good results.*";
P_HTM[4122]="*Micchāvāyāmo, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong effort is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4123]="*sammāvāyāmo dhammo;**Right effort is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[4124]="*ye ca micchāvāyāmapaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong effort are bad results.*";
P_HTM[4125]="*sammāvāyāmapaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho. (6)**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of right effort are good results.*";
P_HTM[4126]="*Micchāsati, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong mindfulness is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4127]="*sammāsati dhammo;**Right mindfulness is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[4128]="*ye ca micchāsatipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong mindfulness are bad results.*";
P_HTM[4129]="*sammāsatipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho. (7)**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of right mindfulness are good results.*";
P_HTM[4130]="*Micchāsamādhi, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong immersion is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4131]="*sammāsamādhi dhammo;**Right immersion is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[4132]="*ye ca micchāsamādhipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong immersion are bad results.*";
P_HTM[4133]="*sammāsamādhipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho. (8)**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of right immersion are good results.*";
P_HTM[4134]="*Micchāñāṇaṃ, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong knowledge is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4135]="*sammāñāṇaṃ dhammo;**Right knowledge is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[4136]="*ye ca micchāñāṇapaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong knowledge are bad results.*";
P_HTM[4137]="*sammāñāṇapaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho. (9)**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of right knowledge are good results.*";
P_HTM[4138]="*Micchāvimutti, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong freedom is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4139]="*sammāvimutti dhammo;**Right freedom is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[4140]="*ye ca micchāvimuttipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong freedom are bad results.*";
P_HTM[4141]="*sammāvimuttipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho. (10)**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of right freedom are good results.*";
P_HTM[4142]="*‘Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo dhammo ca;**‘You should know bad principles and good principles.*";
P_HTM[4143]="*anattho ca veditabbo attho ca.**And you should know bad results and good results.*";
P_HTM[4144]="*Adhammañca viditvā dhammañca, anatthañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti,**Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results.’*";
P_HTM[4145]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttan”ti.**That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.”*";
P_HTM[4146]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4147]="*3. Tatiyaadhammasuttaṃ**Bad Principles (3rd)*";
P_HTM[4148]="*“Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo dhammo ca;**“Mendicants, you should know bad principles and good principles.*";
P_HTM[4149]="*anattho ca veditabbo attho ca.**And you should know bad results and good results.*";
P_HTM[4150]="*Adhammañca viditvā dhammañca, anatthañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabban”ti.**Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results.”*";
P_HTM[4151]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[4152]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ pāvisi.**When he had spoken, the Holy One got up from his seat and entered his dwelling.*";
P_HTM[4153]="*Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:**Soon after the Buddha left, those mendicants considered,*";
P_HTM[4154]="*“idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:**“The Buddha gave this brief passage for recitation, then entered his dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail.*";
P_HTM[4155]="*‘adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo dhammo ca;* **";
P_HTM[4156]="*anattho ca veditabbo attho ca.* **";
P_HTM[4157]="*Adhammañca viditvā dhammañca, anatthañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4158]="*Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā”ti?**Who can explain in detail the meaning of this brief passage for recitation given by the Buddha?”*";
P_HTM[4159]="*Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi:**Then they considered,*";
P_HTM[4160]="*“ayaṃ kho āyasmā ānando satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ.**“This Venerable Ānanda is praised by the Buddha and esteemed by his sensible spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[4161]="*Pahoti cāyasmā ānando imassa bhagavatā saṃkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.**He is capable of explaining in detail the meaning of this brief passage for recitation given by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4162]="*Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāma.**Let’s go to him, and ask him about this matter.*";
P_HTM[4163]="*Yathā no āyasmā ānando byākarissati tathā naṃ dhāressāmā”ti.**As he answers, so we’ll remember it.”*";
P_HTM[4164]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu.**Then those mendicants went to Ānanda, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4165]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavocuṃ:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one side. They told him what had happened, and said,*";
P_HTM[4166]="*“Idaṃ kho no, āvuso ānanda, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:* **";
P_HTM[4167]="*‘adhammo ca … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4168]="*tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4169]="*Tesaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[4170]="*‘idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho—* **";
P_HTM[4171]="*adhammo ca … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4172]="*tathā paṭipajjitabbanti.* **";
P_HTM[4173]="*Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā’ti?* **";
P_HTM[4174]="*Tesaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[4175]="*‘ayaṃ kho āyasmā ānando satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4176]="*Pahoti cāyasmā ānando imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4177]="*Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāma.* **";
P_HTM[4178]="*Yathā no āyasmā ānando byākarissati tathā naṃ dhāressāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4179]="*Vibhajatu āyasmā ānando”ti.**“May Venerable Ānanda please explain this.”*";
P_HTM[4180]="*“Seyyathāpi, āvuso, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva mūlaṃ atikkamma khandhaṃ sākhāpalāse sāraṃ pariyesitabbaṃ maññeyya;**“Reverends, suppose there was a person in need of heartwood. And while wandering in search of heartwood he’d come across a large tree standing with heartwood. But he’d pass over the roots and trunk, imagining that the heartwood should be sought in the branches and leaves.*";
P_HTM[4181]="*evaṃsampadamidaṃ āyasmantānaṃ satthari sammukhībhūte taṃ bhagavantaṃ atisitvā amhe etamatthaṃ paṭipucchitabbaṃ maññatha.**Such is the consequence for the venerables. Though you were face to face with the Buddha, you passed him by, imagining that you should ask me about this matter.*";
P_HTM[4182]="*So hāvuso, bhagavā jānaṃ jānāti passaṃ passati, cakkhubhūto ñāṇabhūto dhammabhūto brahmabhūto vattā pavattā atthassa ninnetā amatassa dātā dhammassāmī tathāgato.**For he is the Buddha, who knows and sees. He is vision, he is knowledge, he is the truth, he is holiness. He is the teacher, the proclaimer, the elucidator of meaning, the bestower of the deathless, the lord of truth, the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[4183]="*So ceva panetassa kālo ahosi yaṃ tumhe bhagavantaṃyeva upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyātha.**That was the time to approach the Buddha and ask about this matter.*";
P_HTM[4184]="*Yathā vo bhagavā byākareyya tathā naṃ dhāreyyāthā”ti.**You should have remembered it in line with the Buddha’s answer.”*";
P_HTM[4185]="*“Addhāvuso ānanda, bhagavā jānaṃ jānāti passaṃ passati cakkhubhūto ñāṇabhūto dhammabhūto brahmabhūto vattā pavattā atthassa ninnetā amatassa dātā dhammassāmī tathāgato.**“Certainly he is the Buddha, who knows and sees. He is vision, he is knowledge, he is the truth, he is holiness. He is the teacher, the proclaimer, the elucidator of meaning, the bestower of the deathless, the lord of truth, the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[4186]="*So ceva panetassa kālo ahosi yaṃ mayaṃ bhagavantaṃyeva upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāma,**That was the time to approach the Buddha and ask about this matter.*";
P_HTM[4187]="*yathā no bhagavā byākareyya tathā naṃ dhāreyyāma.**We should have remembered it in line with the Buddha’s answer.*";
P_HTM[4188]="*Api cāyasmā ānando satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ.**Still, Venerable Ānanda is praised by the Buddha and esteemed by his sensible spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[4189]="*Pahoti cāyasmā ānando imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.**You are capable of explaining in detail the meaning of this brief passage for recitation given by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4190]="*Vibhajatāyasmā ānando agaruṃ katvā”ti.**Please explain this, if it’s no trouble.”*";
P_HTM[4191]="*“Tenahāvuso, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Then listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[4192]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4193]="*Athāyasmā ānando etadavoca:**Ānanda said this:*";
P_HTM[4194]="*“Yaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:**“Reverends, the Buddha gave this brief passage for recitation, then entered his dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail:*";
P_HTM[4195]="*‘adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo dhammo ca;**‘You should know bad principles and good principles.*";
P_HTM[4196]="*anattho ca veditabbo attho ca.**And you should know bad results and good results.*";
P_HTM[4197]="*Adhammañca viditvā dhammañca, anatthañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti.**Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results.’*";
P_HTM[4198]="*Katamo cāvuso, adhammo, katamo ca dhammo, katamo ca anattho, katamo ca attho?**So what are bad principles? What are good principles? What are bad results? And what are good results?*";
P_HTM[4199]="*Micchādiṭṭhi, āvuso, adhammo;**Wrong view is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4200]="*sammādiṭṭhi dhammo;**Right view is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[4201]="*ye ca micchādiṭṭhipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong view are bad results.*";
P_HTM[4202]="*sammādiṭṭhipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho.**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of right view are good results.*";
P_HTM[4203]="*Micchāsaṅkappo, āvuso, adhammo;**Wrong thought is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4204]="*sammāsaṅkappo dhammo …**Right thought is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[4205]="*micchāvācā, āvuso, adhammo;**Wrong speech is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4206]="*sammāvācā dhammo …**Right speech is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[4207]="*micchākammanto, āvuso, adhammo;**Wrong action is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4208]="*sammākammanto dhammo …**Right action is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[4209]="*micchāājīvo, āvuso, adhammo;**Wrong livelihood is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4210]="*sammāājīvo dhammo …**Right livelihood is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[4211]="*micchāvāyāmo, āvuso, adhammo;**Wrong effort is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4212]="*sammāvāyāmo dhammo …**Right effort is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[4213]="*micchāsati, āvuso, adhammo;**Wrong mindfulness is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4214]="*sammāsati dhammo …**Right mindfulness is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[4215]="*micchāsamādhi, āvuso, adhammo;**Wrong immersion is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4216]="*sammāsamādhi dhammo …**Right immersion is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[4217]="*micchāñāṇaṃ, āvuso, adhammo;**Wrong knowledge is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4218]="*sammāñāṇaṃ dhammo ….**Right knowledge is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[4219]="*Micchāvimutti, āvuso, adhammo;**Wrong freedom is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4220]="*sammāvimutti dhammo;**Right freedom is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[4221]="*ye ca micchāvimuttipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong freedom are bad results.*";
P_HTM[4222]="*sammāvimuttipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho.**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of right freedom are good results.*";
P_HTM[4223]="*Ayaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṃkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:**The Buddha gave this brief passage for recitation, then entered his dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail:*";
P_HTM[4224]="*‘adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo dhammo ca … pe …**‘You should know bad principles and good principles …*";
P_HTM[4225]="*tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti, imassa kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā saṃkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa evaṃ vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmi.**and practice accordingly.’ And this is how I understand the detailed meaning of this passage for recitation.*";
P_HTM[4226]="*Ākaṅkhamānā ca pana tumhe, āvuso, bhagavantaṃyeva upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyātha.**If you wish, you may go to the Buddha and ask him about this.*";
P_HTM[4227]="*Yathā vo bhagavā byākaroti tathā naṃ dhāreyyāthā”ti.**You should remember it in line with the Buddha’s answer.”*";
P_HTM[4228]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**“Yes, reverend,” said those mendicants, approving and agreeing with what Ānanda said. Then they rose from their seats and went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. Then they said:*";
P_HTM[4229]="*“Yaṃ kho no bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:* **";
P_HTM[4230]="*‘adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4231]="*tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4232]="*Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[4233]="*‘idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho—* **";
P_HTM[4234]="*adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4235]="*tathā paṭipajjitabbanti.* **";
P_HTM[4236]="*Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā’ti?* **";
P_HTM[4237]="*Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[4238]="*‘ayaṃ kho āyasmā ānando satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4239]="*Pahoti cāyasmā ānando imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4240]="*Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāma.* **";
P_HTM[4241]="*Yathā no āyasmā ānando byākarissati tathā naṃ dhāressāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4242]="*Atha kho mayaṃ, bhante, yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkamimhā; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etamatthaṃ apucchimhā.**“Sir, we went to Ānanda and asked him about this matter.*";
P_HTM[4243]="*Tesaṃ no, bhante, āyasmatā ānandena imehi ākārehi imehi padehi imehi byañjanehi attho suvibhatto”ti.**And Ānanda clearly explained the meaning to us in this manner, with these words and phrases.”*";
P_HTM[4244]="*“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhave.**“Good, good, mendicants!*";
P_HTM[4245]="*Paṇḍito, bhikkhave, ānando.**Ānanda is astute,*";
P_HTM[4246]="*Mahāpañño, bhikkhave, ānando.**he has great wisdom.*";
P_HTM[4247]="*Mañcepi tumhe, bhikkhave, upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyātha, ahampi cetaṃ evamevaṃ byākareyyaṃ yathā taṃ ānandena byākataṃ.**If you came to me and asked this question, I would answer it in exactly the same way as Ānanda.*";
P_HTM[4248]="*Eso ceva tassa attho evañca naṃ dhāreyyāthā”ti.**That is what it means, and that’s how you should remember it.”*";
P_HTM[4249]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4250]="*4. Ajitasuttaṃ**With Ajita*";
P_HTM[4251]="*Atha kho ajito paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the wanderer Ajita went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4252]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho ajito paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4253]="*“Amhākaṃ, bho gotama, paṇḍito nāma sabrahmacārī.**“Master Gotama, we have a spiritual companion called ‘The Philosopher’.*";
P_HTM[4254]="*Tena pañcamattāni cittaṭṭhānasatāni cintitāni, yehi aññatitthiyā upāraddhāva jānanti upāraddhasmā”ti.**He has worked out around five hundred arguments by which followers of other paths will know when they’ve been refuted.”*";
P_HTM[4255]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[4256]="*“dhāretha no tumhe, bhikkhave, paṇḍitavatthūnī”ti?**“Mendicants, do you remember this philosopher’s points?”*";
P_HTM[4257]="*“Etassa, bhagavā, kālo etassa, sugata, kālo**“Now is the time, Blessed One! Now is the time, Holy One!*";
P_HTM[4258]="*yaṃ bhagavā bhāseyya, bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti.**Let the Buddha speak and the mendicants will remember it.”*";
P_HTM[4259]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, mendicants, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[4260]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4261]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4262]="*“Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco adhammikena vādena adhammikaṃ vādaṃ abhiniggaṇhāti abhinippīḷeti, tena ca adhammikaṃ parisaṃ rañjeti.**“Mendicants, take a certain person who rebuts and quashes unprincipled statements with unprincipled statements. This delights an unprincipled assembly,*";
P_HTM[4263]="*Tena sā adhammikā parisā uccāsaddamahāsaddā hoti:**who make a dreadful racket:*";
P_HTM[4264]="*‘paṇḍito vata bho, paṇḍito vata bho’ti.**‘He’s a true philosopher! He’s a true philosopher!’*";
P_HTM[4265]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco adhammikena vādena dhammikaṃ vādaṃ abhiniggaṇhāti abhinippīḷeti, tena ca adhammikaṃ parisaṃ rañjeti.**Another person rebuts and quashes principled statements with unprincipled statements. This delights an unprincipled assembly,*";
P_HTM[4266]="*Tena sā adhammikā parisā uccāsaddamahāsaddā hoti:**who make a dreadful racket:*";
P_HTM[4267]="*‘paṇḍito vata bho, paṇḍito vata bho’ti.**‘He’s a true philosopher! He’s a true philosopher!’*";
P_HTM[4268]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco adhammikena vādena dhammikañca vādaṃ adhammikañca vādaṃ abhiniggaṇhāti abhinippīḷeti, tena ca adhammikaṃ parisaṃ rañjeti.**Another person rebuts and quashes principled and unprincipled statements with unprincipled statements. This delights an unprincipled assembly,*";
P_HTM[4269]="*Tena sā adhammikā parisā uccāsaddamahāsaddā hoti:**who make a dreadful racket:*";
P_HTM[4270]="*‘paṇḍito vata bho, paṇḍito vata bho’ti.**‘He’s a true philosopher! He’s a true philosopher!’*";
P_HTM[4271]="*Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo dhammo ca;**Mendicants, you should know bad principles and good principles.*";
P_HTM[4272]="*anattho ca veditabbo attho ca.**And you should know bad results and good results.*";
P_HTM[4273]="*Adhammañca viditvā dhammañca, anatthañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabbaṃ.**Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results.*";
P_HTM[4274]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, adhammo, katamo ca dhammo, katamo ca anattho, katamo ca attho?**So what are bad principles? What are good principles? What are bad results? And what are good results?*";
P_HTM[4275]="*Micchādiṭṭhi, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong view is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4276]="*sammādiṭṭhi dhammo;**Right view is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[4277]="*ye ca micchādiṭṭhipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong view are bad results.*";
P_HTM[4278]="*sammādiṭṭhipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho.**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of right view are good results.*";
P_HTM[4279]="*Micchāsaṅkappo, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong thought is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4280]="*sammāsaṅkappo dhammo …**Right thought is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[4281]="*micchāvācā, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong speech is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4282]="*sammāvācā dhammo …**Right speech is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[4283]="*micchākammanto, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong action is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4284]="*sammākammanto dhammo …**Right action is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[4285]="*micchāājīvo, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong livelihood is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4286]="*sammāājīvo dhammo …**Right livelihood is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[4287]="*micchāvāyāmo, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong effort is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4288]="*sammāvāyāmo dhammo …**Right effort is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[4289]="*micchāsati, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong mindfulness is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4290]="*sammāsati dhammo …**Right mindfulness is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[4291]="*micchāsamādhi, bhikkhave adhammo;**Wrong immersion is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4292]="*sammāsamādhi dhammo …**Right immersion is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[4293]="*micchāñāṇaṃ, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong knowledge is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4294]="*sammāñāṇaṃ dhammo.**Right knowledge is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[4295]="*Micchāvimutti, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong freedom is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[4296]="*sammāvimutti dhammo;**Right freedom is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[4297]="*ye ca micchāvimuttipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong freedom are bad results.*";
P_HTM[4298]="*sammāvimuttipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho.**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of right freedom are good results.*";
P_HTM[4299]="*‘Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo dhammo ca;**‘You should know bad principles and good principles.*";
P_HTM[4300]="*anattho ca veditabbo attho ca.**And you should know bad results and good results.*";
P_HTM[4301]="*Adhammañca viditvā dhammañca, anatthañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti,**Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results.’*";
P_HTM[4302]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttan”ti.**That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.”*";
P_HTM[4303]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4304]="*5. Saṅgāravasuttaṃ**With Saṅgārava*";
P_HTM[4305]="*Atha kho saṅgāravo brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Saṅgārava the brahmin went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4306]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho saṅgāravo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[4307]="*“kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, orimaṃ tīraṃ, kiṃ pārimaṃ tīran”ti?**“Master Gotama, what is the near shore? And what is the far shore?”*";
P_HTM[4308]="*“Micchādiṭṭhi kho, brāhmaṇa, orimaṃ tīraṃ, sammādiṭṭhi pārimaṃ tīraṃ;**“Wrong view is the near shore, brahmin, and right view is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4309]="*micchāsaṅkappo orimaṃ tīraṃ, sammāsaṅkappo pārimaṃ tīraṃ;**Wrong thought is the near shore, and right thought is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4310]="*micchāvācā orimaṃ tīraṃ, sammāvācā pārimaṃ tīraṃ;**Wrong speech is the near shore, and right speech is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4311]="*micchākammanto orimaṃ tīraṃ, sammākammanto pārimaṃ tīraṃ;**Wrong action is the near shore, and right action is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4312]="*micchāājīvo orimaṃ tīraṃ, sammāājīvo pārimaṃ tīraṃ;**Wrong livelihood is the near shore, and right livelihood is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4313]="*micchāvāyāmo orimaṃ tīraṃ, sammāvāyāmo pārimaṃ tīraṃ;**Wrong effort is the near shore, and right effort is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4314]="*micchāsati orimaṃ tīraṃ, sammāsati pārimaṃ tīraṃ;**Wrong mindfulness is the near shore, and right mindfulness is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4315]="*micchāsamādhi orimaṃ tīraṃ, sammāsamādhi pārimaṃ tīraṃ;**Wrong immersion is the near shore, and right immersion is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4316]="*micchāñāṇaṃ orimaṃ tīraṃ, sammāñāṇaṃ pārimaṃ tīraṃ;**Wrong knowledge is the near shore, and right knowledge is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4317]="*micchāvimutti orimaṃ tīraṃ, sammāvimutti pārimaṃ tīranti.**Wrong freedom is the near shore, and right freedom is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4318]="*Idaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, orimaṃ tīraṃ, idaṃ pārimaṃ tīranti.**This is the near shore, and this is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4319]="*Appakā te manussesu,**Few are those among humans*";
P_HTM[4320]="*ye janā pāragāmino;**who cross to the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4321]="*Athāyaṃ itarā pajā,**The rest just run*";
P_HTM[4322]="*tīramevānudhāvati.**around on the near shore.*";
P_HTM[4323]="*Ye ca kho sammadakkhāte,**When the teaching is well explained,*";
P_HTM[4324]="*dhamme dhammānuvattino;**those who practice accordingly*";
P_HTM[4325]="*Te janā pāramessanti,**are the ones who will cross over*";
P_HTM[4326]="*maccudheyyaṃ suduttaraṃ.**Death’s domain so hard to pass.*";
P_HTM[4327]="*Kaṇhaṃ dhammaṃ vippahāya,**Rid of dark qualities,*";
P_HTM[4328]="*Sukkaṃ bhāvetha paṇḍito;**an astute person should develop the bright.*";
P_HTM[4329]="*Okā anokamāgamma,**Leaving home behind*";
P_HTM[4330]="*Viveke yattha dūramaṃ.**for the seclusion so hard to enjoy,*";
P_HTM[4331]="*Tatrābhiratimiccheyya,**you should try to find delight there,*";
P_HTM[4332]="*hitvā kāme akiñcano;**having left behind sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[4333]="*Pariyodapeyya attānaṃ,**With no possessions, an astute person*";
P_HTM[4334]="*cittaklesehi paṇḍito.**should cleanse themselves of mental corruptions.*";
P_HTM[4335]="*Yesaṃ sambodhiyaṅgesu,**And those whose minds are rightly developed*";
P_HTM[4336]="*sammā cittaṃ subhāvitaṃ;**in the awakening factors;*";
P_HTM[4337]="*Ādānapaṭinissagge,**letting go of attachments,*";
P_HTM[4338]="*anupādāya ye ratā;**they delight in not grasping.*";
P_HTM[4339]="*Khīṇāsavā jutimanto,**With defilements ended, brilliant,*";
P_HTM[4340]="*te loke parinibbutā”ti.**they are extinguished in this world.”*";
P_HTM[4341]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4342]="*6. Orimatīrasuttaṃ**The Near Shore*";
P_HTM[4343]="*“Orimañca, bhikkhave, tīraṃ desessāmi pārimañca tīraṃ.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the near shore and the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4344]="*Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[4345]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4346]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4347]="*“Katamañca, bhikkhave, orimaṃ tīraṃ, katamañca pārimaṃ tīraṃ?**“And what, mendicants, is the near shore? What is the far shore?*";
P_HTM[4348]="*Micchādiṭṭhi orimaṃ tīraṃ, sammādiṭṭhi pārimaṃ tīraṃ … pe …**Wrong view is the near shore, and right view is the far shore. …*";
P_HTM[4349]="*micchāvimutti orimaṃ tīraṃ, sammāvimutti pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Wrong freedom is the near shore, and right freedom is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4350]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, orimaṃ tīraṃ, idaṃ pārimaṃ tīranti.**This is the near shore, and this is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4351]="*Appakā te manussesu,**Few are those among humans*";
P_HTM[4352]="*ye janā pāragāmino;**who cross to the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4353]="*Athāyaṃ itarā pajā,**The rest just run*";
P_HTM[4354]="*tīramevānudhāvati.**around on the near shore.*";
P_HTM[4355]="*Ye ca kho sammadakkhāte,**When the teaching is well explained,*";
P_HTM[4356]="*dhamme dhammānuvattino;**those who practice accordingly*";
P_HTM[4357]="*Te janā pāramessanti,**are the ones who will cross over*";
P_HTM[4358]="*maccudheyyaṃ suduttaraṃ.**Death’s domain so hard to pass.*";
P_HTM[4359]="*Kaṇhaṃ dhammaṃ vippahāya,**Rid of dark qualities,*";
P_HTM[4360]="*sukkaṃ bhāvetha paṇḍito;**an astute person should develop the bright.*";
P_HTM[4361]="*Okā anokamāgamma,**Leaving home behind*";
P_HTM[4362]="*viveke yattha dūramaṃ.**for the seclusion so hard to enjoy,*";
P_HTM[4363]="*Tatrābhiratimiccheyya,**you should try to find delight there,*";
P_HTM[4364]="*hitvā kāme akiñcano;**having left behind sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[4365]="*Pariyodapeyya attānaṃ,**With no possessions, an astute person*";
P_HTM[4366]="*cittaklesehi paṇḍito.**should cleanse themselves of mental corruptions.*";
P_HTM[4367]="*Yesaṃ sambodhiyaṅgesu,**And those whose minds are rightly developed*";
P_HTM[4368]="*sammā cittaṃ subhāvitaṃ;**in the awakening factors;*";
P_HTM[4369]="*Ādānapaṭinissagge,**letting go of attachments,*";
P_HTM[4370]="*anupādāya ye ratā;**they delight in not grasping.*";
P_HTM[4371]="*Khīṇāsavā jutimanto,**With defilements ended, brilliant,*";
P_HTM[4372]="*te loke parinibbutā”ti.**they are extinguished in this world.”*";
P_HTM[4373]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4374]="*7. Paṭhamapaccorohaṇīsuttaṃ**The Ceremony of Descent (1st)*";
P_HTM[4375]="*Tena kho pana samayena jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo tadahuposathe sīsaṃnhāto navaṃ khomayugaṃ nivattho allakusamuṭṭhiṃ ādāya bhagavato avidūre ekamantaṃ ṭhito hoti.**Now, at that time it was the sabbath. The brahmin Jāṇussoṇi had bathed his head and dressed in a new pair of linen robes. Holding a handful of fresh grass, he stood to one side not far from the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4376]="*Addasā kho bhagavā jāṇussoṇiṃ brāhmaṇaṃ tadahuposathe sīsaṃnhātaṃ navaṃ khomayugaṃ nivatthaṃ allakusamuṭṭhiṃ ādāya ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ.**The Buddha saw him,*";
P_HTM[4377]="*Disvāna jāṇussoṇiṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:**and said,*";
P_HTM[4378]="*“kiṃ nu tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, tadahuposathe sīsaṃnhāto navaṃ khomayugaṃ nivattho allakusamuṭṭhiṃ ādāya ekamantaṃ ṭhito?**“Brahmin, why have you bathed your head and dressed in a new pair of linen robes? Why are you standing to one side holding a handful of fresh grass?*";
P_HTM[4379]="*Kiṃ nvajja brāhmaṇakulassā”ti?**What’s going on today with the brahmin clan?”*";
P_HTM[4380]="*“Paccorohaṇī, bho gotama, ajja brāhmaṇakulassā”ti.**“Master Gotama, today is the ceremony of descent for the brahmin clan.”*";
P_HTM[4381]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana, brāhmaṇa, brāhmaṇānaṃ paccorohaṇī hotī”ti?**“But how do the brahmins observe the ceremony of descent?”*";
P_HTM[4382]="*“Idha, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā tadahuposathe sīsaṃnhātā navaṃ khomayugaṃ nivatthā allena gomayena pathaviṃ opuñjitvā haritehi kusehi pattharitvā antarā ca velaṃ antarā ca agyāgāraṃ seyyaṃ kappenti.**“Well, Master Gotama, on the sabbath the brahmins bathe their heads and dress in a new pair of linen robes. They make a heap of fresh cow dung and spread it with green grass. Then they make their beds between the boundary and the fire chamber.*";
P_HTM[4383]="*Te taṃ rattiṃ tikkhattuṃ paccuṭṭhāya pañjalikā aggiṃ namassanti:**That night they rise three times and worship the fire with joined palms:*";
P_HTM[4384]="*‘paccorohāma bhavantaṃ, paccorohāma bhavantan’ti.**‘We descend, lord! We descend, lord!’*";
P_HTM[4385]="*Bahukena ca sappitelanavanītena aggiṃ santappenti.**And they serve the fire with abundant ghee, oil, and butter.*";
P_HTM[4386]="*Tassā ca rattiyā accayena paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena brāhmaṇe santappenti.**And when the night has passed they serve the brahmins with a variety of delicious foods.*";
P_HTM[4387]="*Evaṃ, bho gotama, brāhmaṇānaṃ paccorohaṇī hotī”ti.**That’s how the brahmins observe the ceremony of descent.”*";
P_HTM[4388]="*“Aññathā kho, brāhmaṇa, brāhmaṇānaṃ paccorohaṇī hoti, aññathā ca pana ariyassa vinaye paccorohaṇī hotī”ti.**“The ceremony of descent observed by the brahmins is quite different from that observed in the training of the noble one.”*";
P_HTM[4389]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana, bho gotama, ariyassa vinaye paccorohaṇī hoti?**“But Master Gotama, how is the ceremony of descent observed in the training of the noble one?*";
P_HTM[4390]="*Sādhu me bhavaṃ gotamo tathā dhammaṃ desetu yathā ariyassa vinaye paccorohaṇī hotī”ti.**Master Gotama, please teach me this.”*";
P_HTM[4391]="*“Tena hi, brāhmaṇa, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, brahmin, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[4392]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes sir,” Jāṇussoṇi replied.*";
P_HTM[4393]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4394]="*“Idha, brāhmaṇa, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**“It’s when a noble disciple reflects:*";
P_HTM[4395]="*‘micchādiṭṭhiyā kho pāpako vipāko**‘Wrong view has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4396]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in both this life and the next.’*";
P_HTM[4397]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya micchādiṭṭhiṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up wrong view,*";
P_HTM[4398]="*micchādiṭṭhiyā paccorohati.**they descend from wrong view.*";
P_HTM[4399]="*… ‘Micchāsaṅkappassa kho pāpako vipāko—**‘Wrong thought has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4400]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in both this life and the next.’*";
P_HTM[4401]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya micchāsaṅkappaṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up wrong thought,*";
P_HTM[4402]="*micchāsaṅkappā paccorohati.**they descend from wrong thought.*";
P_HTM[4403]="*… ‘Micchāvācāya kho pāpako vipāko—**‘Wrong speech has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4404]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in both this life and the next.’*";
P_HTM[4405]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya micchāvācaṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up wrong speech,*";
P_HTM[4406]="*micchāvācāya paccorohati.**they descend from wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[4407]="*… ‘Micchākammantassa kho pāpako vipāko—**‘Wrong action has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4408]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in both this life and the next.’*";
P_HTM[4409]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya micchākammantaṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up wrong action,*";
P_HTM[4410]="*micchākammantā paccorohati.**they descend from wrong action.*";
P_HTM[4411]="*… ‘Micchāājīvassa kho pāpako vipāko—**‘Wrong livelihood has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4412]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in both this life and the next.’*";
P_HTM[4413]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya micchāājīvaṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up wrong livelihood,*";
P_HTM[4414]="*micchāājīvā paccorohati.**they descend from wrong livelihood.*";
P_HTM[4415]="*… ‘Micchāvāyāmassa kho pāpako vipāko—**‘Wrong effort has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4416]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in both this life and the next.’*";
P_HTM[4417]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya micchāvāyāmaṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up wrong effort,*";
P_HTM[4418]="*micchāvāyāmā paccorohati.**they descend from wrong effort.*";
P_HTM[4419]="*… ‘Micchāsatiyā kho pāpako vipāko—**‘Wrong mindfulness has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4420]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in both this life and the next.’*";
P_HTM[4421]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya micchāsatiṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up wrong mindfulness,*";
P_HTM[4422]="*micchāsatiyā paccorohati.**they descend from wrong mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[4423]="*… ‘Micchāsamādhissa kho pāpako vipāko—**‘Wrong immersion has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4424]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in both this life and the next.’*";
P_HTM[4425]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya micchāsamādhiṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up wrong immersion,*";
P_HTM[4426]="*micchāsamādhimhā paccorohati.**they descend from wrong immersion.*";
P_HTM[4427]="*… ‘Micchāñāṇassa kho pāpako vipāko—**‘Wrong knowledge has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4428]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in both this life and the next.’*";
P_HTM[4429]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya micchāñāṇaṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up wrong knowledge,*";
P_HTM[4430]="*micchāñāṇamhā paccorohati.**they descend from wrong knowledge.*";
P_HTM[4431]="*… ‘Micchāvimuttiyā kho pāpako vipāko—**‘Wrong freedom has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4432]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in both this life and the next.’*";
P_HTM[4433]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya micchāvimuttiṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up wrong freedom,*";
P_HTM[4434]="*micchāvimuttiyā paccorohati.**they descend from wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4435]="*Evaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, ariyassa vinaye paccorohaṇī hotī”ti.**This is the ceremony of descent in the training of the noble one.”*";
P_HTM[4436]="*“Aññathā, bho gotama, brāhmaṇānaṃ paccorohaṇī, aññathā ca pana ariyassa vinaye paccorohaṇī hoti.**“The ceremony of descent observed by the brahmins is quite different from that observed in the training of the noble one.*";
P_HTM[4437]="*Imissā ca, bho gotama, ariyassa vinaye paccorohaṇiyā brāhmaṇānaṃ paccorohaṇī kalaṃ nāgghati soḷasiṃ.**And, Master Gotama, the ceremony of descent observed by the brahmins is not worth a sixteenth part of a master of the ceremony of descent observed in the training of the noble one.*";
P_HTM[4438]="*Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …**Excellent, Master Gotama! …*";
P_HTM[4439]="*upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[4440]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4441]="*8. Dutiyapaccorohaṇīsuttaṃ**The Ceremony of Descent (2nd)*";
P_HTM[4442]="*“Ariyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, paccorohaṇiṃ desessāmi.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the noble descent.*";
P_HTM[4443]="*Taṃ suṇātha …**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak. …*";
P_HTM[4444]="*katamā ca, bhikkhave, ariyā paccorohaṇī?**And what is the noble descent?*";
P_HTM[4445]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**It’s when a noble disciple reflects:*";
P_HTM[4446]="*‘micchādiṭṭhiyā kho pāpako vipāko—**‘Wrong view has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4447]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in both this life and the next.’*";
P_HTM[4448]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya micchādiṭṭhiṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up wrong view,*";
P_HTM[4449]="*micchādiṭṭhiyā paccorohati.**they descend from wrong view.*";
P_HTM[4450]="*Micchāsaṅkappassa kho pāpako vipāko …**‘Wrong thought has a bad result …’ …*";
P_HTM[4451]="*micchāvācāya kho …**‘Wrong speech …’ …*";
P_HTM[4452]="*micchākammantassa kho …**‘Wrong action …’ …*";
P_HTM[4453]="*micchāājīvassa kho …**‘Wrong livelihood …’ …*";
P_HTM[4454]="*micchāvāyāmassa kho …**‘Wrong effort …’ …*";
P_HTM[4455]="*micchāsatiyā kho …**‘Wrong mindfulness …’ …*";
P_HTM[4456]="*micchāsamādhissa kho …**‘Wrong immersion …’ …*";
P_HTM[4457]="*micchāñāṇassa kho …**‘Wrong knowledge …’ …*";
P_HTM[4458]="*micchāvimuttiyā kho pāpako vipāko—**‘Wrong freedom has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4459]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcāti.**in both this life and the next.’*";
P_HTM[4460]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya micchāvimuttiṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up wrong freedom,*";
P_HTM[4461]="*micchāvimuttiyā paccorohati.**they descend from wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4462]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyā paccorohaṇī”ti.**This is called the noble descent.”*";
P_HTM[4463]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4464]="*9. Pubbaṅgamasuttaṃ**Forerunner*";
P_HTM[4465]="*“Sūriyassa, bhikkhave, udayato etaṃ pubbaṅgamaṃ etaṃ pubbanimittaṃ, yadidaṃ—aruṇuggaṃ.**“Mendicants, the dawn is the forerunner and precursor of the sunrise.*";
P_HTM[4466]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ etaṃ pubbaṅgamaṃ etaṃ pubbanimittaṃ, yadidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi.**In the same way right view is the forerunner and precursor of skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[4467]="*Sammādiṭṭhikassa, bhikkhave, sammāsaṅkappo pahoti, sammāsaṅkappassa sammāvācā pahoti, sammāvācassa sammākammanto pahoti, sammākammantassa sammāājīvo pahoti, sammāājīvassa sammāvāyāmo pahoti, sammāvāyāmassa sammāsati pahoti, sammāsatissa sammāsamādhi pahoti, sammāsamādhissa sammāñāṇaṃ pahoti, sammāñāṇissa sammāvimutti pahotī”ti.**Right view gives rise to right thought. Right thought gives rise to right speech. Right speech gives rise to right action. Right action gives rise to right livelihood. Right livelihood gives rise to right effort. Right effort gives rise to right mindfulness. Right mindfulness gives rise to right immersion. Right immersion gives rise to right knowledge. Right knowledge gives rise to right freedom.”*";
P_HTM[4468]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4469]="*10. Āsavakkhayasuttaṃ**The Ending of Defilements*";
P_HTM[4470]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā āsavānaṃ khayāya saṃvattanti.**“Mendicants, these ten things, when developed and cultivated, lead to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[4471]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[4472]="*Sammādiṭṭhi, sammāsaṅkappo, sammāvācā, sammākammanto, sammāājīvo, sammāvāyāmo, sammāsati, sammāsamādhi, sammāñāṇaṃ, sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4473]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā āsavānaṃ khayāya saṃvattantī”ti.**These ten things, when developed and cultivated, lead to the ending of defilements.”*";
P_HTM[4474]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4475]="*Paccorohaṇivaggo dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[4476]="*Tayo adhammā ajito,* **";
P_HTM[4477]="*Saṅgāravo ca orimaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4478]="*Dve ceva paccorohaṇī,* **";
P_HTM[4479]="*Pubbaṅgamaṃ āsavakkhayoti.* **";
P_HTM[4480]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Purified*";
P_HTM[4481]="*1. Paṭhamasuttaṃ**First*";
P_HTM[4482]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, dhammā parisuddhā pariyodātā, nāññatra sugatavinayā.**“Mendicants, these ten things are not purified and cleansed apart from the Holy One’s training.*";
P_HTM[4483]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[4484]="*Sammādiṭṭhi, sammāsaṅkappo, sammāvācā, sammākammanto, sammāājīvo, sammāvāyāmo, sammāsati, sammāsamādhi, sammāñāṇaṃ, sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4485]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa dhammā parisuddhā pariyodātā, nāññatra sugatavinayā”ti.**These ten things are not purified and cleansed apart from the Holy One’s training.”*";
P_HTM[4486]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4487]="*2. Dutiyasuttaṃ**Second*";
P_HTM[4488]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, dhammā anuppannā uppajjanti, nāññatra sugatavinayā.**“Mendicants, these ten things don’t arise apart from the Holy One’s training.*";
P_HTM[4489]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[4490]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4491]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa dhammā anuppannā uppajjanti, nāññatra sugatavinayā”ti.**These are the ten things that don’t arise apart from the Holy One’s training.”*";
P_HTM[4492]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4493]="*3. Tatiyasuttaṃ**Third*";
P_HTM[4494]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, dhammā mahapphalā mahānisaṃsā, nāññatra sugatavinayā.**“Mendicants, these ten things are not very fruitful and beneficial apart from the Holy One’s training.*";
P_HTM[4495]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[4496]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4497]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa dhammā mahapphalā mahānisaṃsā, nāññatra sugatavinayā”ti.**These are the ten things that are not very fruitful and beneficial apart from the Holy One’s training.”*";
P_HTM[4498]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4499]="*4. Catutthasuttaṃ**Fourth*";
P_HTM[4500]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, dhammā rāgavinayapariyosānā honti dosavinayapariyosānā honti mohavinayapariyosānā honti, nāññatra sugatavinayā.**“Mendicants, these ten things don’t culminate in the removal of greed, hate, and delusion apart from the Holy One’s training.*";
P_HTM[4501]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[4502]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4503]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa dhammā rāgavinayapariyosānā honti dosavinayapariyosānā honti mohavinayapariyosānā honti, nāññatra sugatavinayā”ti.**These are the ten things that don’t culminate in the removal of greed, hate, and delusion apart from the Holy One’s training.”*";
P_HTM[4504]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4505]="*5. Pañcamasuttaṃ**Fifth*";
P_HTM[4506]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, dhammā ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattanti, nāññatra sugatavinayā.**“Mendicants, these ten things don’t lead solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment apart from the Holy One’s training.*";
P_HTM[4507]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[4508]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4509]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa dhammā ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattanti, nāññatra sugatavinayā”ti.**These are the ten things that don’t lead solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment apart from the Holy One’s training.”*";
P_HTM[4510]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4511]="*6. Chaṭṭhasuttaṃ**Sixth*";
P_HTM[4512]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā anuppannā uppajjanti, nāññatra sugatavinayā.**“Mendicants, these ten things don’t arise to be developed and cultivated apart from the Holy One’s training.*";
P_HTM[4513]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[4514]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4515]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā anuppannā uppajjanti, nāññatra sugatavinayā”ti.**These are the ten things that don’t arise to be developed and cultivated apart from the Holy One’s training.”*";
P_HTM[4516]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4517]="*7. Sattamasuttaṃ**Seventh*";
P_HTM[4518]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā honti mahānisaṃsā, nāññatra sugatavinayā.**“Mendicants, these ten things when developed and cultivated are not very fruitful and beneficial apart from the Holy One’s training.*";
P_HTM[4519]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[4520]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4521]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā honti mahānisaṃsā, nāññatra sugatavinayā”ti.**These are the ten things that when developed and cultivated are not very fruitful and beneficial apart from the Holy One’s training.”*";
P_HTM[4522]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4523]="*8. Aṭṭhamasuttaṃ**Eighth*";
P_HTM[4524]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā rāgavinayapariyosānā honti dosavinayapariyosānā honti mohavinayapariyosānā honti, nāññatra sugatavinayā.**“Mendicants, these ten things when developed and cultivated don’t culminate in the removal of greed, hate, and delusion apart from the Holy One’s training.*";
P_HTM[4525]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[4526]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4527]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā rāgavinayapariyosānā honti dosavinayapariyosānā honti mohavinayapariyosānā honti, nāññatra sugatavinayā”ti.**These are the ten things that when developed and cultivated don’t culminate in the removal of greed, hate, and delusion apart from the Holy One’s training.”*";
P_HTM[4528]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4529]="*9. Navamasuttaṃ**Ninth*";
P_HTM[4530]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattanti, nāññatra sugatavinayā.**“Mendicants, these ten things when developed and cultivated don’t lead solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment apart from the Holy One’s training.*";
P_HTM[4531]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[4532]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4533]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattanti, nāññatra sugatavinayā”ti.**These are the ten things that when developed and cultivated don’t lead solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment apart from the Holy One’s training.”*";
P_HTM[4534]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4535]="*10. Dasamasuttaṃ**Tenth*";
P_HTM[4536]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, micchattā.**“Mendicants, there are ten wrong ways.*";
P_HTM[4537]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[4538]="*Micchādiṭṭhi, micchāsaṅkappo, micchāvācā, micchākammanto, micchāājīvo, micchāvāyāmo, micchāsati, micchāsamādhi, micchāñāṇaṃ, micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4539]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa micchattā”ti.**These are the ten wrong ways.”*";
P_HTM[4540]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4541]="*11. Ekādasamasuttaṃ**Eleventh*";
P_HTM[4542]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, sammattā.**“Mendicants, there are ten right ways.*";
P_HTM[4543]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[4544]="*Sammādiṭṭhi, sammāsaṅkappo, sammāvācā, sammākammanto, sammāājīvo, sammāvāyāmo, sammāsati, sammāsamādhi, sammāñāṇaṃ, sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4545]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa sammattā”ti.**These are the ten right ways.”*";
P_HTM[4546]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4547]="*Parisuddhavaggo tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[4548]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Good*";
P_HTM[4549]="*1. Sādhusuttaṃ**Good*";
P_HTM[4550]="*“Sādhuñca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi asādhuñca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you what is good and what is not good.*";
P_HTM[4551]="*Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[4552]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4553]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4554]="*“Katamañca, bhikkhave, asādhu?**“And what, mendicants, is not good?*";
P_HTM[4555]="*Micchādiṭṭhi, micchāsaṅkappo, micchāvācā, micchākammanto, micchāājīvo, micchāvāyāmo, micchāsati, micchāsamādhi, micchāñāṇaṃ, micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4556]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asādhu.**This is called what is not good.*";
P_HTM[4557]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, sādhu?**And what is good?*";
P_HTM[4558]="*Sammādiṭṭhi, sammāsaṅkappo, sammāvācā sammākammanto, sammāājīvo, sammāvāyāmo, sammāsati, sammāsamādhi, sammāñāṇaṃ, sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4559]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sādhū”ti.**This is called what is good.”*";
P_HTM[4560]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4561]="*2. Ariyadhammasuttaṃ**The Teaching of the Noble Ones*";
P_HTM[4562]="*“Ariyadhammañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi anariyadhammañca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the teaching of the noble ones, and what is not the teaching of the noble ones. …*";
P_HTM[4563]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4564]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, anariyo dhammo?**And what is not the teaching of the noble ones?*";
P_HTM[4565]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4566]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, anariyo dhammo.**This is called what is not the teaching of the noble ones.*";
P_HTM[4567]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, ariyo dhammo?**And what is the teaching of the noble ones?*";
P_HTM[4568]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4569]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyo dhammo”ti.**This is called the teaching of the noble ones.”*";
P_HTM[4570]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4571]="*3. Akusalasuttaṃ**Unskillful*";
P_HTM[4572]="*“Akusalañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi kusalañca.**“I will teach you the skillful and the unskillful …*";
P_HTM[4573]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4574]="*katamañca, bhikkhave, akusalaṃ?**And what is the unskillful?*";
P_HTM[4575]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4576]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, akusalaṃ.**This is called the unskillful.*";
P_HTM[4577]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kusalaṃ?**And what is the skillful?*";
P_HTM[4578]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4579]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kusalan”ti.**This is called the skillful.”*";
P_HTM[4580]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4581]="*4. Atthasuttaṃ**Beneficial*";
P_HTM[4582]="*“Atthañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi anatthañca.**“I will teach you the beneficial and the harmful. …*";
P_HTM[4583]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4584]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, anattho?**And what is the harmful?*";
P_HTM[4585]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4586]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, anattho.**This is called the harmful.*";
P_HTM[4587]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, attho?**And what is the beneficial?*";
P_HTM[4588]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4589]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, attho”ti.**This is called the beneficial.”*";
P_HTM[4590]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4591]="*5. Dhammasuttaṃ**The Teaching*";
P_HTM[4592]="*“Dhammañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi adhammañca.**“I will teach you what is the teaching and what is not the teaching. …*";
P_HTM[4593]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4594]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, adhammo?**And what is not the teaching?*";
P_HTM[4595]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4596]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhammo.**This is called what is not the teaching.*";
P_HTM[4597]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, dhammo?**And what is the teaching?*";
P_HTM[4598]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4599]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhammo”ti.**This is called the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[4600]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4601]="*6. Sāsavasuttaṃ**Defiled*";
P_HTM[4602]="*“Sāsavañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi anāsavañca.**“I will teach you the defiled principle and the undefiled. …*";
P_HTM[4603]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4604]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, sāsavo dhammo?**And what is the defiled principle?*";
P_HTM[4605]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4606]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sāsavo dhammo.**This is called the defiled principle.*";
P_HTM[4607]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, anāsavo dhammo?**And what is the undefiled principle?*";
P_HTM[4608]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4609]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, anāsavo dhammo”ti.**This is called the undefiled principle.”*";
P_HTM[4610]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4611]="*7. Sāvajjasuttaṃ**Blameworthy*";
P_HTM[4612]="*“Sāvajjañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi anavajjañca.**“I will teach you the blameworthy principle and the blameless principle. …*";
P_HTM[4613]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4614]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, sāvajjo dhammo?**And what is the blameworthy principle?*";
P_HTM[4615]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4616]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sāvajjo dhammo.**This is called the blameworthy principle.*";
P_HTM[4617]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, anavajjo dhammo?**And what is the blameless principle?*";
P_HTM[4618]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4619]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, anavajjo dhammo”ti.**This is called the blameless principle.”*";
P_HTM[4620]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4621]="*8. Tapanīyasuttaṃ**Mortifying*";
P_HTM[4622]="*“Tapanīyañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi atapanīyañca.**“I will teach you the mortifying principle and the unmortifying. …*";
P_HTM[4623]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4624]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, tapanīyo dhammo?**And what is the mortifying principle?*";
P_HTM[4625]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4626]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, tapanīyo dhammo.**This is called the mortifying principle.*";
P_HTM[4627]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, atapanīyo dhammo?**And what is the unmortifying principle?*";
P_HTM[4628]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4629]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, atapanīyo dhammo”ti.**This is called the unmortifying principle.”*";
P_HTM[4630]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4631]="*9. Ācayagāmisuttaṃ**Accumulation*";
P_HTM[4632]="*“Ācayagāmiñca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi apacayagāmiñca.**“I will teach you the principle that leads to accumulation and that which leads to dispersal. …*";
P_HTM[4633]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4634]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, ācayagāmī dhammo?**And what is the principle that leads to accumulation?*";
P_HTM[4635]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4636]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ācayagāmī dhammo.**This is called the principle that leads to accumulation.*";
P_HTM[4637]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, apacayagāmī dhammo?**And what is the principle that leads to dispersal?*";
P_HTM[4638]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4639]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, apacayagāmī dhammo”ti.**This is called the principle that leads to dispersal.”*";
P_HTM[4640]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4641]="*10. Dukkhudrayasuttaṃ**With Suffering as Outcome*";
P_HTM[4642]="*“Dukkhudrayañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi sukhudrayañca.**“I will teach you the principle that has suffering as outcome, and that which has happiness as outcome. …*";
P_HTM[4643]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4644]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, dukkhudrayo dhammo?**And what is the principle whose outcome is suffering?*";
P_HTM[4645]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4646]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhudrayo dhammo.**This is the principle whose outcome is suffering.*";
P_HTM[4647]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sukhudrayo dhammo?**And what is the principle whose outcome is happiness?*";
P_HTM[4648]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4649]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sukhudrayo dhammo”ti.**This is the principle whose outcome is happiness.”*";
P_HTM[4650]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4651]="*11. Dukkhavipākasuttaṃ**Result in Suffering*";
P_HTM[4652]="*“Dukkhavipākañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi sukhavipākañca.**“I will teach you the principle that results in suffering and that which results in happiness. …*";
P_HTM[4653]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4654]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, dukkhavipāko dhammo?**And what principle results in suffering?*";
P_HTM[4655]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4656]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhavipāko dhammo.**This is called the principle that results in suffering.*";
P_HTM[4657]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sukhavipāko dhammo?**And what principle results in happiness?*";
P_HTM[4658]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4659]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sukhavipāko dhammo”ti.**This is called the principle that results in happiness.”*";
P_HTM[4660]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4661]="*Sādhuvaggo catuttho.* **";
P_HTM[4662]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**The Noble Path*";
P_HTM[4663]="*1. Ariyamaggasuttaṃ**The Noble Path*";
P_HTM[4664]="*“Ariyamaggañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi anariyamaggañca.**“I will teach you the noble path and the ignoble path. …*";
P_HTM[4665]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4666]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, anariyo maggo?**And what is the ignoble path?*";
P_HTM[4667]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4668]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, anariyo maggo.**This is called the ignoble path.*";
P_HTM[4669]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, ariyo maggo?**And what is the noble path?*";
P_HTM[4670]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4671]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyo maggo”ti.**This is called the noble path.”*";
P_HTM[4672]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4673]="*2. Kaṇhamaggasuttaṃ**The Dark Path*";
P_HTM[4674]="*“Kaṇhamaggañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi sukkamaggañca.**“I will teach you the dark path and the bright path. …*";
P_HTM[4675]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4676]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, kaṇhamaggo?**And what is the dark path?*";
P_HTM[4677]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4678]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kaṇhamaggo.**This is called the dark path.*";
P_HTM[4679]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sukkamaggo?**And what is the bright path?*";
P_HTM[4680]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4681]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sukkamaggo”ti.**This is called the bright path.”*";
P_HTM[4682]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4683]="*3. Saddhammasuttaṃ**The True Teaching*";
P_HTM[4684]="*“Saddhammañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi asaddhammañca.**“I will teach you what is the true teaching and what is not the true teaching. …*";
P_HTM[4685]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4686]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, asaddhammo?**And what is not the true teaching?*";
P_HTM[4687]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4688]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asaddhammo.**This is called what is not the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[4689]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, saddhammo?**And what is the true teaching?*";
P_HTM[4690]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4691]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, saddhammo”ti.**This is called the true teaching.”*";
P_HTM[4692]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4693]="*4. Sappurisadhammasuttaṃ**The Teaching of the Good Persons*";
P_HTM[4694]="*“Sappurisadhammañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi asappurisadhammañca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the teaching of the good persons and the teaching of the bad persons. …*";
P_HTM[4695]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4696]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappurisadhammo?**And what is the teaching of the bad persons?*";
P_HTM[4697]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4698]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asappurisadhammo.**This is the teaching of the bad persons.*";
P_HTM[4699]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sappurisadhammo?**And what is the teaching of the good persons?*";
P_HTM[4700]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4701]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sappurisadhammo”ti.**This is the teaching of the good persons.”*";
P_HTM[4702]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4703]="*5. Uppādetabbasuttaṃ**Should Be Activated*";
P_HTM[4704]="*“Uppādetabbañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi na uppādetabbañca.**“I will teach you the principle to activate and the principle not to activate. …*";
P_HTM[4705]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4706]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, na uppādetabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle not to activate?*";
P_HTM[4707]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4708]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, na uppādetabbo dhammo.**This is called the principle not to activate.*";
P_HTM[4709]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, uppādetabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle to activate?*";
P_HTM[4710]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4711]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, uppādetabbo dhammo”ti.**This is called the principle to activate.”*";
P_HTM[4712]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4713]="*6. Āsevitabbasuttaṃ**Should Be Cultivated*";
P_HTM[4714]="*“Āsevitabbañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi na āsevitabbañca.**“I will teach you the principle to cultivate and the principle not to cultivate. …*";
P_HTM[4715]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4716]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, na āsevitabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle not to cultivate?*";
P_HTM[4717]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4718]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, na āsevitabbo dhammo.**This is called the principle not to cultivate.*";
P_HTM[4719]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, āsevitabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle to cultivate?*";
P_HTM[4720]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4721]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, āsevitabbo dhammo”ti.**This is called the principle to cultivate.”*";
P_HTM[4722]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4723]="*7. Bhāvetabbasuttaṃ**Should Be Developed*";
P_HTM[4724]="*“Bhāvetabbañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi na bhāvetabbañca.**“I will teach you the principle to develop and the principle not to develop. …*";
