P_HTM[4727]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4728]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, na bhāvetabbo dhammo.**This is called the principle not to develop.*";
P_HTM[4729]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, bhāvetabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle to develop?*";
P_HTM[4730]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4731]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhāvetabbo dhammo”ti.**This is called the principle to develop.”*";
P_HTM[4732]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4733]="*8. Bahulīkātabbasuttaṃ**Should Be Made Much Of*";
P_HTM[4734]="*“Bahulīkātabbañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi na bahulīkātabbañca.**“I will teach you the principle to make much of and the principle not to make much of. …*";
P_HTM[4735]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4736]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, na bahulīkātabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle not to make much of?*";
P_HTM[4737]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4738]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, na bahulīkātabbo dhammo.**This is called the principle not to make much of.*";
P_HTM[4739]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, bahulīkātabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle to make much of?*";
P_HTM[4740]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4741]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bahulīkātabbo dhammo”ti.**This is called the principle to make much of.”*";
P_HTM[4742]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4743]="*9. Anussaritabbasuttaṃ**Should Be Recollected*";
P_HTM[4744]="*“Anussaritabbañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi na anussaritabbañca.**“I will teach you the principle to recollect and the principle not to recollect. …*";
P_HTM[4745]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4746]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, na anussaritabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle not to recollect?*";
P_HTM[4747]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4748]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, na anussaritabbo dhammo.**This is called the principle not to recollect.*";
P_HTM[4749]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, anussaritabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle to recollect?*";
P_HTM[4750]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4751]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, anussaritabbo dhammo”ti.**This is called the principle to recollect.”*";
P_HTM[4752]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4753]="*10. Sacchikātabbasuttaṃ**Should Be Realized*";
P_HTM[4754]="*“Sacchikātabbañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi na sacchikātabbañca.**“I will teach you the principle to realize and the principle not to realize. …*";
P_HTM[4755]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4756]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, na sacchikātabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle not to realize?*";
P_HTM[4757]="*Micchādiṭṭhi … pe … micchāvimutti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4758]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, na sacchikātabbo dhammo.**This is called the principle not to realize.*";
P_HTM[4759]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sacchikātabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle to realize?*";
P_HTM[4760]="*Sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4761]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sacchikātabbo dhammo”ti.**This is called the principle to realize.”*";
P_HTM[4762]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4763]="*Ariyavaggo pañcamo.* **";
P_HTM[4764]="*Tatiyo paṇṇāsako samatto.* **";
P_HTM[4765]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Persons*";
P_HTM[4766]="*1. Sevitabbasuttaṃ**You Should Associate*";
P_HTM[4767]="*“Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato puggalo na sevitabbo.**“Mendicants, you should not associate with a person who has ten qualities.*";
P_HTM[4768]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[4769]="*Micchādiṭṭhiko hoti, micchāsaṅkappo hoti, micchāvāco hoti, micchākammanto hoti, micchāājīvo hoti, micchāvāyāmo hoti, micchāsati hoti, micchāsamādhi hoti, micchāñāṇī hoti, micchāvimutti hoti—**Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom.*";
P_HTM[4770]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi dhammehi samannāgato puggalo na sevitabbo.**You should not associate with a person who has these ten qualities.*";
P_HTM[4771]="*Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato puggalo sevitabbo.**You should associate with a person who has ten qualities.*";
P_HTM[4772]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[4773]="*Sammādiṭṭhiko hoti, sammāsaṅkappo hoti, sammāvāco hoti, sammākammanto hoti, sammāājīvo hoti, sammāvāyāmo hoti, sammāsati hoti, sammāsamādhi hoti, sammāñāṇī hoti, sammāvimutti hoti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4774]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi dhammehi samannāgato puggalo sevitabbo”ti.**You should associate with a person who has these ten qualities.”*";
P_HTM[4775]="*2-12. Bhajitabbādisuttāni**156–166. Bhajitabbādisutta*";
P_HTM[4776]="*“Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato puggalo na bhajitabbo … pe …**“Mendicants, you should not frequent a person who has ten qualities. …*";
P_HTM[4777]="*bhajitabbo … pe …**you should frequent …*";
P_HTM[4778]="*na payirupāsitabbo …**you should not pay homage …*";
P_HTM[4779]="*payirupāsitabbo … pe …**you should pay homage …*";
P_HTM[4780]="*na pujjo hoti …**you should not venerate …*";
P_HTM[4781]="*pujjo hoti … pe …**you should venerate …*";
P_HTM[4782]="*na pāsaṃso hoti …**you should not praise …*";
P_HTM[4783]="*pāsaṃso hoti … pe …**you should praise …*";
P_HTM[4784]="*agāravo hoti …**you should not respect …*";
P_HTM[4785]="*sagāravo hoti … pe …**you should respect …*";
P_HTM[4786]="*appatisso hoti …**you should not revere …*";
P_HTM[4787]="*sappatisso hoti … pe …**you should revere …*";
P_HTM[4788]="*na ārādhako hoti …**is not a success …*";
P_HTM[4789]="*ārādhako hoti … pe …**is a success …*";
P_HTM[4790]="*na visujjhati …**is not pure …*";
P_HTM[4791]="*visujjhati … pe …**is pure …*";
P_HTM[4792]="*mānaṃ nādhibhoti …**does not win over conceit …*";
P_HTM[4793]="*mānaṃ adhibhoti … pe …**wins over conceit …*";
P_HTM[4794]="*paññāya na vaḍḍhati …**does not grow in wisdom …*";
P_HTM[4795]="*paññāya vaḍḍhati … pe ….**grows in wisdom …*";
P_HTM[4796]="*Bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavati …**makes much bad karma …*";
P_HTM[4797]="*bahuṃ puññaṃ pasavati.**makes much merit.*";
P_HTM[4798]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[4799]="*Sammādiṭṭhiko hoti, sammāsaṅkappo hoti, sammāvāco hoti, sammākammanto hoti, sammāājīvo hoti, sammāvāyāmo hoti, sammāsati hoti, sammāsamādhi hoti, sammāñāṇī hoti, sammāvimutti hoti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[4800]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi dhammehi samannāgato puggalo bahuṃ puññaṃ pasavatī”ti.**A person who has these ten qualities makes much merit.”*";
P_HTM[4801]="*Puggalavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[4802]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**With Jāṇussoṇī*";
P_HTM[4803]="*1. Brāhmaṇapaccorohaṇīsuttaṃ**The Brahmin Ceremony of Descent*";
P_HTM[4804]="*Tena kho pana samayena jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo tadahuposathe sīsaṃnhāto navaṃ khomayugaṃ nivattho allakusamuṭṭhiṃ ādāya bhagavato avidūre ekamantaṃ ṭhito hoti.**Now, at that time it was the sabbath. The brahmin Jāṇussoṇi had bathed his head and dressed in a new pair of linen robes. Holding a handful of fresh grass, he stood to one side not far from the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4805]="*Addasā kho bhagavā jāṇussoṇiṃ brāhmaṇaṃ tadahuposathe sīsaṃnhātaṃ navaṃ khomayugaṃ nivatthaṃ allakusamuṭṭhiṃ ādāya ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ.**The Buddha saw him,*";
P_HTM[4806]="*Disvāna jāṇussoṇiṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:**and said,*";
P_HTM[4807]="*“kiṃ nu tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, tadahuposathe sīsaṃnhāto navaṃ khomayugaṃ nivattho allakusamuṭṭhiṃ ādāya ekamantaṃ ṭhito?**“Brahmin, why have you bathed your head and dressed in a new pair of linen robes? Why are you standing to one side holding a handful of fresh grass?*";
P_HTM[4808]="*Kiṃ nvajja brāhmaṇakulassā”ti?**What’s going on today with the brahmin clan?”*";
P_HTM[4809]="*“Paccorohaṇī, bho gotama, ajja brāhmaṇakulassā”ti.**“Master Gotama, today is the ceremony of descent for the brahmin clan.”*";
P_HTM[4810]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana, brāhmaṇa, brāhmaṇānaṃ paccorohaṇī hotī”ti?**“But how do the brahmins observe the ceremony of descent?”*";
P_HTM[4811]="*“Idha, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā tadahuposathe sīsaṃnhātā navaṃ khomayugaṃ nivatthā allena gomayena pathaviṃ opuñjitvā haritehi kusehi pattharitvā antarā ca velaṃ antarā ca agyāgāraṃ seyyaṃ kappenti.**“Well, Master Gotama, on the sabbath the brahmins bathe their heads and dress in a new pair of linen robes. They make a heap of fresh cow dung and spread it with green grass. Then they make their beds between the boundary and the fire chamber.*";
P_HTM[4812]="*Te taṃ rattiṃ tikkhattuṃ paccuṭṭhāya pañjalikā aggiṃ namassanti:**That night they rise three times and worship the fire with joined palms:*";
P_HTM[4813]="*‘paccorohāma bhavantaṃ, paccorohāma bhavantan’ti.**‘We descend, lord! We descend, lord!’*";
P_HTM[4814]="*Bahukena ca sappitelanavanītena aggiṃ santappenti.**And they serve the fire with abundant ghee, oil, and butter.*";
P_HTM[4815]="*Tassā ca rattiyā accayena paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena brāhmaṇe santappenti.**And when the night has passed they serve the brahmins with a variety of delicious foods.*";
P_HTM[4816]="*Evaṃ, bho gotama, brāhmaṇānaṃ paccorohaṇī hotī”ti.**That’s how the brahmins observe the ceremony of descent.”*";
P_HTM[4817]="*“Aññathā kho, brāhmaṇa, brāhmaṇānaṃ paccorohaṇī hoti, aññathā ca pana ariyassa vinaye paccorohaṇī hotī”ti.**“The ceremony of descent observed by the brahmins is quite different from that observed in the training of the noble one.”*";
P_HTM[4818]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana, bho gotama, ariyassa vinaye paccorohaṇī hoti?**“But Master Gotama, how is the ceremony of descent observed in the training of the noble one?*";
P_HTM[4819]="*Sādhu me bhavaṃ gotamo tathā dhammaṃ desetu yathā ariyassa vinaye paccorohaṇī hotī”ti.**Master Gotama, please teach me this.”*";
P_HTM[4820]="*“Tena hi, brāhmaṇa, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, brahmin, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[4821]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes sir,” Jāṇussoṇi replied.*";
P_HTM[4822]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4823]="*“Idha, brāhmaṇa, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**“It’s when a noble disciple reflects:*";
P_HTM[4824]="*‘pāṇātipātassa kho pāpako vipāko diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**‘Killing living creatures has a bad result in the present life and in lives to come.’*";
P_HTM[4825]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya pāṇātipātaṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up killing living creatures,*";
P_HTM[4826]="*pāṇātipātā paccorohati.**they descend from killing living creatures.*";
P_HTM[4827]="*… ‘Adinnādānassa kho pāpako vipāko—**… ‘Stealing has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4828]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in the present life and in lives to come.’*";
P_HTM[4829]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya adinnādānaṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up stealing,*";
P_HTM[4830]="*adinnādānā paccorohati.**they descend from stealing.*";
P_HTM[4831]="*… ‘Kāmesumicchācārassa kho pāpako vipāko—**… ‘Sexual misconduct has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4832]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in the present life and in lives to come.’*";
P_HTM[4833]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya kāmesumicchācāraṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up sexual misconduct,*";
P_HTM[4834]="*kāmesumicchācārā paccorohati.**they descend from sexual misconduct.*";
P_HTM[4835]="*… ‘Musāvādassa kho pāpako vipāko—**… ‘Lying has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4836]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in the present life and in lives to come.’*";
P_HTM[4837]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya musāvādaṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up lying,*";
P_HTM[4838]="*musāvādā paccorohati.**they descend from lying.*";
P_HTM[4839]="*… ‘Pisuṇāya vācāya kho pāpako vipāko—**… ‘Divisive speech has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4840]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in the present life and in lives to come.’*";
P_HTM[4841]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up divisive speech,*";
P_HTM[4842]="*pisuṇāya vācāya paccorohati.**they descend from divisive speech.*";
P_HTM[4843]="*… ‘Pharusāya vācāya kho pāpako vipāko—**… ‘Harsh speech has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4844]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in the present life and in lives to come.’*";
P_HTM[4845]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya pharusaṃ vācaṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up harsh speech,*";
P_HTM[4846]="*pharusāya vācāya paccorohati.**they descend from harsh speech.*";
P_HTM[4847]="*… ‘Samphappalāpassa kho pāpako vipāko—**… ‘Talking nonsense has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4848]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in the present life and in lives to come.’*";
P_HTM[4849]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya samphappalāpaṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up talking nonsense,*";
P_HTM[4850]="*samphappalāpā paccorohati.**they descend from talking nonsense.*";
P_HTM[4851]="*… ‘Abhijjhāya kho pāpako vipāko—**… ‘Covetousness has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4852]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in the present life and in lives to come.’*";
P_HTM[4853]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya abhijjhaṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up covetousness,*";
P_HTM[4854]="*abhijjhāya paccorohati.**they descend from covetousness.*";
P_HTM[4855]="*… ‘Byāpādassa kho pāpako vipāko—**… ‘Ill will has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4856]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in the present life and in lives to come.’*";
P_HTM[4857]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya byāpādaṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up ill will,*";
P_HTM[4858]="*byāpādā paccorohati.**they descend from ill will.*";
P_HTM[4859]="*… ‘Micchādiṭṭhiyā kho pāpako vipāko—**‘Wrong view has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4860]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in the present life and in lives to come.’*";
P_HTM[4861]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya micchādiṭṭhiṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up wrong view,*";
P_HTM[4862]="*micchādiṭṭhiyā paccorohati.**they descend from wrong view.*";
P_HTM[4863]="*Evaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, ariyassa vinaye paccorohaṇī hotī”ti.**This is the ceremony of descent in the training of the noble one.”*";
P_HTM[4864]="*“Aññathā kho, bho gotama, brāhmaṇānaṃ paccorohaṇī hoti, aññathā ca pana ariyassa vinaye paccorohaṇī hoti.**“The ceremony of descent observed by the brahmins is quite different from that observed in the training of the noble one.*";
P_HTM[4865]="*Imissā, bho gotama, ariyassa vinaye paccorohaṇiyā brāhmaṇānaṃ paccorohaṇī kalaṃ nāgghati soḷasiṃ.**And, Master Gotama, the ceremony of descent observed by the brahmins is not worth a sixteenth part of the ceremony of descent observed in the training of the noble one.*";
P_HTM[4866]="*Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …**Excellent, Master Gotama, excellent! …*";
P_HTM[4867]="*upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[4868]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4869]="*2. Ariyapaccorohaṇīsuttaṃ**The Noble Descent*";
P_HTM[4870]="*“Ariyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, paccorohaṇiṃ desessāmi.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the noble descent.*";
P_HTM[4871]="*Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[4872]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4873]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4874]="*“Katamā ca, bhikkhave, ariyā paccorohaṇī?**“And what, mendicants, is the noble descent?*";
P_HTM[4875]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:**It’s when a noble disciple reflects:*";
P_HTM[4876]="*‘pāṇātipātassa kho pāpako vipāko—**‘Killing living creatures has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4877]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in the present life and in lives to come.’*";
P_HTM[4878]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya pāṇātipātaṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up killing living creatures,*";
P_HTM[4879]="*pāṇātipātā paccorohati.**they descend from killing living creatures.*";
P_HTM[4880]="*… ‘Adinnādānassa kho pāpako vipāko—**… ‘Stealing has a bad result*";
P_HTM[4881]="*diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**in the present life and in lives to come.’*";
P_HTM[4882]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya adinnādānaṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up stealing,*";
P_HTM[4883]="*adinnādānā paccorohati.**they descend from stealing.*";
P_HTM[4884]="*… ‘Kāmesumicchācārassa kho pāpako vipāko … pe …**… ‘Sexual misconduct has a bad result …’ …*";
P_HTM[4885]="*kāmesumicchācārā paccorohati.**they descend from sexual misconduct.*";
P_HTM[4886]="*… ‘Musāvādassa kho pāpako vipāko … pe …**… ‘Lying has a bad result …’ …*";
P_HTM[4887]="*musāvādā paccorohati.**they descend from lying.*";
P_HTM[4888]="*… ‘Pisuṇāya vācāya kho pāpako vipāko … pe …**… ‘Divisive speech has a bad result …’ …*";
P_HTM[4889]="*pisuṇāya vācāya paccorohati.**they descend from divisive speech.*";
P_HTM[4890]="*… ‘Pharusāya vācāya kho pāpako vipāko … pe …**… ‘Harsh speech has a bad result …’ …*";
P_HTM[4891]="*pharusāya vācāya paccorohati.**they descend from harsh speech.*";
P_HTM[4892]="*… ‘Samphappalāpassa kho pāpako vipāko … pe …**… ‘Talking nonsense has a bad result …’ …*";
P_HTM[4893]="*samphappalāpā paccorohati.**they descend from talking nonsense.*";
P_HTM[4894]="*… ‘Abhijjhāya kho pāpako vipāko … pe …**… ‘Covetousness has a bad result …’ …*";
P_HTM[4895]="*abhijjhāya paccorohati.**they descend from covetousness.*";
P_HTM[4896]="*… ‘Byāpādassa kho pāpako vipāko … pe …**… ‘Ill will has a bad result …’ …*";
P_HTM[4897]="*byāpādā paccorohati.**they descend from ill will.*";
P_HTM[4898]="*… ‘Micchādiṭṭhiyā kho pāpako vipāko diṭṭhe ceva dhamme abhisamparāyañcā’ti.**… ‘Wrong view has a bad result both in the present life and in lives to come.’*";
P_HTM[4899]="*So iti paṭisaṅkhāya micchādiṭṭhiṃ pajahati;**Reflecting like this, they give up wrong view,*";
P_HTM[4900]="*micchādiṭṭhiyā paccorohati.**they descend from wrong view.*";
P_HTM[4901]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyā paccorohaṇī”ti.**This is called the noble descent.”*";
P_HTM[4902]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4903]="*3. Saṅgāravasuttaṃ**With Saṅgārava*";
P_HTM[4904]="*Atha kho saṅgāravo brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Saṅgārava the brahmin went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4905]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho saṅgāravo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[4906]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, orimaṃ tīraṃ, kiṃ pārimaṃ tīran”ti?**“Master Gotama, what is the near shore? And what is the far shore?”*";
P_HTM[4907]="*“Pāṇātipāto kho, brāhmaṇa, orimaṃ tīraṃ, pāṇātipātā veramaṇī pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**“Killing living creatures is the near shore, brahmin, and not killing living creatures is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4908]="*Adinnādānaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, orimaṃ tīraṃ, adinnādānā veramaṇī pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Stealing is the near shore, and not stealing is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4909]="*Kāmesumicchācāro orimaṃ tīraṃ, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇī pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Sexual misconduct is the near shore, and avoiding sexual misconduct is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4910]="*Musāvādo orimaṃ tīraṃ, musāvādā veramaṇī pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Lying is the near shore, and not lying is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4911]="*Pisuṇā vācā orimaṃ tīraṃ, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Divisive speech is the near shore, and avoiding divisive speech is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4912]="*Pharusā vācā orimaṃ tīraṃ, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Harsh speech is the near shore, and avoiding harsh speech is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4913]="*Samphappalāpo orimaṃ tīraṃ, samphappalāpā veramaṇī pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Talking nonsense is the near shore, and avoiding talking nonsense is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4914]="*Abhijjhā orimaṃ tīraṃ, anabhijjhā pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Covetousness is the near shore, and contentment is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4915]="*Byāpādo orimaṃ tīraṃ, abyāpādo pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Ill will is the near shore, and good will is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4916]="*Micchādiṭṭhi orimaṃ tīraṃ, sammādiṭṭhi pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Wrong view is the near shore, and right view is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4917]="*Idaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, orimaṃ tīraṃ, idaṃ pārimaṃ tīranti.**This is the near shore, and this is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4918]="*Appakā te manussesu,**Few are those among humans*";
P_HTM[4919]="*ye janā pāragāmino;**who cross to the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4920]="*Athāyaṃ itarā pajā,**The rest just run*";
P_HTM[4921]="*tīramevānudhāvati.**around on the near shore.*";
P_HTM[4922]="*Ye ca kho sammadakkhāte,**When the teaching is well explained,*";
P_HTM[4923]="*dhamme dhammānuvattino;**those who practice accordingly*";
P_HTM[4924]="*Te janā pāramessanti,**are the ones who will cross over*";
P_HTM[4925]="*maccudheyyaṃ suduttaraṃ.**Death’s domain so hard to pass.*";
P_HTM[4926]="*Kaṇhaṃ dhammaṃ vippahāya,**Rid of dark qualities,*";
P_HTM[4927]="*Sukkaṃ bhāvetha paṇḍito;**an astute person should develop the bright.*";
P_HTM[4928]="*Okā anokamāgamma,**Leaving home behind*";
P_HTM[4929]="*Viveke yattha dūramaṃ.**for the seclusion so hard to enjoy,*";
P_HTM[4930]="*Tatrābhiratimiccheyya,**you should try to find delight there,*";
P_HTM[4931]="*hitvā kāme akiñcano;**having left behind sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[4932]="*Pariyodapeyya attānaṃ,**With no possessions, an astute person*";
P_HTM[4933]="*cittaklesehi paṇḍito.**should cleanse themselves of mental corruptions.*";
P_HTM[4934]="*Yesaṃ sambodhiyaṅgesu,**And those whose minds are rightly developed*";
P_HTM[4935]="*sammā cittaṃ subhāvitaṃ;**in the awakening factors;*";
P_HTM[4936]="*Ādānapaṭinissagge,**letting go of attachments,*";
P_HTM[4937]="*anupādāya ye ratā;**they delight in not grasping.*";
P_HTM[4938]="*Khīṇāsavā jutimanto,**With defilements ended, brilliant,*";
P_HTM[4939]="*te loke parinibbutā”ti.**they are extinguished in this world.”*";
P_HTM[4940]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4941]="*4. Orimasuttaṃ**The Near Shore*";
P_HTM[4942]="*“Orimañca, bhikkhave, tīraṃ desessāmi pārimañca tīraṃ.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the near shore and the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4943]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak. …*";
P_HTM[4944]="*katamañca, bhikkhave, orimaṃ tīraṃ, katamañca pārimaṃ tīraṃ?**And what, mendicants, is the near shore? What is the far shore?*";
P_HTM[4945]="*Pāṇātipāto, bhikkhave, orimaṃ tīraṃ, pāṇātipātā veramaṇī pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Killing living creatures is the near shore, mendicants, and not killing living creatures is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4946]="*Adinnādānaṃ orimaṃ tīraṃ, adinnādānā veramaṇī pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Stealing is the near shore, and not stealing is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4947]="*Kāmesumicchācāro orimaṃ tīraṃ, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇī pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Sexual misconduct is the near shore, and avoiding sexual misconduct is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4948]="*Musāvādo orimaṃ tīraṃ, musāvādā veramaṇī pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Lying is the near shore, and not lying is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4949]="*Pisuṇā vācā orimaṃ tīraṃ, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Divisive speech is the near shore, and avoiding divisive speech is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4950]="*Pharusā vācā orimaṃ tīraṃ, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Harsh speech is the near shore, and avoiding harsh speech is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4951]="*Samphappalāpo orimaṃ tīraṃ, samphappalāpā veramaṇī pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Talking nonsense is the near shore, and avoiding talking nonsense is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4952]="*Abhijjhā orimaṃ tīraṃ, anabhijjhā pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Covetousness is the near shore, and contentment is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4953]="*Byāpādo orimaṃ tīraṃ, abyāpādo pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Ill will is the near shore, and good will is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4954]="*Micchādiṭṭhi orimaṃ tīraṃ, sammādiṭṭhi pārimaṃ tīraṃ.**Wrong view is the near shore, and right view is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4955]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, orimaṃ tīraṃ, idaṃ pārimaṃ tīranti.**This is the near shore, and this is the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4956]="*Appakā te manussesu,**Few are those among humans*";
P_HTM[4957]="*ye janā pāragāmino;**who cross to the far shore.*";
P_HTM[4958]="*Athāyaṃ itarā pajā,**The rest just run*";
P_HTM[4959]="*tīramevānudhāvati.**around on the near shore.*";
P_HTM[4960]="*Ye ca kho sammadakkhāte,**When the teaching is well explained,*";
P_HTM[4961]="*dhamme dhammānuvattino;**those who practice accordingly*";
P_HTM[4962]="*Te janā pāramessanti,**are the ones who will cross over*";
P_HTM[4963]="*maccudheyyaṃ suduttaraṃ.**Death’s domain so hard to pass.*";
P_HTM[4964]="*Kaṇhaṃ dhammaṃ vippahāya,**Rid of dark qualities,*";
P_HTM[4965]="*sukkaṃ bhāvetha paṇḍito;**an astute person should develop the bright.*";
P_HTM[4966]="*Okā anokamāgamma,**Leaving home behind*";
P_HTM[4967]="*viveke yattha dūramaṃ.**for the seclusion so hard to enjoy,*";
P_HTM[4968]="*Tatrābhiratimiccheyya,**you should try to find delight there,*";
P_HTM[4969]="*hitvā kāme akiñcano;**having left behind sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[4970]="*Pariyodapeyya attānaṃ,**With no possessions, an astute person*";
P_HTM[4971]="*cittaklesehi paṇḍito.**should cleanse themselves of mental corruptions.*";
P_HTM[4972]="*Yesaṃ sambodhiyaṅgesu,**And those whose minds are rightly developed*";
P_HTM[4973]="*sammā cittaṃ subhāvitaṃ;**in the awakening factors;*";
P_HTM[4974]="*Ādānapaṭinissagge,**letting go of attachments,*";
P_HTM[4975]="*anupādāya ye ratā;**they delight in not grasping.*";
P_HTM[4976]="*Khīṇāsavā jutimanto,**With defilements ended, brilliant,*";
P_HTM[4977]="*te loke parinibbutā”ti.**they are extinguished in this world.”*";
P_HTM[4978]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4979]="*5. Paṭhamaadhammasuttaṃ**Bad Principles (1st)*";
P_HTM[4980]="*“Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo anattho ca;**“Mendicants, you should know bad principles with bad results.*";
P_HTM[4981]="*dhammo ca veditabbo attho ca.**And you should know good principles with good results.*";
P_HTM[4982]="*Adhammañca viditvā anatthañca, dhammañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabbaṃ.**Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results.*";
P_HTM[4983]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, adhammo ca anattho ca?**And what are bad principles with bad results?*";
P_HTM[4984]="*Pāṇātipāto, adinnādānaṃ, kāmesumicchācāro, musāvādo, pisuṇā vācā, pharusā vācā, samphappalāpo, abhijjhā, byāpādo, micchādiṭṭhi—**Killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; covetousness, ill will, and wrong view.*";
P_HTM[4985]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhammo ca anattho ca.**These are called bad principles with bad results.*";
P_HTM[4986]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, dhammo ca attho ca?**And what are good principles with good results?*";
P_HTM[4987]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī, adinnādānā veramaṇī, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇī, musāvādā veramaṇī, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī, samphappalāpā veramaṇī, anabhijjhā, abyāpādo, sammādiṭṭhi—**Avoiding killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; avoiding speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; contentment, good will, and right view.*";
P_HTM[4988]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhammo ca attho ca.**These are called good principles with good results.*";
P_HTM[4989]="*‘Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo anattho ca;**‘You should know bad principles with bad results.*";
P_HTM[4990]="*dhammo ca veditabbo attho ca.**And you should know good principles with good results.*";
P_HTM[4991]="*Adhammañca viditvā anatthañca, dhammañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti,**Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results.’*";
P_HTM[4992]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttan”ti.**That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.”*";
P_HTM[4993]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4994]="*6. Dutiyaadhammasuttaṃ**Bad Principles (2nd)*";
P_HTM[4995]="*“Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo dhammo ca;**“Mendicants, you should know bad principles and good principles.*";
P_HTM[4996]="*anattho ca veditabbo attho ca.**And you should know bad results and good results.*";
P_HTM[4997]="*Adhammañca viditvā dhammañca, anatthañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabban”ti.**Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results.”*";
P_HTM[4998]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[4999]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ pāvisi.**When he had spoken, the Holy One got up from his seat and entered his dwelling.*";
P_HTM[5000]="*Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:**Soon after the Buddha left, those mendicants considered,*";
P_HTM[5001]="*“idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:**“The Buddha gave this brief passage for recitation, then entered his dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail.*";
P_HTM[5002]="*‘adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo dhammo ca;**‘You should know bad principles and good principles.*";
P_HTM[5003]="*anattho ca veditabbo attho ca.**And you should know bad results and good results.*";
P_HTM[5004]="*Adhammañca viditvā dhammañca, anatthañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti.**Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results.’*";
P_HTM[5005]="*Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā”ti?**Who can explain in detail the meaning of this brief passage for recitation given by the Buddha?”*";
P_HTM[5006]="*Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi:**Then those mendicants thought,*";
P_HTM[5007]="*“ayaṃ kho āyasmā mahākaccāno satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito, sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ.**“This Venerable Mahākaccāna is praised by the Buddha and esteemed by his sensible spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[5008]="*Pahoti cāyasmā mahākaccāno imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.**He is capable of explaining in detail the meaning of this brief passage for recitation given by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[5009]="*Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etamatthaṃ puccheyyāma.**Let’s go to him, and ask him about this matter.*";
P_HTM[5010]="*Yathā no āyasmā mahākaccāno byākarissati tathā naṃ dhāressāmā”ti.**As he answers, so we’ll remember it.”*";
P_HTM[5011]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā mahākaccānena saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu.**Then those mendicants went to Mahākaccāna, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[5012]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etadavocuṃ:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one side. They told him what had happened, and said,*";
P_HTM[5013]="*“Idaṃ kho no, āvuso kaccāna, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:* **";
P_HTM[5014]="*‘adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo dhammo ca;* **";
P_HTM[5015]="*anattho ca veditabbo attho ca.* **";
P_HTM[5016]="*Adhammañca viditvā dhammañca, anatthañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5017]="*Tesaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[5018]="*‘idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho—* **";
P_HTM[5019]="*adhammo ca, bhikkhave … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5020]="*tathā paṭipajjitabbanti.* **";
P_HTM[5021]="*Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā’ti?* **";
P_HTM[5022]="*Tesaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[5023]="*‘ayaṃ kho āyasmā mahākaccāno satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito, sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5024]="*Pahoti cāyasmā mahākaccāno imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5025]="*Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāma.* **";
P_HTM[5026]="*Yathā no āyasmā mahākaccāno byākarissati tathā naṃ dhāressāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5027]="*Vibhajatu āyasmā mahākaccāno”ti.**“May Venerable Mahākaccāna please explain this.”*";
P_HTM[5028]="*“Seyyathāpi, āvuso, puriso sāratthiko sāraṃ gavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva mūlaṃ atikkamma khandhaṃ sākhāpalāse sāraṃ pariyesitabbaṃ maññeyya.**“Reverends, suppose there was a person in need of heartwood. And while wandering in search of heartwood he’d come across a large tree standing with heartwood. But he’d pass over the roots and trunk, imagining that the heartwood should be sought in the branches and leaves.*";
P_HTM[5029]="*Evaṃsampadamidaṃ āyasmantānaṃ satthari sammukhībhūte taṃ bhagavantaṃ atisitvā amhe etamatthaṃ paṭipucchitabbaṃ maññatha.**Such is the consequence for the venerables. Though you were face to face with the Buddha, you passed him by, imagining that you should ask me about this matter.*";
P_HTM[5030]="*So hāvuso, bhagavā jānaṃ jānāti passaṃ passati cakkhubhūto ñāṇabhūto dhammabhūto brahmabhūto vattā pavattā atthassa ninnetā amatassa dātā dhammassāmī tathāgato.**For he is the Buddha, who knows and sees. He is vision, he is knowledge, he is the truth, he is holiness. He is the teacher, the proclaimer, the elucidator of meaning, the bestower of the deathless, the lord of truth, the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[5031]="*So ceva panetassa kālo ahosi yaṃ tumhe bhagavantaṃyeva upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyātha.**That was the time to approach the Buddha and ask about this matter.*";
P_HTM[5032]="*Yathā vo bhagavā byākareyya tathā naṃ dhāreyyāthā”ti.**You should have remembered it in line with the Buddha’s answer.”*";
P_HTM[5033]="*“Addhā, āvuso kaccāna, bhagavā jānaṃ jānāti passaṃ passati cakkhubhūto ñāṇabhūto dhammabhūto brahmabhūto vattā pavattā atthassa ninnetā amatassa dātā dhammassāmī tathāgato.**“Certainly he is the Buddha, who knows and sees. He is vision, he is knowledge, he is the truth, he is holiness. He is the teacher, the proclaimer, the elucidator of meaning, the bestower of the deathless, the lord of truth, the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[5034]="*So ceva panetassa kālo ahosi yaṃ mayaṃ bhagavantaṃyeva upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāma.**That was the time to approach the Buddha and ask about this matter.*";
P_HTM[5035]="*Yathā no bhagavā byākareyya tathā naṃ dhāreyyāma.**We should have remembered it in line with the Buddha’s answer.*";
P_HTM[5036]="*Api cāyasmā mahākaccāno satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito, sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ.**Still, Venerable Mahākaccāna is praised by the Buddha and esteemed by his sensible spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[5037]="*Pahoti cāyasmā mahākaccāno imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.**He is capable of explaining in detail the meaning of this brief passage for recitation given by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[5038]="*Vibhajatāyasmā mahākaccāno agaruṃ karitvā”ti.**Please explain this, if it’s no trouble.”*";
P_HTM[5039]="*“Tena hāvuso, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, reverends, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[5040]="*“Evaṃ, āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahākaccānassa paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[5041]="*Athāyasmā mahākaccāno etadavoca:**Mahākaccāna said this:*";
P_HTM[5042]="*“Yaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:**“Reverends, the Buddha gave this brief passage for recitation, then entered his dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail:*";
P_HTM[5043]="*‘adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo … pe …**‘You should know bad principles and good principles …*";
P_HTM[5044]="*tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti.**and practice accordingly.’*";
P_HTM[5045]="*Katamo cāvuso, adhammo; katamo ca dhammo?**So what are bad principles? What are good principles?*";
P_HTM[5046]="*Katamo ca anattho, katamo ca attho?**What are bad results? And what are good results?*";
P_HTM[5047]="*Pāṇātipāto, āvuso, adhammo;**Killing living creatures is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5048]="*pāṇātipātā veramaṇī dhammo;**Not killing living creatures is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[5049]="*ye ca pāṇātipātapaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by killing living creatures are bad results.*";
P_HTM[5050]="*pāṇātipātā veramaṇipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho.**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of not killing living creatures are good results.*";
P_HTM[5051]="*Adinnādānaṃ, āvuso, adhammo;**Stealing is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5052]="*adinnādānā veramaṇī dhammo;**Not stealing is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[5053]="*ye ca adinnādānapaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by stealing are bad results.*";
P_HTM[5054]="*adinnādānā veramaṇipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho.**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of not stealing are good results.*";
P_HTM[5055]="*Kāmesumicchācāro, āvuso, adhammo;**Sexual misconduct is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5056]="*kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇī dhammo;**Avoiding sexual misconduct is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[5057]="*ye ca kāmesumicchācārapaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by sexual misconduct are bad results.*";
P_HTM[5058]="*kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho.**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of avoiding sexual misconduct are good results.*";
P_HTM[5059]="*Musāvādo, āvuso, adhammo;**Lying is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5060]="*musāvādā veramaṇī dhammo;**Not lying is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[5061]="*ye ca musāvādapaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by lying are bad results.*";
P_HTM[5062]="*musāvādā veramaṇipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho.**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of not lying are good results.*";
P_HTM[5063]="*Pisuṇā vācā, āvuso, adhammo;**Divisive speech is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5064]="*pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī dhammo;**Avoiding divisive speech is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[5065]="*ye ca pisuṇāvācāpaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by divisive speech are bad results.*";
P_HTM[5066]="*pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho.**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of avoiding divisive speech are good results.*";
P_HTM[5067]="*Pharusā vācā, āvuso, adhammo;**Harsh speech is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5068]="*pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī dhammo;**Avoiding harsh speech is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[5069]="*ye ca pharusāvācāpaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by harsh speech are bad results.*";
P_HTM[5070]="*pharusāya vācāya veramaṇipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho.**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of avoiding harsh speech are good results.*";
P_HTM[5071]="*Samphappalāpo, āvuso, adhammo;**Talking nonsense is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5072]="*samphappalāpā veramaṇī dhammo;**Avoiding talking nonsense is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[5073]="*ye ca samphappalāpapaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by talking nonsense are bad results.*";
P_HTM[5074]="*samphappalāpā veramaṇipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho.**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of avoiding talking nonsense are good results.*";
P_HTM[5075]="*Abhijjhā, āvuso, adhammo;**Covetousness is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5076]="*anabhijjhā dhammo;**Contentment is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[5077]="*ye ca abhijjhāpaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by covetousness are bad results.*";
P_HTM[5078]="*anabhijjhāpaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho.**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of contentment are good results.*";
P_HTM[5079]="*Byāpādo, āvuso, adhammo;**Ill will is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5080]="*abyāpādo dhammo;**Good will is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[5081]="*ye ca byāpādapaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by ill will are bad results.*";
P_HTM[5082]="*abyāpādapaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho.**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of good will are good results.*";
P_HTM[5083]="*Micchādiṭṭhi, āvuso, adhammo;**Wrong view is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5084]="*sammādiṭṭhi dhammo;**Right view is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[5085]="*ye ca micchādiṭṭhipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong view are bad results.*";
P_HTM[5086]="*sammādiṭṭhipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho.**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of right view are good results.*";
P_HTM[5087]="*‘Yaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho—**The Buddha gave this brief passage for recitation, then entered his dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail:*";
P_HTM[5088]="*adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo … pe …**‘You should know bad principles and good principles …*";
P_HTM[5089]="*tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti.**and practice accordingly.’*";
P_HTM[5090]="*Imassa kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa evaṃ vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmi.**And this is how I understand the detailed meaning of this passage for recitation.*";
P_HTM[5091]="*Ākaṅkhamānā ca pana tumhe, āvuso, bhagavantaṃyeva upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyātha.**If you wish, you may go to the Buddha and ask him about this.*";
P_HTM[5092]="*Yathā no bhagavā byākaroti tathā naṃ dhāreyyāthā”ti.**You should remember it in line with the Buddha’s answer.”*";
P_HTM[5093]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahākaccānassa bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**“Yes, reverend,” said those mendicants, approving and agreeing with what Mahākaccāna said. Then they rose from their seats and went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. Then they said:*";
P_HTM[5094]="*“Yaṃ kho no, bhante, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:* **";
P_HTM[5095]="*‘adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5096]="*tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5097]="*Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[5098]="*‘idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:* **";
P_HTM[5099]="*“adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5100]="*tathā paṭipajjitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5101]="*Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā’ti?* **";
P_HTM[5102]="*Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[5103]="*‘ayaṃ kho āyasmā mahākaccāno satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito, sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5104]="*Pahoti cāyasmā mahākaccāno imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5105]="*Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāma.* **";
P_HTM[5106]="*Yathā no āyasmā mahākaccāno byākarissati tathā naṃ dhāressāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5107]="*Atha kho mayaṃ, bhante, yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkamimhā; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etamatthaṃ apucchimhā.**“Sir, we went to Mahākaccāna and asked him about this matter.*";
P_HTM[5108]="*Tesaṃ no, bhante, āyasmatā mahākaccānena imehi akkharehi imehi padehi imehi byañjanehi attho suvibhatto”ti.**And Mahākaccāna clearly explained the meaning to us in this manner, with these words and phrases.”*";
P_HTM[5109]="*“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhave.**“Good, good, mendicants!*";
P_HTM[5110]="*Paṇḍito, bhikkhave, mahākaccāno. Mahāpañño, bhikkhave, mahākaccāno.**Mahākaccāna is astute, he has great wisdom.*";
P_HTM[5111]="*Mañcepi tumhe, bhikkhave, upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyātha, ahampi cetaṃ evamevaṃ byākareyyaṃ yathā taṃ mahākaccānena byākataṃ.**If you came to me and asked this question, I would answer it in exactly the same way as Mahākaccāna.*";
P_HTM[5112]="*Eso ceva tassa attho. Evañca naṃ dhāreyyāthā”ti.**That is what it means, and that’s how you should remember it.”*";
P_HTM[5113]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5114]="*7. Tatiyaadhammasuttaṃ**Bad Principles (3rd)*";
P_HTM[5115]="*“Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo dhammo ca;**“Mendicants, you should know bad principles and good principles.*";
P_HTM[5116]="*anattho ca veditabbo attho ca.**And you should know bad results and good results.*";
P_HTM[5117]="*Adhammañca viditvā dhammañca, anatthañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabbaṃ.**Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results.*";
P_HTM[5118]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, adhammo, katamo ca dhammo;**So what are bad principles? What are good principles? What are bad results? And what are good results?*";
P_HTM[5119]="*katamo ca anattho, katamo ca attho?* **";
P_HTM[5120]="*Pāṇātipāto, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Killing living creatures is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5121]="*pāṇātipātā veramaṇī dhammo;**Not killing living creatures is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[5122]="*ye ca pāṇātipātapaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by killing living creatures are bad results.*";
P_HTM[5123]="*pāṇātipātā veramaṇipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho.**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of not killing living creatures are good results.*";
P_HTM[5124]="*Adinnādānaṃ, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Stealing is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5125]="*adinnādānā veramaṇī dhammo …**Not stealing is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[5126]="*kāmesumicchācāro, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Sexual misconduct is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5127]="*kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇī dhammo …**Avoiding sexual misconduct is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[5128]="*musāvādo, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Lying is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5129]="*musāvādā veramaṇī dhammo …**Not lying is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[5130]="*pisuṇā vācā, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Divisive speech is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5131]="*pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī dhammo …**Avoiding divisive speech is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[5132]="*pharusā vācā, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Harsh speech is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5133]="*pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī dhammo …**Avoiding harsh speech is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[5134]="*samphappalāpo, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Talking nonsense is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5135]="*samphappalāpā veramaṇī dhammo …**Avoiding talking nonsense is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[5136]="*abhijjhā, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Covetousness is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5137]="*anabhijjhā dhammo …**Contentment is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[5138]="*byāpādo, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Ill will is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5139]="*abyāpādo dhammo ….**Good will is a good principle. …*";
P_HTM[5140]="*Micchādiṭṭhi, bhikkhave, adhammo;**Wrong view is a bad principle.*";
P_HTM[5141]="*sammādiṭṭhi dhammo;**Right view is a good principle.*";
P_HTM[5142]="*ye ca micchādiṭṭhipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, ayaṃ anattho;**And the many bad, unskillful qualities produced by wrong view are bad results.*";
P_HTM[5143]="*sammādiṭṭhipaccayā ca aneke kusalā dhammā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, ayaṃ attho.**And the many skillful qualities fully developed because of right view are good results.*";
P_HTM[5144]="*‘Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo dhammo ca;**‘You should know bad principles and good principles.*";
P_HTM[5145]="*anattho ca veditabbo attho ca.**And you should know bad results and good results.*";
P_HTM[5146]="*Adhammañca viditvā dhammañca, anatthañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti,**Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results.’*";
P_HTM[5147]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttan”ti.**That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.”*";
P_HTM[5148]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5149]="*8. Kammanidānasuttaṃ**Sources of Deeds*";
P_HTM[5150]="*“Pāṇātipātampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, tividhaṃ vadāmi—**“Mendicants, I say that killing living creatures is threefold:*";
P_HTM[5151]="*lobhahetukampi, dosahetukampi, mohahetukampi.**caused by greed, hate, or delusion.*";
P_HTM[5152]="*Adinnādānampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, tividhaṃ vadāmi—**I say that stealing is threefold:*";
P_HTM[5153]="*lobhahetukampi, dosahetukampi, mohahetukampi.**caused by greed, hate, or delusion.*";
P_HTM[5154]="*Kāmesumicchācārampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, tividhaṃ vadāmi—**I say that sexual misconduct is threefold:*";
P_HTM[5155]="*lobhahetukampi, dosahetukampi, mohahetukampi.**caused by greed, hate, or delusion.*";
P_HTM[5156]="*Musāvādampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, tividhaṃ vadāmi—**I say that lying is threefold:*";
P_HTM[5157]="*lobhahetukampi, dosahetukampi, mohahetukampi.**caused by greed, hate, or delusion.*";
P_HTM[5158]="*Pisuṇavācampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, tividhaṃ vadāmi—**I say that divisive speech is threefold:*";
P_HTM[5159]="*lobhahetukampi, dosahetukampi, mohahetukampi.**caused by greed, hate, or delusion.*";
P_HTM[5160]="*Pharusavācampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, tividhaṃ vadāmi—**I say that harsh speech is threefold:*";
P_HTM[5161]="*lobhahetukampi, dosahetukampi, mohahetukampi.**caused by greed, hate, or delusion.*";
P_HTM[5162]="*Samphappalāpampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, tividhaṃ vadāmi—**I say that talking nonsense is threefold:*";
P_HTM[5163]="*lobhahetukampi, dosahetukampi, mohahetukampi.**caused by greed, hate, or delusion.*";
P_HTM[5164]="*Abhijjhampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, tividhaṃ vadāmi—**I say that covetousness is threefold:*";
P_HTM[5165]="*lobhahetukampi, dosahetukampi, mohahetukampi.**caused by greed, hate, or delusion.*";
P_HTM[5166]="*Byāpādampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, tividhaṃ vadāmi—**I say that ill will is threefold:*";
P_HTM[5167]="*lobhahetukampi, dosahetukampi, mohahetukampi.**caused by greed, hate, or delusion.*";
P_HTM[5168]="*Micchādiṭṭhimpāhaṃ, bhikkhave, tividhaṃ vadāmi—**I say that wrong view is threefold:*";
P_HTM[5169]="*lobhahetukampi, dosahetukampi, mohahetukampi.**caused by greed, hate, or delusion.*";
P_HTM[5170]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, lobho kammanidānasambhavo, doso kammanidānasambhavo, moho kammanidānasambhavo.**And so greed, hate, and delusion are sources and origins for deeds.*";
P_HTM[5171]="*Lobhakkhayā kammanidānasaṅkhayo, dosakkhayā kammanidānasaṅkhayo, mohakkhayā kammanidānasaṅkhayo”ti.**With the ending of greed, hate, and delusion, the sources of deeds are ended.”*";
P_HTM[5172]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5173]="*9. Parikkamanasuttaṃ**The Bypass*";
P_HTM[5174]="*“Saparikkamano ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo aparikkamano.**“Mendicants, this teaching provides a bypass, it doesn’t lack a bypass.*";
P_HTM[5175]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, saparikkamano ayaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo aparikkamano?**And how does this teaching provide a bypass, not lacking a bypass?*";
P_HTM[5176]="*Pāṇātipātissa, bhikkhave, pāṇātipātā veramaṇī parikkamanaṃ hoti.**Not killing living creatures bypasses killing living creatures.*";
P_HTM[5177]="*Adinnādāyissa, bhikkhave, adinnādānā veramaṇī parikkamanaṃ hoti.**Not stealing bypasses stealing.*";
P_HTM[5178]="*Kāmesumicchācārissa, bhikkhave, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇī parikkamanaṃ hoti.**Avoiding sexual misconduct bypasses sexual misconduct.*";
P_HTM[5179]="*Musāvādissa, bhikkhave, musāvādā veramaṇī parikkamanaṃ hoti.**Not lying bypasses lying.*";
P_HTM[5180]="*Pisuṇavācassa, bhikkhave, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī parikkamanaṃ hoti.**Avoiding divisive speech bypasses divisive speech.*";
P_HTM[5181]="*Pharusavācassa, bhikkhave, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī parikkamanaṃ hoti.**Avoiding harsh speech bypasses harsh speech.*";
P_HTM[5182]="*Samphappalāpissa, bhikkhave, samphappalāpā veramaṇī parikkamanaṃ hoti.**Avoiding talking nonsense bypasses talking nonsense.*";
P_HTM[5183]="*Abhijjhālussa, bhikkhave, anabhijjhā parikkamanaṃ hoti.**Contentment bypasses covetousness.*";
P_HTM[5184]="*Byāpannacittassa, bhikkhave, abyāpādo parikkamanaṃ hoti.**Good will bypasses ill will.*";
P_HTM[5185]="*Micchādiṭṭhissa, bhikkhave, sammādiṭṭhi parikkamanaṃ hoti.**Right view bypasses wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5186]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, saparikkamano ayaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo aparikkamano”ti.**That’s how this teaching provides a bypass, it doesn’t lack a bypass.”*";
P_HTM[5187]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5188]="*10. Cundasuttaṃ**With Cunda*";
P_HTM[5189]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5190]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā pāvāyaṃ viharati cundassa kammāraputtassa ambavane.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Pāvā in Cunda the smith’s mango grove.*";
P_HTM[5191]="*Atha kho cundo kammāraputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho cundaṃ kammāraputtaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then Cunda the smith went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[5192]="*“kassa no tvaṃ, cunda, soceyyāni rocesī”ti?**“Cunda, whose purity do you believe in?”*";
P_HTM[5193]="*“Brāhmaṇā, bhante, pacchābhūmakā kamaṇḍalukā sevālamālikā aggiparicārikā udakorohakā soceyyāni paññapenti; tesāhaṃ soceyyāni rocemī”ti.**“Sir, I believe in the purity advocated by the western brahmins draped with moss who carry pitchers, serve the sacred flame, and immerse themselves in water.”*";
P_HTM[5194]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana, cunda, brāhmaṇā pacchābhūmakā kamaṇḍalukā sevālamālikā aggiparicārikā udakorohakā soceyyāni paññapentī”ti?**“But Cunda, what kind of purity do these western brahmins advocate?”*";
P_HTM[5195]="*“Idha, bhante, brāhmaṇā pacchābhūmakā kamaṇḍalukā sevālamālikā aggiparicārikā udakorohakā. Te sāvakaṃ evaṃ samādapenti:**“The western brahmins encourage their disciples like this:*";
P_HTM[5196]="*‘ehi tvaṃ, ambho purisa, kālasseva uṭṭhahantova sayanamhā pathaviṃ āmaseyyāsi;**‘Please, good people, rising early you should stroke the earth from your bed.*";
P_HTM[5197]="*no ce pathaviṃ āmaseyyāsi, allāni gomayāni āmaseyyāsi;**If you don’t stroke the earth, stroke fresh cow dung.*";
P_HTM[5198]="*no ce allāni gomayāni āmaseyyāsi, haritāni tiṇāni āmaseyyāsi;**If you don’t stroke fresh cow dung, stroke green grass.*";
P_HTM[5199]="*no ce haritāni tiṇāni āmaseyyāsi, aggiṃ paricareyyāsi;**If you don’t stroke green grass, serve the sacred flame.*";
P_HTM[5200]="*no ce aggiṃ paricareyyāsi, pañjaliko ādiccaṃ namasseyyāsi;**If you don’t serve the sacred flame, revere the sun with joined palms.*";
P_HTM[5201]="*no ce pañjaliko ādiccaṃ namasseyyāsi, sāyatatiyakaṃ udakaṃ oroheyyāsī’ti.**If you don’t revere the sun with joined palms, immerse yourself in water three times, including the evening.’*";
P_HTM[5202]="*Evaṃ kho, bhante, brāhmaṇā pacchābhūmakā kamaṇḍalukā sevālamālikā aggiparicārikā udakorohakā soceyyāni paññapenti; tesāhaṃ soceyyāni rocemī”ti.**The western brahmins advocate this kind of purity.”*";
P_HTM[5203]="*“Aññathā kho, cunda, brāhmaṇā pacchābhūmakā kamaṇḍalukā sevālamālikā aggiparicārikā udakorohakā soceyyāni paññapenti, aññathā ca pana ariyassa vinaye soceyyaṃ hotī”ti.**“The purity advocated by the western brahmins is quite different from that in the training of the noble one.”*";
P_HTM[5204]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana, bhante, ariyassa vinaye soceyyaṃ hoti?**“But what, Master Gotama, is purity in the training of the noble one?*";
P_HTM[5205]="*Sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā tathā dhammaṃ desetu yathā ariyassa vinaye soceyyaṃ hotī”ti.**Master Gotama, please teach me this.”*";
P_HTM[5206]="*“Tena hi, cunda, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, brahmin, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[5207]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho cundo kammāraputto bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” Cunda replied.*";
P_HTM[5208]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[5209]="*“Tividhaṃ kho, cunda, kāyena asoceyyaṃ hoti;**“Cunda, impurity is threefold by way of body,*";
P_HTM[5210]="*catubbidhaṃ vācāya asoceyyaṃ hoti;**fourfold by way of speech,*";
P_HTM[5211]="*tividhaṃ manasā asoceyyaṃ hoti.**and threefold by way of mind.*";
P_HTM[5212]="*Kathañca, cunda, tividhaṃ kāyena asoceyyaṃ hoti?**And how is impurity threefold by way of body?*";
P_HTM[5213]="*Idha, cunda, ekacco pāṇātipātī hoti luddo lohitapāṇi hatapahate niviṭṭho adayāpanno sabbapāṇabhūtesu. (1)**It’s when a certain person kills living creatures. They’re violent, bloody-handed, a hardened killer, merciless to living beings.*";
P_HTM[5214]="*Adinnādāyī hoti. Yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ gāmagataṃ vā araññagataṃ vā taṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādātā hoti. (2)**They steal. With the intention to commit theft, they take the wealth or belongings of others from village or wilderness.*";
P_HTM[5215]="*Kāmesumicchācārī hoti. Yā tā māturakkhitā piturakkhitā mātāpiturakkhitā bhāturakkhitā bhaginirakkhitā ñātirakkhitā gottarakkhitā dhammarakkhitā sasāmikā saparidaṇḍā antamaso mālāguḷaparikkhittāpi, tathārūpāsu cārittaṃ āpajjitā hoti. (3)**They commit sexual misconduct. They have sexual relations with women who have their mother, father, both mother and father, brother, sister, relatives, or clan as guardian. They have sexual relations with a woman who is protected on principle, or who has a husband, or whose violation is punishable by law, or even one who has been garlanded as a token of betrothal.*";
P_HTM[5216]="*Evaṃ kho, cunda, tividhaṃ kāyena asoceyyaṃ hoti.**This is the threefold impurity by way of body.*";
P_HTM[5217]="*Kathañca, cunda, catubbidhaṃ vācāya asoceyyaṃ hoti?**And how is impurity fourfold by way of speech?*";
P_HTM[5218]="*Idha, cunda, ekacco musāvādī hoti. Sabhaggato vā parisaggato vā ñātimajjhagato vā pūgamajjhagato vā rājakulamajjhagato vā abhinīto sakkhipuṭṭho: ‘ehambho purisa, yaṃ jānāsi taṃ vadehī’ti, so ajānaṃ vā āha: ‘jānāmī’ti, jānaṃ vā āha: ‘na jānāmī’ti; apassaṃ vā āha: ‘passāmī’ti, passaṃ vā āha: ‘na passāmī’ti. Iti attahetu vā parahetu vā āmisakiñcikkhahetu vā sampajānamusā bhāsitā hoti. (4)**It’s when a certain person lies. They’re summoned to a council, an assembly, a family meeting, a guild, or to the royal court, and asked to bear witness: ‘Please, mister, say what you know.’ Not knowing, they say ‘I know.’ Knowing, they say ‘I don’t know.’ Not seeing, they say ‘I see.’ And seeing, they say ‘I don’t see.’ So they deliberately lie for the sake of themselves or another, or for some trivial worldly reason.*";
P_HTM[5219]="*Pisuṇavāco hoti. Ito sutvā amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, amutra vā sutvā imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya. Iti samaggānaṃ vā bhettā, bhinnānaṃ vā anuppadātā, vaggārāmo vaggarato vagganandī vaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. (5)**They speak divisively. They repeat in one place what they heard in another so as to divide people against each other. And so they divide those who are harmonious, supporting division, delighting in division, loving division, speaking words that promote division.*";
P_HTM[5220]="*Pharusavāco hoti. Yā sā vācā aṇḍakā kakkasā parakaṭukā parābhisajjanī kodhasāmantā asamādhisaṃvattanikā, tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. (6)**They speak harshly. They use the kinds of words that are cruel, nasty, hurtful, offensive, bordering on anger, not leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[5221]="*Samphappalāpī hoti akālavādī abhūtavādī anatthavādī adhammavādī avinayavādī; anidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti akālena anapadesaṃ apariyantavatiṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ.**They talk nonsense. Their speech is untimely, and is neither factual nor beneficial. It has nothing to do with the teaching or the training. Their words have no value, and are untimely, unreasonable, rambling, and pointless.*";
P_HTM[5222]="*Evaṃ kho, cunda, catubbidhaṃ vācāya asoceyyaṃ hoti. (7)**This is the fourfold impurity by way of speech.*";
P_HTM[5223]="*Kathañca, cunda, tividhaṃ manasā asoceyyaṃ hoti?**And how is impurity threefold by way of mind?*";
P_HTM[5224]="*Idha, cunda, ekacco abhijjhālu hoti. Yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ taṃ abhijjhātā hoti: ‘aho vata yaṃ parassa taṃ mamassā’ti. (8)**It’s when a certain person is covetous. They covet the wealth and belongings of others: ‘Oh, if only their belongings were mine!’*";
P_HTM[5225]="*Byāpannacitto hoti paduṭṭhamanasaṅkappo: ‘ime sattā haññantu vā bajjhantu vā ucchijjantu vā vinassantu vā mā vā ahesun’ti. (9)**They have ill will and hateful intentions: ‘May these sentient beings be killed, slaughtered, slain, destroyed, or annihilated!’*";
P_HTM[5226]="*Micchādiṭṭhiko hoti viparītadassano:**They have wrong view. Their perspective is distorted:*";
P_HTM[5227]="*‘natthi dinnaṃ, natthi yiṭṭhaṃ, natthi hutaṃ, natthi sukaṭadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, natthi ayaṃ loko, natthi paro loko, natthi mātā, natthi pitā, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi loke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sammaggatā sammāpaṭipannā ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti.**‘There’s no meaning in giving, sacrifice, or offerings. There’s no fruit or result of good and bad deeds. There’s no afterlife. There’s no obligation to mother and father. No beings are reborn spontaneously. And there’s no ascetic or brahmin who is well attained and practiced, and who describes the afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.’*";
P_HTM[5228]="*Evaṃ kho, cunda, manasā tividhaṃ asoceyyaṃ hoti. (10)**This is the threefold impurity by way of mind.*";
P_HTM[5229]="*Ime kho, cunda, dasa akusalakammapathā.**These are the ten ways of doing unskillful deeds.*";
P_HTM[5230]="*Imehi kho, cunda, dasahi akusalehi kammapathehi samannāgato kālasseva uṭṭhahantova sayanamhā pathaviñcepi āmasati, asuciyeva hoti; no cepi pathaviṃ āmasati, asuciyeva hoti.**When you have these ten ways of doing unskillful deeds, then if you rise early, whether or not you stroke the earth from your bed, you’re still impure.*";
P_HTM[5231]="*Allāni cepi gomayāni āmasati, asuciyeva hoti; no cepi allāni gomayāni āmasati, asuciyeva hoti.**Whether or not you stroke fresh cow dung, you’re still impure.*";
P_HTM[5232]="*Haritāni cepi tiṇāni āmasati, asuciyeva hoti; no cepi haritāni tiṇāni āmasati, asuciyeva hoti.**Whether or not you stroke green grass, you’re still impure.*";
P_HTM[5233]="*Aggiñcepi paricarati, asuciyeva hoti, no cepi aggiṃ paricarati, asuciyeva hoti.**Whether or not you serve the sacred flame, you’re still impure.*";
P_HTM[5234]="*Pañjaliko cepi ādiccaṃ namassati, asuciyeva hoti; no cepi pañjaliko ādiccaṃ namassati, asuciyeva hoti.**Whether or not you revere the sun with joined palms, you’re still impure.*";
P_HTM[5235]="*Sāyatatiyakañcepi udakaṃ orohati, asuciyeva hoti; no cepi sāyatatiyakaṃ udakaṃ orohati, asuciyeva hoti.**Whether or not you immerse yourself in water three times, you’re still impure.*";
P_HTM[5236]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[5237]="*Ime, cunda, dasa akusalakammapathā asucīyeva honti asucikaraṇā ca.**These ten ways of doing unskillful deeds are impure and make things impure.*";
P_HTM[5238]="*Imesaṃ pana, cunda, dasannaṃ akusalānaṃ kammapathānaṃ samannāgamanahetu nirayo paññāyati, tiracchānayoni paññāyati, pettivisayo paññāyati, yā vā panaññāpi kāci duggatiyo.**It’s because of those who do these ten kinds of unskillful deeds that hell, the animal realm, the ghost realm, or any other bad places are found.*";
P_HTM[5239]="*Tividhaṃ kho, cunda, kāyena soceyyaṃ hoti;**Cunda, purity is threefold by way of body,*";
P_HTM[5240]="*catubbidhaṃ vācāya soceyyaṃ hoti;**fourfold by way of speech,*";
P_HTM[5241]="*tividhaṃ manasā soceyyaṃ hoti.**and threefold by way of mind.*";
P_HTM[5242]="*Kathaṃ, cunda, tividhaṃ kāyena soceyyaṃ hoti?**And how is purity threefold by way of body?*";
P_HTM[5243]="*Idha, cunda, ekacco pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho, lajjī dayāpanno, sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati. (1)**It’s when a certain person gives up killing living creatures. They renounce the rod and the sword. They’re scrupulous and kind, living full of compassion for all living beings.*";
P_HTM[5244]="*Adinnādānaṃ pahāya, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti. Yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ gāmagataṃ vā araññagataṃ vā, na taṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādātā hoti. (2)**They give up stealing. They don’t, with the intention to commit theft, take the wealth or belongings of others from village or wilderness.*";
P_HTM[5245]="*Kāmesumicchācāraṃ pahāya, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti yā tā māturakkhitā piturakkhitā mātāpiturakkhitā bhāturakkhitā bhaginirakkhitā ñātirakkhitā gottarakkhitā dhammarakkhitā sasāmikā saparidaṇḍā antamaso mālāguḷaparikkhittāpi, tathārūpāsu na cārittaṃ āpajjitā hoti. (3)**They give up sexual misconduct. They don’t have sexual relations with women who have their mother, father, both mother and father, brother, sister, relatives, or clan as guardian. They don’t have sexual relations with a woman who is protected on principle, or who has a husband, or whose violation is punishable by law, or even one who has been garlanded as a token of betrothal.*";
P_HTM[5246]="*Evaṃ kho, cunda, tividhaṃ kāyena soceyyaṃ hoti.**This is the threefold purity by way of body.*";
P_HTM[5247]="*Kathañca, cunda, catubbidhaṃ vācāya soceyyaṃ hoti?**And how is purity fourfold by way of speech?*";
P_HTM[5248]="*Idha, cunda, ekacco musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti. Sabhaggato vā parisaggato vā ñātimajjhagato vā pūgamajjhagato vā rājakulamajjhagato vā abhinīto sakkhipuṭṭho: ‘ehambho purisa, yaṃ jānāsi taṃ vadehī’ti, so ajānaṃ vā āha: ‘na jānāmī’ti, jānaṃ vā āha: ‘jānāmī’ti, apassaṃ vā āha: ‘na passāmī’ti, passaṃ vā āha: ‘passāmī’ti. Iti attahetu vā parahetu vā āmisakiñcikkhahetu vā na sampajānamusā bhāsitā hoti. (4)**It’s when a certain person gives up lying. They’re summoned to a council, an assembly, a family meeting, a guild, or to the royal court, and asked to bear witness: ‘Please, mister, say what you know.’ Not knowing, they say ‘I don’t know.’ Knowing, they say ‘I know.’ Not seeing, they say ‘I don’t see.’ And seeing, they say ‘I see.’ So they don’t deliberately lie for the sake of themselves or another, or for some trivial worldly reason.*";
P_HTM[5249]="*Pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pahāya, pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti—na ito sutvā amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, na amutra vā sutvā imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya. Iti bhinnānaṃ vā sandhātā sahitānaṃ vā anuppadātā samaggārāmo samaggarato samagganandī samaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. (5)**They give up divisive speech. They don’t repeat in one place what they heard in another so as to divide people against each other. Instead, they reconcile those who are divided, supporting unity, delighting in harmony, loving harmony, speaking words that promote harmony.*";
P_HTM[5250]="*Pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti. Yā sā vācā nelā kaṇṇasukhā pemanīyā hadayaṅgamā porī bahujanakantā bahujanamanāpā, tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. (6)**They give up harsh speech. They speak in a way that’s mellow, pleasing to the ear, lovely, going to the heart, polite, likable and agreeable to the people.*";
P_HTM[5251]="*Samphappalāpaṃ pahāya, samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī;**They give up talking nonsense. Their words are timely, true, and meaningful, in line with the teaching and training.*";
P_HTM[5252]="*nidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti kālena sāpadesaṃ pariyantavatiṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ. (7)**They say things at the right time which are valuable, reasonable, succinct, and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[5253]="*Evaṃ kho, cunda, catubbidhaṃ vācāya soceyyaṃ hoti.**This is the fourfold purity by way of speech.*";
P_HTM[5254]="*Kathañca, cunda, tividhaṃ manasā soceyyaṃ hoti?**And how is purity threefold by way of mind?*";
P_HTM[5255]="*Idha, cunda, ekacco anabhijjhālu hoti. Yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ taṃ anabhijjhitā hoti: ‘aho vata yaṃ parassa taṃ mamassā’ti. (8)**It’s when a certain person is content. They don’t covet the wealth and belongings of others: ‘Oh, if only their belongings were mine!’*";
P_HTM[5256]="*Abyāpannacitto hoti appaduṭṭhamanasaṅkappo: ‘ime sattā averā hontu abyāpajjā, anīghā sukhī attānaṃ pariharantū’ti. (9)**They have a kind heart and loving intentions: ‘May these sentient beings live free of enmity and ill will, untroubled and happy!’*";
P_HTM[5257]="*Sammādiṭṭhiko hoti aviparītadassano:**They have right view, an undistorted perspective:*";
P_HTM[5258]="*‘atthi dinnaṃ, atthi yiṭṭhaṃ, atthi hutaṃ, atthi sukaṭadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, atthi ayaṃ loko, atthi paro loko, atthi mātā, atthi pitā, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi loke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sammaggatā sammāpaṭipannā ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti. (10)**‘There is meaning in giving, sacrifice, and offerings. There are fruits and results of good and bad deeds. There is an afterlife. There is obligation to mother and father. There are beings reborn spontaneously. And there are ascetics and brahmins who are well attained and practiced, and who describe the afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.’*";
P_HTM[5259]="*Evaṃ kho, cunda, tividhaṃ manasā soceyyaṃ hoti.**This is the threefold purity by way of mind.*";
P_HTM[5260]="*Ime kho, cunda, dasa kusalakammapathā.**These are the ten ways of doing skillful deeds.*";
P_HTM[5261]="*Imehi kho, cunda, dasahi kusalehi kammapathehi samannāgato kālasseva uṭṭhahantova sayanamhā pathaviñcepi āmasati, suciyeva hoti; no cepi pathaviṃ āmasati, suciyeva hoti.**When you have these ten ways of doing skillful deeds, then if you rise early, whether or not you stroke the earth from your bed, you’re still pure.*";
P_HTM[5262]="*Allāni cepi gomayāni āmasati, suciyeva hoti; no cepi allāni gomayāni āmasati, suciyeva hoti.**Whether or not you stroke fresh cow dung, you’re still pure.*";
P_HTM[5263]="*Haritāni cepi tiṇāni āmasati, suciyeva hoti; no cepi haritāni tiṇāni āmasati, suciyeva hoti.**Whether or not you stroke green grass, you’re still pure.*";
P_HTM[5264]="*Aggiñcepi paricarati, suciyeva hoti; no cepi aggiṃ paricarati, suciyeva hoti.**Whether or not you serve the sacred flame, you’re still pure.*";
P_HTM[5265]="*Pañjaliko cepi ādiccaṃ namassati, suciyeva hoti; no cepi pañjaliko ādiccaṃ namassati, suciyeva hoti.**Whether or not you revere the sun with joined palms, you’re still pure.*";
P_HTM[5266]="*Sāyatatiyakañcepi udakaṃ orohati, suciyeva hoti; no cepi sāyatatiyakaṃ udakaṃ orohati, suciyeva hoti.**Whether or not you immerse yourself in water three times, you’re still pure.*";
P_HTM[5267]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[5268]="*Ime, cunda, dasa kusalakammapathā sucīyeva honti sucikaraṇā ca.**These ten ways of doing skillful deeds are pure and make things pure.*";
P_HTM[5269]="*Imesaṃ pana, cunda, dasannaṃ kusalānaṃ kammapathānaṃ samannāgamanahetu devā paññāyanti, manussā paññāyanti, yā vā panaññāpi kāci sugatiyo”ti.**It’s because of those who do these ten kinds of skillful deeds that gods, humans, or any other good places are found.”*";
P_HTM[5270]="*Evaṃ vutte, cundo kammāraputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Cunda the smith said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[5271]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bhante … pe …**“Excellent, sir! Excellent! …*";
P_HTM[5272]="*upāsakaṃ maṃ, bhante, bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[5273]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5274]="*11. Jāṇussoṇisuttaṃ**With Jāṇussoṇi*";
P_HTM[5275]="*Atha kho jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the brahmin Jāṇussoṇi went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[5276]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[5277]="*“Mayamassu, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā nāma.**“We who are known as brahmins*";
P_HTM[5278]="*Dānāni dema, saddhāni karoma:**give gifts and perform memorial rites for the dead:*";
P_HTM[5279]="*‘idaṃ dānaṃ petānaṃ ñātisālohitānaṃ upakappatu, idaṃ dānaṃ petā ñātisālohitā paribhuñjantū’ti.**‘May this gift aid my departed relatives and family. May they partake of this gift.’*";
P_HTM[5280]="*Kacci taṃ, bho gotama, dānaṃ petānaṃ ñātisālohitānaṃ upakappati;**But does this gift really aid departed relatives and family?*";
P_HTM[5281]="*kacci te petā ñātisālohitā taṃ dānaṃ paribhuñjantī”ti?**Do they actually partake of it?”*";
P_HTM[5282]="*“Ṭhāne kho, brāhmaṇa, upakappati, no aṭṭhāne”ti.**“It aids them if the conditions are right, brahmin, but not if the conditions are wrong.”*";
P_HTM[5283]="*“Katamaṃ pana, bho gotama, ṭhānaṃ, katamaṃ aṭṭhānan”ti?**“Then, Master Gotama, what are the right and wrong conditions?”*";
P_HTM[5284]="*“Idha, brāhmaṇa, ekacco pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti, pisuṇavāco hoti, pharusavāco hoti, samphappalāpī hoti, abhijjhālu hoti, byāpannacitto hoti, micchādiṭṭhiko hoti.**“Brahmin, take someone who kills living creatures, steals, and commits sexual misconduct. They use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re covetous, malicious, with wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5285]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā nirayaṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in hell.*";
P_HTM[5286]="*Yo nerayikānaṃ sattānaṃ āhāro, tena so tattha yāpeti, tena so tattha tiṭṭhati.**There they survive feeding on the food of the hell beings.*";
P_HTM[5287]="*Idampi kho, brāhmaṇa, aṭṭhānaṃ yattha ṭhitassa taṃ dānaṃ na upakappati.**The conditions there are wrong, so the gift does not aid the one who lives there.*";
P_HTM[5288]="*Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekacco pāṇātipātī … pe … micchādiṭṭhiko hoti.**Take someone else who kills living creatures … and has wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5289]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā tiracchānayoniṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the animal realm.*";
P_HTM[5290]="*Yo tiracchānayonikānaṃ sattānaṃ āhāro, tena so tattha yāpeti, tena so tattha tiṭṭhati.**There they survive feeding on the food of the beings in the animal realm.*";
P_HTM[5291]="*Idampi kho, brāhmaṇa, aṭṭhānaṃ yattha ṭhitassa taṃ dānaṃ na upakappati.**The conditions there too are wrong, so the gift does not aid the one who lives there.*";
P_HTM[5292]="*Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekacco pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, anabhijjhālu hoti, abyāpannacitto hoti, sammādiṭṭhiko hoti.**Take someone else who doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, or use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. They're contented, kind-hearted, and have right view.*";
P_HTM[5293]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manussānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the human realm.*";
P_HTM[5294]="*Yo manussānaṃ āhāro, tena so tattha yāpeti, tena so tattha tiṭṭhati.**There they survive feeding on human food.*";
P_HTM[5295]="*Idampi kho, brāhmaṇa, aṭṭhānaṃ yattha ṭhitassa taṃ dānaṃ na upakappati.**The conditions there too are wrong, so the gift does not aid the one who lives there.*";
P_HTM[5296]="*Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekacco pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … sammādiṭṭhiko hoti.**Take someone else who doesn’t kill living creatures … and has right view.*";
P_HTM[5297]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the gods.*";
P_HTM[5298]="*Yo devānaṃ āhāro, tena so tattha yāpeti, tena so tattha tiṭṭhati.**There they survive feeding on the food of the gods.*";
P_HTM[5299]="*Idampi, brāhmaṇa, aṭṭhānaṃ yattha ṭhitassa taṃ dānaṃ upakappati.**The conditions there too are wrong, so the gift does not aid the one who lives there.*";
P_HTM[5300]="*Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekacco pāṇātipātī hoti … pe … micchādiṭṭhiko hoti.**Take someone else who kills living creatures … and has wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5301]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pettivisayaṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the ghost realm.*";
P_HTM[5302]="*Yo pettivesayikānaṃ sattānaṃ āhāro, tena so tattha yāpeti, tena so tattha tiṭṭhati, yaṃ vā panassa ito anuppavecchanti mittāmaccā vā ñātisālohitā vā, tena so tattha yāpeti, tena so tattha tiṭṭhati.**There they survive feeding on the food of the beings in the ghost realm. Or else they survive feeding on what friends and colleagues, relatives and kin provide them with from here.*";
P_HTM[5303]="*Idaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, ṭhānaṃ yattha ṭhitassa taṃ dānaṃ upakappatī”ti.**The conditions there are right, so the gift aids the one who lives there.”*";
P_HTM[5304]="*“Sace pana, bho gotama, so peto ñātisālohito taṃ ṭhānaṃ anupapanno hoti, ko taṃ dānaṃ paribhuñjatī”ti?**“But Master Gotama, who partakes of that gift if the departed relative is not reborn in that place?”*";
P_HTM[5305]="*“Aññepissa, brāhmaṇa, petā ñātisālohitā taṃ ṭhānaṃ upapannā honti, te taṃ dānaṃ paribhuñjantī”ti.**“Other departed relatives reborn there will partake of that gift.”*";
P_HTM[5306]="*“Sace pana, bho gotama, so ceva peto ñātisālohito taṃ ṭhānaṃ anupapanno hoti aññepissa ñātisālohitā petā taṃ ṭhānaṃ anupapannā honti, ko taṃ dānaṃ paribhuñjatī”ti?**“But who partakes of the gift when neither that relative nor other relatives have been reborn in that place?”*";
P_HTM[5307]="*“Aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, brāhmaṇa, anavakāso yaṃ taṃ ṭhānaṃ vivittaṃ assa iminā dīghena addhunā yadidaṃ petehi ñātisālohitehi.**“It’s impossible, brahmin, it cannot happen that that place is vacant of departed relatives in all this long time.*";
P_HTM[5308]="*Api ca, brāhmaṇa, dāyakopi anipphalo”ti.**It’s never fruitless for the donor.”*";
P_HTM[5309]="*“Aṭṭhānepi bhavaṃ gotamo parikappaṃ vadatī”ti?**“Does Master Gotama propose this even when the conditions are wrong?”*";
P_HTM[5310]="*“Aṭṭhānepi kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, parikappaṃ vadāmi.**“I propose this even when the conditions are wrong.*";
P_HTM[5311]="*Idha, brāhmaṇa, ekacco pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti, pisuṇavāco hoti, pharusavāco hoti, samphappalāpī hoti, abhijjhālu hoti, byāpannacitto hoti, micchādiṭṭhiko hoti;**Take someone who kills living creatures, steals, and commits sexual misconduct. They use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re covetous, malicious, with wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5312]="*so dātā hoti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ.**They give to ascetics or brahmins such things as food, drink, clothing, vehicles; garlands, perfumes, and makeup; and bed, house, and lighting.*";
P_HTM[5313]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā hatthīnaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of elephants.*";
P_HTM[5314]="*So tattha lābhī hoti annassa pānassa mālānānālaṅkārassa.**There they get to have food and drink, garlands and various adornments.*";
P_HTM[5315]="*Yaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, idha pāṇātipātī adinnādāyī kāmesumicchācārī musāvādī pisuṇavāco pharusavāco samphappalāpī abhijjhālu byāpannacitto micchādiṭṭhiko, tena so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā hatthīnaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**Since in this life they killed living creatures … and had wrong view, they were reborn in the company of elephants.*";
P_HTM[5316]="*Yañca kho so dātā hoti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ, tena so tattha lābhī hoti annassa pānassa mālānānālaṅkārassa.**Since they gave to ascetics or brahmins … they get to have food and drink, garlands and various adornments.*";
P_HTM[5317]="*Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekacco pāṇātipātī hoti … pe … micchādiṭṭhiko hoti.**Take someone else who kills living creatures … and has wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5318]="*So dātā hoti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ.**They give to ascetics or brahmins …*";
P_HTM[5319]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā assānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati … pe …**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of horses. …*";
P_HTM[5320]="*gunnaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati … pe …**cattle …*";
P_HTM[5321]="*kukkurānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**dogs.*";
P_HTM[5322]="*So tattha lābhī hoti annassa pānassa mālānānālaṅkārassa.**There they get to have food and drink, garlands and various adornments.*";
P_HTM[5323]="*Yaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, idha pāṇātipātī … pe … micchādiṭṭhiko, tena so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā kukkurānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**Since in this life they killed living creatures … and had wrong view, they were reborn in the company of dogs.*";
P_HTM[5324]="*Yañca kho so dātā hoti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ, tena so tattha lābhī hoti annassa pānassa mālānānālaṅkārassa.**Since they gave to ascetics or brahmins … they get to have food and drink, garlands and various adornments.*";
P_HTM[5325]="*Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekacco pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … sammādiṭṭhiko hoti.**Take someone else who doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, or commit sexual misconduct. They don’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re contented, kind-hearted, with right view.*";
P_HTM[5326]="*So dātā hoti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ.**They give to ascetics or brahmins …*";
P_HTM[5327]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manussānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the human realm.*";
P_HTM[5328]="*So tattha lābhī hoti mānusakānaṃ pañcannaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ.**There they get to have the five kinds of human sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[5329]="*Yaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, idha pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … sammādiṭṭhiko, tena so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manussānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**Since in this life they didn’t kill living creatures … and had right view, they were reborn in the company of humans.*";
P_HTM[5330]="*Yañca kho so dātā hoti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ, tena so tattha lābhī hoti mānusakānaṃ pañcannaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ.**Since they gave to ascetics or brahmins … they get to have the five kinds of human sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[5331]="*Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekacco pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … sammādiṭṭhiko hoti.**Take someone else who doesn’t kill living creatures … and has right view.*";
P_HTM[5332]="*So dātā hoti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ.**They give to ascetics or brahmins …*";
P_HTM[5333]="*So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the gods.*";
P_HTM[5334]="*So tattha lābhī hoti dibbānaṃ pañcannaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ.**There they get to have the five kinds of heavenly sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[5335]="*Yaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, idha pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … sammādiṭṭhiko, tena so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati.**Since in this life they didn’t kill living creatures … and had right view, they were reborn in the company of the gods.*";
P_HTM[5336]="*Yañca kho so dātā hoti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ, tena so tattha lābhī hoti dibbānaṃ pañcannaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ.**Since they gave to ascetics or brahmins … they get to have the five kinds of heavenly sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[5337]="*Api ca, brāhmaṇa, dāyakopi anipphalo”ti.**It’s never fruitless for the donor.”*";
P_HTM[5338]="*“Acchariyaṃ, bho gotama, abbhutaṃ, bho gotama.**“It’s incredible, Master Gotama, it’s amazing,*";
P_HTM[5339]="*Yāvañcidaṃ, bho gotama, alameva dānāni dātuṃ, alaṃ saddhāni kātuṃ, yatra hi nāma dāyakopi anipphalo”ti.**Just this much is quite enough to justify giving gifts and performing memorial rites for the dead, since it’s never fruitless for the donor.”*";
P_HTM[5340]="*“Evametaṃ, brāhmaṇa, dāyakopi hi, brāhmaṇa, anipphalo”ti.**“That’s so true, brahmin. It’s never fruitless for the donor.”*";
P_HTM[5341]="*“Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …**“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! …*";
P_HTM[5342]="*upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[5343]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5344]="*Jāṇussoṇivaggo dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[5345]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Good*";
P_HTM[5346]="*1. Sādhusuttaṃ**Good*";
P_HTM[5347]="*“Sādhuñca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi asādhuñca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you what is good and what is not good.*";
P_HTM[5348]="*Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[5349]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[5350]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[5351]="*“Katamañca, bhikkhave, asādhu?**“And what, mendicants, is not good?*";
P_HTM[5352]="*Pāṇātipāto, adinnādānaṃ, kāmesumicchācāro, musāvādo, pisuṇā vācā, pharusā vācā, samphappalāpo, abhijjhā, byāpādo, micchādiṭṭhi—**Killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; covetousness, ill will, and wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5353]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asādhu.**This is called what is not good.*";
P_HTM[5354]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, sādhu?**And what is good?*";
P_HTM[5355]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī, adinnādānā veramaṇī, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇī, musāvādā veramaṇī, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī, samphappalāpā veramaṇī, anabhijjhā, abyāpādo, sammādiṭṭhi—**Avoiding killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; avoiding speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; contentment, good will, and right view.*";
P_HTM[5356]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sādhū”ti.**This is called what is good.”*";
P_HTM[5357]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5358]="*2. Ariyadhammasuttaṃ**The Teaching of the Noble Ones*";
P_HTM[5359]="*“Ariyadhammañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi anariyadhammañca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the teaching of the noble ones, and what is not the teaching of the noble ones.*";
P_HTM[5360]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak. …*";
P_HTM[5361]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, anariyo dhammo?**And what is not the teaching of the noble ones?*";
P_HTM[5362]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5363]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5364]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, anariyo dhammo.**This is called what is not the teaching of the noble ones.*";
P_HTM[5365]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, ariyo dhammo?**And what is the teaching of the noble ones?*";
P_HTM[5366]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5367]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5368]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyo dhammo”ti.**This is called the teaching of the noble ones.”*";
P_HTM[5369]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5370]="*3. Kusalasuttaṃ**Skillful*";
P_HTM[5371]="*“Kusalañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi akusalañca.**“I will teach you the skillful and the unskillful …*";
P_HTM[5372]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5373]="*katamañca, bhikkhave, akusalaṃ?**And what is the unskillful?*";
P_HTM[5374]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5375]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5376]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, akusalaṃ.**This is called the unskillful.*";
P_HTM[5377]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, kusalaṃ?**And what is the skillful?*";
P_HTM[5378]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5379]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5380]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kusalan”ti.**This is called the skillful.”*";
P_HTM[5381]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5382]="*4. Atthasuttaṃ**Beneficial*";
P_HTM[5383]="*“Atthañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi anatthañca.**“I will teach you the beneficial and the harmful. …*";
P_HTM[5384]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5385]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, anattho?**And what is the harmful?*";
P_HTM[5386]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5387]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5388]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, anattho.**This is called the harmful.*";
P_HTM[5389]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, attho?**And what is the beneficial?*";
P_HTM[5390]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5391]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5392]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, attho”ti.**This is called the beneficial.”*";
P_HTM[5393]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5394]="*5. Dhammasuttaṃ**The Teaching*";
P_HTM[5395]="*“Dhammañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi adhammañca.**“I will teach you what is the teaching and what is not the teaching. …*";
P_HTM[5396]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5397]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, adhammo?**And what is not the teaching?*";
P_HTM[5398]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5399]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5400]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhammo.**This is called what is not the teaching.*";
P_HTM[5401]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, dhammo?**And what is the teaching?*";
P_HTM[5402]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5403]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5404]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhammo”ti.**This is called the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[5405]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5406]="*6. Āsavasuttaṃ**Defiled*";
P_HTM[5407]="*“Sāsavañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi anāsavañca.**“I will teach you the defiled principle and the undefiled. …*";
P_HTM[5408]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5409]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, sāsavo dhammo?**And what is the defiled principle?*";
P_HTM[5410]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5411]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5412]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sāsavo dhammo.**This is called the defiled principle.*";
P_HTM[5413]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, anāsavo dhammo?**And what is the undefiled principle?*";
P_HTM[5414]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5415]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5416]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, anāsavo dhammo”ti.**This is called the undefiled principle.”*";
P_HTM[5417]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5418]="*7. Vajjasuttaṃ**Blameworthy*";
P_HTM[5419]="*“Sāvajjañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi anavajjañca.**“I will teach you the blameworthy principle and the blameless. …*";
P_HTM[5420]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5421]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, sāvajjo dhammo?**And what is the blameworthy principle?*";
P_HTM[5422]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5423]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5424]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sāvajjo dhammo.**This is called the blameworthy principle.*";
P_HTM[5425]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, anavajjo dhammo?**And what is the blameless principle?*";
P_HTM[5426]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5427]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5428]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, anavajjo dhammo”ti.**This is called the blameless principle.”*";
P_HTM[5429]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5430]="*8. Tapanīyasuttaṃ**Mortifying*";
P_HTM[5431]="*“Tapanīyañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi atapanīyañca.**“I will teach you the mortifying principle and the unmortifying. …*";
P_HTM[5432]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5433]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, tapanīyo dhammo?**And what is the mortifying principle?*";
P_HTM[5434]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5435]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5436]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, tapanīyo dhammo.**This is called the mortifying principle.*";
P_HTM[5437]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, atapanīyo dhammo?**And what is the unmortifying principle?*";
P_HTM[5438]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5439]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5440]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, atapanīyo dhammo”ti.**This is called the unmortifying principle.”*";
P_HTM[5441]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5442]="*9. Ācayagāmisuttaṃ**Leading to Accumulation*";
P_HTM[5443]="*“Ācayagāmiñca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi apacayagāmiñca.**“I will teach you the principle that leads to accumulation and that which leads to dispersal. …*";
P_HTM[5444]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5445]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, ācayagāmī dhammo?**And what is the principle that leads to accumulation?*";
P_HTM[5446]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5447]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5448]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ācayagāmī dhammo.**This is called the principle that leads to accumulation.*";
P_HTM[5449]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, apacayagāmī dhammo?**And what is the principle that leads to dispersal?*";
P_HTM[5450]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5451]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5452]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, apacayagāmī dhammo”ti.**This is called the principle that leads to dispersal.”*";
P_HTM[5453]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5454]="*10. Dukkhudrayasuttaṃ**With Suffering as Outcome*";
P_HTM[5455]="*“Dukkhudrayañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi sukhudrayañca.**“I will teach you the principle that has suffering as outcome, and that which has happiness as outcome. …*";
P_HTM[5456]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5457]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, dukkhudrayo dhammo?**And what is the principle whose outcome is suffering?*";
P_HTM[5458]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5459]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5460]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhudrayo dhammo.**This is the principle whose outcome is suffering.*";
P_HTM[5461]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sukhudrayo dhammo?**And what is the principle whose outcome is happiness?*";
P_HTM[5462]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5463]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5464]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sukhudrayo dhammo”ti.**This is the principle whose outcome is happiness.”*";
P_HTM[5465]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5466]="*11. Vipākasuttaṃ**Result*";
P_HTM[5467]="*“Dukkhavipākañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi sukhavipākañca.**“I will teach you the principle that results in suffering and that which results in happiness. …*";
P_HTM[5468]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5469]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, dukkhavipāko dhammo?**And what is the principle that results in suffering?*";
P_HTM[5470]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5471]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5472]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhavipāko dhammo.**This is called the principle that results in suffering.*";
P_HTM[5473]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sukhavipāko dhammo?**And what is the principle that results in happiness?*";
P_HTM[5474]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5475]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5476]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sukhavipāko dhammo”ti.**This is called the principle that results in happiness.”*";
P_HTM[5477]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5478]="*Sādhuvaggo tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[5479]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**The Noble Path*";
P_HTM[5480]="*1. Ariyamaggasuttaṃ**The Noble Path*";
P_HTM[5481]="*“Ariyamaggañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi anariyamaggañca.**“I will teach you the noble path and the ignoble path. …*";
P_HTM[5482]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5483]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, anariyo maggo?**And what is the ignoble path?*";
P_HTM[5484]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5485]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5486]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, anariyo maggo.**This is called the ignoble path.*";
P_HTM[5487]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, ariyo maggo?**And what is the noble path?*";
P_HTM[5488]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5489]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5490]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyo maggo”ti.**This is called the noble path.”*";
P_HTM[5491]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5492]="*2. Kaṇhamaggasuttaṃ**The Dark Path*";
P_HTM[5493]="*“Kaṇhamaggañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi sukkamaggañca.**“I will teach you the dark path and the bright path. …*";
P_HTM[5494]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5495]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, kaṇho maggo?**And what is the dark path?*";
P_HTM[5496]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5497]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5498]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kaṇho maggo.**This is called the dark path.*";
P_HTM[5499]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sukko maggo?**And what is the bright path?*";
P_HTM[5500]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5501]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5502]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sukko maggo”ti.**This is called the bright path.”*";
P_HTM[5503]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5504]="*3. Saddhammasuttaṃ**The True Teaching*";
P_HTM[5505]="*“Saddhammañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi asaddhammañca.**“I will teach you what is the true teaching and what is not the true teaching. …*";
P_HTM[5506]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5507]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, asaddhammo?**And what is not the true teaching?*";
P_HTM[5508]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5509]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5510]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asaddhammo.**This is called what is not the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[5511]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, saddhammo?**And what is the true teaching?*";
P_HTM[5512]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5513]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5514]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, saddhammo”ti.**This is called the true teaching.”*";
P_HTM[5515]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5516]="*4. Sappurisadhammasuttaṃ**The Teaching of the Good Persons*";
P_HTM[5517]="*“Sappurisadhammañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi asappurisadhammañca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the teaching of the good persons and the teaching of the bad persons.*";
P_HTM[5518]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5519]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappurisadhammo?**And what is the teaching of the bad persons?*";
P_HTM[5520]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5521]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5522]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asappurisadhammo.**This is the teaching of the bad persons.*";
P_HTM[5523]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sappurisadhammo?**And what is the teaching of the good persons?*";
P_HTM[5524]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5525]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5526]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sappurisadhammo”ti.**This is the teaching of the good persons.”*";
P_HTM[5527]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5528]="*5. Uppādetabbadhammasuttaṃ**Principles That Should Be Activated*";
P_HTM[5529]="*“Uppādetabbañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi na uppādetabbañca.**“I will teach you the principle to activate and the principle not to activate. …*";
P_HTM[5530]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5531]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, na uppādetabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle not to activate?*";
P_HTM[5532]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5533]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5534]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, na uppādetabbo dhammo.**This is called the principle not to activate.*";
P_HTM[5535]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, uppādetabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle to activate?*";
P_HTM[5536]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5537]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5538]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, uppādetabbo dhammo”ti.**This is called the principle to activate.”*";
P_HTM[5539]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5540]="*6. Āsevitabbadhammasuttaṃ**Principles That Should Be Cultivated*";
P_HTM[5541]="*“Āsevitabbañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi nāsevitabbañca.**“I will teach you the principle to cultivate and the principle not to cultivate. …*";
P_HTM[5542]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5543]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, nāsevitabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle not to cultivate?*";
P_HTM[5544]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5545]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5546]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, nāsevitabbo dhammo.**This is called the principle not to cultivate.*";
P_HTM[5547]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, āsevitabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle to cultivate?*";
P_HTM[5548]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5549]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5550]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, āsevitabbo dhammo”ti.**This is called the principle to cultivate.”*";
P_HTM[5551]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5552]="*7. Bhāvetabbadhammasuttaṃ**Principles That Should Be Developed*";
P_HTM[5553]="*“Bhāvetabbañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi na bhāvetabbañca.**“I will teach you the principle to develop and the principle not to develop. …*";
P_HTM[5554]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.*";
P_HTM[5555]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, na bhāvetabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle not to develop?*";
P_HTM[5556]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5557]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5558]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, na bhāvetabbo dhammo.**This is called the principle not to develop.*";
P_HTM[5559]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, bhāvetabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle to develop?*";
P_HTM[5560]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5561]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5562]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhāvetabbo dhammo”ti.**This is called the principle to develop.”*";
P_HTM[5563]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5564]="*8. Bahulīkātabbasuttaṃ**Principles That Should Be Made Much Of*";
P_HTM[5565]="*“Bahulīkātabbañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi na bahulīkātabbañca.**“I will teach you the principle to make much of and the principle not to make much of. …*";
P_HTM[5566]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5567]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, na bahulīkātabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle not to make much of?*";
P_HTM[5568]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5569]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5570]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, na bahulīkātabbo dhammo.**This is called the principle not to make much of.*";
P_HTM[5571]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, bahulīkātabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle to make much of?*";
P_HTM[5572]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5573]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5574]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bahulīkātabbo dhammo”ti.**This is called the principle to make much of.”*";
P_HTM[5575]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5576]="*9. Anussaritabbasuttaṃ**Should Be Recollected*";
P_HTM[5577]="*“Anussaritabbañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi nānussaritabbañca.**“I will teach you the principle to recollect and the principle not to recollect. …*";
P_HTM[5578]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5579]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, nānussaritabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle not to recollect?*";
P_HTM[5580]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5581]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5582]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, nānussaritabbo dhammo.**This is called the principle not to recollect.*";
P_HTM[5583]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, anussaritabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle to recollect?*";
P_HTM[5584]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5585]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5586]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, anussaritabbo dhammo”ti.**This is called the principle to recollect.”*";
P_HTM[5587]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5588]="*10. Sacchikātabbasuttaṃ**Should Be Realized*";
P_HTM[5589]="*“Sacchikātabbañca vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi na sacchikātabbañca.**“I will teach you the principle to realize and the principle not to realize. …*";
P_HTM[5590]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5591]="*katamo ca, bhikkhave, na sacchikātabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle not to realize?*";
P_HTM[5592]="*Pāṇātipāto … pe …**Killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5593]="*micchādiṭṭhi—**wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5594]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, na sacchikātabbo dhammo.**This is called the principle not to realize.*";
P_HTM[5595]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sacchikātabbo dhammo?**And what is the principle to realize?*";
P_HTM[5596]="*Pāṇātipātā veramaṇī … pe …**Not killing living creatures …*";
P_HTM[5597]="*sammādiṭṭhi—**right view.*";
P_HTM[5598]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sacchikātabbo dhammo”ti.**This is called the principle to realize.”*";
P_HTM[5599]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5600]="*Ariyamaggavaggo catuttho.* **";
P_HTM[5601]="*Nasevitabbādisuttāni**199–210. Nasevitabbādisutta*";
P_HTM[5602]="*“Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato puggalo na sevitabbo.**“Mendicants, you should not associate with a person who has ten qualities.*";
P_HTM[5603]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[5604]="*Pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti, pisuṇavāco hoti, pharusavāco hoti, samphappalāpī hoti, abhijjhālu hoti, byāpannacitto hoti, micchādiṭṭhiko hoti—**They kill living creatures, steal, and commit sexual misconduct. They use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re covetous, malicious, with wrong view.*";
P_HTM[5605]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi dhammehi samannāgato puggalo na sevitabbo.**You should not associate with a person who has these ten qualities.*";
P_HTM[5606]="*Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato puggalo sevitabbo.**You should associate with a person who has ten qualities.*";
P_HTM[5607]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[5608]="*Pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, anabhijjhālu hoti, abyāpannacitto hoti, sammādiṭṭhiko hoti—**They don’t kill living creatures, steal, or commit sexual misconduct. They don’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. They’re contented, kind-hearted, with right view.*";
P_HTM[5609]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi dhammehi samannāgato puggalo sevitabbo. (1)**You should associate with a person who has these ten qualities.”*";
P_HTM[5610]="*Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato puggalo na bhajitabbo … pe …**“Mendicants, you should not frequent a person who has ten qualities.*";
P_HTM[5611]="*bhajitabbo …**you should frequent …*";
P_HTM[5612]="*na payirupāsitabbo …**you should not pay homage …*";
P_HTM[5613]="*payirupāsitabbo …**you should pay homage …*";
P_HTM[5614]="*na pujjo hoti …**you should not venerate …*";
P_HTM[5615]="*pujjo hoti …**you should venerate …*";
P_HTM[5616]="*na pāsaṃso hoti …**you should not praise …*";
P_HTM[5617]="*pāsaṃso hoti …**you should praise …*";
P_HTM[5618]="*agāravo hoti …**you should not revere …*";
P_HTM[5619]="*gāravo hoti …**you should revere …*";
P_HTM[5620]="*appatisso hoti …**you should not defer to …*";
P_HTM[5621]="*sappatisso hoti …**you should defer to …*";
P_HTM[5622]="*na ārādhako hoti …**is not a success …*";
P_HTM[5623]="*ārādhako hoti …**is a success …*";
