P_HTM[5698]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5699]="*3. Mātugāmasuttaṃ**A Female*";
P_HTM[5700]="*“Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato mātugāmo yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“A female with ten qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5701]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[5702]="*Pāṇātipātī hoti … pe …**She kills living creatures. …*";
P_HTM[5703]="*adinnādāyī hoti …**She steals. …*";
P_HTM[5704]="*kāmesumicchācārī hoti …**She commits sexual misconduct. …*";
P_HTM[5705]="*musāvādī hoti …**She lies. …*";
P_HTM[5706]="*pisuṇavāco hoti …**She speaks divisively. …*";
P_HTM[5707]="*pharusavāco hoti …**She speaks harshly. …*";
P_HTM[5708]="*samphappalāpī hoti …**She indulges in talking nonsense. …*";
P_HTM[5709]="*abhijjhālu hoti …**She’s covetous. …*";
P_HTM[5710]="*byāpannacitto hoti …**She has cruel intentions. …*";
P_HTM[5711]="*micchādiṭṭhiko hoti ….**She has wrong view. …*";
P_HTM[5712]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi dhammehi samannāgato mātugāmo yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**A female with these ten qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5713]="*Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato mātugāmo yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**A female with ten qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[5714]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[5715]="*Pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe …**She doesn’t kill living creatures. …*";
P_HTM[5716]="*adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti …**She doesn’t steal. …*";
P_HTM[5717]="*kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti …**She doesn’t commit sexual misconduct. …*";
P_HTM[5718]="*musāvādā paṭivirato hoti …**She doesn’t lie. …*";
P_HTM[5719]="*pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti …**She doesn’t speak divisively. …*";
P_HTM[5720]="*pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti …**She doesn’t speak harshly. …*";
P_HTM[5721]="*samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti …**She doesn’t indulge in talking nonsense. …*";
P_HTM[5722]="*anabhijjhālu hoti …**She’s content. …*";
P_HTM[5723]="*abyāpannacitto hoti …**She’s kind hearted. …*";
P_HTM[5724]="*sammādiṭṭhiko hoti ….**She has right view. …*";
P_HTM[5725]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi dhammehi samannāgato mātugāmo yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**A female with these ten qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[5726]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5727]="*4. Upāsikāsuttaṃ**A Laywoman*";
P_HTM[5728]="*“Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatā upāsikā yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ niraye.**“A laywoman with ten qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5729]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[5730]="*Pāṇātipātinī hoti … pe …**She kills living creatures. …*";
P_HTM[5731]="*micchādiṭṭhikā hoti ….**She has wrong view. …*";
P_HTM[5732]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi dhammehi samannāgatā upāsikā yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ niraye.**A laywoman with these ten qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5733]="*Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatā upāsikā yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ sagge.**A laywoman with ten qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[5734]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[5735]="*Pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā hoti … pe …**She doesn’t kill living creatures. …*";
P_HTM[5736]="*sammādiṭṭhikā hoti ….**She has right view. …*";
P_HTM[5737]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi dhammehi samannāgatā upāsikā yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ sagge”.**A laywoman with these ten qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[5738]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5739]="*5. Visāradasuttaṃ**Assured*";
P_HTM[5740]="*“Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatā upāsikā avisāradā agāraṃ ajjhāvasati.**“A laywoman living at home with these ten qualities is not self-assured.*";
P_HTM[5741]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[5742]="*Pāṇātipātinī hoti …**She kills living creatures. …*";
P_HTM[5743]="*adinnādāyinī hoti …* **";
P_HTM[5744]="*kāmesumicchācārinī hoti …* **";
P_HTM[5745]="*musāvādinī hoti …* **";
P_HTM[5746]="*pisuṇavācā hoti …* **";
P_HTM[5747]="*pharusavācā hoti …* **";
P_HTM[5748]="*samphappalāpinī hoti …* **";
P_HTM[5749]="*abhijjhālunī hoti …* **";
P_HTM[5750]="*byāpannacittā hoti …* **";
P_HTM[5751]="*micchādiṭṭhikā hoti ….**She has wrong view. …*";
P_HTM[5752]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi dhammehi samannāgatā upāsikā avisāradā agāraṃ ajjhāvasati.**A laywoman living at home with these ten qualities is not self-assured.*";
P_HTM[5753]="*Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatā upāsikā visāradā agāraṃ ajjhāvasati.**A laywoman living at home with these ten qualities is self-assured.*";
P_HTM[5754]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[5755]="*Pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā hoti …**She doesn’t kill living creatures. …*";
P_HTM[5756]="*adinnādānā paṭiviratā hoti …* **";
P_HTM[5757]="*kāmesumicchācārā paṭiviratā hoti …* **";
P_HTM[5758]="*musāvādā paṭiviratā hoti …* **";
P_HTM[5759]="*pisuṇāya vācāya paṭiviratā hoti …* **";
P_HTM[5760]="*pharusāya vācāya paṭiviratā hoti …* **";
P_HTM[5761]="*samphappalāpā paṭiviratā hoti …* **";
P_HTM[5762]="*anabhijjhālunī hoti …* **";
P_HTM[5763]="*abyāpannacittā hoti …* **";
P_HTM[5764]="*sammādiṭṭhikā hoti ….**She has right view. …*";
P_HTM[5765]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi dhammehi samannāgatā upāsikā visāradā agāraṃ ajjhāvasatī”ti.**A laywoman living at home with these ten qualities is self-assured.”*";
P_HTM[5766]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5767]="*6. Saṃsappanīyasuttaṃ**Creepy Creatures*";
P_HTM[5768]="*“Saṃsappanīyapariyāyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, dhammapariyāyaṃ desessāmi.**“Mendicants, I will teach you an exposition of the teaching on creepy creatures.*";
P_HTM[5769]="*Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[5770]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[5771]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[5772]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, saṃsappanīyapariyāyo dhammapariyāyo?**“What is the exposition of the teaching on creepy creatures?*";
P_HTM[5773]="*Kammassakā, bhikkhave, sattā kammadāyādā kammayonī kammabandhū kammapaṭisaraṇā, yaṃ kammaṃ karonti—**Sentient beings are the owners of their deeds and heir to their deeds. Deeds are their womb, their relative, and their refuge.*";
P_HTM[5774]="*kalyāṇaṃ vā pāpakaṃ vā—tassa dāyādā bhavanti.**They shall be the heir of whatever deeds they do, whether good or bad.*";
P_HTM[5775]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātī hoti luddo lohitapāṇi hatapahate niviṭṭho, adayāpanno sabbapāṇabhūtesu.**Take a certain person who kills living creatures. They’re violent, bloody-handed, a hardened killer, merciless to living beings.*";
P_HTM[5776]="*So saṃsappati kāyena, saṃsappati vācāya, saṃsappati manasā.**They’re creepy in body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[5777]="*Tassa jimhaṃ kāyakammaṃ hoti, jimhaṃ vacīkammaṃ, jimhaṃ manokammaṃ, jimhā gati, jimhupapatti.**Doing crooked deeds by way of body, speech, and mind, their destiny and rebirth is crooked.*";
P_HTM[5778]="*Jimhagatikassa kho panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, jimhupapattikassa dvinnaṃ gatīnaṃ aññataraṃ gatiṃ vadāmi—**Someone whose destiny and rebirth is crooked is reborn in one of two places, I say:*";
P_HTM[5779]="*ye vā ekantadukkhā nirayā yā vā saṃsappajātikā tiracchānayoni.**in an exclusively painful hell, or among the species of creepy animals.*";
P_HTM[5780]="*Katamā ca sā, bhikkhave, saṃsappajātikā tiracchānayoni?**And what are the species of creepy animals?*";
P_HTM[5781]="*Ahi vicchikā satapadī nakulā biḷārā mūsikā ulūkā, ye vā panaññepi keci tiracchānayonikā sattā manusse disvā saṃsappanti.**Snakes, scorpions, centipedes, mongooses, cats, mice, owls, or whatever other species of animal that creep away when they see humans.*";
P_HTM[5782]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, bhūtā bhūtassa upapatti hoti.**This is how a being is born from a being.*";
P_HTM[5783]="*Yaṃ karoti tena upapajjati.**For your deeds determine your rebirth,*";
P_HTM[5784]="*Upapannamenaṃ phassā phusanti.**and when you’re reborn contacts affect you.*";
P_HTM[5785]="*Evamahaṃ, bhikkhave, ‘kammadāyādā sattā’ti vadāmi.**This is why I say that sentient beings are heirs to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[5786]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco adinnādāyī hoti … pe …**Take someone else who steals …*";
P_HTM[5787]="*kāmesumicchācārī hoti …**commits sexual misconduct …*";
P_HTM[5788]="*musāvādī hoti …**lies …*";
P_HTM[5789]="*pisuṇavāco hoti …**speaks divisively …*";
P_HTM[5790]="*pharusavāco hoti …**speaks harshly …*";
P_HTM[5791]="*samphappalāpī hoti …**indulges in talking nonsense …*";
P_HTM[5792]="*abhijjhālu hoti …**is covetous …*";
P_HTM[5793]="*byāpannacitto hoti …**has cruel intentions …*";
P_HTM[5794]="*micchādiṭṭhiko hoti viparītadassano:**has wrong view …*";
P_HTM[5795]="*‘natthi dinnaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5796]="*sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5797]="*So saṃsappati kāyena, saṃsappati vācāya, saṃsappati manasā.**They’re creepy in body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[5798]="*Tassa jimhaṃ kāyakammaṃ hoti, jimhaṃ vacīkammaṃ, jimhaṃ manokammaṃ, jimhā gati, jimhupapatti.**Doing crooked deeds by way of body, speech, and mind, their destiny and rebirth is crooked.*";
P_HTM[5799]="*Jimhagatikassa kho panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, jimhupapattikassa dvinnaṃ gatīnaṃ aññataraṃ gatiṃ vadāmi—**Someone whose destiny and rebirth is crooked is reborn in one of two places, I say:*";
P_HTM[5800]="*ye vā ekantadukkhā nirayā yā vā saṃsappajātikā tiracchānayoni.**in an exclusively painful hell, or among the species of creepy animals.*";
P_HTM[5801]="*Katamā ca sā, bhikkhave, saṃsappajātikā tiracchānayoni?**And what are the species of creepy animals?*";
P_HTM[5802]="*Ahi vicchikā satapadī nakulā biḷārā mūsikā ulūkā, ye vā panaññepi keci tiracchānayonikā sattā manusse disvā saṃsappanti.**Snakes, scorpions, centipedes, mongooses, cats, mice, owls, or whatever other species of animal that creep away when they see humans.*";
P_HTM[5803]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, bhūtā bhūtassa upapatti hoti,**This is how a being is born from a being.*";
P_HTM[5804]="*yaṃ karoti tena upapajjati.**For your deeds determine your rebirth,*";
P_HTM[5805]="*Upapannamenaṃ phassā phusanti.**and when you’re reborn contacts affect you.*";
P_HTM[5806]="*Evamahaṃ, bhikkhave, ‘kammadāyādā sattā’ti vadāmi.**This is why I say that sentient beings are heirs to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[5807]="*Kammassakā, bhikkhave, sattā kammadāyādā kammayonī kammabandhū kammapaṭisaraṇā, yaṃ kammaṃ karonti—**Sentient beings are the owners of their deeds and heir to their deeds. Deeds are their womb, their relative, and their refuge.*";
P_HTM[5808]="*kalyāṇaṃ vā pāpakaṃ vā—tassa dāyādā bhavanti.**They shall be the heir of whatever deeds they do, whether good or bad.*";
P_HTM[5809]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho, lajjī dayāpanno sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati.**Take a certain person who gives up killing living creatures. They renounce the rod and the sword. They’re scrupulous and kind, living full of compassion for all living beings.*";
P_HTM[5810]="*So na saṃsappati kāyena, na saṃsappati vācāya, na saṃsappati manasā.**They’re not creepy in body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[5811]="*Tassa uju kāyakammaṃ hoti, uju vacīkammaṃ, uju manokammaṃ, uju gati, ujupapatti.**Doing virtuous deeds by way of body, speech, and mind, their destiny and rebirth is virtuous.*";
P_HTM[5812]="*Ujugatikassa kho panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ujupapattikassa dvinnaṃ gatīnaṃ aññataraṃ gatiṃ vadāmi—**Someone whose destiny and rebirth is virtuous is reborn in one of two places, I say:*";
P_HTM[5813]="*ye vā ekantasukhā saggā yāni vā pana tāni uccākulāni khattiyamahāsālakulāni vā brāhmaṇamahāsālakulāni vā gahapatimahāsālakulāni vā aḍḍhāni mahaddhanāni mahābhogāni pahūtajātarūparajatāni pahūtavittūpakaraṇāni pahūtadhanadhaññāni.**in a heaven of perfect happiness, or in an eminent well-to-do family of aristocrats, brahmins, or householders—rich, affluent, and wealthy, with lots of gold and silver, lots of property and assets, and lots of money and grain.*";
P_HTM[5814]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, bhūtā bhūtassa upapatti hoti.**This is how a being is born from a being.*";
P_HTM[5815]="*Yaṃ karoti tena upapajjati.**For your deeds determine your rebirth,*";
P_HTM[5816]="*Upapannamenaṃ phassā phusanti.**and when you’re reborn contacts affect you.*";
P_HTM[5817]="*Evamahaṃ, bhikkhave, ‘kammadāyādā sattā’ti vadāmi.**This is why I say that sentient beings are heirs to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[5818]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti … pe …**Take someone else who gives up stealing …*";
P_HTM[5819]="*kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti …**sexual misconduct …*";
P_HTM[5820]="*musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti …**lying …*";
P_HTM[5821]="*pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti …**divisive speech …*";
P_HTM[5822]="*pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti …**harsh speech …*";
P_HTM[5823]="*samphappalāpaṃ pahāya samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti …**talking nonsense …*";
P_HTM[5824]="*anabhijjhālu hoti …**They’re content …*";
P_HTM[5825]="*abyāpannacitto hoti …**kind hearted …*";
P_HTM[5826]="*sammādiṭṭhiko hoti aviparītadassano:**they have right view …*";
P_HTM[5827]="*‘atthi dinnaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[5828]="*ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5829]="*So na saṃsappati kāyena, na saṃsappati vācāya, na saṃsappati manasā.**They’re not creepy in body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[5830]="*Tassa uju kāyakammaṃ hoti, uju vacīkammaṃ, uju manokammaṃ, uju gati, ujupapatti.**Doing virtuous deeds by way of body, speech, and mind, their destiny and rebirth is virtuous.*";
P_HTM[5831]="*Ujugatikassa kho pana ahaṃ, bhikkhave, ujupapattikassa dvinnaṃ gatīnaṃ aññataraṃ gatiṃ vadāmi—**Someone whose destiny and rebirth is virtuous is reborn in one of two places, I say:*";
P_HTM[5832]="*ye vā ekantasukhā saggā yāni vā pana tāni uccākulāni khattiyamahāsālakulāni vā brāhmaṇamahāsālakulāni vā gahapatimahāsālakulāni vā aḍḍhāni mahaddhanāni mahābhogāni pahūtajātarūparajatāni pahūtavittūpakaraṇāni pahūtadhanadhaññāni.**in a heaven of perfect happiness, or in an eminent well-to-do family of aristocrats, brahmins, or householders—rich, affluent, and wealthy, with lots of gold and silver, lots of property and assets, and lots of money and grain.*";
P_HTM[5833]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, bhūtā bhūtassa upapatti hoti.**This is how a being is born from a being.*";
P_HTM[5834]="*Yaṃ karoti tena upapajjati.**For your deeds determine your rebirth,*";
P_HTM[5835]="*Upapannamenaṃ phassā phusanti.**and when you’re reborn contacts affect you.*";
P_HTM[5836]="*Evamahaṃ, bhikkhave, ‘kammadāyādā sattā’ti vadāmi.**This is why I say that sentient beings are heirs to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[5837]="*Kammassakā, bhikkhave, sattā kammadāyādā kammayonī kammabandhū kammapaṭisaraṇā, yaṃ kammaṃ karonti—**Sentient beings are the owners of their deeds and heir to their deeds. Deeds are their womb, their relative, and their refuge.*";
P_HTM[5838]="*kalyāṇaṃ vā pāpakaṃ vā—tassa dāyādā bhavanti.**They shall be the heir of whatever deeds they do, whether good or bad.*";
P_HTM[5839]="*Ayaṃ kho so, bhikkhave, saṃsappanīyapariyāyo dhammapariyāyo”ti.**This is the exposition of the teaching on creepy creatures.”*";
P_HTM[5840]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5841]="*7. Paṭhamasañcetanikasuttaṃ**Intentional (1st)*";
P_HTM[5842]="*“Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ appaṭisaṃveditvā byantībhāvaṃ vadāmi.**“Mendicants, I don’t say that intentional deeds that have been performed and accumulated are eliminated without being experienced.*";
P_HTM[5843]="*Tañca kho diṭṭheva dhamme upapajje vā apare vā pariyāye.**And that may be in the present life, or in the next life, or in some subsequent period.*";
P_HTM[5844]="*Na tvevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ appaṭisaṃveditvā dukkhassantakiriyaṃ vadāmi.**And I don’t say that suffering is ended without experiencing intentional deeds that have been performed and accumulated.*";
P_HTM[5845]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti;**Now, there are three kinds of corruption and failure of bodily action that have unskillful intention, with suffering as their outcome and result.*";
P_HTM[5846]="*catubbidhā vacīkammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti;**There are four kinds of corruption and failure of verbal action that have unskillful intention, with suffering as their outcome and result.*";
P_HTM[5847]="*tividhā manokammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti.**There are three kinds of corruption and failure of mental action that have unskillful intention, with suffering as their outcome and result.*";
P_HTM[5848]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti?**And what are the three kinds of corruption and failure of bodily action?*";
P_HTM[5849]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātī hoti, luddo lohitapāṇi hatapahate niviṭṭho adayāpanno sabbapāṇabhūtesu. (1)**It’s when a certain person kills living creatures. They’re violent, bloody-handed, a hardened killer, merciless to living beings.*";
P_HTM[5850]="*Adinnādāyī hoti, yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ gāmagataṃ vā araññagataṃ vā, taṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādātā hoti. (2)**They steal. With the intention to commit theft, they take the wealth or belongings of others from village or wilderness.*";
P_HTM[5851]="*Kāmesumicchācārī hoti, yā tā māturakkhitā … pe … antamaso mālāguḷaparikkhittāpi, tathārūpāsu cārittaṃ āpajjitā hoti. (3)**They commit sexual misconduct. They have sex with women who have their mother, father, both mother and father, brother, sister, relatives, or clan as guardian. They have sex with a woman who is protected on principle, or who has a husband, or whose violation is punishable by law, or even one who has been garlanded as a token of betrothal.*";
P_HTM[5852]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti.**These are the three kinds of corruption and failure of bodily action.*";
P_HTM[5853]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, catubbidhā vacīkammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti?**And what are the four kinds of corruption and failure of verbal action?*";
P_HTM[5854]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco musāvādī hoti. Sabhaggato vā parisaggato vā ñātimajjhagato vā pūgamajjhagato vā rājakulamajjhagato vā abhinīto sakkhipuṭṭho**It’s when a certain person lies. They’re summoned to a council, an assembly, a family meeting, a guild, or to the royal court, and asked to bear witness:*";
P_HTM[5855]="*‘ehambho purisa, yaṃ jānāsi taṃ vadehī’ti, so ajānaṃ vā āha: ‘jānāmī’ti, jānaṃ vā āha: ‘na jānāmī’ti, apassaṃ vā āha: ‘passāmī’ti, passaṃ vā āha: ‘na passāmī’ti, iti attahetu vā parahetu vā āmisakiñcikkhahetu vā sampajānamusā bhāsitā hoti. (4)**‘Please, mister, say what you know.’ Not knowing, they say ‘I know.’ Knowing, they say ‘I don’t know.’ Not seeing, they say ‘I see.’ And seeing, they say ‘I don’t see.’ So they deliberately lie for the sake of themselves or another, or for some trivial worldly reason.*";
P_HTM[5856]="*Pisuṇavāco hoti, ito sutvā amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, amutra vā sutvā imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya. Iti samaggānaṃ vā bhettā bhinnānaṃ vā anuppadātā vaggārāmo vaggarato vagganandī, vaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. (5)**They speak divisively. They repeat in one place what they heard in another so as to divide people against each other. And so they divide those who are harmonious, supporting division, delighting in division, loving division, speaking words that promote division.*";
P_HTM[5857]="*Pharusavāco hoti, yā sā vācā aṇḍakā kakkasā parakaṭukā parābhisajjanī kodhasāmantā. Asamādhisaṃvattanikā, tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. (6)**They speak harshly. They use the kinds of words that are cruel, nasty, hurtful, offensive, bordering on anger, not leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[5858]="*Samphappalāpī hoti, akālavādī abhūtavādī anatthavādī adhammavādī avinayavādī, anidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti akālena anapadesaṃ apariyantavatiṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ. (7)**They indulge in talking nonsense. Their speech is untimely, and is neither factual nor beneficial. It has nothing to do with the teaching or the training. Their words have no value, and are untimely, unreasonable, rambling, and pointless.*";
P_HTM[5859]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catubbidhā vacīkammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti.**These are the four kinds of corruption and failure of verbal action.*";
P_HTM[5860]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, tividhā manokammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti?**And what are the three kinds of corruption and failure of mental action?*";
P_HTM[5861]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco abhijjhālu hoti. Yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ, taṃ abhijjhātā hoti: ‘aho vata, yaṃ parassa taṃ mama assā’ti. (8)**It’s when someone is covetous. They covet the wealth and belongings of others: ‘Oh, if only their belongings were mine!’*";
P_HTM[5862]="*Byāpannacitto hoti, paduṭṭhamanasaṅkappo: ‘ime sattā haññantu vā bajjhantu vā ucchijjantu vā vinassantu vā mā vā ahesun’ti. (9)**They have ill will and hateful intentions: ‘May these sentient beings be killed, slaughtered, slain, destroyed, or annihilated!’*";
P_HTM[5863]="*Micchādiṭṭhiko hoti, viparītadassano:**They have wrong view. Their perspective is distorted:*";
P_HTM[5864]="*‘natthi dinnaṃ … pe … ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti. (10)**‘There’s no meaning in giving, sacrifice, or offerings. There’s no fruit or result of good and bad deeds. There’s no afterlife. There’s no obligation to mother and father. No beings are reborn spontaneously. And there’s no ascetic or brahmin who is well attained and practiced, and who describes the afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.’*";
P_HTM[5865]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tividhā manokammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti.**These are the three kinds of corruption and failure of mental action.*";
P_HTM[5866]="*Tividhakāyakammantasandosabyāpattiakusalasañcetanikāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti; catubbidhavacīkammantasandosabyāpattiakusalasañcetanikāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti; tividhamanokammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti.**When their body breaks up, after death, sentient beings are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell because of these three kinds of corruption and failure of bodily action, these four kinds of corruption and failure of verbal action, or these three kinds of corruption and failure of mental action that have unskillful intention, with suffering as their outcome and result.*";
P_HTM[5867]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, apaṇṇako maṇi uddhaṅkhitto yena yeneva patiṭṭhāti suppatiṭṭhitaṃyeva patiṭṭhāti;**It’s like throwing loaded dice: they always fall the right side up.*";
P_HTM[5868]="*evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tividhakāyakammantasandosabyāpattiakusalasañcetanikāhetu vā sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti; catubbidhavacīkammantasandosabyāpattiakusalasañcetanikāhetu vā sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti; tividhamanokammantasandosabyāpattiakusalasañcetanikāhetu vā sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjantīti.**In the same way, when their body breaks up, after death, sentient beings are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell because of these three kinds of corruption and failure of bodily action, these four kinds of corruption and failure of verbal action, or these three kinds of corruption and failure of mental action that have unskillful intention, with suffering as their outcome and result.*";
P_HTM[5869]="*Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ appaṭisaṃveditvā byantībhāvaṃ vadāmi,**I don’t say that intentional deeds that have been performed and accumulated are eliminated without being experienced.*";
P_HTM[5870]="*tañca kho diṭṭheva dhamme upapajje vā apare vā pariyāye.**And that may be in the present life, or in the next life, or in some subsequent period.*";
P_HTM[5871]="*Na tvevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ appaṭisaṃveditvā dukkhassantakiriyaṃ vadāmi.**And I don’t say that suffering is ended without experiencing intentional deeds that have been performed and accumulated.*";
P_HTM[5872]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti;**Now, there are three kinds of successful bodily action that have skillful intention, with happiness as their outcome and result.*";
P_HTM[5873]="*catubbidhā vacīkammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti;**There are four kinds of successful verbal action that have skillful intention, with happiness as their outcome and result.*";
P_HTM[5874]="*tividhā manokammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti.**There are three kinds of successful mental action that have skillful intention, with happiness as their outcome and result.*";
P_HTM[5875]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti?**And what are the three kinds of successful bodily action?*";
P_HTM[5876]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho lajjī dayāpanno, sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati … pe …. (1)**It’s when a certain person gives up killing living creatures. They renounce the rod and the sword. They’re scrupulous and kind, living full of compassion for all living beings.*";
P_HTM[5877]="*Adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ gāmagataṃ vā araññagataṃ vā, na taṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādātā hoti. (2)**They don’t steal. They don’t, with the intention to commit theft, take the wealth or belongings of others from village or wilderness.*";
P_HTM[5878]="*Kāmesumicchācāraṃ pahāya, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti. Yā tā māturakkhitā … pe … antamaso mālāguḷaparikkhittāpi, tathārūpāsu na cārittaṃ āpajjitā hoti. (3)**They give up sexual misconduct. They don’t have sex with women who have their mother, father, both mother and father, brother, sister, relatives, or clan as guardian. They don’t have sex with a woman who is protected on principle, or who has a husband, or whose violation is punishable by law, or even one who has been garlanded as a token of betrothal.*";
P_HTM[5879]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti.**These are the three kinds of successful bodily action.*";
P_HTM[5880]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, catubbidhā vacīkammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti?**And what are the four kinds of successful verbal action?*";
P_HTM[5881]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti. Sabhaggato vā parisaggato vā ñātimajjhagato vā pūgamajjhagato vā rājakulamajjhagato vā abhinīto sakkhipuṭṭho ‘ehambho purisa, yaṃ jānāsi taṃ vadehī’ti, so ajānaṃ vā āha: ‘na jānāmī’ti, jānaṃ vā āha: ‘jānāmī’ti, apassaṃ vā āha: ‘na passāmī’ti, passaṃ vā āha: ‘passāmī’ti, iti attahetu vā parahetu vā āmisakiñcikkhahetu vā na sampajānamusā bhāsitā hoti. (4)**It’s when a certain person gives up lying. They’re summoned to a council, an assembly, a family meeting, a guild, or to the royal court, and asked to bear witness: ‘Please, mister, say what you know.’ Not knowing, they say ‘I don’t know.’ Knowing, they say ‘I know.’ Not seeing, they say ‘I don’t see.’ And seeing, they say ‘I see.’ They don’t deliberately lie for the sake of themselves or another, or for some trivial worldly reason.*";
P_HTM[5882]="*Pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pahāya, pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti—na ito sutvā amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, amutra vā sutvā na imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya. Iti bhinnānaṃ vā sandhātā sahitānaṃ vā anuppadātā samaggārāmo samaggarato samagganandiṃ, samaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. (5)**They give up divisive speech. They don’t repeat in one place what they heard in another so as to divide people against each other. Instead, they reconcile those who are divided, supporting unity, delighting in harmony, loving harmony, speaking words that promote harmony.*";
P_HTM[5883]="*Pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti. Yā sā vācā nelā kaṇṇasukhā pemanīyā hadayaṅgamā porī bahujanakantā bahujanamanāpā, tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. (6)**They give up harsh speech. They speak in a way that’s mellow, pleasing to the ear, lovely, going to the heart, polite, likable and agreeable to the people.*";
P_HTM[5884]="*Samphappalāpaṃ pahāya, samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī, nidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti kālena sāpadesaṃ pariyantavatiṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ. (7)**They give up talking nonsense. Their words are timely, true, and meaningful, in line with the teaching and training. They say things at the right time which are valuable, reasonable, succinct, and beneficial.*";
P_HTM[5885]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catubbidhā vacīkammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti.**These are the four kinds of successful verbal action.*";
P_HTM[5886]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, tividhā manokammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti?**And what are the three kinds of successful mental action?*";
P_HTM[5887]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco anabhijjhālu hoti. Yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ taṃ anabhijjhātā hoti: ‘aho vata, yaṃ parassa taṃ mamassā’ti. (8)**It’s when someone is content. They don’t covet the wealth and belongings of others: ‘Oh, if only their belongings were mine!’*";
P_HTM[5888]="*Abyāpannacitto hoti appaduṭṭhamanasaṅkappo: ‘ime sattā averā hontu abyāpajjā anīghā, sukhī attānaṃ pariharantū’ti. (9)**They have a kind heart and loving intentions: ‘May these sentient beings live free of enmity and ill will, untroubled and happy!’*";
P_HTM[5889]="*Sammādiṭṭhiko hoti aviparītadassano:**They have right view, an undistorted perspective:*";
P_HTM[5890]="*‘atthi dinnaṃ, atthi yiṭṭhaṃ … pe … ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti. (10)**‘There is meaning in giving, sacrifice, and offerings. There are fruits and results of good and bad deeds. There is an afterlife. There is obligation to mother and father. There are beings reborn spontaneously. And there are ascetics and brahmins who are well attained and practiced, and who describe the afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.’*";
P_HTM[5891]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tividhā manokammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti.**These are the three kinds of successful mental action.*";
P_HTM[5892]="*Tividhakāyakammantasampattikusalasañcetanikāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti; catubbidhavacīkammantasampattikusalasañcetanikāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti; tividhamanokammantasampattikusalasañcetanikāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti.**When their body breaks up, after death, sentient beings are reborn in a good place, in heaven because of these three kinds of successful bodily action, these four kinds of successful verbal action, or these three kinds of successful mental action that have skillful intention, with happiness as their outcome and result.*";
P_HTM[5893]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, apaṇṇako maṇi uddhaṅkhitto yena yeneva patiṭṭhāti suppatiṭṭhitaṃyeva patiṭṭhāti;**It’s like throwing loaded dice: they always fall the right side up.*";
P_HTM[5894]="*evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tividhakāyakammantasampattikusalasañcetanikāhetu vā sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti; catubbidhavacīkammantasampattikusalasañcetanikāhetu vā sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti; tividhamanokammantasampattikusalasañcetanikāhetu vā sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti.**In the same way, when their body breaks up, after death, sentient beings are reborn in a good place, in heaven because of these three kinds of successful bodily action, these four kinds of successful verbal action, or these three kinds of successful mental action that have skillful intention, with happiness as their outcome and result.*";
P_HTM[5895]="*Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ appaṭisaṃveditvā byantībhāvaṃ vadāmi.**I don’t say that intentional deeds that have been performed and accumulated are eliminated without being experienced.*";
P_HTM[5896]="*Tañca kho diṭṭheva dhamme upapajje vā apare vā pariyāye.**And that may be in the present life, or in the next life, or in some subsequent period.*";
P_HTM[5897]="*Na tvevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ appaṭisaṃveditvā dukkhassantakiriyaṃ vadāmī”ti.**And I don’t say that suffering is ended without experiencing intentional deeds that have been performed and accumulated.”*";
P_HTM[5898]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5899]="*8. Dutiyasañcetanikasuttaṃ**Intentional (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5900]="*“Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ appaṭisaṃveditvā byantībhāvaṃ vadāmi,**“Mendicants, I don’t say that intentional deeds that have been performed and accumulated are eliminated without being experienced.*";
P_HTM[5901]="*tañca kho diṭṭheva dhamme upapajje vā apare vā pariyāye.**And that may be in the present life, or in the next life, or in some subsequent period.*";
P_HTM[5902]="*Na tvevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ appaṭisaṃveditvā dukkhassantakiriyaṃ vadāmi.**And I don’t say that suffering is ended without experiencing intentional deeds that have been performed and accumulated.*";
P_HTM[5903]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti;**Now, there are three kinds of corruption and failure of bodily action that have unskillful intention, with suffering as their outcome and result.*";
P_HTM[5904]="*catubbidhā vacīkammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti;**There are four kinds of corruption and failure of verbal action that have unskillful intention, with suffering as their outcome and result.*";
P_HTM[5905]="*tividhā manokammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti.**There are three kinds of corruption and failure of mental action that have unskillful intention, with suffering as their outcome and result.*";
P_HTM[5906]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti … pe …**And what are the three kinds of corruption and failure of bodily action? …*";
P_HTM[5907]="*evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti.**These are the three kinds of corruption and failure of bodily action.*";
P_HTM[5908]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, catubbidhā vacīkammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti … pe …**And what are the four kinds of corruption and failure of verbal action? …*";
P_HTM[5909]="*evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catubbidhā vacīkammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti.**These are the four kinds of corruption and failure of verbal action.*";
P_HTM[5910]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, tividhā manokammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti … pe …**And what are the three kinds of corruption and failure of mental action? …*";
P_HTM[5911]="*evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tividhā manokammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti.**These are the three kinds of corruption and failure of mental action.*";
P_HTM[5912]="*Tividhakāyakammantasandosabyāpattiakusalasañcetanikāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti, catubbidhavacīkammanta … pe … tividhamanokammantasandosabyāpattiakusalasañcetanikāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti.**When their body breaks up, after death, sentient beings are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell because of these three kinds of corruption and failure of bodily action, these four kinds of corruption and failure of verbal action, or these three kinds of corruption and failure of mental action that have unskillful intention, with suffering as their outcome and result.*";
P_HTM[5913]="*Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ appaṭisaṃveditvā byantībhāvaṃ vadāmi,**I don’t say that intentional deeds that have been performed and accumulated are eliminated without being experienced.*";
P_HTM[5914]="*tañca kho diṭṭheva dhamme upapajje vā apare vā pariyāye.**And that may be in the present life, or in the next life, or in some subsequent period.*";
P_HTM[5915]="*Na tvevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ appaṭisaṃveditvā dukkhassantakiriyaṃ vadāmi.**And I don’t say that suffering is ended without experiencing intentional deeds that have been performed and accumulated.*";
P_HTM[5916]="*Tatra kho, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti;**Now, there are three kinds of successful bodily action that have skillful intention, with happiness as their outcome and result.*";
P_HTM[5917]="*catubbidhā vacīkammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti;**There are four kinds of successful verbal action that have skillful intention, with happiness as their outcome and result.*";
P_HTM[5918]="*tividhā manokammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti.**There are three kinds of successful mental action that have skillful intention, with happiness as their outcome and result.*";
P_HTM[5919]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti … pe …**And what are the three kinds of successful bodily action? …*";
P_HTM[5920]="*evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti.**These are the three kinds of successful bodily action.*";
P_HTM[5921]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, catubbidhā vacīkammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti … pe …**And what are the four kinds of successful verbal action? …*";
P_HTM[5922]="*evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catubbidhā vacīkammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti.**These are the four kinds of successful verbal action.*";
P_HTM[5923]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, tividhā manokammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti … pe …**And what are the three kinds of successful mental action? …*";
P_HTM[5924]="*evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tividhā manokammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti.**These are the three kinds of successful mental action.*";
P_HTM[5925]="*Tividhakāyakammantasampattikusalasañcetanikāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti; catubbidhavacīkammantasampatti … pe … tividhamanokammantasampattikusalasañcetanikāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti … pe …**When their body breaks up, after death, sentient beings are reborn in a good place, in heaven because of these three kinds of successful bodily action, these four kinds of successful verbal action, or these three kinds of successful mental action that have skillful intention, with happiness as their outcome and result. …”*";
P_HTM[5926]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5927]="*9. Karajakāyasuttaṃ**The Body Born of Deeds*";
P_HTM[5928]="*“Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ appaṭisaṃveditvā byantībhāvaṃ vadāmi,**“Mendicants, I don’t say that intentional deeds that have been performed and accumulated are eliminated without being experienced.*";
P_HTM[5929]="*tañca kho diṭṭheva dhamme upapajje vā apare vā pariyāye.**And that may be in the present life, or in the next life, or in some subsequent period.*";
P_HTM[5930]="*Na tvevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ appaṭisaṃveditvā dukkhassantakiriyaṃ vadāmi.**And I don’t say that suffering is ended without experiencing intentional deeds that have been performed and accumulated.*";
P_HTM[5931]="*Sa kho so, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako evaṃ vigatābhijjho vigatabyāpādo asammūḷho sampajāno paṭissato mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati tathā dutiyaṃ tathā tatiyaṃ tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati.**That noble disciple is rid of desire, rid of ill will, unconfused, aware, and mindful. They meditate spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[5932]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand:*";
P_HTM[5933]="*‘pubbe kho me idaṃ cittaṃ parittaṃ ahosi abhāvitaṃ, etarahi pana me idaṃ cittaṃ appamāṇaṃ subhāvitaṃ. Yaṃ kho pana kiñci pamāṇakataṃ kammaṃ, na taṃ tatrāvasissati na taṃ tatrāvatiṭṭhatī’ti.**‘Formerly my mind was limited and undeveloped. Now it’s limitless and well developed. Whatever limited deeds I’ve done don’t remain or persist there.’*";
P_HTM[5934]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[5935]="*daharatagge ce so ayaṃ kumāro mettaṃ cetovimuttiṃ bhāveyya, api nu kho pāpakammaṃ kareyyā”ti?**Suppose a child had developed the heart’s release by love from their childhood on. Would they still do any bad deed?”*";
P_HTM[5936]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5937]="*“Akarontaṃ kho pana pāpakammaṃ api nu kho dukkhaṃ phuseyyā”ti?**“Not doing any bad deed, would they still experience any suffering?”*";
P_HTM[5938]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[5939]="*Akarontañhi, bhante, pāpakammaṃ kuto dukkhaṃ phusissatī”ti.**For if they don’t do any bad deed, from where would suffering afflict them?”*";
P_HTM[5940]="*“Bhāvetabbā kho panāyaṃ, bhikkhave, mettācetovimutti itthiyā vā purisena vā.**“This heart’s release by love should be developed by women or men.*";
P_HTM[5941]="*Itthiyā vā, bhikkhave, purisassa vā nāyaṃ kāyo ādāya gamanīyo.**For neither women nor men take this body with them when they go.*";
P_HTM[5942]="*Cittantaro ayaṃ, bhikkhave, macco.**The mind is what’s inside mortal beings.*";
P_HTM[5943]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand:*";
P_HTM[5944]="*‘yaṃ kho me idaṃ kiñci pubbe iminā karajakāyena pāpakammaṃ kataṃ, sabbaṃ taṃ idha vedanīyaṃ;**‘Whatever bad deeds I have done in the past with this deed-born body I will experience here.*";
P_HTM[5945]="*na taṃ anugaṃ bhavissatī’ti.**It will not follow me to my next life.’*";
P_HTM[5946]="*Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, bhikkhave, mettā cetovimutti anāgāmitāya saṃvattati, idha paññassa bhikkhuno uttari vimuttiṃ appaṭivijjhato.**The heart’s release by love developed in this way leads to non-return for a wise mendicant here who has not penetrated to a higher freedom.*";
P_HTM[5947]="*Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā …**They meditate spreading a heart full of compassion …*";
P_HTM[5948]="*muditāsahagatena cetasā …**They meditate spreading a heart full of rejoicing …*";
P_HTM[5949]="*upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati tathā dutiyaṃ tathā tatiyaṃ tathā catutthaṃ.**They meditate spreading a heart full of equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth.*";
P_HTM[5950]="*Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati.**In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[5951]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand:*";
P_HTM[5952]="*‘pubbe kho me idaṃ cittaṃ parittaṃ ahosi abhāvitaṃ, etarahi pana me idaṃ cittaṃ appamāṇaṃ subhāvitaṃ. Yaṃ kho pana kiñci pamāṇakataṃ kammaṃ, na taṃ tatrāvasissati na taṃ tatrāvatiṭṭhatī’ti.**‘Formerly my mind was limited and undeveloped. Now it’s limitless and well developed. Whatever limited deeds I’ve done don’t remain or persist there.’*";
P_HTM[5953]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[5954]="*daharatagge ce so ayaṃ kumāro upekkhaṃ cetovimuttiṃ bhāveyya, api nu kho pāpakammaṃ kareyyā”ti?**Suppose a child had developed the heart’s release by equanimity from their childhood on. Would they still do any bad deed?”*";
P_HTM[5955]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5956]="*“Akarontaṃ kho pana pāpakammaṃ api nu kho dukkhaṃ phuseyyā”ti?**“Not doing any bad deed, would they still experience any suffering?”*";
P_HTM[5957]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[5958]="*Akarontañhi, bhante, pāpakammaṃ kuto dukkhaṃ phusissatī”ti.**For if they don’t do any bad deed, from where would suffering afflict them?”*";
P_HTM[5959]="*“Bhāvetabbā kho panāyaṃ, bhikkhave, upekkhā cetovimutti itthiyā vā purisena vā.**“This heart’s release by equanimity should be developed by women or men.*";
P_HTM[5960]="*Itthiyā vā, bhikkhave, purisassa vā nāyaṃ kāyo ādāya gamanīyo.**For neither women nor men take this body with them when they go.*";
P_HTM[5961]="*Cittantaro ayaṃ, bhikkhave, macco.**The mind is what’s inside mortal beings.*";
P_HTM[5962]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand:*";
P_HTM[5963]="*‘yaṃ kho me idaṃ kiñci pubbe iminā karajakāyena pāpakammaṃ kataṃ, sabbaṃ taṃ idha vedanīyaṃ;**‘Whatever bad deeds I have done in the past with this deed-born body I will experience here.*";
P_HTM[5964]="*na taṃ anugaṃ bhavissatī’ti.**It will not follow me to my next life.’*";
P_HTM[5965]="*Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, bhikkhave, upekkhā cetovimutti anāgāmitāya saṃvattati, idha paññassa bhikkhuno uttari vimuttiṃ appaṭivijjhato”ti.**The heart’s release by equanimity developed in this way leads to non-return for a wise mendicant here who has not penetrated to a higher freedom.”*";
P_HTM[5966]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5967]="*10. Adhammacariyāsuttaṃ**Unprincipled Conduct*";
P_HTM[5968]="*Atha kho aññataro brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then a certain brahmin went up to the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[5969]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[5970]="*“ko nu kho, bho gotama, hetu ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjantī”ti?**“What is the cause, Master Gotama, what is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell?”*";
P_HTM[5971]="*“Adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu kho, brāhmaṇa, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjantī”ti.**“Unprincipled and immoral conduct is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.”*";
P_HTM[5972]="*“Ko pana, bho gotama, hetu ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjantī”ti?**“But what is the cause, Master Gotama, what is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm?”*";
P_HTM[5973]="*“Dhammacariyāsamacariyāhetu kho, brāhmaṇa, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjantī”ti.**“Principled and moral conduct is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.”*";
P_HTM[5974]="*“Na kho ahaṃ imassa bhoto gotamassa saṅkhittena bhāsitassa vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmi.**“I don’t understand the detailed meaning of what Master Gotama has said in brief.*";
P_HTM[5975]="*Sādhu me bhavaṃ gotamo tathā dhammaṃ desetu yathāhaṃ imassa bhoto gotamassa saṅkhittena bhāsitassa vitthārena atthaṃ ājāneyyan”ti.**Please, Master Gotama, teach me this matter so I can understand the detailed meaning.”*";
P_HTM[5976]="*“Tena hi, brāhmaṇa, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, brahmin, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[5977]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho so brāhmaṇo bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” the brahmin replied.*";
P_HTM[5978]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[5979]="*“Tividhā kho, brāhmaṇa, kāyena adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti;**“Brahmin, unprincipled and immoral conduct is threefold by way of body,*";
P_HTM[5980]="*catubbidhā vācāya adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti;**fourfold by way of speech,*";
P_HTM[5981]="*tividhā manasā adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti.**and threefold by way of mind.*";
P_HTM[5982]="*Kathañca, brāhmaṇa, tividhā kāyena adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti … pe …**And how is unprincipled and immoral conduct threefold by way of body? …*";
P_HTM[5983]="*evaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, tividhā kāyena adhammacariyā visamacariyā hoti.**That’s how unprincipled and immoral conduct is threefold by way of body.*";
P_HTM[5984]="*Kathañca, brāhmaṇa, catubbidhā vācāya adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti … pe …**And how is unprincipled and immoral conduct fourfold by way of speech? …*";
P_HTM[5985]="*evaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, catubbidhā vācāya adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti.**That’s how unprincipled and immoral conduct is fourfold by way of speech.*";
P_HTM[5986]="*Kathañca, brāhmaṇa, tividhā manasā adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti … pe …**And how is unprincipled and immoral conduct threefold by way of mind? …*";
P_HTM[5987]="*evaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, tividhā manasā adhammacariyāvisamacariyā hoti.**That’s how unprincipled and immoral conduct is threefold by way of mind.*";
P_HTM[5988]="*Evaṃ adhammacariyāvisamacariyāhetu kho, brāhmaṇa, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti.**That’s how unprincipled and immoral conduct is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[5989]="*Tividhā, brāhmaṇa, kāyena dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti;**Principled and moral conduct is threefold by way of body,*";
P_HTM[5990]="*catubbidhā vācāya dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti;**fourfold by way of speech,*";
P_HTM[5991]="*tividhā manasā dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti.**and threefold by way of mind.*";
P_HTM[5992]="*Kathañca, brāhmaṇa, tividhā kāyena dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti … pe …**And how is principled and moral conduct threefold by way of body? …*";
P_HTM[5993]="*evaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, tividhā kāyena dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti.**That’s how principled and moral conduct is threefold by way of body.*";
P_HTM[5994]="*Kathañca, brāhmaṇa, catubbidhā vācāya dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti … pe …**And how is principled and moral conduct fourfold by way of speech? …*";
P_HTM[5995]="*evaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, catubbidhā vācāya dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti.**That’s how principled and moral conduct is fourfold by way of speech.*";
P_HTM[5996]="*Kathañca, brāhmaṇa, tividhā manasā dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti … pe …**And how is principled and moral conduct threefold by way of mind? …*";
P_HTM[5997]="*evaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, tividhā manasā dhammacariyāsamacariyā hoti.**That’s how principled and moral conduct is threefold by way of mind.*";
P_HTM[5998]="*Evaṃ dhammacariyāsamacariyāhetu kho, brāhmaṇa, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjantī”ti.**That’s how principled and moral conduct is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.”*";
P_HTM[5999]="*“Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …**“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! …*";
P_HTM[6000]="*upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[6001]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6002]="*Karajakāyavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[6003]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ***";
P_HTM[6004]="*“Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Someone with ten qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[6005]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[6006]="*Pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti, pisuṇavāco hoti, pharusavāco hoti, samphappalāpī hoti, abhijjhālu hoti, byāpannacitto hoti, micchādiṭṭhiko hoti—**They kill living creatures, steal, and commit sexual misconduct. They use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. And they’re covetous, malicious, with wrong view.*";
P_HTM[6007]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Someone with these ten qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[6008]="*Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**Someone with ten qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[6009]="*Katamehi dasahi?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[6010]="*Pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, anabhijjhālu hoti, abyāpannacitto hoti, sammādiṭṭhiko hoti—**They don’t kill living creatures, steal, or commit sexual misconduct. They don’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. They’re contented, kind-hearted, with right view.*";
P_HTM[6011]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, dasahi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**Someone with these ten qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[6012]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ***";
P_HTM[6013]="*“Vīsatiyā, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Someone with twenty qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[6014]="*Katamehi vīsatiyā?**What twenty?*";
P_HTM[6015]="*Attanā ca pāṇātipātī hoti, parañca pāṇātipāte samādapeti;**They kill living creatures, steal, and commit sexual misconduct. They use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. They’re covetous, malicious, with wrong view. And they encourage others to do these things.*";
P_HTM[6016]="*attanā ca adinnādāyī hoti, parañca adinnādāne samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[6017]="*attanā ca kāmesumicchācārī hoti, parañca kāmesumicchācāre samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[6018]="*attanā ca musāvādī hoti, parañca musāvāde samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[6019]="*attanā ca pisuṇavāco hoti, parañca pisuṇāya vācāya samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[6020]="*attanā ca pharusavāco hoti, parañca pharusāya vācāya samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[6021]="*attanā ca samphappalāpī hoti, parañca samphappalāpe samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[6022]="*attanā ca abhijjhālu hoti, parañca abhijjhāya samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[6023]="*attanā ca byāpannacitto hoti, parañca byāpāde samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[6024]="*attanā ca micchādiṭṭhiko hoti, parañca micchādiṭṭhiyā samādapeti—* **";
P_HTM[6025]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, vīsatiyā dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Someone with these twenty qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[6026]="*Vīsatiyā, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**Someone with twenty qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[6027]="*Katamehi vīsatiyā?**What twenty?*";
P_HTM[6028]="*Attanā ca pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, parañca pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;**They don’t kill living creatures, steal, or commit sexual misconduct. They don’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. They’re contented, kind-hearted, with right view. And they encourage others to do these things.*";
P_HTM[6029]="*attanā ca adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, parañca adinnādānā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[6030]="*attanā ca kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, parañca kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[6031]="*attanā ca musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, parañca musāvādā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[6032]="*attanā ca pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, parañca pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[6033]="*attanā ca pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, parañca pharusāya vācāya veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[6034]="*attanā ca samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, parañca samphappalāpā veramaṇiyā samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[6035]="*attanā ca anabhijjhālu hoti, parañca anabhijjhāya samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[6036]="*attanā ca abyāpannacitto hoti, parañca abyāpāde samādapeti;* **";
P_HTM[6037]="*attanā ca sammādiṭṭhiko hoti, parañca sammādiṭṭhiyā samādapeti—* **";
P_HTM[6038]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, vīsatiyā dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**Someone with these twenty qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[6039]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ***";
P_HTM[6040]="*“Tiṃsāya, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Someone with thirty qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[6041]="*Katamehi tiṃsāya?**What thirty?*";
P_HTM[6042]="*Attanā ca pāṇātipātī hoti, parañca pāṇātipāte samādapeti, pāṇātipāte ca samanuñño hoti;**They kill living creatures, steal, and commit sexual misconduct. They use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. They’re covetous, malicious, with wrong view. They encourage others to do these things. And they approve of these things.*";
P_HTM[6043]="*attanā ca adinnādāyī hoti, parañca adinnādāne samādapeti, adinnādāne ca samanuñño hoti;* **";
P_HTM[6044]="*attanā ca kāmesumicchācārī hoti, parañca kāmesumicchācāre samādapeti, kāmesumicchācāre ca samanuñño hoti;* **";
P_HTM[6045]="*attanā ca musāvādī hoti, parañca musāvāde samādapeti, musāvāde ca samanuñño hoti;* **";
P_HTM[6046]="*attanā ca pisuṇavāco hoti, parañca pisuṇāya vācāya samādapeti, pisuṇāya vācāya ca samanuñño hoti;* **";
P_HTM[6047]="*attanā ca pharusavāco hoti, parañca pharusāya vācāya samādapeti, pharusāya vācāya ca samanuñño hoti;* **";
P_HTM[6048]="*attanā ca samphappalāpī hoti, parañca samphappalāpe samādapeti, samphappalāpe ca samanuñño hoti;* **";
P_HTM[6049]="*attanā ca abhijjhālu hoti, parañca abhijjhāya samādapeti, abhijjhāya ca samanuñño hoti;* **";
P_HTM[6050]="*attanā ca byāpannacitto hoti, parañca byāpāde samādapeti, byāpāde ca samanuñño hoti;* **";
P_HTM[6051]="*attanā ca micchādiṭṭhiko hoti, parañca micchādiṭṭhiyā samādapeti, micchādiṭṭhiyā ca samanuñño hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6052]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tiṃsāya dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Someone with these thirty qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[6053]="*Tiṃsāya, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**Someone with thirty qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[6054]="*Katamehi tiṃsāya?**What thirty?*";
P_HTM[6055]="*Attanā ca pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, parañca pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti;**They don’t kill living creatures, steal, or commit sexual misconduct. They don’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. They’re contented, kind-hearted, with right view. They encourage others to do these things. And they approve of these things.*";
P_HTM[6056]="*attanā ca adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, parañca adinnādānā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, adinnādānā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti;* **";
P_HTM[6057]="*attanā ca kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, parañca kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti;* **";
P_HTM[6058]="*attanā ca musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, parañca musāvādā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, musāvādā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti;* **";
P_HTM[6059]="*attanā ca pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, parañca pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇiyā samādapeti, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti;* **";
P_HTM[6060]="*attanā ca pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, parañca pharusāya vācāya veramaṇiyā samādapeti, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti;* **";
P_HTM[6061]="*attanā ca samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, parañca samphappalāpā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, samphappalāpā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti;* **";
P_HTM[6062]="*attanā ca anabhijjhālu hoti, parañca anabhijjhāya samādapeti, anabhijjhāya ca samanuñño hoti;* **";
P_HTM[6063]="*attanā ca abyāpannacitto hoti, parañca abyāpāde samādapeti, abyāpāde ca samanuñño hoti;* **";
P_HTM[6064]="*attanā ca sammādiṭṭhiko hoti, parañca sammādiṭṭhiyā samādapeti, sammādiṭṭhiyā ca samanuñño hoti—* **";
P_HTM[6065]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, tiṃsāya dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**Someone with these thirty qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[6066]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ***";
P_HTM[6067]="*“Cattārīsāya, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Someone with forty qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[6068]="*Katamehi cattārīsāya?**What forty?*";
P_HTM[6069]="*Attanā ca pāṇātipātī hoti, parañca pāṇātipāte samādapeti, pāṇātipāte ca samanuñño hoti, pāṇātipātassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;**They kill living creatures, steal, and commit sexual misconduct. They use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. They’re covetous, malicious, with wrong view. They encourage others to do these things. They approve of these things. And they praise these things.*";
P_HTM[6070]="*attanā ca adinnādāyī hoti, parañca adinnādāne samādapeti, adinnādāne ca samanuñño hoti, adinnādānassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;* **";
P_HTM[6071]="*attanā ca kāmesumicchācārī hoti, parañca kāmesumicchācāre samādapeti, kāmesumicchācāre ca samanuñño hoti, kāmesumicchācārassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;* **";
P_HTM[6072]="*attanā ca musāvādī hoti, parañca musāvāde samādapeti, musāvāde ca samanuñño hoti, musāvādassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;* **";
P_HTM[6073]="*attanā ca pisuṇavāco hoti, parañca pisuṇāya vācāya samādapeti, pisuṇāya vācāya ca samanuñño hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;* **";
P_HTM[6074]="*attanā ca pharusavāco hoti, parañca pharusāya vācāya samādapeti, pharusāya vācāya ca samanuñño hoti, pharusāya vācāya ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;* **";
P_HTM[6075]="*attanā ca samphappalāpī hoti, parañca samphappalāpe samādapeti, samphappalāpe ca samanuñño hoti, samphappalāpassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;* **";
P_HTM[6076]="*attanā ca abhijjhālu hoti, parañca abhijjhāya samādapeti, abhijjhāya ca samanuñño hoti, abhijjhāya ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;* **";
P_HTM[6077]="*attanā ca byāpannacitto hoti, parañca byāpāde samādapeti, byāpāde ca samanuñño hoti, byāpādassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;* **";
P_HTM[6078]="*attanā ca micchādiṭṭhiko hoti, parañca micchādiṭṭhiyā samādapeti, micchādiṭṭhiyā ca samanuñño hoti, micchādiṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—* **";
P_HTM[6079]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, cattārīsāya dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Someone with these forty qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[6080]="*Cattārīsāya, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**Someone with forty qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[6081]="*Katamehi cattārīsāya?**What forty?*";
P_HTM[6082]="*Attanā ca pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, parañca pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti, pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;**They don’t kill living creatures, steal, or commit sexual misconduct. They don’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. They’re contented, kind-hearted, with right view. They encourage others to do these things. They approve of these things. And they praise these things.*";
P_HTM[6083]="*attanā ca adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, parañca adinnādānā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, adinnādānā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti, adinnādānā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;* **";
P_HTM[6084]="*attanā ca kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, parañca kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;* **";
P_HTM[6085]="*attanā ca musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, parañca musāvādā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, musāvādā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti, musāvādā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;* **";
P_HTM[6086]="*attanā ca pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, parañca pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇiyā samādapeti, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;* **";
P_HTM[6087]="*attanā ca pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, parañca pharusāya vācāya veramaṇiyā ca samādapeti, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;* **";
P_HTM[6088]="*attanā ca samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, parañca samphappalāpā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, samphappalāpā veramaṇiyā ca samanuñño hoti, samphappalāpā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;* **";
P_HTM[6089]="*attanā ca anabhijjhālu hoti, parañca anabhijjhāya samādapeti, anabhijjhāya ca samanuñño hoti, anabhijjhāya ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;* **";
P_HTM[6090]="*attanā ca abyāpannacitto hoti, parañca abyāpāde samādapeti, abyāpāde ca samanuñño hoti, abyāpādassa ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;* **";
P_HTM[6091]="*attanā ca sammādiṭṭhiko hoti, parañca sammādiṭṭhiyā samādapeti, sammādiṭṭhiyā ca samanuñño hoti, sammādiṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati—* **";
P_HTM[6092]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, cattārīsāya dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**Someone with these forty qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[6093]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**225–228*";
P_HTM[6094]="*“Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati … pe …**“Someone with ten qualities keeps themselves broken and damaged …*";
P_HTM[6095]="*akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati … pe …**keeps themselves healthy and whole …*";
P_HTM[6096]="*vīsatiyā, bhikkhave … pe …**twenty …*";
P_HTM[6097]="*tiṃsāya, bhikkhave … pe …**thirty …*";
P_HTM[6098]="*cattārīsāya, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati … pe ….**forty …”*";
P_HTM[6099]="*()**()*";
P_HTM[6100]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**229–232*";
P_HTM[6101]="*“Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato idhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati … pe …**“When they have ten qualities, some people, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. …*";
P_HTM[6102]="*idhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**some people, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm …*";
P_HTM[6103]="*Vīsatiyā, bhikkhave … pe …**twenty …*";
P_HTM[6104]="*tiṃsāya, bhikkhave … pe …**thirty …*";
P_HTM[6105]="*cattārīsāya, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato idhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati … pe …**forty …”*";
P_HTM[6106]="*idhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati”.* **";
P_HTM[6107]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**233–236*";
P_HTM[6108]="*“Dasahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bālo veditabbo … pe …**“A fool is known by ten qualities …*";
P_HTM[6109]="*paṇḍito veditabbo … pe …**astute person …*";
P_HTM[6110]="*vīsatiyā, bhikkhave … pe …**twenty …*";
P_HTM[6111]="*tiṃsāya, bhikkhave … pe …**thirty …*";
P_HTM[6112]="*cattārīsāya, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bālo veditabbo … pe …**forty …”*";
P_HTM[6113]="*paṇḍito veditabbo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[6114]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, cattārīsāya dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito veditabbo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6115]="*Sāmaññavaggo dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[6116]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ***";
P_HTM[6117]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya dasa dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“For insight into greed, ten things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[6118]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[6119]="*Asubhasaññā, maraṇasaññā, āhāre paṭikūlasaññā, sabbaloke anabhiratasaññā, aniccasaññā, anicce dukkhasaññā, dukkhe anattasaññā, pahānasaññā, virāgasaññā, nirodhasaññā—**The perceptions of ugliness, death, repulsiveness of food, dissatisfaction with the whole world, impermanence, suffering in impermanence, and not-self in suffering, giving up, fading away, and cessation.*";
P_HTM[6120]="*rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime dasa dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti.**For insight into greed, these ten things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[6121]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ***";
P_HTM[6122]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya dasa dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“For insight into greed, ten things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[6123]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[6124]="*Aniccasaññā, anattasaññā, āhāre paṭikūlasaññā, sabbaloke anabhiratasaññā, aṭṭhikasaññā, puḷavakasaññā, vinīlakasaññā, vipubbakasaññā, vicchiddakasaññā, uddhumātakasaññā—**The perceptions of impermanence, not-self, death, repulsiveness of food, dissatisfaction with the whole world, a skeleton, a worm-infested corpse, a livid corpse, a split open corpse, and a bloated corpse.*";
P_HTM[6125]="*rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime dasa dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti.**For insight into greed, these ten things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[6126]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ***";
P_HTM[6127]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya dasa dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“For insight into greed, ten things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[6128]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[6129]="*Sammādiṭṭhi, sammāsaṅkappo, sammāvācā, sammākammanto, sammāājīvo, sammāvāyāmo, sammāsati, sammāsamādhi, sammāñāṇaṃ, sammāvimutti—**Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom.*";
P_HTM[6130]="*rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime dasa dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti.**For insight into greed, these ten things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[6131]="*123. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**240–266*";
P_HTM[6132]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, pariññāya … pe …**“For the complete understanding of greed …*";
P_HTM[6133]="*parikkhayāya …**complete ending …*";
P_HTM[6134]="*pahānāya …**giving up …*";
P_HTM[6135]="*khayāya …**ending …*";
